<DIV1 N="1" TYPE="tract"><PB REF="00000066.tif">

<PB REF="00000067.tif" N="1">
<HEAD>I. OF THE LEAVEN OF PHARISEES.</HEAD>
<HEADNOTE><P>WITH regard to this tract, as with many that follow, I can give no decided opinion as to authorship. I find it monotonous and poor in style, but in substance it contains nothing that may not be Wyclif's, while there is so much of his characteristic teaching that it must be by one of his intimate disciples if not by himself. The reference to Bishop Spencer's crusade (p. 8) shows that it was written about 1383. In some parts it very much resembles the Fifty Heresies and Errors of Friars, printed by Mr. Arnold, No. XXIV. Compare especially pp. 14, 15, with Chapter XVII. of the Fifty Heresies (S. E. W. III. 280).</P><P>There is a lively description in Chap. III. of the tricks of the friars, which agrees well with Chaucer's description of his friar, whose</P><Q><L>typet was aye farsed full of knyfes</L><L>And pynnes for to give faire wyfes.</L></Q><P>The touch about their making friends with women by giving them pet dogs (p. 12) is, so far as I know, peculiar to this tract.</P><P>Copied from the Corpus MS. X., and collated with the Dublin MS. AA.</P><P><TABLE>
<HEAD>SUMMARY.</HEAD>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. I.</CELL>
<CELL>Christ commands us to flee the leaven of Pharisees, who belonged to a singular religion. The Religious of these days are like them.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>II.</CELL>
<CELL>Proofs of hypocrisy. Their pride, envy, persecution of true preachers, covetousness, self-indulgence, and unchastity.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>III.</CELL>
<CELL>How they offend against each of the Ten Commandments.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>IV.</CELL>
<CELL>How they do the contrary of the works of bodily mercy.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>V.</CELL>
<CELL>How they do the contrary of the works of spiritual mercy.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>VI.</CELL>
<CELL>How they fail in Faith, Hope, and Charity.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>VII.</CELL>
<CELL>The duty of exposing their wickedness.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>VIII.</CELL>
<CELL>Cowardice and falseness prevalent among all classes. Faults of priests.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>IX.</CELL>
<CELL>Faults of Lords.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>X.</CELL>
<CELL>Faults of Commons.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>XI.</CELL>
<CELL>The faults of the Religious are much the worst.</CELL>
</ROW>
</TABLE></P></HEADNOTE>
<EPIGRAPH>

<PB REF="00000068.tif" N="2">
<Q>Attendite a fermento phariseorum quod est ypocrisis</Q>
<BIBL>Luc&aelig;, 12<SUP>o</SUP>.</BIBL>
</EPIGRAPH>
<DIV2 N="1" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum primum.</HEAD>
<P>Crist comandi&thorn; to his disciplis and to alle cristene men to vndirstonde &amp; flee &thorn;e sowrdow of pharisees, &thorn;e wiche is ypocrisie. First pharisees been men of synguler religioun founden of synful men, biside &thorn;e ordynaunce of god &thorn;at is tau&yogh;t in holi writ. And yn cristes tyme &thorn;ere weren &thorn;re sectes of ordres founden of mannys ordinaunces, as pharisees, saduces and esseis. of two &thorn;e firste mathew speke&thorn; in his gospel. And of &thorn;e &thorn;ridde speke&thorn; &thorn;e maister of stories. The firste two weren grete men of name and hauynge, and weren stronge enemyes to crist &amp; his lawe, and disceyueden &thorn;e peple by ypocrisie, &amp; weren ful coueitous. And &thorn;erfore Seint Joon baptist &amp; crist clepede hem ypocritis &amp; serpentis and addir kyndles, &amp; jhu cursede hem ofte, &yogh;ee ei&yogh;te tymes, as &thorn;e gospel sei&thorn;. But crist louede &amp; sauede summe gode men of hem, as nicodeme &amp; poul, &amp; brou&yogh;te hem out of her ordris to fredom of &thorn;e gospel &amp; distroied &thorn;ese ordris, as holi writ sei&thorn;. And &yogh;if oure newe religious ben in &thorn;ese same synnys, as ful of coueitise &amp; ypocrisie, &amp; stryuen a&yogh;ens &thorn;e fredom of &thorn;e gospel &amp; cristis lif &amp; his apostlis, &thorn;ei ben cursid of god; and &thorn;ei shullen be brou&yogh;t out of here ordris maad of synful men &amp; brou&yogh;t clenly to &thorn;e gospel &amp; fredom of cristis ordre, for it is most perfit &amp; most esi to wynne heuene by &amp; most sikir, for &thorn;e most my&yogh;t, most wisdom, &amp; most charite of jhu crist &thorn;at made it and made nou&yogh;t &thorn;ise newe ordris. And &yogh;if &thorn;ei hadden be needful or profitable he wolde haue maad hem by hym silf or by his apostelis, or teld in holi writ bi what man &amp; what tyme &thorn;ei shulden haue come in; but nou&yogh;t of al &thorn;is is founden in holi writ, in wich is al nedful and profitable ordynaunce of holi chirche; &amp; &thorn;erfore al &thorn;is nouelrie of ordris is suspect of ypocrisie &amp; luciferis pride and blasfemye 
<PB REF="00000069.tif" N="3"> of antecristis ypocrisie. last men doon &thorn;is nouelrie for vein glorie &amp; for getynge more plentifousli of wordli godis bi abite &amp; o&thorn;er sygnes of holinesse; si&thorn;&thorn;e &thorn;ei my&yogh;ten lyue as plesandeli to god &amp; as moche profit to holi chirche, and fulli ocupie al &thorn;e my&yogh;tis bo&thorn;e of soule &amp; body be &thorn;at clene religioun &thorn;at crist made hym self to his disciplis &amp; prestis as bi &thorn;ese nouelries maad of ydiotis &amp; synful wrecchis of lucifers pride; for &thorn;ei ben taken as holier men &amp; holden hem self more wor&thorn;i for &thorn;ise newe ordinaunces of her owen fonnyd heuedis, &thorn;at letten hem from &thorn;e better ocupacioun,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Up to this point is copied from AA, as the text in X is illegible from damp.</NOTE><MILESTONE UNIT="MS.Corp. page" N="2">&thorn;an for clennesse of cristis ordre, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei seruen<NOTE PLACE="foot">suwen AA.</NOTE> neuere so perfitly crist in holy lyuyng and trewe techyng wi&thorn;oute &thorn;is newe pro|fessioun and cermonyes, &thorn;e whiche crist and his apostlis diden neuere ne tau&yogh;ten in al holy writ. It is a fendis pride a synful creature to putte defautte in &thorn;e ordynaunce of crist, seiynge in word or dede &thorn;at crist tau&yogh;te not his disciplis and his prestes &thorn;e beste ordre and religioun, but lefte &thorn;e beste ordre bihynde a &thorn;ousand &yogh;eer and more til sathanas was vn|bounden to desceyue men bi lesyngis and ypocrisie, and si&thorn;en crist made and tau&yogh;te &thorn;e beste religioun, it is a stynkynge pride of luciferis children to leue &thorn;e betre, and constreyne men to leue &thorn;e betere, and take and nede men to holde for&thorn;e &thorn;e worse. Of blasphemye, for &thorn;es newe religious seyn in word or dede &thorn;at crist my&yogh;t not, coude not,<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> or wolde not teche cristen men &thorn;e beste religion to wynnen heuene by; and &yogh;if &thorn;is be so&thorn; crist was not god, for &thorn;anne he was oute of charite. And in &thorn;is same &thorn;ei seyn priueily &thorn;at a synful ydiot was more<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> wis and fullere of charite &thorn;an <ABBR>ihu</ABBR> crist, si&thorn; bi hem &thorn;is synful ydiot &yogh;af and vsed a betere religioun &thorn;an euere dide crist god almy&yogh;ty. ypocrisie is a fals feynyng of holynes whan it is not in trew&thorn;e bifore god, and so ypocrisie is fully contrarie to crist, &thorn;at is trew&thorn;e as &thorn;e gospel teche&thorn;, and it is comunly &thorn;e moste perylous synne of alle. For comunly an ypocrite do&thorn; neuere verrey penaunce, for trist &thorn;at he has 
<PB REF="00000070.tif" N="4"> in his owen holy feyned lif and for likyng of veyne glorie and for wynnynge of worldly goodis; and ypocritis ben most cursed before al o&thorn;er &thorn;eues, for &thorn;ei ben &thorn;eues of goodis of grace and dysceyuen o&thorn;er men in goodis of vertu, &thorn;at ben betere &thorn;an goodis of fortune or goodis of kynde, and as a &thorn;ing is betere so &thorn;e mysusyng &thorn;er-of is more dampnable, as lyncolne and o&thorn;er clerkis prouen; and &thorn;erfore crist in &thorn;e gospel cursid so ofte ypocritis more &thorn;an o&thorn;ere synful men.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 2<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>See now whe&thorn;er oure religious &thorn;is day ben ypocritis.</P>
<P>&YOGH;if &thorn;ei bynden hem self bi herte, word and sygnes to moste mekenesse after crist and his apostelis, and &yogh;it ben most proude of worldly goodes, of beaute, of welschap, of streng&thorn;e of body, of connyng, of worldly and fleschly frenschipe, of kyn, and of holynesse<MILESTONE N="3" UNIT="page"> of here singuler religion, &thorn;an ben &thorn;ei moost cursed and synful ypocritis.</P>
<P>&YOGH;if &thorn;ei maken hem self in si&yogh;te of peple more holi<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &thorn;an o&thorn;ere men and bosten &thorn;ereof in owtward signes or wordes, as morn|ynge abite, lettris of fraternite, &thorn;at crien here holynesse and synguler deuocions bifor men, and bihynde ceesen of; and do &thorn;is for worldely wynnyng and veyn glorie, and preisen more here owen longe preieris &thorn;an o&thorn;er mennus,<NOTE PLACE="foot">The MS. contraction-mark is that for -us, though 'mannes' occurs on p. 30, l. 22, and in the first two sheets at least, all the other noun flexions, except this 'mennus' (or 'mannus') are in 'is,' 'ys' or 'es.'</NOTE> &thorn;ei ben &thorn;an foule ypocritis.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei bynden hem to most charite and &thorn;er wi&thorn; ben in gret enuye amongis hem self, and han dispitt and indignacion of good lyf and trewe techyng of cristis gospel &thorn;at symple men don out of here ordre, &thorn;es ben perilous ypocritis and cursed of god for defaute of charite.</P>
<P>&YOGH;if &thorn;ei ben glad of here enemys myslyuyng or techynge, to lette &thorn;er-by men to teche freliche goddis lawe, &thorn;ei ben cursed ypocritis.</P>
<P>&YOGH;if &thorn;ei bynden hem to most pacience and mercy and &thorn;er 
<PB REF="00000071.tif" N="5"> wy&thorn; haten and ben woode wro&thorn; with men &thorn;at trewly dispisen synne and reprouen here ypocrisie, and pursuen hem cruely and with out mercy &thorn;at frely and sadly techyn &thorn;e gospel and &thorn;e comaundements of god wherby here symonye and ypocrisie is more knowen of &thorn;e peple, &thorn;anne &thorn;ei ben cruel ypocritis.</P>
<P>&YOGH;if &thorn;ei pursuen trwe men for techyng of &thorn;e gospel, and seyn &thorn;ere wi&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ei pursuen hem for errours &thorn;at &thorn;ei seyn openly to &thorn;e peple when &thorn;ei lien &amp; falsly sclaundren trewe men, but &thorn;e pursuyt is maad for prestes techyng men where &thorn;ei schullen do here almes to here moste nedy nei&yogh;bores after &thorn;e gospel; &thorn;an be &thorn;ei cursed ypocritis.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei maken prelatis and lordis, bi here fals flateryng and lesyngis in confessions and preuei conseils, to lette prestis to preche goddis lawe and to lette &thorn;e peple to knowe and to kepe &thorn;e comaundementis of god, lest freris ypocrisie and wynny[n]g be stoppid and &thorn;e peples almes betere spendid, &thorn;anne be &thorn;ei cursed ypocritis.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei come in to &thorn;e chirche to holde and meyntene &thorn;e pouert of crist and his apostelis and bynden hem &thorn;er to, and &thorn;er with ben most coueitouse abouten worldely goodis, summe aboute temperal almes nedles and summe aboute worldely lordyschype, bi ypocrisie and lesyngis and flateryngs, &thorn;ei ben &thorn;an trecherous ypocritis and perilous enemys of crist and his chirche.</P>
<P><MILESTONE N="4" UNIT="page">&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei maken profession to most hey pouert and to be deed to &thorn;e world and worldely &thorn;ingis, and wi&thorn; &thorn;is stryuen ny&yogh;t and day who of hem may bilde gaiest wast housis and costly places, as chirchis or castelis to herberwen lordis inne and ladyes, and beggen of pore men &thorn;er-to &thorn;at han nou&yogh;t to lyuen by ne here children, &thorn;ei ben perilous ypocritis and dysceyuen riche and poore.</P>
<P>&YOGH;if &thorn;ei ordeynen ydiotis to ben lymytours &thorn;at best kunnyn begge, and holde goode men and kunnyng in holy writt fro prechynge, and disceyuen men bi pardons, lettris of fraternite and priuat preieris for to geten worldely muk more &thorn;an soule hel&thorn;e, &thorn;anne be &thorn;ei fals ypocritis and worschipen false maummetis.
<PB REF="00000072.tif" N="6"></P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei bynden hem to traueile faste and techyng of &thorn;e gospel frely, as crist and his apostelis diden, and her-wi&thorn; ordeynen costly chambris and beddis and siluerene vessel and gay clo&thorn;es and costly mete and drink, as kny&yogh;ttis, barouns or erlis, and prechyn<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> not but onys or &thorn;ries in &thorn;e &yogh;eer bi|fore grete lordis and comuntees for veyn glorie or worldely wynnyng, &thorn;ei be &thorn;anne ypocritis at &thorn;e fulle.</P>
<P>&YOGH;if &thorn;ei traueilen faste in aristole<NOTE PLACE="foot">Aristotile AA.</NOTE> and newe sophymes to ben clepyd maistres, and &thorn;an traueilen not in holy writt but veyn pleies &amp; corioustees, and excusen hem her-bi fro preiynge and rysynge at mydny&yogh;t, &thorn;ei ben ypocritis; for &thorn;ei don not goddis seruyce in hem selfe but drawen o&thorn;ere men &thorn;er-fro.</P>
<P>&YOGH;if &thorn;ei bynden hem to grete penaunce and abstynence of mete and drynk and &thorn;er-of bosten to &thorn;e peple, and here-with seken lustys of costly metis and drynkis, and bien hem derrere &thorn;an lordis don, and dwellen in courtis with lordes and ladies to feden here bely faat, and leuen here deuocions of cloistre, &thorn;ei ben foul ypocritis, for &thorn;ei maken here stynkynge bely here false god as seynt poule sei&thorn;.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Phil. iii. 19.</NOTE></P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei plesen lordes and ladies in synne and counforten hem to don extorcions to here pore tenauntes and to meyn|tene false causes for to haue lykyngis of here foule wombe; &thorn;ei ben wickid ypocritis and robberis of poore men and traitours to lordes and ladyes.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei bynde hem self to clene chastite bo&thorn;e of body and soule and of dede and wille, and here-wi&thorn; don fornycacioun and auoutrie wi&thorn; wyues and nonnes, and slen wommen &thorn;at with-stonden <MILESTONE N="5" UNIT="page">hem in &thorn;is synne; &thorn;ei ben foule ypocritis.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei don &thorn;e cursed synne of sodom wi&thorn; hem self, and seyn to nyse wymmen &thorn;at it is lesse synne to trespase with hem &thorn;an with o&thorn;ere weddid men, and vndir taken for &thorn;e synne of &thorn;e wommen, and norischen ryche men and wymmen in lecherie and in auoutrie for monye and to haue here owne lustis; &thorn;ei ben cursid ypocritis and distroien cristendom. It seme&thorn; &thorn;e deuyl gedre&thorn; siche lumpis of &yogh;onge men, fatte 
<PB REF="00000073.tif" N="7"> and lykynge and ydyl, and byndi&thorn; hem fro wyues, &thorn;at men my&yogh;ten haue bi goddis lawe, to maken false heiris and to for-do &thorn;e kynde of men and so make &thorn;e er&thorn;e cursed of god and alle his seyntis. And &thorn;us &thorn;ei ben ypocritis moste damp|nable bi-for god.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben most holy and best men of religion, and &thorn;er wi&thorn; lyuen in most pride, most enuye and wra&thorn;e, in most coueitise and ydilnesse, in most glotone, dronkennesse, or surfet and leccherie.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Probably there should follow "&thorn;ei ben cursid ypocritis," unless the preceding clause is to be taken as part of the sentence. But in both MSS. it is distinctly marked off.</NOTE></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="3" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 3<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>See now where &thorn;ei breken falsly alle &thorn;e comaundementis of god. &YOGH;if &thorn;ei chesyn to be reulid more after &thorn;e ordynaunce of synful men and ydiotis &thorn;an after &thorn;e clene ordynaunce of crist, and seyn &thorn;at synful mennus ordynaunce is betere and sikerere for men and more perfit &thorn;an is &thorn;e clene ordynaunce of crist; &thorn;ei worschipen false goddis and ben heretikys and blasphemes; and so &thorn;ei breken &thorn;e first maundement of god. &YOGH;if &thorn;ei dreden more and ponyschen more for brekynge of synful mennes contradicions &thorn;an for comaundementis of god cursedly broken, and studien and louen more here priuat reulis &thorn;an &thorn;e hestis of god, &thorn;ei worschepen, louen and dreden more synful men, and in caas dampnyd deuelis, &thorn;an god almy&yogh;ti. for as austyn sei&thorn; a man maki&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ing his god &thorn;e whiche he dredi&thorn; most or loue&thorn; most.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei chargen men more to seke blynde stockys or ymagis and to offre to hem more &thorn;an to pore bedrede men and more &thorn;an to charge goddis hestis; &thorn;ei worschipen false goddis. for &thorn;ou&yogh; a man breke goddis hestis &thorn;ei wole soone and li&yogh;tly assoile him, but &yogh;if he make a vow to a blynd pylgrymage or to sende his offrynge to siche a stok; &thorn;at schal not be dis|pensid wi&thorn; but reserued to a grettere satrap. And in &thorn;is &thorn;ei chargen more &thorn;e brekynge of a folie a-vow of synful men &thorn;an &thorn;e brekynge of goddis <MILESTONE N="6" UNIT="page">hestis; but whe&thorn;ere is more ydolatrie?
<PB REF="00000074.tif" N="8"></P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei sweren in veyn and many false o&thorn;is to bigile &yogh;onge children to here veyn religion, sweryng &thorn;at it is &thorn;e beste; who taki&thorn; &thorn;e name of god in more ydelnesse and more dispitt? &YOGH;if &thorn;ei taken &thorn;e charge to ben trewe vikeris or seruauntis of crist and &thorn;er-wi&thorn; taken vpon hem falsly &thorn;at &thorn;inge &thorn;at is reserued to god only, as to make men partyners of here medeful dedis, and to graunte hem &thorn;e blisse of heuene and pardon to slee cristen men for to meyntene worldely lordschip and coueitise of &thorn;at prist &thorn;at schulde be most meke, most pore, most redy to dye for cristen mennus soulis; who taki&thorn; more cursidly &thorn;e name of god in veyn?</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei vndirtaken to brynge soules out of purgatorie bi here preiers and here to receyuen myche gold or rentis, and &thorn;er-wi&thorn; lyuen in pride, enuye and o&thorn;ere grete synnes; who taki&thorn; more goddis name in veyn, and more cursidly dis|ceyue&thorn; cristen men? &para; For crist sei&thorn; to siche men in &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke vi. 46.</NOTE> gospel of seynt luk: What seie &yogh;ee to me lord! lord! and don not my comaundementis; and in &thorn;e gospel of matheu<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matth. xv. 8.</NOTE> sei&thorn; crist &thorn;at siche ypocritis worschipen him wi&thorn; outen cause; and by salomons bok sei&thorn; god &thorn;at his preiere is cursid<NOTE PLACE="marg">Prov. xxviii. [9.]</NOTE> and abhomynable &thorn;at turne&thorn; a wey his eris &thorn;at he here not goddis lawe; and also bi &thorn;e prophete ysaie and malachie and<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isaiah i. [15.]</NOTE> austyn and gregory and many moo.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Mal. i. [10.]</NOTE></P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei maken hem besi on &thorn;e holy day to preche fablis and lesyngis to &thorn;e peple and not &thorn;e gospel, and gon fro place to place and fro man to man to begge of pore men for here false lesyngis, and letten men fro here deuocioun; &thorn;ei kepen not wel here holiday. &para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei drawen &thorn;e peple in &thorn;e holiday by coryouste of gaye wyndownes and colours and peyntyngis and babwynrie fro conpunccion of here synnes and fro mynde of heuenely &thorn;inges, and fede riche men wi&thorn; pore mennus goodis, wi&thorn; costly metis and wynes and wast spicerie to glotonye, dronkenesse, lecherie, and weiward talis, and suffren pore men hungry and &thorn;risti and in gret mischef; &thorn;ei kepen euyl here holyday and letten o&thorn;ere men to kepen it. &para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei studien on &thorn;e holy day aboute experymentis or 
<PB REF="00000075.tif" N="9"> wiche craft <MILESTONE N="7" UNIT="page">or <SUP>1</SUP>veyn songis and <SUP>1</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">1_1 omitted X.</NOTE>knackynge and harpynge, gyternynge &amp; daunsynge &amp; o&thorn;ere veyn triflis to geten &thorn;e stynkyng loue of damyselis, and stere hem to worldely vanyte and synnes; &thorn;ei breken foule &thorn;er holyday and ben procuratours of &thorn;e fend.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei worschipen gretly here singuler patroun and dis|pisen god &thorn;e trynite and ih&umacr; crist oure goode fader, when &thorn;ei putten his lawe and his ordynaunce bihynde; &thorn;ei worschipen not here fadir after goodis lawe. &YOGH;if &thorn;ei louen more here singulere congregacion &thorn;an &thorn;e comynte of cristen men, &thorn;ei worschipen not but dispisen owre modire holy chirche. &yogh;if &thorn;ei drawen parischenes fro obedience and loue &amp; <NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE>sacramentis of here gostely fadris for here owne wynnyng, as in confessioun and beriynge &amp; herynge<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> of massis for offryng; how worschipen &thorn;ei and techen o&thorn;ere to worchipe here gostli fadris? &YOGH;if &thorn;ei drawen children fro fadir and modir and maken hem of here singulere religioun, &thorn;at &thorn;ei may not susteyne here heldris lif be &thorn;ei neuer so feble and pore; how worschipen &thorn;ei god and techen childre to leue &thorn;e maundement of god and to suffere fadire and modir to perische for feyned obydience to synful mannus tradiciouns? certis &thorn;is ilke fals religious is gilty of &thorn;efte and manquellyng also, si&thorn; he is cause of &thorn;e old pore mannus de&thorn;.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei haten and sclaundren with false lesynges trewe men to techen frely holy writt and repreuen synne, and namely ypocrisie, and falsly pursuen hem to &thorn;e de&thorn;, &thorn;ei slen hem, and ioon &thorn;e euaungelist sei&thorn; as to here dampnacion. &YOGH;if &thorn;ei<NOTE PLACE="marg">l John iii. 15.</NOTE> conforten men to slee here bre&thorn;ren in false werris, by open prechynge or preuei conseilynge, or vndirtakynge for false domesmen &thorn;at slen innocent men for coueityse or enmyte whanne men &yogh;euen hem myche tresoure; &thorn;ei ben false menquelleris and most gyltif of alle.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei letten curatis and pore prestis to techen men goddis lawe bi sotil ypocrisie and slei&yogh;tis of anticristis lawe, for 
<PB REF="00000076.tif" N="10"> drede lest here ypocrisie be parceyued and here wynnynge and worldly fame leid a-doun; &thorn;ei ben cursed manquelleris, and gylti of dampnacion of alle &thorn;e soulis &thorn;at perischen for &thorn;e defaute of kunnynge and kepynge of goddis comaunde|mentis.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei prechen principaly for worldeli muk or veyn glorie, and so prechen here owne sotiltes to be preised of men, and not <MILESTONE N="8" UNIT="page">symply and pleynly &thorn;e gospel of crist for his glorie and sauyng of mennus soulis; &thorn;ei don gostely lecherie bi goddis word as poul sei&thorn;.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei seyn and meyntenen in scole and o&thorn;ere placis &thorn;at &thorn;e wordis of holy writt ben false and manere of spekyng of newe idiotis is trewe, &thorn;ei don gostly auoutrie and putten falsnesse and blasphemye vpon god; for in &thorn;at &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at an he&thorn;ene philosofre or a newe synful caitif is wittiere and trewere &thorn;an almy&yogh;ti god, &yogh;e &thorn;at god is fals and a fole and &thorn;es he&thorn;ene blasphemes and newe dremeris ben trewe and witti.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei feynen hem sotil of fisik and knowynge of wym|menys complexcion and preuyte, seiynge &thorn;at siche siknesse or de&thorn; schal com to hem in absence of here housbondis but &yogh;if &thorn;ei haue mannus helpe, and &thorn;us defoulen on and o&thorn;er; &thorn;ei breken foule &thorn;is comaundement &thorn;at biddi&thorn; men do no lecherie; and in &thorn;is poynt men dreden &thorn;at &thorn;es pharisees geten hem moo holderis vp for here putrie &thorn;an for here trewe prechyng or holy lyf.</P>
<P>&para; Whanne lordis ben fro hom in werris, in iustis and par|lementis and in dyuerse lordschipis, and whanne marchauntis ben out of lond or in fer cuntrees for here marchaundise, and whanne plowmen ben al day in &thorn;e feld at here plow&yogh; ore medes; &thorn;an &thorn;es pharisees presen faste to here wyues vnder colour of holynesse.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei stelen mennus children, bo&thorn;e gentyl mennus and pore, to make hem of here synguler ordre &thorn;at is maad of synful men and confermyd, &amp; in cas of<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> deuelis and not of god; &thorn;ei don cursed &thorn;efte a&yogh;enst &thorn;e seue[n]&thorn;e maundement of 
<PB REF="00000077.tif" N="11"> god. for many men ben drawen, bi lesynges and &yogh;iftis and so by symonye, fro &thorn;e betere ordre to &thorn;e werse and maad more cursed and deppere dampnyd in helle. For &thorn;ou&yogh; children ben brou&yogh;t be lesyngis, symonye and fals bihestis in-to &thorn;is feyned ordre bifore tyme of discrecion and ben not able &thorn;er-to, &yogh;it &thorn;ei schulle be nedid bi peyne of dampnynge in helle, as &thorn;ei seyn, and bi drede of bodely de&thorn; to holde for&thorn; &thorn;is feyned religion a&yogh;enst here conscience and fredom of &thorn;e gospel. and he &thorn;at most steli&thorn; children to &thorn;es priuatis ordris is most preised of &thorn;es cursed congregacion, and &thorn;at is a cursed reward. For he &thorn;at steli&thorn; an oxe or a cowe is a &thorn;ef and gretly <MILESTONE N="9" UNIT="page">peyned bi mannus lawe; myche more owi&thorn; he to be ponyschid bo&thorn;e of god and man &thorn;at steli&thorn; his owne child, &thorn;at is betere &thorn;an alle worldely goodis; and here-bi ben gentil mennus heiris distroied, and so lordis and also laboreris and sumtyme trewe prestis and curatis ben made beggeris and lesyngmongeris to destruction of londis. &YOGH;if &thorn;ei techen wyues, prentis, seruauntis and children to stele fro here housbondis, maistris and fadir and modir and &yogh;euen it to &thorn;es pharisees, as hildegar sei&thorn;, &thorn;ei ben perilous &thorn;euys to make discencioun among manye. &YOGH;if &thorn;ei feynen hem nedy and pore whanne &thorn;ei ben ryche and proude, and beggen of &thorn;e pore peple, and maken men to wene &thorn;at &thorn;ei schulden haue more &thorn;ank of god to &yogh;eue here almes to riche possessioners or o&thorn;er ryche pharisees &thorn;an to &yogh;euen it to here pore nei&yogh;bores as crist biddi&thorn;; &thorn;ei ben foule &thorn;eues, for &thorn;ei robben &thorn;e almes &yogh;euere bo&thorn;e of fei&thorn;, of worldely catel, and pore bedrede men of here liflode.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei putten on here pore bre&thorn;ren &thorn;at lyuen wel and reprouen hem of here synnes &thorn;at &thorn;ei wolden distroie holy religion, and here-fore disceisen hem and putten hem in prison, and sumtyme mor&thorn;ere hem a&yogh;enst goddis lawe and &thorn;e kyngys; &thorn;ei beren false wyttenesse a&yogh;enst here nei&yogh;ebore, and ben cursed manquelleris. &para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei beren on pore prestis &thorn;at techen &thorn;e trew&thorn;e of &thorn;e gospel and &thorn;e goodenesse of cristis ordynaunce &thorn;at &thorn;ei wolde distroie holi chirche, and here-fore 
<PB REF="00000078.tif" N="12"> pursuen hem to &thorn;e de&thorn; and maken prelatys lordis and comunes to do also; &thorn;ei beren false wittenesse, and ben manquelleris and irregulere bifore god and traitouris to god and alle holi chirche. &yogh;if &thorn;ei pursuen to &thorn;e de&thorn; pore freris serabitis, &thorn;at kepen fraunseis reule and testament to &thorn;e ri&yogh;te vndyrstond|ynge and wille of fraunceis wi&thorn; outen glose of antecristis clerkis; &thorn;ei beren false wyttenesse a&yogh;eyns here patron and ben caynis bre&thorn;ren &thorn;at killyd his bro&thorn;er fore his goode lyuynge. &yogh;if &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at cristis lawe is not ynow&yogh; and &thorn;e beste to reule holy chirche, but lawis of proude coueitouse and worldly clerkis ben nedful and betere, and stryuen a&yogh;enst goode men &thorn;at techen &thorn;e goodnesse and excellence of cristis lawe and his ordynaunce and declaren &thorn;e falsenesse and ypocrisie of worldly prestis newe lawis; &thorn;ei beren false witnesse and ben traitours to god and stynkynge blasphemes.</P>
<P><MILESTONE N="10" UNIT="page">&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei coueiten vnresonabiliche &thorn;e housis, &thorn;at ben goodis vnmeble of here nei&yogh;eboris as londis or rentis, or perpetual almes of coffris, si&thorn; &thorn;ei bynden hem to pouert of crist and his apostelis, &thorn;ei breken &thorn;e neyn&thorn;e maundement of god.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei leden a-wey mennus wyues or wenches in here newe habitis, to do lecherie bi hem as hem liste, &thorn;ei breken &thorn;e laste comaundement. &YOGH;if &thorn;ei maken wyues and o&thorn;er wymmen hure sustris bi lettris of fraternite or o&thorn;ere iapes, and geten children vpon hem to make hem freris or nunnes to holde vp here veyn sectis bi lordischipe, &thorn;ei coueiten euyle here nei&yogh;bores wyues and wenchis; namely, &yogh;if &thorn;ei waiten hem in feldis alone or gardyns and sleen hem &thorn;er by keruynge to moche vsynge of lecherie. &YOGH;if &thorn;ei becomen pedderis berynge knyues, pursis, pynnys and girdlis and spices and sylk and precious pellure and forrouris for wymmen, and &thorn;erto smale gentil hondis, to gete loue of hem and to haue many grete &yogh;iftis for litil good ore nou&yogh;t; &thorn;ei coueiten euyle here nei&yogh;eboris goodis.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei ben made wafreris, &yogh;euynge lordes, ladies and riche men a fewe peris, appelis or nottis to haue huge &yogh;iftis to 
<PB REF="00000079.tif" N="13"> &thorn;e couent, euyl &thorn;ei coueiten here ne&yogh;eboris goodis. &YOGH;if &thorn;ei meyntenen men in extorscions, in robberie, in false sweryng to sille ouer dere &thorn;er marchaundise and bie to grete cheep of pore men, and in lecherie and grete synnes, vndirtakynge for &thorn;es cursed men at domes day for part of wynnyng; &thorn;ei coueiten euyle here nei&yogh;eboris goodis; for &thorn;ei dysceyuen here soulis herfore to euere dampnynge in helle. and &yogh;if &thorn;ei breken &thorn;is, and worse alle &thorn;e comaundementis of god; &thorn;ei ben perilous ypocritis and disceyuen foule cristen men to meyntene goddis traitors principaly. &YOGH;if &thorn;ei geten hem worldly offis in lordis courtis, summe to ben stiwardis of halle,<SUP>1</SUP> summe to ben kechene clerkis, <SUP>1</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">1_1 omitted X.</NOTE>summe to ben lordis anyneris, and summe to ben conseilours and reuleris of werris, and also to bein chamberleyns to lordes and ladies, and putten out pore gentil men of here office, and forsaken here cloistre and o&thorn;er deuocions for to haue lykynge of mete and drynk and clo&thorn; and worldly worschipe, and to sende a grett quantite to here couent &thorn;at pore bedrede men schulden haue; <MILESTONE N="11" UNIT="page">&thorn;anne &thorn;ei ben ypocritis, enemyes of pore gentil men<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> and traitours of pore men and of lordes and ladies.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="4" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 4<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>See now where &thorn;es religious don a&yogh;enst &thorn;e werkis of mercy bo&thorn;e bodili and gostely. &yogh;if &thorn;ei wasten delicat metis and drynkis and &yogh;euen nou&yogh;t to pore men of here owene secte ne o&thorn;ere &thorn;at ben in gret nede, but drawen pore mennus almes and liflode to here owne couent &thorn;at ha&thorn; to moche of worldly goodis, to make festis huge to lordis and ladies and riche men of contres; &thorn;ei feden not pore men but robben hem of here liflode, and so ben manquelleris bifore god.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei feynen hem to be men of abstynence and grete penaunce, and &thorn;er wi&thorn; drynkyn dilicious ale and spisid and hei&yogh;e wynes, and beggen of &thorn;e comune peple to holden vp 
<PB REF="00000080.tif" N="14"> &thorn;is realte, and &yogh;euen lordis and ladies &thorn;es swete drynkys for to magnyfie &thorn;es sectis, and suffren here owene bre&thorn;eren bo&thorn;e wi&thorn; inne and oute to perische for &thorn;rist and myschef; &thorn;ei &yogh;euen not drenk to pore &thorn;risti men but ra&thorn;ere drawen here sustynaunce fro hem vndir colour of holynesse, and so ben worse &thorn;an comune &thorn;eues and outlawis, for &thorn;ei take fro riche men and parte oft wi&thorn; pore men.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei gederen to hem self many wast and precious clo&thorn;es bi feyned beggerie and sotil ypocrisie, and parti&thorn; not with pore nedy men &thorn;at han nakid sidis and torne sleues and here children steruen for cold, nei&thorn;er here owen bre&thorn;eren, be &thorn;ei in neuere so gret myschef &amp; cheueren for cold, hou clo&thorn;e &thorn;ei nakid men, whanne bi ypocrisie &thorn;ei drawen fro hem &thorn;is bodily almes bi whiche &thorn;es poralis schulden be clo&thorn;id and kept fro de&thorn;. certis &thorn;ei ben cursed disceyueris bo&thorn;e of pore and riche, and ben irreguler bi-for god for myschefous de&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;es nedy men suffren. &YOGH;if &thorn;ei han grete waste houses for to resceyuen lordis and ladies, &yogh;e to soiorne among hem daies and &yogh;eris, and o&thorn;ere riche men ny&yogh;t and day, and helpen not pore nedi men with hereberwe in &thorn;o grete placis as kyngis paleis, but ra&thorn;ere drawe pore mennus goodis fro hem to &thorn;es waste placis, hou receyue &thorn;ei pore men to herberwe? namely, whanne &thorn;ei disceyuen riche men in makyng restitu|cioun of extorcions and euyl geten goodis, and suren hem of al perel &yogh;if &thorn;ei maken siche costly houses and wast paleises to men <MILESTONE N="12" UNIT="page">&thorn;at haue forsaken alle worldly ioie and pride and taken cristis mekenesse and gret pouert bi wilful profession. it seme&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben preuy enemys of pore men and dis|ceyueris of riche men and sclaunderis of crist puttyng on hym siche worldly pompe and ypocrisie.</P>
<P>And &yogh;if &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at grete chirchis ben worschipful to god and lykynge for &thorn;e peple to serue god inne, axe hem what charite it is to laten parische chirchis fallen doun for defaute, where &thorn;e peple schulde heere goodis worde, goddis seruyce, and resceyue here sacramentis, and to maken newe chirchis as castelis wi&thorn; outen nede; and whe&thorn;er crist preied most in 
<PB REF="00000081.tif" N="15"> &thorn;e ny&yogh;t in hillis, as &thorn;e gospel sei&thorn;, and tau&yogh;te mychel &thorn;e peple in desert and in &thorn;e wilde felde, and seide &thorn;at &thorn;e hei&yogh;e temple schulde be distroied for &thorn;e synne of prestis &thorn;at weren &thorn;er-inne. And seyn &thorn;at lucifer and adam serueden not god in heuene ne paradis as &thorn;ei schulden, but iob seruede wel god in &thorn;e donge hille and adam also in &thorn;e valey of wepynge, and so dide crist in &thorn;e hillis, and &thorn;e prophete danyel in &thorn;e deen of lyonys. and &thorn;ou&yogh; men suffreden resonable cost of chirchis whi schulde &thorn;ei suffre so grete cost of kechenes and &yogh;ate housis and wast chambris for lordis and ladies and riche men, and a frere to haue a chambre for an erl or duk or a kyng whanne he is bounden to &thorn;e pouert of crist, si&thorn; &thorn;is cost is geten bi beggen of pore men and disceit of riche mennus almes. &yogh;if &thorn;ei visiten not pore men in prison for charite of god and sauynge of soulis, bute riche men in here prosperite to han part of here worldly goodis, hou don &thorn;ei werkis of mercy? for sumtyme for enuye and hate ful trewe men ben sett in prison, and &thorn;anne it were most nede to conforte hem in bodi and soule a&yogh;enst defaute of mete and drynk and clo&thorn; and grucchynge a&yogh;enst god or dispeir; but it is worse &yogh;if &thorn;ei be ypocrisie and false beggynge reuen fro pore prisoneris &thorn;e almes &thorn;at &thorn;ei schulden ellis haue.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei visyten not pore men in here sikenesse but riche men wi&thorn; preue massis and placeboes and dirige, &thorn;ou&yogh; pore men ben neuere so deuout and han neuere so myche nede to ben amendid of here lif, hou seken &thorn;ei &thorn;e helpe<NOTE PLACE="foot">hel&thorn;e AA.</NOTE> of soule? but only or principaly worldly muk or auauntage. where helpen &thorn;ei sike men of bodely almes, &thorn;ou&yogh; <MILESTONE N="13" UNIT="page">&thorn;ei hem self han neuere so muche wast of mete and drynk, but ra&thorn;ere in siche tyme &thorn;ei gedren fro sike men al &thorn;at &thorn;ei may.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei ben faste aboute to haue riche men biried in here housis for wynnynge and offrynge and worldly meyntenaunce and forsaken pore men to be biried &thorn;ere, &thorn;ei ben false ypocritis, traueilynge in coueitise and pride and &thorn;efte, for &thorn;ei drawen riche men fro her gostly fadris and here owne 
<PB REF="00000082.tif" N="16"> parischenys, and so departen in tyme of de&thorn; curatis and here gostly children.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei pursuen pore prestis to prison and bodily de&thorn;, as hangynge, drawynge or brennynge, for &thorn;ei techen trewely and frely &thorn;e gospel of ih&umacr; crist and techen men wiche ben false prophetis and ypocritis, si&thorn; holy writt speki&thorn; of siche and biddi&thorn; cristen men knowe hem bi here opyn werkis and flee fro hem; &thorn;anne ben &thorn;ei perilous ypocritis and heretikis a&yogh;enst goddis worschipe and sauynge of cristene soulis.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei &thorn;ursuen trewe lige men of &thorn;e kyng to endityng falsly and wyttyngly for &thorn;ei reprouen here open synnes, hou visiten &thorn;ei men in prison? si&thorn; &thorn;ei drawe trewe men to prison to loos of catel and de&thorn; wi&thorn; outen resonable cause.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei drawen pore husbondemen to dom for &thorn;e bi-he&yogh;ten &thorn;em almes sumtyme and now ben tau&yogh;t to &yogh;euen here almes to pore nei&yogh;eboris aftir &thorn;e gospel, or &thorn;at may not now paie so gret almes for pouerte and myschif &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben inne, hou don &thorn;ei &thorn;e werkis of mercy? si&thorn; &thorn;ei don opynly a&yogh;enst charite.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="5" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 5<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>See now where &thorn;ei failen in werkis of gostly mercy. first &yogh;if &thorn;ei techen opynly fablys, cronyklis and lesyngis and leuen cristis gospel and &thorn;e maundementis of god, and &yogh;it don &thorn;ei &thorn;is principaly for worldly wynnynge, frendschipe or veyn name &thorn;ei don a&yogh;enst &thorn;e chifwerk of gostly mercy; nameliche &yogh;if &thorn;ei techen &thorn;at here singuler preiere is betere &thorn;an &thorn;e pater noster &thorn;at crist made him self, and &thorn;at preiynge bi lippis is plesaunt to god &thorn;ou&yogh; mennus lif &thorn;at preien be cursed of god for brekynge of his hestis and defaute of charite.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei counseilen men to be bysi a-boute worldliche richessis more &thorn;an a-boute here soule hel&thorn;e and &thorn;e blisse of heuene, and conseilen men more to taken vengaunce bi open werre of here bre&thorn;ren &thorn;an to suffren paciently wrongys and 
<PB REF="00000083.tif" N="17"> haue mercy on o&thorn;er nei&yogh;eboris; &thorn;ei don foule <MILESTONE N="14" UNIT="page">a&yogh;enst &thorn;e secunde werk of gostly mercy, to dampnacion of many men bo&thorn; of body and soule. &YOGH;if &thorn;ei conseilen men to leue &thorn;e fredom of cristis ordre and take here singuler ordre maad of synful men, seiynge &thorn;at it is &thorn;e beste for hem vp peril of here soule; &thorn;ei don a&yogh;enst &thorn;e charite for loue of here owne worschipe or wynnynge and blasphemen a&yogh;enst god, makynge hem self as witti as &thorn;e holy gost. si&thorn; it is reseruyd only to &thorn;e holy gost to &yogh;euen ful conseil of &thorn;ingis &thorn;at [ben] not expresly comaundyd ne defendid in holy writt, and &thorn;ei taken &thorn;is &thorn;inge vpon hem whanne &thorn;ei ensuren to men &thorn;at it is best for hem to be men of priuat religion. and also &thorn;ei conseilen sumtyme euene a&yogh;enst &thorn;e sterynge of &thorn;e holy gost, and maken men dispeire dampnyd for schrewidnesse of &thorn;is ordre and of men &thorn;er-inne, for &thorn;er-by &thorn;ei lasten more and ben more hardid in synne and ypocrisie.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei chastisen not here bre&thorn;eren for grete synnes, so &thorn;at &thorn;ei be preue, but ouerscharply ponyschen hem for smale synnes &thorn;at ben open and make hem seme vnholy to &thorn;e world; &thorn;ei failen foule in werkis of charite and ben false ypocritis. and &yogh;if &thorn;ei chastisen not here bre&thorn;ren for opyn sweryng veynly and pride and inpacience and false coueitynge of &thorn;er nei&yogh;eboris goodis, but for litil trespasynge a&yogh;enst here owne statutis or customys; &thorn;ei failen in dwe chastisynge of synne, for &thorn;ei chargen not dispit or trespas don a&yogh;enst god, but a&yogh;enst here owen worldly worschipe and name of holynesse.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei conforten not pore men in here myschif bo&thorn;e of soule and body but suffren hem perische for dispeir or defaute of bodily goodis, but ra&thorn;ere visiten hem in here prosperite for worldly muk; &thorn;ei failen fully in werkis of charite and mercy to here bre&thorn;eren. &para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei gon gladly and faste to lordis housis and ladies &thorn;at ben gloriously araied, and deynen not to come in pore mennus houses for stynk and o&thorn;ere fil&thorn;e; hou suen &thorn;ei charite? si&thorn; crist sparid not to visyte pore men in a foul stynkynge stable and cold, and in &thorn;e colde greue and in helle, and in many foule weies in &thorn;is world, bo&thorn;e in 
<PB REF="00000084.tif" N="18"> gret hungur and &thorn;rist and gret werynesse and cold and muche sclaundrynge and cursynge aud o&thorn;ere peynes ynowe. &para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei wolen not for&yogh;eue litel trespace don a&yogh;enst hem self or feyned seyntis of here singuler secte but moste cruelly <MILESTONE N="15" UNIT="page">pursuen men &thorn;erfore; &thorn;ei forsaken pacience and mekenesse and ensaumple of cristis lif. and men dreden &thorn;at enuye, rancour and euyl wille dwelli&thorn; lengest amonges hem of alle o&thorn;ere men, be &thorn;ei lordis, be &thorn;ei prelatis, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei ben men of armys; but where is falsere holynesse, and so foulere ypocrisie? for &thorn;ou&yogh; a man speke a&yogh;enst a lord, clerk or prelat he schal sonere be reconsilid be weie of mekenesse &thorn;an to newe feyned religions; for &thorn;ei wolen pursue to de&thorn; or open schame, and &yogh;it vndir colour of holynesse.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei soone lesen pacience and bringgyn men out of pacience &thorn;at speken a&yogh;enst here ypocrisie and euyl dedis; hou don &thorn;ei werkis of mercy, si&thorn; &thorn;ei schulde be here meke|nesse and pacience bryngyn o&thorn;ere in-to reste and pees of body and soule. &YOGH;if &thorn;ei profren gentil men and o&thorn;ere to fi&yogh;te wi&thorn; hem whanne &thorn;ei reprouen hem of here opyn wyckyd dedis, hou ben &thorn;ei ensaumple of crist and his apostelis to saue o&thorn;ere men in reste and charite? it seme&thorn; &thorn;ei ben fendis children to stryue a&yogh;enst &thorn;e treu&thorn;e, and meyntene syn and brynge o&thorn;er men to helle bi procurynge of fi&yogh;t and lesynge of pacience and charite.</P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei cursen and warien and pursuen here enemyes and axen vengaunce of god a&yogh;enst hem; hou suen &thorn;ei charite of crist &thorn;at biddi&thorn; men to loue here enemyes, and don good to men &thorn;at haten vs, and to preie for hem &thorn;at falsly chalengen vs and falsly and wickidly pursuen vs? &yogh;if &thorn;ei don &thorn;us and welle werse a&yogh;enst &thorn;e hestis of god and werkis of mercy bo&thorn;e bodily and gostly, &thorn;ei ben foule ypocritis and not wor&thorn;i but to be putt out fro cristen men and defoulid, and not wor&thorn;i to be putt in &thorn;e er&thorn;e, &thorn;at is to haue &thorn;e leste office in &thorn;e chirche.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="6" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000085.tif" N="19">
<HEAD>Capitulum 6<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>See now whe&thorn;er &thorn;ei faile in fei&thorn;, hope and charite. &yogh;if &thorn;at o part holdi&thorn; wi&thorn; o pope and &thorn;e to&thorn;er wi&thorn; o no&thorn;ere pope, and eche partie seie and techi&thorn; as bileue &thorn;at &thorn;is pope is verray and noon o&thorn;ere, and alle &thorn;at bileuen not so ben cursed heretikis out of bileue; &thorn;ei ben alle out of bileue and bryngen alle o&thorn;er out of bileue; and &yogh;it &thorn;ei comunen to|gidre bo&thorn;e partis as cristen men, and so &thorn;ei seyn o &thorn;ing and don &thorn;e contrarie as ful false men. &YOGH;if &thorn;ei techen opynly and meyntene &thorn;at &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">here X.</NOTE> bileue &thorn;at crist and his apostelis tau&yogh;ten is not &thorn;e best and ynow&yogh; to brynge men to heuene, but lawis maade of worldly prestis ben nedful and betere to reule holy chirche bi; &thorn;ei erren foule <MILESTONE N="16" UNIT="page">in &thorn;e fei&thorn; and blasphemen crist god and man. &yogh;if &thorn;ei seyn, written and techen openly &thorn;at &thorn;e sacrament of &thorn;e auter &thorn;at men seen bitwen &thorn;e prestis hondis is accidentis wi&thorn;-outen suget and nei&thorn;er bred ne cristis body; si&thorn; holy writt sei&thorn; &thorn;at it is breede and cristis precious body, &thorn;ei ben cursed heretikis. &yogh;if &thorn;ei putten on<NOTE PLACE="foot">of X.</NOTE> crist &thorn;at he beggid as &thorn;ei don fro toun to toun and fro hous to hous wi&thorn; open cryeng; &thorn;ei erren foule in &thorn;e fei&thorn; and putten errour vpon crist. &yogh;if &thorn;ei disceyuen men in fei&thorn; bi fals pardons, bi mannus preiere, bi letteris of fraternyte and bi here feyned roten abite; &thorn;ei ben false prophetis hauynge &thorn;e lickenesse of holy religion and dis|troien<NOTE PLACE="marg">2 Tim. iii. 5 (?).</NOTE> cristis religion, as poul sei&thorn;. and so<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted.</NOTE> of signes of anticrist, of fiftene tokenes bifore domes-day, and of veyn nouelries wi&thorn;-outen noumbre as to men.</P>
<P>&YOGH;if &thorn;ei hopen to plese god more bi kepynge of here owne tradicions and singuler obedience and profession to synful wrecchis, and maken o&thorn;ere more<NOTE PLACE="foot">more is inserted in AA by a corrector.</NOTE> sikyrly to hopen &thorn;us, &thorn;anne for kepynge of cristis gospel and trewe obedience, eche man to o&thorn;er in &thorn;e drede<NOTE PLACE="foot">degre X.</NOTE> of crist as crist and his apostelis diden, &thorn;ei failen foule in good hope.
<PB REF="00000086.tif" N="20"></P>
<P>&para; &YOGH;if &thorn;ei louen more fonnyd ordynaunce of men &thorn;an ordy|naunce of ih&umacr; crist, &yogh;if &thorn;ei seken more here owne worschipe &thorn;an worschipe of god, &yogh;if &thorn;ei setten here hertis more aboute worldly muk &thorn;an aboute verteuous lif and &thorn;e blisse of heuene and sauynge of cristen soulis; &thorn;ei failen foule a&yogh;enst charite and alle o&thorn;ere vertues. &thorn;is men my&yogh;ten schewe bi seuene &yogh;iftis of &thorn;e holy gost, bi myspendynge of fyue wittis, bi sixe consentis of synne, and colourynge and meyntenynge of alle synnes preue and apert, and namely bi false procurynge of matrymonye bi soteltees and queyntese and false bihetynges, and fals dyuors makynge, hou &thorn;es newe feyned religious ben anticristis, sent preuyly of &thorn;e fend to disceyue men in gostly goodis and worldly, and norischen hem esily in synne, and dryuen hem to helle to euerlastynge de&thorn;. and &thorn;erfore comaundi&thorn; crist &thorn;at we be war and flee fro &thorn;e ypocrisie of pharisees.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="7" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 7<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>And [Christ] sei&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;er is no &thorn;ing keuerid &thorn;at ne it<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke xii. 2.</NOTE> schal be schewid, and &thorn;ere is no &thorn;ing hid so priue &thorn;at it ne schal be wist and knowen. for &thorn;o &thorn;ingis &thorn;at &yogh;e han seyd in derknessis schullen be seid in li&yogh;t, and &thorn;at &thorn;ing &thorn;at &yogh;e han spoken in &yogh;oure couchis or smale beddis schal be prechid in &thorn;e roof of housis. Here crist meni&thorn; &thorn;at men schulden be war and oppynly telle &thorn;e <MILESTONE N="17" UNIT="page">trew&thorn;e a&yogh;enst &thorn;is ypocrisie; for &thorn;ou&yogh; it be now hid it schal be schewid at &thorn;e laste at &thorn;e day of dom. &para; And also cowardise of cristis disciplis, &yogh;if &thorn;ei spare for bodyli peyne and de&thorn; to telle openly &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> treu&thorn;e of goddis lawe. And &thorn;erfore telli&thorn; crist after to his disciplis<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke xii. 4.</NOTE> &thorn;at &thorn;ei schulden drede god and no &thorn;ing ellis souereynly. So&thorn;li sei&thorn; crist: I sei to &yogh;ow, my frendis, &thorn;at &yogh;e ben not agast of hem &thorn;at sleen &thorn;e body and haue<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> no &thorn;ing more<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> to do after &thorn;es &thorn;inges; but I schal schewe &yogh;ou whom &yogh;e owen to drede. drede &yogh;e hym souereynly, &thorn;at after &thorn;at he ha&thorn; sclayn 
<PB REF="00000087.tif" N="21"> &thorn;e bodi, ha&thorn; power to sende bo&thorn;e bodi and soule to helle with outen ende. so, I say to &yogh;ow; drede &yogh;e him. here crist wol &thorn;at men drede no &thorn;ing principaly but god and his offence. for &yogh;if men dreden bodili peynes and de&thorn;, and &thorn;erfore ceessen to telle openly &thorn;e treu&thorn;e, &thorn;ei ben wi&thorn; &thorn;is vnable to resceyue &thorn;e blisse of heuene; and &yogh;if &thorn;ei seyn openly and sadly &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of god, no &thorn;ing may harmen hem so &thorn;at &thorn;ei kepen pacience and charite. &para; And herefore sei&thorn; crist aftir|ward to conforte his disciplis bi reson: ne be not fyue sparwis sold for an halpeny, and on of hem is not for&yogh;etyn<NOTE PLACE="foot">for&yogh;euen X.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke xii. 6.</NOTE> bifore god; but also alle &thorn;e heris of &yogh;oure heuyd ben noum|brid, &thorn;erfore nyle &yogh;ee drede; &yogh;e ben of more pris &thorn;an many sparwis. as &yogh;if crist menede and made &thorn;is reson: si&thorn; god almy&yogh;ty taki&thorn; so gret kepyng of smale briddis &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;an.</NOTE> on<NOTE PLACE="foot">or X.</NOTE> of hem, &yogh;e &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> leste, is not for&yogh;eten, how myche more schal god kepen &yogh;ow; si&thorn; he is almy&yogh;ty, alwytti, and al ful of good wille, &amp; &thorn;ere may no &thorn;ing come with outen his wittyng and his ordynaunce, and it is al for &thorn;e beste. &para; And no &thorn;ing may a&yogh;enstonde, so &thorn;at men takyt paciently and &thorn;anke hem &thorn;erfore; and whanne &thorn;e heris of oure heuyd ben countid &thorn;at &thorn;ei may not be lost, where we may be lost o&thorn;ere in bodi or soule, si&thorn;e eche of vs is betre &thorn;an &thorn;e heris of oure hed. as &yogh;if crist seide &thorn;at no &thorn;ing of vs, nere of bodi ne of soule, may perische ne suffre peyne to oure harim, so &thorn;at we kepen pacience and charite. at &thorn;e laste word crist make&thorn; vs siker to dye for his lawe bi reward of &thorn;e blisse of heuene, whanne he sei&thorn; &thorn;us, &thorn;at eche who euere knowlechi&thorn; me bi-for men,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke xii. 8.</NOTE> and mannus sone schal knowleche hym bi-fore &thorn;e angelis of god. here crist clepi&thorn; hym self mannus sone, for he is &thorn;e sone of &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> vergyne marie, and so a persone of mankynde, &thorn;at is clepyd a man bi speche of holy writt. and knowlechynge <SUP>6</SUP>is seid here fore verrei knowlegchynge <SUP>6</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">6_6 omitted X.</NOTE>of crist, bo&thorn;e in herte bi saad fei&thorn; &thorn;at he is verrey god and verrey man with outen synne, &amp; alle degrees, in &thorn;ou&yogh;t and speche and dede and alle circumstauncis &thorn;er of, and witnessynge in word &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of 
<PB REF="00000088.tif" N="22"> &thorn;e gospel, hou crist lyuede most mekely and most porely and most vertuously bi-forn alle o&thorn;ere men as &thorn;e gospel teche&thorn;; and knowlechynge in lif, lyuynge after &thorn;e lawe of god and in<MILESTONE N="18" UNIT="page">wille to die &thorn;er-fore &yogh;if it be nede; &thorn;is verrei knowlechynge schal make men to ben approued of crist at &thorn;e day of dome, biforn alle &thorn;e compayne of angelis and seyntis and good creaturis and euyle, hou &thorn;ei were verrei wittenesse of crist in er&thorn;e bifore men, and in fulwille to suffre sclandris pursuynge and bodili de&thorn; for &thorn;e loue of ih&umacr; crist and his lawe.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="8" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 8<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Here may men touche &thorn;e cowardise and fal[s]nesse of prestis, lordis, marchauntis and alle o&thorn;ere men &thorn;at failen in charite anemtis god and his lawe. where ben &thorn;o prestis &thorn;at maken hem so bisy aboute grete benefices, wordly worschipis and stynkynge muk or drit of worldeli richesse, &thorn;at &thorn;ei wolen travaile<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> gladly ny&yogh;t and day in lordis courtis, in worldely offis, for litel cost takynge of &thorn;e lord in hope of beneficis; and so bisily &thorn;at vnne&thorn;is may &thorn;ei at reste seie metenes or masse with deuocioun. o&thorn;ere prestis rennen out of oure lond ouer grete sees and &thorn;oru&yogh; londes of enemyes in peril of here lif, in gret cold, hungur, &thorn;rist, stormes and tempestis, &thorn;at it is wondir hou &thorn;ei may lyue; but hou bisi maken &thorn;ei hem self and o&thorn;ere to lerne, kepe and teche goddis lawe? certis but &yogh;if &thorn;ei more bisily lerne bi grete traueile and studie holy writt, and kepen it trewly in here lyuynge, and openly to &yogh;eue good ensaumple to alle men, and prechen it sadly and trewly with als myche traueile and more, and &yogh;it it be nede ben wilful to die &thorn;erfore, &thorn;ei may drede ful sore &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben out of charite and out of fei&thorn;, but &yogh;if it be ded fei&thorn; as fendis han; for &thorn;ei traueilen more for worldly worschipe and stynkynge drit &thorn;an for loue of god and hel&thorn;e of mannus soule. And &yogh;it, &thorn;at is werse, &thorn;ei beren gold out of englond, and 
<PB REF="00000089.tif" N="23"> sumtyme it comi&thorn; to oure enemys and &thorn;er-bi &thorn;ei ben strengyed a&yogh;enst vs, and bi takynge of prisoneris of oure nacion, and sumtyme oure enemys killen many of oure lond &thorn;orou&thorn; siche traueile for benefices to gret reprof of oure rewme. And &yogh;if &thorn;e gold<NOTE PLACE="foot">god X.</NOTE> come to rome, &thorn;er-bi ben benefices of &thorn;e chirches bou&yogh;t and sold. &para; For who so may most gold brynge sunnest schal be sped to grete benefices, &thorn;ou&yogh; he be vnable bo&thorn;e of kunnynge and lif, and able men of kunnynge and lif ben putt bihynde; summe for &thorn;ei willen not chaffare by symonye, and summe bi bisinesse of studie and techynge of holy writt, for &thorn;ei<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> wollen nei&thorn;er dwelle in lordis courtis ne renne to rome wi&thorn; &thorn;e kyngis gold. and &yogh;if gooddis lawe and mannus and reson ben wel sou&yogh;t &thorn;is chaffarynge wi&thorn; suche benefyces and gold is symonye on bo&thorn;e partis; and so heresie, as &thorn;es lawereris written openly in here owene lawe. And &thorn;us &thorn;es rome renneris beren &thorn;e <MILESTONE N="19" UNIT="page">kyngys gold out of oure lond &amp; bryngen a&yogh;en deed leed and heresie and symonye and goddis curse. and comunly whanne &thorn;es heretikis comen bi symonye to gret benefices &thorn;ei ben not bisi to lerne &thorn;e gospel &amp; teche it cristen men, but &yogh;eue hem to huntynge and hauk[y]nge and veyn pleies, and hanten tauernys of wyn and ale, aboute strumpetis and grete festes, riche clo&thorn;ing and gay squyeris and o&thorn;ere getteris, &thorn;at al-most noon schal be so nyse and worldly proude as &thorn;es stynkynge heretikis. and &yogh;if ony poore prestis wole come to here chirchis and treuly dispise synne and frely teche goddis lawe, &thorn;e gospel of ih&umacr; crist, and comaundementis of god, &thorn;es coueitous symonyentis welen be &thorn;e firste to lette hem with &thorn;is grete colour &thorn;at suche prechoris ben heretikis; and &thorn;is &thorn;ei seyn for &thorn;ei ben ful of heresie and wolden &thorn;at no man spoke a&yogh;enst here cursed lif. &thorn;us &thorn;ei techen not hem self but ensaumple of pride, lecherie and o&thorn;ere synnes, and letten o&thorn;ere trewe prestis to techen goddis lawe. and &thorn;is is on of &thorn;e most vengaunce &thorn;at god taki&thorn; on synful men, to suffre suche ypocritis to reule &thorn;e peple &amp; drawe hem to helle bi wi&thorn;-drawynge of goddis word 
<PB REF="00000090.tif" N="24"> and &yogh;euynge of opyn<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> ensaumple of synne. for haue &thorn;ei here myr&thorn;e and iolite, nowarde to hem hou faste &thorn;e woluys of helle wirien cristen soulis &amp; beren hem to helle; for &thorn;ei han maad priuyly couenaunt with &thorn;e deuyl &thorn;at hou many beneficis &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &thorn;ei may gete bi lesynges &amp; symonye &thorn;e deuyl schal strangle &thorn;e soulis at his wille as for hem, so &thorn;at &thorn;ei han here lustis of grete statis and worschipe of &thorn;e world and plente of richessis and glotonye and lecherie and meynteneris &thorn;er|inne. &amp; &thorn;is is luciferis pride, stynkynge ypocrisie and anti|cristis blasphemye, to crie and meyntene &thorn;at suche ben able curatis and grete men of holy chirche.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="9" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 9<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also lordis fallen foule in ypocrisie and in defaute of charite, for &thorn;ei ben redi to holde vp here worldly name, lordschipe and meyntene here courtis wi&thorn; gret cost, sendynge of men bo&thorn;e of lawe and of armes, &amp; prikynge bi here owen persones for to plede, for to fi&yogh;tte and for to lyue &amp; dye &thorn;er-fore, and to be vengid on men &thorn;at don a&yogh;enst here wille, worschipe, or profit; but for to meyntene goddis lawe and stond for his worschipe, &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben holden to vp peyne of lesynge of here lordischipe &amp; anemtis god, and lesynge of bodi and soule and helle wi&thorn;-outen hende, who is &thorn;at lord &thorn;at wolle treuli speke, coste, traueile, and suffre mekely dispit, pursuynge and de&thorn; in tyme of nede. &thorn;es lordis owen to quake a&yogh;enst domes day and tyme of here de&thorn;, &thorn;at more bisili traueilen to meyntenen here litil worldely lordshipe<NOTE PLACE="foot">worschipe X.</NOTE> and to seke here owen worschipe &amp; drit of &thorn;is world &thorn;anne &thorn;ei traueile <MILESTONE N="20" UNIT="page">to meyntene &thorn;e most ri&yogh;tful lawe &amp; ordenaunce of ih&umacr; crist in his chirche, &amp; to procure, norische &amp; meyntene cristen soulis in good gouernaile and holy lif. certis &yogh;if &thorn;ei don &thorn;us and coueiten &thorn;er-bi to be holden goode cristen lordis, here pride, ypocrisie and false coueitise wole brynge hem to euere-lastynge peyne in helle. &para; Also marchauntis and riche men of &thorn;is wikked world fallen in 
<PB REF="00000091.tif" N="25"> moche ypocrise; for &thorn;ei traueilen ny&yogh;t &amp; day, bi watir &amp; lond in cold, &amp; in hete, bi false sotiltis and cautelis &amp; grete sweri[n]ges nedles &amp; false, for to gete muche drit or muk of &thorn;is world, to gete riche wyues, &amp; purchase londis &amp; rentis, &amp; dewelle in pore mennus dette after &thorn;at &thorn;ei han desceyued hem in byynge of here catel; &amp; &yogh;it ben so bisi in &thorn;ou&yogh;t &amp; speche in goyng and rydyng abouten &thorn;is muk &thorn;at vnne&thorn;e may &thorn;ei onys &thorn;enke on god &amp; han mynde of here false robberie &thorn;at &thorn;ei vsen bi false wettes &amp; mesures to amende hem. &yogh;if alle here bisinesse &amp; loue goo &thorn;us wrongly to &thorn;e world &amp; nou&yogh;t or to litel to heuene and heuenely &thorn;ingis, &thorn;ei failen foule of holy lif; &amp; &yogh;it holden hem self holy &amp; coueiten to ben holden holy of o&thorn;er men, &amp; ben wode &yogh;if men speken treuly a&yogh;enst here cursed synnes; but certes &thorn;is is ypocrisie.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="10" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 10<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Generaly ypocrisie regne&thorn; among alle statis of cristen men; for whanne men ben cristened &thorn;ei forsaken &thorn;e deuyl, al his pride &amp; al his werkis, &thorn;at ben werkis of synne; and &yogh;it &thorn;ei turnen to synne as an hound to his spuyng and here-wi&thorn; holden hem goode cristen men. but summe don verrey penaunce for &thorn;es synnes, &amp; summe dwelle euere stille &thorn;er-inne &amp; rennen to helle, as crist sei&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel &amp; in &thorn;e bok of iob; &amp; many men don bodily penaunce, as fastynge and goynge barfote, but &thorn;ei fasten not fro pride ne enuye ne coueitise, but preien for wrongful vengaunce of o&thorn;ere enemyes a&yogh;enst charite, and &thorn;is is foule ypocrisie to make men holden hem holy whanne &thorn;ei stynken bifore god for old endured synne. For god sei&thorn; be ysaye &thorn;at a<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isaiah lviii. 5.</NOTE> man to turmente his hed and peyne his bodi only is not &thorn;at fast &thorn;e whiche god chees, <SUP>1</SUP>but &thorn;is is &thorn;e fast &thorn;at god ches; <SUP>1</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">1_1 omitted X.</NOTE> a man to breke &thorn;e bondis of synne &amp; do werkis of mercy to poore men &amp; nedi. &para; But vpon &thorn;e text of &thorn;is gospel bi ordre of seynt matheu Ion with &thorn;e gildene 
<PB REF="00000092.tif" N="26"> mou&thorn; sei&thorn; &thorn;at a prest is in dette to teche openly and treuly &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of goddis lawe, and ellis he is traitour to &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of holy writt. <SUP>1</SUP>So a lewyd man is boundyn to mayntene &thorn;e treu&thorn;e<SUP>1</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">1_1 omitted X.</NOTE> of holy writt, and ellis he is traitour to god &amp; to his lawe and his peple. &amp; here-fore riche men owen to drede of treson and traitre a&yogh;enst god &amp; his lawe whanne &thorn;ei meyntene not &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of &thorn;e gospel, but ben aboute to stoppe it &amp; techeris &thorn;er-of bi sotil cautelis &amp; false lesynges for fleschli loue or coueitise. for as iudas dide &thorn;ei sillen &thorn;e treu&thorn;e, and so crist &thorn;at is treu&thorn;e, <MILESTONE N="21" UNIT="page">for money or<NOTE PLACE="foot">of X.</NOTE> fleschly loue. And si&thorn; &thorn;ei sillen treu&thorn;e &thorn;at is a spiritual good for money or worldely &thorn;yng<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &thorn;ei ben cursed symo|nyentis &amp; so heretikis. moche owen &thorn;ei to quake, si&thorn; crist sei&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel &thorn;at who euere dispisi&thorn; cristis disciplis, in &thorn;at he dispisi&thorn; crist; and at &thorn;e day of dom &thorn;ere schal be lesse peyne to sodom &amp; gomor, &thorn;at weren distroied for synne, &thorn;an to &thorn;o men &thorn;at wolen not resceyue cristis disciplis and his gospel, ne lyue after &thorn;e techyng of cristis gospel. principaly si&thorn; suche men slen crist as moche as in hem is, and dryuen &thorn;e holy gost out of his temple &amp; &thorn;e holy trynite; &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ei taken &thorn;e office to meyntene goddis lawe and techeris &thorn;er-of, &amp; vpon &thorn;is seruyces &thorn;ei han &thorn;es hei&yogh;e statis &amp; lordischipis. but certis it is foul ypocrisie &thorn;us to suffre synne regne, si&thorn; lordis and men of grete statis, as maires, ben so muche biholden to destroie it, &amp; mowne welle don it in dede, &amp; to lette trewe prechoris of &thorn;e gospel, &amp; meyntene prechours of lesyngis, fablis &amp; cronyclys for monye &amp; worldely frendschipe.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="11" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 11.<NOTE PLACE="foot">This is headed Chap. XII. in X. In AA Chap. IX. and X. are run together, and this is marked Chap. X.</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>But &yogh;it ypocrisie of phariseis is most cursed &amp; perilous of alle o&thorn;ere; for whanne &thorn;ei han disceyued cristendom &thorn;is hundrid &yogh;eer &amp; more bi ypocrisie &amp; false prechynge of fablis &amp; errouris &amp; heresies, magnifyenge synful mennus ordenaunce 
<PB REF="00000093.tif" N="27"> abouen goddis lawe &amp; ordenaunce, &amp; drawen pore mennus almes &amp; liflode to proude beggeris to make grete wast houses, and desceyue men bi fals assoilyng, bi fals<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> pardon, bi veyne preiers &amp; synguler or specyal, &amp; letteris of fraternite, puttynge open beggynge &amp; clamours on ih&umacr; crist, &thorn;anne &thorn;ei crien fast &thorn;at poore prestis treuli &amp; frely prechynge &thorn;e gospel as crist biddi&thorn;, techynge men to do verray penaunce for here synnes &amp; not trusten ouermoche to false pardon &amp; cursed preieris of ypocritis, &amp; to do here almes to pore feble men crokid &amp; blynde, as crist sei&thorn; him self; &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben cause of alle &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> perturbacion of &thorn;e rewme; but &thorn;ei lyen falsly &amp; openly to eche trewe man. for si&thorn; synne is cause of pertur|bacion, &amp; &thorn;es prestis vpon here kunnynge &thorn;at god &yogh;eue&thorn; hem of holy writt &amp; &thorn;er-wi&thorn; bisien hem ny&yogh;t &amp; day to distroye synne, &thorn;ei ben aboute to make pees betwixe god &amp; man. &amp; &thorn;ei &thorn;at meyntenen synne bi false confessionys &amp; veyn special preieris &amp; pardons ben most cause of discencion &amp; werris. but here &thorn;ei suen &thorn;e fadir of lesyngis &thorn;at stirede &thorn;e hei&yogh;e prestis &amp; pharisees in cristis tyme to pute on hym &amp; his disciplis &thorn;at &thorn;ei disturbleden &thorn;e lond of iude &amp; wolden distroie it, for crist and his disciplis reproueden &thorn;e coueitise, ypocrisie &amp; falsenesse of &thorn;e hei&yogh;e prestis &amp; false pharisees. so &thorn;e deuyl steri&thorn; now false newe pharisees of synguler religion wi&thorn;-oute cristis ordynaunce, &thorn;at ben more sotil in malice &amp; lesyngis and ypocrisie &thorn;an<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;at X.</NOTE> &thorn;e firste, to stoppe pore prestis fro prechynge of <MILESTONE N="22" UNIT="page">&thorn;e gospel &amp; reprouynge of synne, for bi &thorn;is offis of crist don treuly here synnes of lesyngis and ypocrisie schulde be knowen and distroied and goddis lawe knowen and kept and synne chasid out of lond. but false ypocritis stryuen a&yogh;enst &thorn;is profet of cristen men, &amp; clepen techynge of &thorn;e gospel &amp; goddis hestis newe techynge, &amp; techynge of verrey penaunce doynge &amp; of ri&yogh;tful &yogh;euynge &amp; of almes and open prechynge a&yogh;enst synne errour a&yogh;enst charite. God kepe cristen men fro ypocrisie &amp; false lesyngis of pharisees and here meynteneris. Amen.</P>


</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="2" TYPE="tract"><PB REF="00000094.tif" N="28">
<HEAD>II. HOW MEN OUGHT TO OBEY PRELATES. </HEAD>
<HEADNOTE><P>I DO not think this tract is by Wyclif. Its tone is not that of a man who has known the Court and been engaged in political affairs, but rather of some poor clergyman, who felt the burdens laid upon him by the bad government of the Church, and spoke from the bitterness of his personal experience. The extravagant expression, 'two or three thousand miles' (p. 30), points in the same direction. On the other hand, the text, 1 Cor. v. 5, is used here in the same way as in Prelates, No. IV. in this volume, and the warning against misusing the freedom given by God (p. 32) recalls a fine passage in the tract on Feigned Contemplative Life (No. X.).</P><P>Copied from the Corpus MS. X, and collated with the Dublin MS. AA.</P><P><TABLE>
<HEAD>SUMMARY.</HEAD>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. I.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates charge poor priests and those who believe with them that they disobey their superiors, that they make light of excommunication, and break the law. They are willing to obey as far as they may in accordance with God's commandments. But there is a hardship in men being summoned to distant places for no good purpose. It hinders men from doing the duties which God commands. Wickedness of prelates&mdash;their simony and other sins. If prelates will do their duty, poor priests will obey them.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>II.</CELL>
<CELL>As to excommunication, poor priests say that they will not incur God's curse for anything in heaven or earth, but they would rather be wrongfully cursed by man than break God's law. Excommunication often inflicted from spite. Curates ought not to execute letters of excommunication which they know to be ill-grounded.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>III.</CELL>
<CELL>As to law, true men will obey man's law so far as it agrees with God's. Laws are often made only to support the pride and pomp of prelates, and are an undue burden.</CELL>
</ROW>
</TABLE></P></HEADNOTE>

<PB REF="00000095.tif" N="29">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>Hou men owen obesche to prelatis drede curs &amp; kepe lawe.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<DIV2 N="1" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum primum.</HEAD>
<P>Prelatis sclaundren pore prestis &amp; o&thorn;ere cristen men &thorn;at &thorn;ei wolen not obesche to here souereynes, ne dreden curs, ne drede ne kepe &thorn;e lawe, but dispise alle &thorn;ing &thorn;at is a&yogh;enst here likynge. And herfore &thorn;ei ben werse &thorn;an iewis or paynymes, and alle lordis &amp; prelates &amp; my&yogh;ti men schulden distroie hem, for ellis &thorn;ei wolen distroie holy chirche &amp; make eche man to lyue as hym liki&thorn;; and no &thorn;ing may more distroie cristendom.</P>
<P>&para; But here poore prestis &amp; trewe men mekely wolen and wilfully obesche to god &amp; holy chirche, &amp; to eche man in er&thorn;e in as myche as he techi&thorn; treuly goddis comaundementis &amp; profitable treu&thorn;e for here soulis, and no more owi&thorn; ony man to obeche to crist god &amp; man, ne to ony apostle. and &yogh;if ony worldly prelat axe more obedience he his anticrist &amp; luciferis maister, for ih&umacr; crist is god of ri&yogh;twisnesse &amp; treu&thorn;e &amp; of pees &amp; charite, and may not do a&yogh;enst ri&yogh;twisnesse ne treu&thorn;e ne hel&thorn;e of mennus soulis ne charite, si&thorn; he may not lye ne denye him self. hou &thorn;anne schulde or my&yogh;tte ony synful prelat charge men and constreyne to do a&yogh;enst ry&yogh;twisnesse &amp; hel&thorn;e of soulis and<NOTE PLACE="foot">in X.</NOTE> good conscience; for<NOTE PLACE="marg">John v. 19.</NOTE> crist sei&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel of seynt ion &thorn;at &thorn;e sone may not do but &thorn;at &thorn;ing he ha&thorn; seyn his fadir don; &amp; &thorn;erfore crist comaundid to alle men &thorn;at &thorn;ei schulde not bileue to him<NOTE PLACE="marg">John x. 37.</NOTE> but &yogh;if he dide &thorn;e werkis of &thorn;e fadir of heuene. where cristen men schullen be constreyned be anticristis clerkis to don after here comaundement whanne &thorn;ei don not werkis of god but werkis of &thorn;e fend? &amp; &thorn;us crist speki&thorn; to &thorn;e iewis<NOTE PLACE="marg">John viii. [46].</NOTE> &amp; axe&thorn; hem whi &thorn;ei bileuen not to hym &yogh;if he sei&thorn;e trew&thorn;e; as who sei&thorn;, &yogh;if he seide nou&yogh;t<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> treu&thorn;e &thorn;ei schulde nou&yogh;t<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000096.tif" N="30"> bileue to hym. and &thorn;er-for crist sei&thorn; to &thorn;e iewis who of &yogh;ou schal repreue me of synne, &amp; he wold &thorn;at eche man hadde do so &yogh;if he my&yogh;tt treuly. &thorn;erfore in tyme of his passion crist seide to &thorn;e bischopis seruaunt whanne he smote him in &thorn;e face: <MILESTONE N="23" UNIT="page">&yogh;if I haue spoken euyl, bere &thorn;ou witnesse of<NOTE PLACE="marg">John xviii. [23].</NOTE> euyl. &amp; si&thorn; prelatis ben vikeris of crist, &thorn;ei owen to suen to hym in &thorn;is obedience &amp; axe no more of ony man. &para; But here is &thorn;e sore in &thorn;is obedience; prelatis axen &thorn;at prestis &amp; o&thorn;ere sugetis schulden come for here souereyns whider euere hem likid, at &thorn;e fer&thorn;este place of here diecise, &thorn;ou&yogh; prelatis kunnyn not holy writt ne kepen it, but don opynly &thorn;er a&yogh;enst many weies; &amp; &thorn;is is wrong for many skillis. first, si&thorn; crist god &amp; man sou&yogh;te mannus soule lost &thorn;oru&yogh; synne bi &thorn;ritti &yogh;eer and more wi&thorn; grete traiuele, werynesse &amp; many peynes, bi many &thorn;ousand myles vpon his feet, in gret cold and stormes &amp; tempestis, prelatis schulden not couche in castellis &amp; suffre &thorn;e fende to deuoure cristene soulis, &amp; &thorn;anne make a pore man to renne two or &thorn;re &thorn;ousand myles &amp; &yogh;eue hem &thorn;ere ensaumple of pride &amp; o&thorn;ere synnes. si&thorn; &thorn;ei han so myche tresour &amp; grete hors, &amp; ben hei&yogh;e vikeris of crist to seue his lif in mekenesse and pouerte and harde traueile to saue mennes soulis, and si&thorn; &thorn;ei ben holden to spende here catel and lese here bodily lif for sauynge of cristen soulis as did crist &amp; his apostelis, myche more owe &thorn;ei to spende a litil traueile and money to seke &amp; visyte synful men &amp; esen hem<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> in body &amp; soule. And not maken hem nedlis to spende here litel catel and be inpacient &amp; grucchynge a&yogh;enst god &amp; man &amp; out of charite. for we reden not in al &thorn;e lawe of grace &thorn;at crist or ony of his disciplis vsede &thorn;is symonynge or axid &thorn;is obedience of ony synful man riche or pore. lord whi schulde a synful ydiot axe more obedience &thorn;an<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;at X.</NOTE> diden crist &amp; his apostelis? &amp; we rede not in &thorn;e lawe of grace &thorn;at crist apperid comunly bifore &thorn;e hei&yogh;e prestis and pharisees fore here symonynge ne his apostelis after sendynge of &thorn;e holy goste, But &yogh;if &thorn;ei weren constreyned 
<PB REF="00000097.tif" N="31"> bi violence or ellis &yogh;if &thorn;ei weren in place where criste tau&yogh;te in &thorn;e temple. &para; Also crist techi&thorn; in the gospel &thorn;at a man owi&thorn; to leue &thorn;e lasse good &amp; do &thorn;e more; si&thorn; he comaundid a man to leue &thorn;e beriynge of his fadir and go preche &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matthew viii. 21.</NOTE> gospel. &thorn;anne a prest schulde not leue prechynge of the gospel &amp; renne to vncerteyn placis for biddynge of worldly prelatis, enemyes to god &amp; his seruauntis, si&thorn; prechynge of &thorn;e gospel is betere &thorn;an bodely rennynge so to ferre placis, for peril of enemyes, for wastynge of pore mennus goodis, and for drede of rebelte a&yogh;enst god. for seynt ierom sei&thorn; in &thorn;e popis lawe &thorn;at he &thorn;at leue&thorn; &thorn;e more good or putte&thorn; it behynde &thorn;e lesse good synne&thorn; not menely but greuously. si&thorn; siche <MILESTONE N="24" UNIT="page">somonynge of prelatis is not groundid in cristis lif ne his apostelis ne reson, but in anticristis power bi dowynge of clerkis wi&thorn; seculer lordischipe a&yogh;enst holy writt. and &thorn;us instede of cristis mekenesse &amp; pouert and charite and trewe techynge of &thorn;e gospel is brou&yogh;t in worldly pride of prestis and coueitise &amp; enuye and discencion in cristis peple, &amp; bodily turmentynge bi prestis, as &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei weren worldly lordis of &thorn;e kyngis lege men bo&thorn;e of bodi &amp; of catel, &amp; chargynge of soulis with grete chargis a&yogh;enst &thorn;e fredom of goddis lawe and the hel&thorn;e of soulis her-bi brou&yogh;t in; for &thorn;es worldly prelatis chargen men to speke not a&yogh;enst here pride and coueitise ne brynge hem to &thorn;e ordynaunce of crist, but ra&thorn;er to lyue hem self in pride and falsnesse of &thorn;is world &thorn;an to turne to &thorn;e mekenesse and trewe lif and to &thorn;enke on here de&thorn; day, for bi &thorn;is goode lif of seculeris &thorn;e lif of worldly prelatis schulde be knowen for ypocrisie and cursed|nesse. and &thorn;us bi &thorn;is feyned power of somonynge and cursynge worldly prelatis ben maad cruel turmentours of cristis seruauntis, and schewen hem self &amp; make, but falsly, lordis of mennus bodies &amp; catel &amp; soulis also, to stoppe &amp; lette good lif of cristene men, &thorn;at &thorn;e holy trynyte may not do for his ri&yogh;twisnesse &amp; charite; but where ben falsere anticristis, perilousere heretikis, &amp; cursedher blasphe|meres. &para; Also no man owi&thorn; to putte by-hynde goddis 
<PB REF="00000098.tif" N="32"> biddynge and &thorn;e byddynge of a synful man bifore; &amp; god biddi&thorn; eche man vp peyne of dampnacion &thorn;at ha&thorn; wif &amp; children &amp; meyne to gouerne hem wel in goddis lawe. &thorn;anne no weddid man owi&thorn; to leue his wife &amp; children &amp; meyne vngouerned, &amp; goo many hundred myles in drede of &thorn;eues &amp; enemyes, &amp; wast his goodis &amp; suffre his folk to perische in soule or in body. and myche more no curat owi&thorn; to leue his schepe vnkept among &thorn;e wolues of helle, &amp; ride with grete coost to ferre placis for pride, enuye or coueitise of worldly clerkis. &amp; &thorn;is reson maki&thorn; sikernesse for prestis to dewelle with goddis peple &amp; profite to hem, &amp; for children to take cure of here heldris, &amp; not ride ne renne aboute &amp; leue &thorn;is heste of god vndon for somonynge of worldly prelatis. Also crist sei&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel &thorn;at &yogh;if<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke vi. 39.</NOTE> &thorn;e blynde lede &thorn;e blynde &thorn;ei fallen bo&thorn;e into &thorn;e lake. &thorn;anne si&thorn; worldly prelatis ben blynde in goddis lawe, bo&thorn;e in kunnynge &thorn;er-of &amp; lif &thorn;er-after, no man schulde be led bi hem in kepynge of his soule, for drede lest &thorn;ei falle bo&thorn; in-to <SUP>1</SUP>helle. For si&thorn;&thorn;e &thorn;ei ledyn hemself to <SUP>1</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">1_1 omitted X.</NOTE> helle-ward for ignoraunce of holy writt or coueitise of worldeli worschipe, hei&yogh;e states &amp; worldly muk, &thorn;ei wolen lede o&thorn;ere men &thorn;e same weie. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei ben cursed of god, for &thorn;at &thorn;at is good &amp; goddis lawe &thorn;ei dampnen for euyl &amp; erroure, <MILESTONE N="25" UNIT="page">&amp; <SUP>2</SUP> &thorn;at &thorn;at is errour &amp; <SUP>2</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">2_2 omitted X.</NOTE> euyl a&yogh;enst goddis lawe &thorn;ei chesen &amp; techen for good and profytable; &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei dampnen hemself &amp; alle &thorn;at ben led bi hem. Also bi reson &amp; mannus lawe &yogh;if a man be somonyd to-gidre to &thorn;e hei&yogh;ere iuge &amp; a lasse he schal be excused fro &thorn;e lasse bi &thorn;e vertue of &thorn;e hei&yogh;ere iuge; but eche man is somoned first of god to worschipe hym in<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; X.</NOTE> alle his witt &amp; alle his my&yogh;t, bifor &thorn;at a worldly prelat somone hym to renne aboute, in whiche rennynge his witt &amp; his my&yogh;t schullen be perid; &thorn;anne bi vertue of &thorn;is cheef domesman he owi&thorn; to be excused fro &thorn;is somonynge of worldly prelat. but be<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &thorn;e suget ware of feynynge here, &thorn;at he waste not ne mysvsse &thorn;e &yogh;iftis of god vnder colour 
<PB REF="00000099.tif" N="33"> of &thorn;is fredom; for god wole haue rekennynge of eche dede, of eche word, &amp; of eche &thorn;ou&yogh;t, &amp; of eche &yogh;ifte, &amp; eche tyme, &amp; moment. And be &thorn;e worldly prelat ward of blasphemye here, &thorn;at he compelle not for his pride &thorn;is suget to putte bihynde &thorn;e betre worschipynge of god and vnder colour of obedience make hym to myspende &thorn;e tyme &amp; goddis &yogh;iftis. &para; Also men of lawe &amp; resoun seyn it is worst of alle to take<NOTE PLACE="foot">make AA.</NOTE> dom vndir a suspect domesman; but &thorn;es worldly prelatis ben suspect domesmen anemtis goddis seruauntis, for &thorn;ei been enemys to &thorn;e persone of cristis seruauntis &amp; also to &thorn;e cause of god. for comunly &thorn;ei comen to here statis bi symonye &amp; so ben heretikis, as &thorn;e popis lawe sei&thorn;, &amp; contynen<NOTE PLACE="foot">conteynen X.</NOTE> in pride, coueitise, extorciouns,<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &amp; meyntenynge of here synne &amp; o&thorn;ere mennys for annuel rente, &amp; haten &amp; pursuen bo&thorn;e cristis lawe &amp; his seruauntis &thorn;at speken a&yogh;enst here synne, to amende hem &thorn;er-of &amp; alle &thorn;at ben vnkunnynge in goddis lawe; how schulde a treue man be demyd bi suspect iuges. &amp; siche vnkunnynge &amp; euyl leuynge prelatis ben most hardy to dampne trewe <SUP>4</SUP>treuthis of holi writ &amp; pursue trewe <SUP>4</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">4_4 omitted X.</NOTE> men to prison &amp; de&thorn; &thorn;at meyntenen holy writt &amp; trew&thorn;e a&yogh;enst here coueitise, pride, symonye &amp; lustis. &para; And newe religious assessours of &thorn;es vnkunnynge worldely prelatis ben more suspect &thorn;an ony o&thorn;er; for &thorn;ei grounden hem in &thorn;is, &thorn;at holy writt is fals but here owen doctours and gloses ben trewe. And so &thorn;ei putten falsnesse &amp; defaute of witt in god, &amp; seyn &thorn;at a synful ydiot &amp; in caas a deuyl of helle is trewere, wittiere &amp; more ful of charite &amp; my&yogh;t to teche men treu&thorn;e &thorn;anne is &thorn;e trinyte &amp; ih&umacr; crist god &amp; man. &amp; &thorn;ei haten more cristis seruauntis &thorn;at stonden for &thorn;e trew&thorn;e of holy writt &amp; ih&umacr; cristis leuynge &amp; reprouen here ypocrisie &amp; schewen here falsnesse to &thorn;e peple; and &thorn;ey<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> ben more sotil in malice, &amp; dysceyuen more lordis &amp; ladies &amp; &thorn;e comunes in fei&thorn; &amp; charite, &amp; maken hem to triste &thorn;at it<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> is almes 
<PB REF="00000100.tif" N="34"> to distroye trewe men &thorn;at stonden <MILESTONE N="26" UNIT="page">for goddis lawe &amp; trewe lyuynge. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;e dampnable ignoraunce of goddis lawe &amp; cursed lif of &thorn;es worldly prelatis &amp; stronge meyntenynge of here owen synne &amp; o&thorn;ere mennus ben cause whi pore prestis &amp; cristen men han hem suspect of heresie &amp; enemyte bo&thorn;e of goddis cause &amp; his seruauntis; &amp; &thorn;er-fore &thorn;e flen fro hem as-anticrist and heretykes, as ioon &thorn;e euaungelist<NOTE PLACE="marg">2 John, 10.</NOTE> techi&thorn; in his epistilis. &para; But lete prelatis studie bisili &amp; treuly holy<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> writt &amp; lyuen opyn wel &thorn;er-aftir, and distroie opyn synne of o&thorn;ere men be here witt and my&yogh;t, &amp; pore prestis &amp; cristene men wi&thorn;-outen ony somonynge wolen wi&thorn; gret traueile and cost and wille, &yogh;ee bi londe &amp; bi water, mekely come to hem &amp; don hem obedience &amp; reuerence, as &thorn;ei wolden to petir &amp; poul &amp; cristis apostlis. deme &thorn;e world whe&thorn;er &thorn;is dyuysion belong on worldely prelatis vnkunnynge and cursed of lif, or on pore prestis and trewe men &thorn;at fayn desiren ny&yogh;t &amp; day to knowe goddis wille &amp; worschipe &amp; do it bifore alle o&thorn;ere &thorn;ingis.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 2<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>As to cursynge, cristen men seyn trewely &thorn;at &thorn;ei dreden it so moche &thorn;at &thorn;ei wollen not wilfully &amp; wityngly disserue goddis curse, nei&thorn;er for good in er&thorn;e ne in heuene; ne mannus curse in as myche as it acordi&thorn; wi&thorn; &thorn;e ri&yogh;tful curs of god; but &thorn;ei wolle wi&thorn; grete ioie of soule ra&thorn;ere suffre mannus wrongful curs &thorn;an wityngly &amp; wilfully breke ony comaundement of god for to wynne &thorn;er-bi alle worschipis of &thorn;is world, and to kepe here body in alle likyngis neuere so longe; &amp; ra&thorn;ere to suffre sclaundryng &amp; bacbityng and prisonyng and exilid, hangyng, drawyng, quarterynge and brennynge wi&thorn; helpe and grace of god &thorn;an to forsake &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of holy writt &amp; lif of crist, for ellis &thorn;ei weren not in charite ne in weie of saluacion. but anticristis clerkis magnyfien so myche mannus curs &thorn;at &thorn;ei taken noon hede to &thorn;e dredeful curs of god; as &yogh;if 
<PB REF="00000101.tif" N="35"> men were more my&yogh;tti &amp; ri&yogh;tful &thorn;an is almy&yogh;tti god in trynyte. for &thorn;ou&yogh; men breken opynly alle &thorn;e comaunde|mentis of god &amp; lyuen in pride, coueityse, enuye, glotonye and o&thorn;er synnes, but &yogh;if it be lecherie, &thorn;ere renne&thorn; no mannus curs; ne for lecherie &yogh;if men wolen paie rente bi &yogh;eere &amp; dwelle stil &thorn;er-inne als longe as hym liste; so al &thorn;e drede is turned to mannus curs and no &thorn;ing to goddis curs.</P>
<P>&para; But &yogh;if a man trespas litel or nou&yogh;t a&yogh;enst a prelat or a&yogh;enst &thorn;e wynnynge of clerkis, he schal be cursed &amp; pursued &thorn;at al &thorn;e ende of his kyn may haue sorowe &thorn;erfore; &yogh;ee, &thorn;ou&yogh; a treu&thorn;e of holy writt &amp; reson be seid <MILESTONE N="27" UNIT="page">bi charite a&yogh;enst &thorn;e pride, coueitise &amp; open wrong &thorn;at prelatis don to here nei&yogh;boris, bo&thorn;e in here gostly offis &amp; also worldly wrongis; and here-bi &thorn;ei ponyschen more for here owen dispit or wrong &thorn;an for dispit of god almy&yogh;tty. &para; But here men musen<NOTE PLACE="foot">mowe sen X.</NOTE> whi prelatis ben so redy to curse in here owne cause, si&thorn; petir techi&thorn; cristen men to blisse &amp; not no werie<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Peter ii. [23?]</NOTE> ne curse; &amp; god biddi&thorn; vs loue oure enemyes &amp; don good<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. v. [44.]</NOTE> to hem &thorn;at haten vs, and to preie for men &thorn;at falsly pursuen vs. si&thorn; he &thorn;at cu[r]se&thorn; ano&thorn;er man for his owne vengaunce or worldly catel more &thorn;anne for to venge synne don a&yogh;enst god &amp; for &thorn;e hel&thorn;e of &thorn;e cursed mannus soule cursi&thorn; him-self, for he doi&thorn; a&yogh;enst charite, as gregori techi&thorn; in &thorn;e popis lawe. certes men dreden &thorn;at &thorn;es prelatis ben ful of goddis curse for here symonye in<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; X.</NOTE> here entre, &amp; sillynge of sacramentis &amp; gostly officis, as ordres &yogh;euynge for money, &amp; halwynge of chirchis &amp; auteris, &amp; for extorcions of pore men, &amp; meyntenynge of synful men in here synne for money, &thorn;at &thorn;ei han no part of goddis blissyng and &thorn;erfore cursed fruyt spryngi&thorn; out of a cursed tree.</P>
<P>&para; Lord, whi schulde curatis pronounsen here bre&thorn;eren a cursed for nakid lettris of syche coueitous prelatis, enemyes of crist &amp; his seruauntis, when &thorn;ei knowe no cause bi-for god where-for &thorn;ei be cursed of hym but han euydence bi spekynge &amp; open lif of here neie&yogh;boris &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben in good 
<PB REF="00000102.tif" N="36"> lif &amp; in charite. Si&thorn; crist sei&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel &thorn;at he &thorn;at sei&thorn; to his bro&thorn;er: &thorn;ou fool! wi&thorn;-out sufficiente cause, &amp;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. v. 22.</NOTE> he &thorn;at sei&thorn; to his bro&thorn;er &thorn;at ha&thorn; &thorn;e holi gost wi&thorn; good lif &amp; charite &thorn;at he is voide &amp; wi&thorn;-oute kunnynge, schal be gilti of helle, whe&thorn;er &thorn;is be charite to curse a man for sexe pans whan he may vnne&thorn;is lyue be al his traueile, &amp; for he traueli&thorn; not at here som[on]ynge an hundrid myle or moo or lesse &amp; leue&thorn; not his wif &amp; children vngouerned. for &yogh;if a preste pronounse siche a man a cursed &thorn;at is blissed of god he li&yogh;e&thorn; vpon his bro&thorn;er &amp; beri&thorn; fals witenesse a&yogh;enst goddis dom. for &thorn;ou&yogh; he apere not at here somonynge to &yogh;euen hem mony at here wille, he may ben excused a&yogh;enst god &amp; man for many skillis. &thorn;erfor &thorn;is nakid lettre of coueitouse prelatis is no sykirnesse anemtis god to pro|nounse a cristen man for cursed, &amp; noon obedience schulde constreyne a prest to wittenesse a falshede a&yogh;enst his bro&thorn;er and a&yogh;enst his conscience but &yogh;if it be anticristis obedience, for certis god wole not constreyne a man to &thorn;is false obedyence. Lord, where anticrist &amp; his clerkis schullen. &YOGH;if prelatis knowen &thorn;at &thorn;is man were cursed of god for brekyng of his hestis &thorn;ei my&yogh;ten pronounse &thorn;is to &thorn;e peple to make o&thorn;ere men to flee his companye as an he&thorn;ene mannys. But comunly &thorn;ei knowe not &thorn;is so wel as o&thorn;ere pore men, <MILESTONE N="28" UNIT="page">for &thorn;ei taken no reward to &thorn;e hestis of god, but al to here owen lawes &amp; customes. &thorn;e apostelis hadden<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. v. 5.</NOTE> &thorn;is power when a synful man was rebel a&yogh;enst goddis lawe to &yogh;eue &thorn;e fend power of his body to traueilen it, so &thorn;at &thorn;e soule were saaf. But owre prelatis han not &thorn;is power, &thorn;erfore &thorn;ei feynen &thorn;at &thorn;ei sleen &thorn;e soule bi &thorn;er cursyng wanne &thorn;e bodi is neuere &thorn;e werse, &amp; &thorn;anne &thorn;ei techen lordis to enprisone &thorn;e bodi aftir fourti daies a cursyng, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;e man be cursed<NOTE PLACE="foot">blessed AA.</NOTE> for holdyng goddis hestis; &amp; maken lordis to ben turmentouris of cristene men, whanne &thorn;e fendis doren not touche hem for drede of god. &thorn;is cursynge schulde be suspendid for peril on alle sidis, and trewe techynge of 
<PB REF="00000103.tif" N="37"> cristis gospel &amp; holy ensaumplis of prelatis lif &amp; manasynge of purgatorie &amp; helle and confortynge of &thorn;e blisse of heuene schulde be schewed &amp; regne among cristene peple; and &thorn;es foure schulden maken men to flee synne &amp; lyue wel &amp; ende in perfit charite, &amp; &thorn;is were best for alle parties.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="3" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 3<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>As to lawe, trewe men seyn &thorn;at &thorn;ei willen mekely &amp; wilfully drede &amp; kepe goddis lawe vp here kunnynge &amp; my&yogh;t, &amp; eche lawe of mannes makynge in as myche as &thorn;ei witen &thorn;at it acordi&thorn; wi&thorn; goddis lawe &amp; reson &amp; good con|science &amp; to &thorn;e ri&yogh;tful execucion &thorn;er-of; &amp; god him self may bynde man no more to his owen lawe for his endeles ri&yogh;twis|nesse &amp; charite &thorn;at he ha&thorn; to mannes soule. lord, where synful men &thorn;at ben anticristis, &amp; in caas deuelis in flesch &amp; blood, may bynde men more to here wickid lawis &amp; wrong execucions of hem &thorn;anne god wille bynde hem to his most ri&yogh;tful lawe &amp; profitable. cristen men knowen wel of fei&thorn; &thorn;at nei&thorn;er petir ne poul ne ony creature may do ou&yogh;t lawe|fully a&yogh;enst &thorn;e trew&thorn;e of holi writt ne a&yogh;enst &thorn;e edificacion of holy chirche, &thorn;at is good techynge &amp; gouernynge &amp; amend|ynge of cristene soulis. what power han &thorn;an worldly prelatis to make so many wickid lawes? si&thorn; god curse&thorn; hem &thorn;at maken wickid lawes, &amp; comaundi&thorn; &thorn;at no man schal adde to his wordis ne drawe fro hem vp peyne of grete cursynge of god &amp; dampnynge in helle. &thorn;at is to seie &thorn;at no man adde false sentence ne false glose to holy writt, for &thorn;an, as ierom sei&thorn;, he is an heretik; and &thorn;at no man drawe ony treu&thorn;e fro goddis wordis, for &thorn;ei enclosen alle nedeful treu&thorn;e &amp; profitable for mannys soule. &amp; to &thorn;is entente si&thorn; poul in his pistel &thorn;at &yogh;if ony man, &yogh;ee apostil or angel of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gal. i. 8.</NOTE> heuene, preche o&thorn;er &thorn;ing &thorn;an is tau&yogh;te of crist &amp; his apostelis <SUP>1</SUP>he is cursid. And Seint Jon sei&thorn;e,<SUP>1</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">1_1 omitted X.</NOTE> in &thorn;e ende of &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Rev. xxii. 18.</NOTE> apocalips, &thorn;at &yogh;if ony man adde &thorn;us to goddis wordis, god schal brynge vpon hym alle &thorn;e vengaunces wryten in &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000104.tif" N="38"> apocalips, &amp; &yogh;if ony man wi&thorn;drawe &thorn;us fro goddis wordis, <MILESTONE N="29" UNIT="page"> god schal don hym out of &thorn;e bok of lif. &para; Lord, si&thorn; goddis lawe is so myche &amp; so hard to vndirstonde, as austyn &amp; o&thorn;ere seyntis techen, &thorn;at &thorn;ou&yogh; eche man hadde neuere so gret witt &amp; my&yogh;tte lyue hool &amp; sond in bodi &amp; wittis til &thorn;e day of dome, he schulde euere haue ynow&yogh; to lerne and ocupie him &thorn;erine at &thorn;e fulle, whi schulle wordly curatis &amp; prelatis<NOTE PLACE="foot">X. inserts and.</NOTE> make so many bokis of here newe lawis for to meyntene here pride &amp; coueitise &amp; worldly array? si&thorn; men be nowe of lesse wittis &amp; schortere tyme &amp; feblere of com|plexion. certis &thorn;e chargen men ouer my&yogh;t &amp; maken hem bysy to kunne wrongful tradiciouns of synful folis makynge &amp; to leue holy writt vnstudied, vnknoud &amp; vnkept; &amp; &thorn;is is a sotil cautel of &thorn;e fend to for-do goddis lawe &amp; knowynge &amp; loue of oure goode god. And &thorn;erfore crist pleyne&thorn; of &thorn;is peple, bi &thorn;e prophete ysaie, &amp; in &thorn;e gospel also, &thorn;at is peple worschipi&thorn; him in lippis but here herte is fer fro god, &amp; &thorn;ei<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isaiah xxix. 13.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. xv. 8, 9.</NOTE> worschipen hym with-outen cause, for &thorn;ei techen &thorn;e loris of men &amp; here maundementis. &amp; &yogh;it seyntis in &thorn;e popis lawe reprouen euyle lawis vngroundid in holy writt &amp; reson, &amp; hem &thorn;at maken hem also, &amp; seyn &thorn;at we owen to take hede what crist sei&thorn;, &amp; to no man ellis but in alse myche as he acordi&thorn; wi&thorn; crist, &amp; he his false &thorn;at sei&thorn; or teche&thorn; ony &thorn;ing &thorn;at is not euydently groundid in goddis lawe. &amp; &thorn;erfore seynt petyr comaundi&thorn; &yogh;if ony speke, loke he speke as goddis wordis.<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Peter iv. 11.</NOTE> &thorn;us &thorn;es worldly prelatis drawen cristen men fro holy writt &thorn;at is &thorn;e beste lawe &amp; constreyne men to here owne lawis ful of errour, maad to coloure here cursed pride &amp; coueitise; for &thorn;ei ponysche men sorere for breken of here owen lawis &thorn;an for brekynge of goddis lawe, &amp; louen &amp; chirischen men of here lawe and dispisen &amp; putten abac men of goddis lawe. Late wordly prelatis ceesse to schlaundre pore men, seynge &thorn;at &thorn;ei wolen not obesche to here souereyns &amp; dreden not curs but dispise lawe. for in alle &thorn;es &thorn;re &thorn;ei ben clere bifore god &amp; man &yogh;if ri&yogh;t &amp; reson &amp; charite be wel sou&yogh;t.</P>


</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="3" TYPE="tract"><PB REF="00000105.tif" N="39">
<HEAD>III. THE RULE AND TESTAMENT OF ST. FRANCIS. </HEAD>
<HEADNOTE><P>THIS tract is distinguished among the many directed against the friars by its method of attack. The first and longer part consists merely in a translation of the rule by which the Franciscans admitted themselves bound, and the comment confines itself to pointing out how completely that rule was disregarded or evaded. The peculiar interest of the tract lies in its bringing before us how nearly in its idea the Franciscan order approached the body of poor priests, whom Wyclif sent out to preach. When the writer complains that at Rome "false menours" persecute those who would keep Francis' rule to the letter, we have an expression of the sympathy which we might have divined between the Lollards and the Spiritual Franciscans. (Cf. the Tract on the Leaven of Pharisees.) But before we have read to the end we find the author true to the "freedom of the gospel," which Wyclif consistently preached, declaring that no other order than Christ's is needed, since those who can carry out the highest and best life have that duty laid upon them by Christ's order to serve God with all their heart and all their strength. We may compare with this the saying (S. E. W. III. 452), "Every conseil of Crist is to sum man and sum tyme a precept."</P><P>I think that the author is Wyclif. The tract, Fifty Heresies of Friars, printed by Mr. Arnold (No. 24), seems like an amplification of this; and it is probably of later date, as the doctrine of transubstantiation is attacked there, but not mentioned here.</P><P>Copied from the Corpus MS. X, and collated with the Dublin MS. AA, and with the Oxford MS. W. All through W. has &thorn;o for &thorn;e; hor for her; hom for hem; and has the third person singular in <I>s</I>.</P><P><TABLE>
<HEAD>SUMMARY.</HEAD>
<ROW>
<CELL>The greater part of this tract is simply a translation from the Latin of the law laid down for the Franciscans by their founder. To this is added a short comment, pointing out&mdash;
<TABLE>
<ROW>
<CELL>1st.</CELL>
<CELL>That the testament is binding upon Franciscans;</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>2nd.</CELL>
<CELL>That the Franciscans keep neither rule nor testament, failing in obedience, in poverty, and in charity.</CELL>
</ROW>
</TABLE></CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>After this general statement of their faults comes an account of various ways in which they evade the letter of the rule. The tract ends with a declaration that no rule is of use except so far as it agrees with that laid down by Christ.</CELL>
</ROW>
</TABLE></P></HEADNOTE>

<PB REF="00000106.tif" N="40">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>&THORN;is his &thorn;e reule of seynt fraunseis.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<DIV2 N="1" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum primum.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;e reule and &thorn;e lyuynge of frere menours is &thorn;is: to kepe &thorn;e holy gospel of oure lord ih&umacr; crist, lyuynge in obedience, wi&thorn;-outen propre, &amp; in chastitie. Frere fraunseis biheti&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">behetis W.</NOTE> obedience and reuerence to &thorn;e lord &thorn;e pope honorie, &amp; to his successouris, &thorn;e whiche entren bi general &amp; holy eleccion, &amp; to &thorn;e chirche of rome, &amp; be o&thorn;ere freris holden to obesche<NOTE PLACE="foot">obes&thorn;e X.</NOTE> to frere fraunseis &amp; to his successouris.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="chapter">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>Of hem &thorn;at wolen take &thorn;is lif, hou &thorn;ei schullen be resceyued.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<HEAD>Capitulum 2<SUP>m.</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">In W. this is reckoned as part of Chapter I.</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>&YOGH;if ony wille take &thorn;is lif, &amp; comen to oure bre&thorn;eren, sende hem to &thorn;e mynystris prouyncials, to whom only, &amp; not to o&thorn;ere, be grauntid <MILESTONE N="30" UNIT="page"> leue to resceyue freris. &thorn;erfore late &thorn;e mynystris diligently examyne hem of<NOTE PLACE="foot">for X.</NOTE> &thorn;e comun fei&thorn; and &thorn;e sacramentis of holy chirche, &thorn;at &yogh;if &thorn;ei beleuen alle &thorn;es &thorn;ingis, and wilen fe&thorn;fully knowleche hem, &amp; stedefastly kepe hem to &thorn;e ende of &thorn;e world, &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ei han noon wyues, or &yogh;if &thorn;ei han wyues &amp; here wyues ben entrid in-to religion, or ellis &thorn;at here wyues han &yogh;ouen here housbondis lyue<NOTE PLACE="foot">leeve W.</NOTE> bi auctorite of &thorn;e bischop of &thorn;e diocise &amp; now maad a vow of chastite or contynce, and here wyues ben of sich age &thorn;at noon euyl suspecion may be reysed of hem, late &thorn;e prouyn|cials seie to hem wordes of &thorn;e holi gospel &thorn;at &thorn;ei goo &amp; sille alle here goodis &amp; &yogh;eue hem to pore men, &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ei may not do &thorn;is here goode wille is ynow to hem; &amp; be &thorn;e freris &amp; here mynystris war &thorn;at &thorn;ei be not bisi of here temporal goodis, &thorn;at &thorn;ei don freli of here &thorn;ingis what euere &thorn;e lord inspiri&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">enpropri&thorn; X.; inspiraverit Lat.</NOTE> to hem. &para; Ne&thorn;eles &yogh;if conseil be nedful her-to, haue &thorn;e mynystris leue to sende hem to summe men &thorn;at dreden god, bi whos conseil here goodis schullen be &yogh;ouen to pore men. aftirward graunte &thorn;e mynystris to hem clo&thorn;is of probacion, &thorn;at is to<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> seie tweie<NOTE PLACE="foot">two W.</NOTE> cotis or kirtlis wi&thorn;-outen hood and a girdil &amp; a brech &amp; a chaperon to &thorn;e girdel, but &yogh;if o&thorn;er &thorn;ing after god be seyn to ye mynystris. &para; But whanne &thorn;e &yogh;eer of probacion is endid be &thorn;ei resceyued to obedience, bihetynge to kepe &thorn;is lif &amp; reule; &amp; in no manere schal it 
<PB REF="00000107.tif" N="41"> be leffel to hem to goo out of &thorn;is ordre vp<NOTE PLACE="foot">upon W.</NOTE> &thorn;e comaundement of &thorn;e lord &thorn;e pope, for aftir &thorn;e holy gospel no man sendynge his hond to &thorn;e plow&yogh; and lokenge a-&yogh;en is able to &thorn;e kyngdom of god. &amp; haue &thorn;ei &thorn;at han bihi&yogh;t obedience cotis or kirtlis<NOTE PLACE="foot">coote or kirtel W.</NOTE> wi&thorn; an hood and an o&thorn;er wi&thorn;outen<NOTE PLACE="foot">wi&thorn; an out X. and AA.</NOTE> hood; &thorn;ei &thorn;at wilen haue schon &amp; be nedid &thorn;er-to may bere hem. &para; And be alle freris clo&thorn;id wi&thorn; foule clo&thorn;is, &amp; &thorn;ei may pese hem a&yogh;en or cloute hem of sacchis &amp; o&thorn;ere pecis wi&thorn; &thorn;e blissyng of god. And I moneste &amp; stire &thorn;es freris &thorn;at &thorn;ei dispise not and deme not &thorn;o men whom &thorn;ei seen clo&thorn;id wi&thorn; softe clo&thorn;is &amp; colourid, &amp; vse delicat metis &amp; drynkis, but more eche of hem deme &amp; dispise him self.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="3" TYPE="chapter">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>Of goddis seruyce &amp; fastyngys, &amp; hou freris schullen go bi &thorn;e world.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<HEAD><SUP>4</SUP>Capitulum 3<SUP>m.4</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">4_4 cap<SUP>m.</SUP> ij<SUP>m.</SUP> W.; omitted X.</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Do clerkis deuyn officis<NOTE PLACE="foot">office W.</NOTE> after &thorn;e ordre of &thorn;o<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X. and AA.</NOTE> holy chirche of rome, out taken &thorn;e sautir, of wheche &thorn;ei may have breuyaries, &thorn;at is smale sauteris or abreggid; but late lewid freris seie four &amp; twenti pater nostris for matynes, for laudis fyue, for prime, tierce, vndren, noon, for eche of hem seuene pater nostris, &amp; for euensong twelue, &amp; for compleyn seuene. &para; And preie &thorn;ei for dede men. and faste &thorn;ei <MILESTONE N="31" UNIT="page"> fro &thorn;e feste of all hawen<NOTE PLACE="foot">halowe W.</NOTE> til &thorn;e natyuyte of crist, &amp; &thorn;o<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X. and AA.</NOTE> holy lenten &thorn;at bygynne&thorn; fro &thorn;e twel&thorn;e day of cristemasse to &thorn;e fulle fourti daies, &thorn;e whiche lenten oure lord halwid wi&thorn; &thorn;is holy fast, be &thorn;ei blissed of &thorn;e lord &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; X.</NOTE> fasten wilfully &thorn;is lenten; &amp; be &thorn;ei not constreyned &thorn;at wilen not, but faste &thorn;ei ano&thorn;er lenten til &thorn;e resurreccioun of &thorn;e lord. but in o&thorn;ere tymes ben &thorn;ei not holden to faste but on &thorn;e friday; but in tyme of opyn nede ben &thorn;e freris not bounden to bodily fast. but I conseile, amoneste, and stire my freris in oure lord ih&umacr; crist &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;an X.</NOTE> whanne &thorn;ei gon bi &thorn;e world &thorn;at &thorn;ei chide not and stryue not bi wordis, &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;ei iuge not o&thorn;ere men, but &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben mylde, peisble and manerly, homly &amp; meke, spekynge of al &thorn;ingis as it is semely. &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;ei schullen not ride but &yogh;if &thorn;ei ben nedid for opyn nede or siknesse. &para; In|to what euere hous &thorn;ei schullen entre seie &thorn;ei first, pees be to &thorn;is hous, &amp; aftir &thorn;e holy gospel be it lefful to hem to ete of alle metis &thorn;at ben sett to hem, as I haue seid.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="4" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000108.tif" N="42">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>&THORN;at Freris resceyuen no money.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<HEAD>Capitulum 4<SUP>m.</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">cap<SUP>m.</SUP> iij<SUP>m.</SUP> W.</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>I comaunde stedefastly to alle freris &thorn;at in no manere &thorn;ei resceyue no money or pens; nei&thorn;er bi hem self ne mene<NOTE PLACE="foot">none X.</NOTE> persone putt bitwixe. ne&thorn;eles for &thorn;e nede of sike men &amp; to clo&thorn;e o&thorn;ere freris bi gostly frendis only, &thorn;e mynystrys &amp; custodis schullen bere bisy cure, vpe placis &amp; tymes &amp; colde regiouns or contres; as &thorn;ei schulle see &thorn;at it is spedy to here nedy. &thorn;at &thorn;is &thorn;ing be euermore saaf, &thorn;at as it is seid &thorn;ei resceyue no pens ne money.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="5" TYPE="chapter">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>Of &thorn;e manere of trauayle of freris.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<HEAD>Capitulum 5<SUP>m.</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">4<SUP>m.</SUP> W.</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Oure freris to whom god ha&thorn; &yogh;ouen grace to traueile, labore &thorn;ei treuly &amp; deuoutly so &thorn;at ydelnesse enemy of soule be excludid or putt awey. And &thorn;ei quenche not &thorn;e spirit of holy deuocion and preire to whiche o&thorn;er spiritual <NOTE PLACE="foot">So in all MSS. The Latin has 'temporalia.'</NOTE> &thorn;ingis schullen serue. But of &thorn;e hire of labour receyue &thorn;ei neces|saries for hem self &amp; here bre&thorn;eren wi&thorn;-outen pens or mony, and &thorn;at mekely, as it is semynge to seruauntis of god foloweris of &thorn;e moste holy pouert.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="6" TYPE="chapter">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>&THORN;at freris apropren no &thorn;ing to hem self, &amp; hou &thorn;ei schullen axe almes, &amp; of sike freris.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<HEAD>Capitulum 6<SUP>m.</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">v<SUP>m.</SUP> W.</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Freris schulle no &thorn;ing apropre to hem self nei&thorn;er hous ne place ne ony o&thorn;er &thorn;ing, but as pilgrimes &amp; gestis or come|lyngyns in &thorn;is world, in pouert &amp; mekenesse seruynge to &thorn;e lord, goo &thorn;ei tristiliche for almes, and hem nedi&thorn; not to be a-schamyd, for oure <SUP>6</SUP>lord made hymsilf pore in &thorn;is werld<SUP>6</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">6_6 omitted X.</NOTE> for vs. &thorn;is is &thorn;e heynesse of &thorn;e moste hey&yogh; pouert, &thorn;at maki&thorn; &yogh;ou my bre&thorn;eren heiris &amp; kyngis of &thorn;e kyngdom of heuenys; &thorn;is ha&thorn; maad &yogh;ou<MILESTONE N="32" UNIT="page"> pore in &thorn;ingis &amp; enhaunsed &yogh;ou in vertues. be &thorn;is &yogh;oure porcion, or deel, &thorn;at bryngi&thorn; perfitely to &thorn;e lond of lyuynge men. to &thorn;e whiche pouert &thorn;e most loued bre&thorn;eren, hooliche cleuynge for &thorn;e reuerence of oure lord ih&umacr; crist, wile &yogh;e noo&thorn;ing haue lastinge &thorn;e world vnder heuene. And where euere freris ben &amp; fynden hem to-gidre schewe &thorn;ei hem homly bitwixe hem self, &amp; sikyrly schewe eche to o&thorn;er his nede. for &yogh;if a modir norsche&thorn; &amp; loue&thorn; here fleschly child, wi&thorn; hou mychel more diligence schal on loue 
<PB REF="00000109.tif" N="43"> &amp; norische his gostly bro&thorn;er, &amp; &yogh;if ony of hem falle in-to sike|nesse o&thorn;ere freris schullen serue hym as &thorn;ei wolden be seruyd</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="7" TYPE="chapter">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>Of penaunce to be putt to freris for synnes.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<HEAD>Capitulum 7<SUP>m.</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">vj<SUP>m.</SUP> W.</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>&YOGH;if ony of freris bi tisynge of &thorn;e enemye happen to synne deedly &thorn;e synnes of whiche it is ordeyned among freris &thorn;at &thorn;ei rennen to here mynystris prouyncial, &thorn;e same freris ben holden to renne to hem also sone as &thorn;ei may wi&thorn;-outen dwellyng. &amp; &thorn;o mynystris &yogh;if &thorn;ei ben prestis schullen wi&thorn; mercy enyonye hen penaunce, &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ei ben noone prestis make &thorn;ei to be enyoyned to hem bi o&thorn;er freris of &thorn;e ordre, as it seme&thorn; to spede most aftir god. &amp; &thorn;ei schullen be war &thorn;at &thorn;ei be not wra&thorn;id and disturblid for &thorn;e synne of ony, for wra&thorn;e &amp; disturblynge letten charite in hem &amp; o&thorn;ere.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="8" TYPE="chapter">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>Of &thorn;e chesyng of &thorn;e general mynystere &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> of &thorn;e prouyncial chapitris of &thorn;e ordre.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<HEAD>Capitulum 8<SUP>m.</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">vij<SUP>m.</SUP> W.</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Be alle freris holden to haue euermore on of &thorn;e freris of &thorn;is religion a general mynystre &amp; seruaunt of al &thorn;e bre&thorn;erhed, &amp; be &thorn;ei holden to obliche stedefastly to him. &amp; whanne he die&thorn; &thorn;e chesynge of his successour be maad <SUP>4</SUP>of mynistris prouincial &amp; custodis in &thorn;e chapitre of witsontide, in whiche chapitre be &thorn;e <SUP>4</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">4_4 omitted X.</NOTE>mynystris prouyncial holden euermore to come to-gidre, where euer it ha&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">hit has W.</NOTE> ben ordeyned of &thorn;e general mynystre; &amp; onys in &thorn;re &yogh;eer, or at ano&thorn;ere terme lasse or more as it is ordeyned of &thorn;e forseid mynystre. &amp; &yogh;if it seme ony tyme to &thorn;e generalte of mynystris prouyncial &amp; custodis &thorn;at &thorn;e forseide mynyster is not sufficient to &thorn;e seruyce &amp; comune profite of freris, <SUP>6</SUP>be &thorn;e forseide freris <SUP>6</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">6_6 omitted X.</NOTE>holden, to whom &thorn;e chesynge is &yogh;ouen, to chese hem ano&thorn;er in &thorn;e name of god to here kepere. Aftir &thorn;e chapitre of witsonday &thorn;e mynystris &amp; custodis may eche bi hem self, &yogh;if &thorn;ei wilen &amp; it seme to hem spedeful, in &thorn;e same &yogh;eer in here custodries onys clepe<NOTE PLACE="foot">calle W.</NOTE> to-gidre here bre&thorn;eren to chapitre.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="9" TYPE="chapter">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>Of prechours to &thorn;e puple.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<HEAD>Capitulum 9<SUP>m.</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">viij<SUP>m.</SUP> W.</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Preche not freris in &thorn;e bischopriche of ony bischop whanne &thorn;e bischop a&yogh;en sei&thorn; hym, &amp; noon of freris be hardy in ony manere to preche to &thorn;e peple but &yogh;if he be examyned &amp; aprouyd of &thorn;e mynystre of &thorn;is fraternyte, &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;e office 
<PB REF="00000110.tif" N="44"> of prechynge be graunted to hym of &thorn;e <MILESTONE N="33" UNIT="page">mynystre. &para; Also I moonest &amp; stire &thorn;e same freris &thorn;at in prechynge &thorn;at &thorn;ei maken here spechis be examyned as chast &amp; to profit &amp; to edificacion of &thorn;e peple. Schewynge to hem vices &amp; vertues, peyne &amp; glorie, wi&thorn; schortnesse of sermon. for &thorn;e lord ha&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">haad X.</NOTE> maad abreggid word vpon &thorn;e er&thorn;e.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="10" TYPE="chapter">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>Of &thorn;e monestynge &amp; of correccioun.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<HEAD>Capitulum 10<SUP>m.</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">ix<SUP>m.</SUP> W.</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Freris &thorn;at ben mynystris &amp; seruantis of o&thorn;ere freris schullen visite and moneste here bre&thorn;eren mekely &amp; charitably, &amp; &thorn;ei schullen correcte, not commandynge to hem ony &thorn;ing &thorn;at be a&yogh;enst here soule and oure<NOTE PLACE="foot">hor W.</NOTE> reule. And freris &thorn;at ben soget owen to &thorn;enke &thorn;at for god &thorn;ei han forsaken here owen willes; werfore I comaunde stedfastly to hem &thorn;at &thorn;ei obeche to here<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;o W.</NOTE> mynystris in alle &thorn;ingis &thorn;at &thorn;ei han behi&yogh;t to oure lord to kepe, &amp; noon contrarie &thorn;ingis to here soule &amp; to oure reule. &amp; where euere ben ony freris &thorn;at wisten or knewen &thorn;at &thorn;ei may not kepe gostly &thorn;e reule &thorn;ei may &amp; owen to renne to here mynystris, &amp; &thorn;e mynystris owe to resceyue hem benygnely &amp; bi charite, and haue &thorn;ei so muche famularite, or homlynesse, aboute hem &thorn;at &thorn;ei may seie<NOTE PLACE="foot">see X.; ut dicere possint Lat.</NOTE> to hem &amp; do as lordis to here seruauntis. for whi so it schal be, &thorn;at mynystris be seruauntis of alle freris. I amoneste &amp; stire in oure lord ih&umacr; crist &thorn;at freris ben war &amp; flee fro alle pride, fro veyn glorie, enuye and coueitise, &amp; cure &amp; bisynesse of &thorn;is world, fro detraccion &amp; grucchynge. &amp; recke not &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &thorn;ei ben vnkunnynge to lerne letteris, but vndirstonde &thorn;ei &thorn;at aboue alle thingis &thorn;ei owen to desire to haue &thorn;e spirit of &thorn;e lord &amp; his holy werchynge, and euere preie to god wi&thorn; clene herte, &amp; haue mekenesse &amp; pacience in pursuyt &amp; in infirmyte, and to loue hem &thorn;at pursuen vs &amp; reprouen &amp; dispisen vs. for oure lord sei&thorn;: loue &yogh;e &yogh;oure enemyes, &amp; preien for hem &thorn;at pursuen &yogh;ou, and for men &thorn;at falsly chalengen &yogh;ow. blissed be &thorn;ei &thorn;at suffren persecucion for ri&yogh;twisnesse, for here is &thorn;e kyngdom of heuenys; &amp; who euere lasti&thorn; in-to &thorn;e ende he schal be saaf.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="11" TYPE="chapter">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>&THORN;at freris entre not in-to abbeies of nunnes.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<HEAD>Capitulum 11<SUP>m.</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">x<SUP>m.</SUP> W.</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>I comaunde stably to freris &thorn;at &thorn;ei haue not suspect com|panyes or conseilis of wymmen, &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;ei entren not &thorn;e abbeies of nunnes, out take &thorn;o to whom fro &thorn;e see of apostaile is 
<PB REF="00000111.tif" N="45"> licence grauntid; and be &thorn;ei not maad godfadris of men, last bi &thorn;is occasion among freris &amp; of freris be gendrid sclaundre.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="12" TYPE="chapter">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>Of &thorn;e manere of goynge among sarasyns &amp; o&thorn;ere men out of bileue.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<HEAD>Capitulum 12<SUP>m.</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">xj<SUP>m.</SUP> W.</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Who euere of freris bi inspiracioun of god wilen goon among sarasyns &amp; o&thorn;ere vnbelefful, axe &thorn;ei leue &thorn;erof of here mynystris prouyncyal, and &yogh;eue &thorn;es mynystris to noon leue to go but to hem whom &thorn;ei seen ablee to be sent to &thorn;is &thorn;ing. I enyoyne to mynystris bi obedience &thorn;at &thorn;ei axe of &thorn;e lord &thorn;e pope on of &thorn;e cardynales of &thorn;e <MILESTONE N="34" UNIT="page">chirche of rome, &thorn;at be gouernour, meyntenour, and correctour of &thorn;is fraternyte, &thorn;at we be euere suget to &thorn;e feet of &thorn;e same holy chirche, and stable in general fei&thorn; of cristene men, &amp; &thorn;at we kepe pouert &amp; mekenesse &amp; &thorn;e holy gospel of oure lord ih&umacr; crist, &thorn;e whiche we han stedefastly bi-hi&yogh;t or awowid bi profession.</P>
<P>Here endi&thorn; &thorn;e reule of seynt fraunseis, &amp; here bigynne&thorn; &thorn;e testament of seynt fraunceis.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="13" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 13<SUP>m.</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Testamentum</I> francisci W.</NOTE></HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="testament">
<P>In &thorn;e name of &thorn;e fadir &amp; sone &amp; &thorn;e holy gost. Amen. Houre lord ha&thorn; &yogh;ouen to me fraunseis to bigynne to do penaunce; &amp; whanne I was in ouere myche synnes it semyd to me bittrere to see leprous men, and &thorn;e same lord brou&yogh;te me among hem and I dede mercy wi&thorn; hem. &amp; wanne I departed fro hem &thorn;at &thorn;ing &thorn;at was semynge bitter to me was turned to me in-to swetnesse of soule &amp; bodi. &amp; aftirward I stood a litel and wente out of &thorn;e world, &amp; oure lord &yogh;af me sich fei&thorn; in chirchis &thorn;at I schulde preie &thorn;us sympli &amp; seie: we worschipen &thorn;e, lord ih&umacr; crist, at alle &thorn;e chirchis &thorn;e wiche ben in al &thorn;e world, and we blissen to &thorn;e for by &thorn;yn holy crois &thorn;u hast a&yogh;en bou&yogh;t &thorn;e world.</P>
<P>&para; Aftirward &thorn;e lord &yogh;af to me &amp; &yogh;eue&thorn; so myche fei&thorn; &thorn;at I wille renne to &thorn;e prestis &thorn;at lyuen aftir &thorn;e forme of &thorn;e chirche of rome for &thorn;e ordeynynge of hem, al-&thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei diden to me persecucion. &amp; &thorn;ou&yogh; I hadde as myche wisdom as hadde salamon &amp; I founde litel pore prestis of &thorn;is world &thorn;at dwellen in parichis I wille not preche a&yogh;enst here wille. and I<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X. and AA.</NOTE> wille honoure alle prestis as my lordis, &amp; I wile not biholde in hem ony synne, fore in hem I 
<PB REF="00000112.tif" N="46"> take bi discrecion goddis sone &amp; &thorn;ei ben my lordis. &amp; here-fore I do &thorn;at I see noo bodily &thorn;ing in this world of hym, &thorn;e hei&yogh;est goddis sone, but his holieste bodi &amp; blood &thorn;at &thorn;ei resceyuen &amp; &thorn;ei only mynystren to o&thorn;ere. &amp; I wile abouen alle &thorn;ingis honoure &thorn;es holieste preuytes or mysteries, &amp; putte &thorn;es holieste names in most precious places, &amp; where euere I fynde his wordis writen in vnlefful placis I wile gedre &amp; preie &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben gedrid &amp; kepte<NOTE PLACE="foot">be putt W.</NOTE> in an honeste place. &amp; we schal worschipen in herte &amp; word alle clerkis of dyuynyte &thorn;at mynystren to vs most holy wordis as hem &thorn;at mynystren to vs &thorn;e holy gost &amp; lif. And after &thorn;at &thorn;e lord hadde &yogh;ouen to me of freris no man schewid to me what I schulde do, but he &thorn;at is hi&yogh;est schewid to me &thorn;at I schulde lyue after &thorn;e forme of &thorn;e gospel: &amp; I in fewe wordis &amp; sympliche maade to write it, &amp; &thorn;e lord pope confermyd it to me. And summe comen<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X. and AA.</NOTE> to taken &thorn;is lif, And &thorn;ei &yogh;auen to pore men alle &thorn;inges &thorn;at &thorn;ei my&yogh;tten. And &thorn;ei weren <MILESTONE N="35" UNIT="page">apeied wi&thorn; o cote or kirtil with-ynne for&thorn;e &amp; with-oute for&thorn; &amp; wolde not haue more. clerkis schulden seie here officis aftir clerkis, but lewed freris schulde seie &thorn;e pater noster. and we dwelten to-gidre in chirchis, &amp; weren idiotis, &amp; vnderloute to ale men. &amp; I traueiled wi&thorn; myn hondis &amp; wile traueile, &amp; I<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X. and AA.</NOTE> wile &thorn;at alle o&thorn;ere freris traueile in labour &thorn;e whiche pertyne&thorn; to honeste, &amp; &thorn;ei &thorn;at kunnen not, lerne &thorn;ei; not for coueitise to take hire, but for ensample to putte awey idelnesse; &amp; whanne men &yogh;euen vs nou&yogh;t renne we to &thorn;e borde of &thorn;e lord, axynge almes fro dore to dore.</P>
<P>&para; God schewid to me &thorn;is salutacion &thorn;at I schulde seie, &thorn;e lord &yogh;eue pees to &thorn;e, &thorn;erfor be freris war &thorn;at &thorn;ei resceyue not in no<NOTE PLACE="foot">any W.</NOTE> manere, nei&thorn;er chirchis, ne placis to dwellen onne, ne ony o&thorn;er &thorn;ingis &thorn;at ben bilded for hem, but as it seme&thorn; holy pouert, &thorn;e whiche we han bi-fore seid in &thorn;e reule, euer|more dwellynge &thorn;ere as gestis &amp; comelyngis &amp; pilgrymys. I comaunde sadly to alle freris be obedience &thorn;at where so euere &thorn;ei ben be &thorn;ei not chargid<NOTE PLACE="foot">hardy X.</NOTE> to axe ony lettre in &thorn;e court of rome, nei&thorn;er be hem self ne by mene persone put bitwyxe, wi&thorn; &thorn;e blissynge of god. And I wile &thorn;at freris obeche to &thorn;e general mynystre of &thorn;is fraternyte whom it plesed to me to &yogh;eue &thorn;erto, and I wile &thorn;at I be so taken in his hondis &thorn;at I may not goo or do a&yogh;enst his obedience &amp; his wille, for he is my lord. &amp; &thorn;ou&yogh; I be simpul<NOTE PLACE="foot">sinful AA.; Latin simplex.</NOTE> &amp; sik ne&thorn;eles I wile euere haue a clerk &thorn;at schal do me dyuyne office after &thorn;e reule. And &thorn;o &thorn;at ben founden &thorn;at don not &thorn;e office after &thorn;e reule &amp; wilen varie on o&thorn;er manere &amp; be not 
<PB REF="00000113.tif" N="47"> of ry&yogh;t cristen fei&thorn;, be alle freris holden bi obedience where euere &thorn;ei ben &thorn;at, where euere &thorn;ei schulle fynde ony of &thorn;oo, &thorn;ei schullen presenten hym to &thorn;e nexte custode of &thorn;at place where euere &thorn;ei fynden sychon. and be &thorn;at custode holde sadly bi obedience to kepe hym strongly as a man in bondis day &amp; ny&yogh;t, so &thorn;at he may not be delyuerid of his hond til he represente hym <SUP>1</SUP>in his owen persone in &thorn;e hondis of his mynystre, and be &thorn;e mynystre holden sadly bi obedience to holde hym bi freris &thorn;at kepe men ny&yogh;t &amp; day as in bondis til &thorn;at he represente hym to &thorn;e <SUP>1</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">1_1 omitted W.</NOTE>cardynal hostiense, &thorn;at is lord, gouernour, meyntenour &amp; corectour of alle &thorn;e fraternyte.</P>
<P>And seie not, freris, &thorn;at &thorn;is is ano&thorn;er reule: for it is a remembraunce, amonestynge, a reprouynge, and my testament &thorn;e whiche I frere fraunseis, litel, make to my blissed bre&thorn;eren, &thorn;at for &thorn;is<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X. and AA.</NOTE> we kepe bettere &thorn;e reule &thorn;e whiche we han bihi&yogh;t to &thorn;e lord. &amp; &thorn;e general mynystre &amp; alle o&thorn;ere mynystris &amp; custodes ben holden bi obedience to <MILESTONE N="36" UNIT="page">adde no &thorn;ing to &thorn;es wordis ne drawe &thorn;er fro &amp; rede &thorn;ei &thorn;es wordis.</P>
<P>And I comaunde bi obedience to alle my bre&thorn;eren, bo&thorn;e clerkis &amp; lewid, &thorn;at &thorn;ei putte not glosis vnto &thorn;e reule, ne seynge wi&thorn; &thorn;es wordis: "so &thorn;ei wilen be vndirstonden," but as &thorn;e lord &yogh;af to me sympliche and pureliche to seie &amp; to write &thorn;e reule; and vndirstonde &yogh;e &thorn;es wordis so symplely and clenly with-oute glose &amp; kepe &yogh;ee hem in to &thorn;e ende wi&thorn; holy werchynge. and who euere kepi&thorn; &thorn;is be he fulfillid in heuene with &thorn;e blissynge of &thorn;e hei&yogh;est fadir, and be he fulfillid in er&thorn;e with &thorn;e blissynge of his louyd sone, wi&thorn; &thorn;e holiest gost confortour, &amp; wi&thorn; alle vertues of heuenes and wi&thorn; alle seyntis; and I frere fraunseis, &yogh;oure litel and &yogh;oure seruant, conferme to &yogh;ou how euere myche I may wi&thorn;-in &amp; wi&thorn;-outen &thorn;is moste holy blissyng. Amen.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Finis testamenti W.</NOTE></P>
<TRAILER>Here endi&thorn; &thorn;e testament of seynt fraunseis.</TRAILER>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="comment">
<HEAD>[Comment.]</HEAD>
<P>But here &thorn;e menours seyn &thorn;at &thorn;e pope dischargi&thorn; hem of &thorn;is testament &amp; sei&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben not holden &thorn;er-to, for a man ha&thorn; not lordschipe ne iurisdiccion vpon his pere, &amp; si&thorn; &thorn;e pope was more &thorn;an fraunseis he my&yogh;tte not bynde &thorn;e pope &thorn;at he ne my&yogh;te dispense &amp; reproue what he wolde. &para; But to &thorn;is trewe men seyn &thorn;us, &thorn;at freris ben bounden to &thorn;is testament for many skillis: first fraunseis sei&thorn; &thorn;at god schewid hym 
<PB REF="00000114.tif" N="48"> &thorn;is lyuyng and not man; &thorn;anne o&thorn;er &thorn;is testament is of goddis wille or fraunseis is fals &thorn;at sei&thorn; so. &yogh;if it be goddis wille &thorn;e pope may not do a&yogh;enst it, &yogh;if fraunseis be false in &thorn;is seiynge his doynge cam of &thorn;e fend<NOTE PLACE="foot">deuel W.</NOTE> of helle &thorn;at is fadir of lesyngis. &para; Also fraunseis sei&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;is testament is noon o&thorn;er reule but &thorn;e firste, and &thorn;anne as &thorn;ei taken &thorn;e firste reule so moste &thorn;ei take &thorn;e testament, si&thorn;&thorn;en &thorn;ei ben al oon. &para; Also it semi&thorn; &thorn;at fraunseis in his laste daies schulde beste knowe &thorn;e treu&thorn;e &amp; most be in charite to his bre&thorn;eren, &amp; &thorn;an he made &thorn;is testament; &amp; herefore it seme&thorn; &thorn;at he was a liere &amp; out of charite but &yogh;if &thorn;is testament were acordynge wi&thorn; goddis dom; but what pope or deuyl<NOTE PLACE="foot">ordeyned W.</NOTE> schulde &thorn;anne distroie it? &para; Also men seyn &thorn;at he is cursed &thorn;at letti&thorn; &thorn;e ri&yogh;tful wille of a dede man. But &thorn;is testament is ri&yogh;tful wille of dede fraunseis; &thorn;anne it semi&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;at pope &thorn;at letti&thorn; it &amp; &thorn;e freris also ben acursed of god, of fraunseis, and of alle hawen.</P>
<P>&para; As to &thorn;e substance of the reule &thorn;ei forsaken obedience of god and obeschen to a synful idiot biddynge &thorn;e contrarie of goddis wille, &thorn;e whiche synful ydiot is in cas a dampnyd deuyl, &amp; so for plesynge of &thorn;e world or lustis of here flech &thorn;ei leuen &thorn;e comaundementis of god &amp; don vnri&yogh;tful comaundement of &thorn;e fend, &amp; magnyfien more obedience to synful men, &amp; in caas to fendis, &thorn;an obedience <MILESTONE N="37" UNIT="page">to crist &thorn;at is eueremore medeful; &amp; so &thorn;ei seyen &thorn;at a good &thorn;ing doon after &thorn;e comaundement of god is not of so gret meri&yogh;t as a &thorn;ing don after &thorn;e comaundement of a synful ydiot, &amp; in cas a dep deuyl in helle. but &thorn;is newe profession was not vsed of crist &amp; his apostelis but in &thorn;e time &thorn;at sathanas was vnbounden, as &thorn;e apcalips telli&thorn;; and so it semi&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;es newe ordris distroien obedience of cristis lawe (bi whiche eche man is holden obeche to o&thorn;er in &thorn;e drede of crist, &thorn;at is in as myche as ony techi&thorn; a no&thorn;er to don &thorn;e wille of god) &amp; magnyfie obedience to synful men, &yogh;ee a&yogh;enst &thorn;e preceptis of god. and so as myche as is in hem &thorn;ei maken a synful idiot &amp; in cas a dampnyd deuyl in helle more than almy&yogh;ti 
<PB REF="00000115.tif" N="49"> god in trinyte, for &thorn;ei don more aftir his false comaundement &thorn;an aftir comaundement of almy&yogh;ty god.</P>
<P>&para; To &thorn;e secunde part of &thorn;e reule wi&thorn;-outen proprete of worldly goodis; si&thorn; propre &thorn;ing stondi&thorn; most in wille &amp; &thorn;ei traueilen more for propre worschipe or wynnynge &thorn;an for comune profit of cristen men, it seme&thorn; &thorn;ei don alle a&yogh;enst &thorn;is reule; for &thorn;ei han grete housis proprid to hem self, many costly bokis, &amp; myche hid tresour biried in here houses fro &thorn;e comunte of cristen men lyuynge in &thorn;e world bi gret labor, as god enyoyned adam; &amp; &thorn;is tresour is kept proprely to idel men or fendis, si&thorn;&thorn;en it is geten by false lesyngis, false beggynge, &amp; fals meyntenynge of foule synnes. &para; Also o strong beggere or flaterere ha&thorn; a chaumber for a lord, erl or duk wi&thorn; many preciouse iuellis, &amp; ano&thorn;er frere ha&thorn; nakid sidis &amp; many other myscheues &thorn;ou&yogh; he be wor&thorn; siche a &thorn;ousand bifore god. &para; As to chastite deme men of here bodily chastite, but of gostly chastite it seme&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben alle avoutreris, for &thorn;ei halde religioun &thorn;at is maad of synful men bettre &thorn;an religion maad of crist hym self, &amp; &thorn;ei chargen more tradicions or customes maad of here owen errouris &thorn;an &thorn;e iust lawis &amp; heste maad of almy&yogh;tty god, &amp; &thorn;us is gostely matrimonye bitwixe crist &amp; cristen mennus soulis broken, si&thorn; it stondi&thorn; in ri&yogh;tfulnesse &amp; mercy &amp; fei&thorn;.</P>
<P>&para; But see now hou freris don openly a&yogh;enst &thorn;is reule &amp; testament. also in takynge money many weies; for &thorn;ei leden wi&thorn; hem a scarioth stolen fro is eldris by &thorn;efte to robbe pore men bi beggynge dampnyd of goddis lawe. &amp; seen more ypocrisie of hem: &thorn;ei wolen telle gold and money &amp; touche it wi&thorn; a sticke or wi&thorn; gloues &amp; a grete cuppe of gold or pece of siluer wor&thorn; many markis to drynke noble wyn of, but &thorn;ei wilen not touche an halpeny or fer&thorn;ing wi&thorn; &thorn;e coyn &amp; armes of &thorn;e cros &amp; of the kyng, &amp; &thorn;is seme&thorn; for dispit of &thorn;e cros or of &thorn;e kyng, for a weeg of siluer<NOTE PLACE="foot">gold W.</NOTE> or a <MILESTONE N="38" UNIT="page">cuppe of gold &thorn;ei wolen handil faste, and &thorn;e money &thorn;at &thorn;ei robben of pore men bi fals beggynge &thorn;ei wolen leyn it 
<PB REF="00000116.tif" N="50"> vndir here beddis hed at ny&yogh;t. &amp; so of clo&thorn;ing &thorn;ei don a&yogh;enst &thorn;is reule in many maneres; for men seen &thorn;at &thorn;e kyng or &thorn;e emperour my&yogh;tte wi&thorn; worschipe were a garnement of a frere for goodnesse of &thorn;e clo&thorn;, &amp; namely of suche freris as schulden most kepe pouert of crist &amp; his apostelis, as ben clepid maistris of diuynyte, but verreily maistris of errour bo&thorn;e in techynge &amp; in ensaumple, &amp; summe oone ha&thorn; wast clo&thorn;is &amp; costi, and a no&thorn;er symple frere &thorn;at nys not so gret flaterere nakid or to rent. &para; As to propre &thorn;ingis freris seyn &thorn;at &thorn;e pope is lord worldly of housis, bokis, iewelis and al &thorn;at &thorn;ei han, but her seme&thorn; myche venym: first &thorn;e euyl children putten in-to here fadir &thorn;e pope &thorn;e venym of worldly lordschipe si&thorn; &thorn;ei may not haue it for distroynge of here perfeccioun, &amp; yit &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at &thorn;e pope mot be most holy &amp; perfyt &amp; nexte sue crist in alle manere vertues, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei putten a veyn &thorn;orn in his feet. As to here kyng &thorn;ei ben vnkynde &amp; vntrewe, for wi&thorn;-outen his leeve<NOTE PLACE="foot">love X.</NOTE> or is conseil &thorn;ei alien in-to straunge<NOTE PLACE="foot">stronge X. and AA.</NOTE> rewmes, &amp; in caas to oure enemyes, al &thorn;at &thorn;ei may gete bi robberie of pore men<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X. and AA.</NOTE> &amp; flaterynge &amp; o&thorn;ere false menes in &thorn;e lond &thorn;at &thorn;ei dwelli&thorn; inne; &amp; so, &yogh;if &thorn;e pope ben enemye to oure lond &amp; sende enemyes to oure lond, he ha&thorn; many stronge houses as caastelis; &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ei ben his ri&yogh;tfully oure kyng may not warne ne lette his hoste to reste in &thorn;o places, &amp; &thorn;anne is oure lond in gret peril. &para; As anemtis prechynge, men knowen wel &thorn;at freris wile flatere &amp; spare to reproue scharply synnes of grete men for drede of los of worldly goodis or frendischipe or fauour; &amp; so for loue of here stynkynge bely &thorn;ei laten &thorn;e fend strangle many<NOTE PLACE="foot">mennus W.</NOTE> soulis, and &yogh;it dispisen and letten o&thorn;ere men to preche the treu&thorn;e of goddis lawe, laste here synne were knowen &amp; here pride &amp; worldly wynnynge leid a doun. &para; And &yogh;it &thorn;ei tellen not schortly ne plenerly<NOTE PLACE="foot">pleynely W.</NOTE> &thorn;e gospel, &amp; vices &amp; vertues, &amp; peynes and ioie, but maken longe talis of fablis, or cronyclis, or comenden here owen nouelries. &para; As anemtis 
<PB REF="00000117.tif" N="51"> traueile of freris it is knowen hou &thorn;ei gon ydel fro contre to contre, &amp; fro toun to toun, &amp; fro hous to hous, beggynge nedles of pore men, techynge o&thorn;ere to ben idel, &amp; stelen mennus children to &thorn;is ydelnesse, where &thorn;ei ben tau&yogh;t to lyue in swet of here body bi comaundement of god and bi here owen reule &amp; by ensaumple of petir and poule; whanne petir fischid aftir cristis resurreccion, &amp; poul traueilid <MILESTONE N="39" UNIT="page">wi&thorn; his hondis after cristis ascencion; and seynt austyn techi&thorn; munkis to labore wi&thorn; here hondis, &amp; so do&thorn; seynt benet &amp; seynt bernard. &para; Also bisiden rome frere menours bi false name pursuen trewe pore freris to de&thorn;, for as myche as &thorn;ei wolden kepe fraunseis reule to &thorn;e lettere in pouert &amp; meke|nesse &amp; in grete penaunce, &amp; &thorn;er-fore, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei haue name of franseis freris, &thorn;ei ben enemys of crist &amp; fraunseis &amp; cruel man-sleeris. &para; Also, &yogh;if fraunseis take only &thorn;e gospel and no &thorn;ing addi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">asdi&thorn; X.</NOTE> of his owne &thorn;er-to, it schulde not be clepid<NOTE PLACE="foot">calde W.</NOTE> fraunseis reule but reule of crist or of &thorn;e gospel; &amp; &yogh;if he putte to &thorn;e gospel of his owne fyndynge, whi schulde he make &thorn;er-of a newe ordre, si&thorn; &thorn;e ordre &thorn;at crist made him self is most perfit &amp; most li&yogh;t &amp; most siker to geten heuene by, &amp; what goode dede ony man may doo he is holden to don it bi &thorn;is most comaundement of god: "&thorn;ou schalt loue &thorn;i lord &thorn;i god of ale &thorn;in herte, of al &thorn;i lif, of al &thorn;i &thorn;ou&yogh;tis, &amp; of al &thorn;i steng&thorn;es or my&yogh;tis." what nede is it &thorn;anne to make ano&thorn;er religion, si&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;at crist made is I-now&yogh; at &thorn;e fulle; &amp; so si&thorn; noone apostle of crist ne angel of heuene ha&thorn; ony power but &yogh;if it be to edificacion &amp; profit of holy chirche, &thorn;e pope ha&thorn; no<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X. and AA.</NOTE> power to dispense a&yogh;enst fraunseis testament &amp; his reule, si&thorn; &thorn;ei ben al on, but &yogh;if it be to profit of holy chirche &thorn;at men kepen nei&thorn;er his reule ne his testament. Of &thorn;is reule &amp; errour my&yogh;te men speke ful myche. But god for his mercy brynge clerkis to cristis clene<NOTE PLACE="foot">trewe X. and AA.</NOTE> religion, si&thorn; it is &thorn;e beste on alle weies &amp; most profitable to alle parties. Amen.</P>


</DIV3>
</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="4" TYPE="tract"><PB REF="00000118.tif" N="52">
<HEAD>IV. OF PRELATES.</HEAD>
<HEADNOTE><P>THIS tract is less orderly in arrangement and fuller of repetition than is usual in Wyclif's work, but some parts of it are worthy of him, and it contains no opinions that are not to be found in his genuine writings. There is a great resemblance between this and the tract on the office of Curates, No. VII. Both have references to the Crusade in Flanders, and are therefore late works of Wyclif, if his at all; while both of them are silent as to his doctrine of the Eucharist, and are comparatively mild in their language as to the Friars, who are not treated as at all worse than the monks. This would be natural enough in Wyclif's earlier years, but is not in accordance with his usual tone after 1380. I incline to think that they were written by an intimate disciple rather than by the master.</P><P>As to evidence of date, I have little doubt that the mention of "anticrists bullis to maken cristene men to werre with each othere" (p. 73), and of pardons granted "to make discensioun &amp; werris" (p. 82) refer to Spencer's Crusade, although it is just possible that they may point to one of the other occasions on which popes have encouraged bloodshed.</P><P>The tone as to persecution is uncertain. The passage (p. 87) "prisonen hem and slen hem <I>algates in wille</I>" looks as if the infliction of death for heresy was not yet allowed. There is stronger language in the Sermons and the Trialogus. Yet we are told on p. 79, that lords who support poor priests are cursed and taken to prison "if thei stonden sadde in goddis cause." This may have happened in Wyclif's time, merely as the result of excommunication, but I know no instance of it. Were the tract written much after his death, its tone would probably be fiercer.</P><P>I cannot identify the "litel harlot" who "dispiseth the pope and stroieth his lordship," p. 83.</P><P>Copied from the Corpus MS. X. and collated with the Dublin MS. AA.</P><P>A leaf is wanting in AA. from end of Chapter XLI. to the early part of Chapter XLIII. "for his entier sorwe of synne."</P><P><TABLE>
<HEAD>SUMMARY.</HEAD>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. I.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates are bound to preach, since they take the place of apostles whom Christ ordered to preach. Examples and warnings from Scripture. Wicked|ness of neglect. Prelates more bound to preach than the people to pay tithes. Duty of making them amend.</CELL>

<PB REF="00000119.tif" N="53">
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. II.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates will not allow priests to preach without their licence. They permit the new religious to go about preaching lies and fables, but it is on condition that they do not preach against the sins of prelates, and that they pay largely from the money which they extort.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. III.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates are heretics, for by their life they set an example of living against Christ's law. Their pomp, litigiousness, luxury and covetousness.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. IV.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates rob the king's lieges by taking money for licences to sin. They bribe nobles and jurors to support them, but curse all who try to correct them.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. V.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates come to their benefices by simony. Nature of simony. Its prevalence. Common forms of it. Worst in the Court of Rome, and most harmful. Condemnation of simony in Scripture. It is a heresy. Bishops, friars, and curates alike guilty of it.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. VI.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates think more of the consecration of churches and ornaments than of consecrating the sacrament of the altar, which they leave to every priest, while they keep the others for themselves. They use these offices as a means of extortion.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. VII.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates teach man's law, but hinder preaching of the gospel. Prayer to God to give courage to his servants, and understanding to lords.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. VIII.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates care more for money than for men's souls. Witness the sin|rents.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. IX.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates live in lechery and lead others into sin. They raise money from poor men, who want it to live on. They publish bulls to encourage wars. They allow friars to go about begging. Thus they kill men's souls.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. X.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates lay more stress on their own curse than on God's. They enforce their excommunication by imprisonment. For real sins they sell absolution, but they put true preachers under curse, and condemn them by false witness.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XI.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates deceive men by their false prayers and singing. Prayer without good life useless. God only knows the worth of each man's prayer. Prayers of wicked men are not made useful by the virtue of the Church. If they cannot pray effectively for themselves, neither can they for others.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XII.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates frighten men by their excommunications; forbid true preachers, and persecute those who would support them.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XIII.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates deceive men by indulgences, which have no authority from Christ, and are useless except as a means of extortion. Pardon is wholly in God's hands.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XIV.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates make the way to heaven harder by their new laws. They add also new points to the Creed; as the headship of the pope.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XV.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates exalt themselves above Christ; for he told men to judge him by his deeds, and they say their subjects should not judge them.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XVI.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates stop men from doing God's will, as in saying mass and preaching. They pretend it is to stop heresy, but they are not true judges of heresy, for they neither know nor keep God's law.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XVII.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates refuse obedience and taxes to secular lords. Christ paid tribute to the Emperor. Much more should they who are rich help the land. They set example of rebellion.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XVIIII.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates worse than Jews, for they persecute Christ in his members and take blood-money.</CELL>

<PB REF="00000120.tif" N="54">
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XIX.</CELL>
<CELL>Avarice of prelates, their litigiousness, oppression; their pomp and war|like ways.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XX.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates teach other men to maintain them in their sins and to persecute poor priests.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXI.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates set more store by their own laws than by the gospel.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXII.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates teach that nothing in the church is lawful that is not confirmed by the pope, who is commonly the worst of prelates and antichrist.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXIII.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates are enemies of peace, counselling war to divert attention from their own sins. Besides advising it, they take part in it.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXIV.</CELL>
<CELL>The worldly and pompous life of prelates an ill example.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXV.</CELL>
<CELL>Money sent out of the realm to bring preferment and to maintain suits at Rome.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXVI.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates by their invention of new laws declare Christ's laws to be in|sufficient, and so slander Christ.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXVII.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates make men assent to their false teaching, and deceive lords so as to make them imprison true men.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXVIII.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates make men study new laws, and keep them from studying Holy Writ.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXIX.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates make lords imprison any one who has been under curse for forty days. Lords should make sure that the curse is rightful.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXX.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates' arguments for their claims to obedience and power are like the arguments of apes and gluttons.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXXI.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates despoil all classes of men in different ways.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXXII.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates think more of their parks being broken than of breaking of God's laws.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXXIII.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates take upon them the state of the apostles, and live contrary to it, so deceiving men like enemies who mount false arms.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXXIV.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates compel priests to fight in person.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXXV.</CELL>
<CELL>Evils caused by celibacy of priests.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXXVI.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates silence those who would rebuke them, lest their hypocrisy be known, and they lose their endowments.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXXVII.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates maintain vicious men in their retinue.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXXVIII.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates deceive men as to pilgrimages and pardons, and teach them to care more for vows than for God's laws.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XXXIX.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates rob the lower clergy in assessment of taxes.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XL.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates are dumb dogs, who do not warn the flock committed to them, but give it to Satan in exchange for wealth.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XLI.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates crucify Christ and slay his apostles spiritually, and so are worse than Jews.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XLII.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates blaspheme the Holy Ghost by preventing true preaching.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. XLIII.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates claim the power of absolution, which God has reserved to himself. They have only power to act as messengers. Yet they lay more stress on their absolution than on God's forgiveness.</CELL>
</ROW>
</TABLE></P></HEADNOTE>

<PB REF="00000121.tif" N="55">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>Here it telle&thorn; of prelatis.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<DIV2 N="1" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum Primum.</HEAD>
<P><MILESTONE N="65" UNIT="page">&THORN;at prelatis leuen prechynge of &thorn;e gospel &amp; ben gostly manquelleris of mennys soulis, And sathanas transfigurid in-to an aungel of li&yogh;t, &amp; ben gostly sodomytis worse &thorn;an bodily sodomytis of sodom and gomor. first, crist sei&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel of seyn ion &thorn;at he was boren &amp; cam in-to &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">John xviii. 37.</NOTE> world for &thorn;is ende, to<NOTE PLACE="foot">betere inserted X.</NOTE> bere witnesse to treu&thorn;e; also crist cam in-to &thorn;is world to seke and to saue mankynde, &thorn;e whiche was perischid. &amp; certis crist sauyd mannus soule<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke xix. 10.</NOTE> bi trewe lyuynge in his owen persone, &amp; trewe &amp; opyn &amp; fre prechynge of &thorn;e gospel, &amp; wilful passion &amp; de&thorn; for prechynge &amp; meyntenynge of &thorn;e gospel; &amp; to &thorn;is same ende &amp; werk crist ordeyned alle his apostlis &amp; disciplis, bo&thorn;e bi-forn his de&thorn; &amp; after his resurreccion, to preche &thorn;us &thorn;e gospel to alle men. &thorn;anne, si&thorn; prelatis &amp; prestis ordeyned of good comen in &thorn;e stede of postlis &amp; disciples, &thorn;ei ben alle bounden bi ih&umacr; crist god &amp; man to preche &thorn;us &thorn;e gospel. &para; Also crist biddi&thorn; &thorn;ries to petir &thorn;at &yogh;if peter loue crist &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">[John xxi. 15.]</NOTE> he fede his scheep; &thorn;at ben cristen soulis; &amp; first fede bi ensaumple of good lif, &thorn;e secunde tyme bi trewe techynge of &thorn;e gospel, and &thorn;e &thorn;ridde tyme bi wilful suffrynge of dei&thorn;, to make men stable in &thorn;e gospel &amp; in hope of blisse: &amp; here-to crist comaunded his disciples to preche opynly &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Matt. x. 27, 28.]</NOTE> treu&thorn;e &thorn;at &thorn;ei herden priuely, &amp; drede not men &thorn;at turmenten &amp; slen &thorn;e bodi, but drede hym &thorn;at may putte body &amp; soule in-to helle wi&thorn;-outen ende. &para; Of &thorn;es two gospellis it is cleer &thorn;at prelatis &thorn;at prechen not &thorn;us &thorn;e gospel louen not crist, but don fully a&yogh;enst his heste, whanne &thorn;ei leuen for drede of men to teche &thorn;e gospel; &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;e he&yogh;e prestis ely was dede for he tau&yogh;te not his children goddis lawe and reproued not at &thorn;e fulle here synnes, &amp; &thorn;e arke<NOTE PLACE="foot">"whiche" both MSS.</NOTE> or couere of god was conquerid in-to enemyes hondis, &amp; goddis 
<PB REF="00000122.tif" N="56"> peple ouercomen, and many &thorn;ousandis slayn in bataile as<NOTE PLACE="marg">[1 Sam. iv.]</NOTE> &thorn;e first bok of kyngis telli&thorn;. &para; And herefore &thorn;e holy prophete ysaie crie&thorn; &thorn;at woo is to hym, for &thorn;at he was stille and dwelte among synful peple, &amp; telle hem not here synnes,<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Isaiah vi. 5.]</NOTE> si&thorn; &thorn;is is offis of a prophete. also god se&thorn; to prelatis bi e&yogh;echiel, &thorn;at &yogh;if a synful man die in his synne &amp; &thorn;e prelate<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Ezekiel iii. 18.]</NOTE> telle him not his peyne for synne, god schal seke &thorn;e synful mannus bloode, &thorn;at is his synne, of &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;ere X.</NOTE> prelatis hondis. &para; And here-for sei&thorn; poul &thorn;at woo is to hym, &thorn;at is euerlastynge dampnacion, but &yogh;if he preche &thorn;e gospel; &amp; si&thorn; cristen men<NOTE PLACE="marg">[1 Cor. ix. 16.]</NOTE> may not lyue gostly but bi goddis word, <MILESTONE N="66" UNIT="page">prelatis &thorn;at wi&thorn;|drawen &thorn;us goddis word fro here sugetis ben cause of de&thorn; of here soulis, &thorn;at is a &thorn;ousand folde worse &thorn;an is de&thorn; of body, &amp; so &thorn;ei be worse man-sleeris &thorn;an &thorn;ei &thorn;at only sleen &thorn;e body. &para; And si&thorn; petir was sathanas for he wolde haue<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Matt. xvi. 23.]</NOTE> lettid cristis de&thorn; &amp; saluacion of mannus soule, him wnwyt|tyngge; moche more &thorn;es prelatis ben sathanas, &thorn;at &thorn;us myche contrarien cristis wille &amp; sauynge of mennus soulis &thorn;oru&yogh; prechynge of &thorn;e gospel, &amp; &thorn;ei ben turned in-to an aungel of li&yogh;t, for &thorn;ei feynen hem in &thorn;e stede of apostlis &amp; worche wi&thorn; &thorn;e fend to suffre mennus soulis go to helle; &amp; si&thorn; goddis word, bi whiche men schulden gostly be gendrid goddis sones, is betere &thorn;an bodely seed of man bi whiche &thorn;e body of man schulde be gendred, &amp; &thorn;es prelatis mysusen &thorn;is betere seed, &thorn;anne &thorn;ei don more synne &thorn;an diden &thorn;e sodomytis &thorn;at wasted manus seed; for euere &thorn;e betre &thorn;at a &thorn;ing is &thorn;e worse &amp; &thorn;e more abhominable is &thorn;e mysusynge &thorn;er-of. &amp; &thorn;e grete doctour lyncolne robert grosted groundi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Grosset&ecirc;te.]</NOTE> &thorn;is pleynly &thorn;at siche prelatis &thorn;at leuen to preche &thorn;us cristis gospel ben more abhominable and enemys of god &amp; his peple &thorn;an weren &thorn;e cursed men of sodom &amp; gomor. &amp; si&thorn; god se&thorn; bi &thorn;e prophete &thorn;at euyl prestis ben cause of fallynge of &thorn;e peple, alle manere men ben bounde to amende &thorn;is defaute; for ellis &thorn;ei stonden not in goddis hestis ne charite. &amp; here-fore gregory sei&thorn; &thorn;at no man harme&thorn; more cristis<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Gregory.]</NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000123.tif" N="57"> chirche &thorn;an he &thorn;at ha&thorn; &thorn;e name of ordre &amp; holynesse and &thorn;er-wi&thorn; lyueth euele, for comunly no man reproue&thorn; hym, &amp; men taken gretly ensaumple of his synne; &amp; &thorn;erfore crist purgid &thorn;e temple with his owen hondis, as &thorn;e gospel telli&thorn;, in<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; X.</NOTE> tokene &thorn;at &yogh;if prestis weren good &thorn;e peple schulde sone be amendid. &amp; for &thorn;is skille trewe men seyn &thorn;at prelatis ben more bounden to preche trewely &thorn;e gospel &thorn;an &thorn;es sugetis ben holden to paie here dymes, for god chargi&thorn; &thorn;at more, and &thorn;at is more profitable to bo&thorn;e parties &amp; more esy. And &thorn;erfore prelatis ben more cursed to cesse of &thorn;is prechynge &thorn;anne &thorn;e sugetis &yogh;if &thorn;ei cessen to paye ti&thorn;es; &yogh;e, whanne here prelatis don wel here offis. &para; Also prelatis ben more bounden to &thorn;is prechynge, for &thorn;at is comaundement of crist bifore his de&thorn; &amp; eke aftir, &thorn;an to seie matynes, masse, euen song, or placebo, for &thorn;at is mannus ordynaunce; &thorn;anne si&thorn; prelatis ben not wor&thorn;i to haue dymes &amp; offrynges &yogh;if &thorn;ei don not matynes, masse &amp; o&thorn;er mannes ordeynyngis, moche more &yogh;if &thorn;ei don not &thorn;is he&yogh;e ordynaunce of god; &amp; here-fore sei&thorn; crist, &yogh;if &thorn;e salt be fonnyd it is not worthi ouer &thorn;is, but &yogh;if it be to be cast out &amp; be defoulid of men; &thorn;at is &yogh;if prelatis<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Matt. v. 13.]</NOTE> failen of good lif &amp; techynge, &thorn;ei moten be &thorn;us seruyd of men, for &yogh;if men vnder hem knowe &thorn;is defaute &amp; may amenden it &amp; don not, &thorn;ei consenten &amp; meyntenen hem in &thorn;is grete synne.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 2<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P><MILESTONE N="67" UNIT="page">Also prelatis letten men to do goddis wille &amp; comaunde|ment, &amp; so &thorn;ei neden hem to be dampnyd, &amp; letten many to here goddis lawe; for prelatis letten &amp; forbeden prestis to preche &thorn;e gospel in here iurdiccion or bischope-riche, but &yogh;if &thorn;ei han leue &amp; letteris of hem; &amp; &yogh;it god comaunde&thorn; &amp; chargi&thorn; alle his<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;es X.</NOTE> prestis to preche freely the gospel. for alle cristis apostlis &amp; disciplis weren chargid to preche &thorn;e gospel, &amp; alle prestis ordeyned of god comen o&thorn;er in staat of apostlis or disciplis of crist, as bede &amp; &thorn;e popis lawe sei&thorn;; &thorn;anne 
<PB REF="00000124.tif" N="58"> alle prestis ben chargid to preche &thorn;e gospel. Also god sei&thorn; be &thorn;e prophete, &thorn;at lippis of a prest kepen kunnynge of<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Malachi ii. 7.]</NOTE> goddis lawe, &amp; men seken the lawe of his mou&thorn;, for he is an aungel of &thorn;e lord of compaynes. an aungel is a messager, &thorn;anne si&thorn; &thorn;e prest generaly is a messager of god he mot schewe his message, &thorn;at is &thorn;e gospel, in whiche is perfitly teld goddis wille; and gregory vpon &thorn;e gospel proue&thorn; wel &thorn;at eche prest mot preche, haue he litel kunnynge or moche. &para; Also gregory sei&thorn; in &thorn;e popis lawe, &thorn;at who euere come&thorn; to prestod taki&thorn; &thorn;e office of a bedele or criere to goo bi-fore &thorn;e dredful doom<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> of god; and<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> as in &thorn;e olde lawe &thorn;e prest schulde die &yogh;if he ne entrid in-to a sanctuarie wi&thorn;-outen noyse, so in &thorn;e lawe of grace &yogh;if a prest be doumb of &thorn;e prechynge he stere&thorn; goddis wrat&thorn;e vpon hym. &amp; si&thorn; men ben gretly cursid &thorn;at don a&yogh;enst &thorn;e popis lawe, as men seyn, &amp; &thorn;is is a grete popis lawe, groundid on goddis lawe &amp; reson &amp; charite, moche more ben &thorn;ei cursed &thorn;at don a&yogh;enst &thorn;is lawe. &para; Also ierom sei&thorn; &thorn;at prestis owen to preche bifore bischopis, &amp; &thorn;ei owen to be glad &thorn;erof for &thorn;at is here worschipe. &para; Also austyn in a sermon sei&thorn; &thorn;at eche man is holden to teche &thorn;e good &thorn;at he can; &yogh;e, &thorn;ou&yogh; he kunne litel. &para; Also it is a gret werk of mercy to teche men &thorn;e ri&yogh;tte weie to heuene, &amp; eche man is holden bi comaundement of god to do werkis of mercy; &thorn;an is eche prest holden to teche &thorn;e gospel, &thorn;at is &thorn;e ri&yogh;t weie to heuene. &para; Also in &thorn;e holde lawe a man is holde to brynge &thorn;e beste of his enemye in-to &thorn;e ry&yogh;tte weie;<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Exodus xxiii. 4.]</NOTE> moche more is a man holden to brynge his bro&thorn;eres soulis out of synne in-to good weie to heuene ward. And bi &thorn;is reson alle cristis enemyes weren stoppid to speke a&yogh;enst him<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Mark iii. 4.]</NOTE> whanne he helid a sik man vpon &thorn;e sabaat day, as &thorn;e gospel telli&thorn;. &para; Also &thorn;at riche man is out of charite &thorn;at helpi&thorn; not his bro&thorn;er in bodely nede, &yogh;if he may wel, as ioon &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">[1 John iii. 17.]</NOTE> euaungelist sei&thorn;; myche more is a man nedid bi charite to releue his bro&thorn;eres soule out of myschif of synne, &yogh;if he haue kunnynge of goddis lawe. &para; Also men demen <MILESTONE N="68" UNIT="page">it a grete 
<PB REF="00000125.tif" N="59"> charite to saue a mannus bodi fro de&thorn; or dryncchyng; it is moche more charite to saue mennus soulis fro de&thorn; of synne &amp; of helle bi trewe prechynge of goddis lawe. &para; A lord, what deuelis blyndnesse and cursednesse is &thorn;is, whanne &thorn;e prelat or curat is chargid of god, vp peyne of his owen dampnacion, to teche &thorn;e gospel &amp; comaundementis of god to alle his sugetis, &amp; here-wi&thorn; can not teche &thorn;us, or may not for worldly bisynesse, or wole not for idelnesse or negligence, &thorn;an to lette o&thorn;ere to preche frely &thorn;e gospel of crist &amp; saue mennus soulis; but &thorn;anne &thorn;ei senden o&thorn;ere, &thorn;at tellen lesyngis, fablis, &amp; cronyclis, &amp; robben &thorn;e peple bi fals beggyngis, &amp; dore not telle hem here grete synnes &amp; auoutrie <SUP>1</SUP>lest &thorn;ei<SUP>1</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">1_1 omitted X.</NOTE> lesen wynnynge or frendischipe. &para; Certis he were a cruel fadir &thorn;at my&yogh;tte not &yogh;eue his owene childre bred &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei perischeden for hunger, &amp; &yogh;it wolde not suffre ano&thorn;er man to helpe &thorn;es children bi weie of mercy; but moche more cruel ben &thorn;es prelatis &amp; curatis, &thorn;at kunnen not or may not or wolen not &yogh;eue here gostly children gostly bred of &thorn;e gospel, &thorn;ou&yogh; here soulis ben in neuere so gret myschef, &amp; &yogh;it forbeden &amp; cursen o&thorn;ere men &yogh;if &thorn;ei wolen for mercy &yogh;eue here bre&thorn;er techyng of goddis lawe, bo&thorn;e treuly &amp; frely, with-outen beggynge as crist biddi&thorn;. &para; It seme&thorn; &thorn;at syche prelatis &amp; newe religious ben a-ferd of cristis gospel, for it approue&thorn; not but distroie&thorn; worldly lordschipe of prelatis &amp; feyned holynesse of newe religious; si&thorn; cristis religion &thorn;at he made for prestis is &thorn;e beste, most perfyt, most esy, &amp; most siker. And oure ih&umacr; wolde haue no worse religion in prestis &thorn;an &thorn;at &thorn;at he made himself. &para; Also it seme&thorn; &thorn;at sich iurdic|cion of prelatis, &thorn;at &thorn;us letten cristis gospel, dryuen awey god fro mannus soule, &amp; vertuous lif &amp; charite, &amp; brynge&thorn; &thorn;e fend in, and cherischi&thorn; hym &amp; synnes &amp; debatis &amp; werris. ne&thorn;eles men supposen &thorn;at newe religious han leue of worldly prelatis to preche here fablis and lesyngis &amp; to robbe &thorn;e pore peple bi beggyng, vpon this condiccion, &thorn;at &thorn;ei preche not spedily a&yogh;enst symonye, extorsions &amp; o&thorn;ere orible synnes of false 
<PB REF="00000126.tif" N="60"> prelatis, &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;ei &yogh;eue &thorn;es worldly prelatis gold in gret quantite, &thorn;at &thorn;ei robben of pore men. &para; And &thorn;us &thorn;es worldly prelatis dampnen hem self &thorn;es newe religious, hem self, &amp; also o&thorn;ere prestis &thorn;at wolden preche &thorn;e gospel trewely &amp; frely as moche as in hem is, and &thorn;e peple also; si&thorn; &thorn;ei suffren not &thorn;e peple to here goddis word frely, but lesyngis, fablis, and &thorn;erto to<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> be robbid, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;es prelatis ben procuratours of &thorn;e fend, enemyes of crist, &amp; traitours to <NOTE PLACE="foot">of X.</NOTE>his peple.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="3" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 3<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also comunly prelatis ben false prophetis &amp; heretikis, for &thorn;ei indede <MILESTONE N="69" UNIT="page">seyn heresie &amp; techen a&yogh;enst ih&umacr; crist &amp; his apostlis; for a&yogh;enst cristis wilful pouert &thorn;ei techen in dede worldly coueitise &amp; moche wast in worldly goodis, &amp; a&yogh;enst cristis mekenesse &thorn;ei techen in-dede pompe &amp; pride of &thorn;e world &amp; of here statis, and a&yogh;en cristis bysynesse in prechynge &amp; preieyng &amp; traueile bi contrees &thorn;ei techen in-dede vanyte &amp; idelnesse, &amp; ben &yogh;euen to glotonye &amp; worldly bisynesse, &amp; haunten courtis of lordis &amp; worldly plees, &amp; ben doumb fro &thorn;e gospel &amp; tellen here owen lawis to magnyfie here power &amp; pride &amp; coueitise, &amp; couchen in castelis as lordis; &amp; wi&thorn; all &thorn;is &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at cristis &amp; his apostlis lif &amp; here proude lif acorden, &amp; seyn &thorn;at &thorn;ei lyuen as crist &amp; his apostlis diden.</P>
<P>&para; A lord! si&thorn; prelatis comen in stede of apostlis, hou may &thorn;ei for schame lyue so contrariously a&yogh;enst here pore lif, in wast seruauntis, in grete fatte hors &amp; nedles, in shynyng vessel, in gret aray of clo&thorn;is; &yogh;e, more &thorn;an many grete lordis. certis in ensaumple of here lif &thorn;ei techen errour a&yogh;enst crist &amp; his apostlis, si&thorn; &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at &thorn;ei suen crist and apostlis in manere of lyuynge. O lord! what tokene of mekenesse &amp; forsakynge of worldly richesses is &thorn;is; a prelat as an abott or a priour, &thorn;at is ded to &thorn;e world &amp; pride &amp; vanyte &thorn;er-of, to ride wi&thorn; foure score hors, wi&thorn; harneis of siluer &amp; gold, &amp; many raggid &amp; fittrid squyeris &amp; o&thorn;ere men swerynge herte &amp; bonys &amp; nailis &amp; o&thorn;ere membris of crist, &amp; to spende 
<PB REF="00000127.tif" N="61"> wi&thorn; erlis &amp; barons &amp; here pore tenauntis bo&thorn;e &thorn;ousand markis &amp; poundes to meyntene a false plee of &thorn;e world, &amp; forbarre men of here ri&yogh;t. &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;es ypocritis seyn &thorn;at &thorn;is is worschipe of holy chirche, but certis &thorn;ei lien, but &yogh;if &thorn;ei clepen be contrarie name &thorn;e deuelis chirche to be holy chirche, as &thorn;ei clepen hem self men of religion &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;ei forsaken &thorn;e world; but certis &thorn;ei distroien holy religion &amp; magnyfien veyn religion, of whiche seynt Iames speki&thorn;, &amp; forsaken traueile &amp; peyne &amp; dissese of &thorn;e world, &amp; han lordschipis, rentis, gaie houses &amp; costy, &amp; welfare of mete &amp; drynk, &thorn;ere &thorn;ei my&yogh;tten vnne&thorn;e before haue bene-bred &amp; watir or feble ale. &yogh;e, wi&thorn; moche care &amp; traueile now vnne&thorn;e ony mete<NOTE PLACE="foot">nite X.</NOTE> or wyn may serue &amp; plese hem, but likerousnesse &amp; lustis of here bely han now alle &thorn;e bisinessis, and deuocion &amp; holynesse &amp; penaunce litel or ri&yogh;t nou&yogh;t. Of &thorn;is veyn pride of religious it seme&thorn; wel &thorn;ei ben not bok of cristis pouert &amp; holynesse, as &thorn;ei seye in here wordis, but bok of pride, coueitise, vanyte &amp; o&thorn;ere synnes, to disceit<NOTE PLACE="foot">dissect X.</NOTE> of goddis peple &amp; distroiynge of his lawe. &para; harde crie&thorn; seynt bernard a&yogh;enst pompous prelatis &amp; axe&thorn; hem &thorn;us: &yogh;ee<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;e X.</NOTE> prelatis, what do&thorn; gold in &yogh;oure bridelis &amp; o&thorn;ere araies, where it kepe hem fro cold; we perischen for hunger <MILESTONE N="70" UNIT="page"> and cold, seyn pore men, oure goodis &thorn;ei ben &thorn;at &yogh;e wasten from vs, &thorn;ei ben drawen cruelly a&yogh;enst mercy, &amp; &thorn;us &yogh;ee<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;ei X.</NOTE> don tweie euele &thorn;ingis, on for &yogh;oure pride &amp; wast of pore mennus goodis &yogh;e gon to helle, And we pore men perischen in &thorn;is world for &yogh;oure vanyte &amp; pride. &amp; si&thorn; &thorn;e lif of prelatis is bok &amp; ensaumple of sugetis, as grosted sei&thorn; wi&thorn; many moo, &amp; &thorn;ei lyuen so opynly in pride, coueitise &amp; idelnesse, passynge alle o&thorn;ere, &thorn;ei ben open heretikis &amp; stronge, &thorn;at han no schame of here heresie, for heresie in fals lif meyntened is werse &thorn;an heresie only in herte or wordis, and for sclaundere &thorn;at &thorn;ei &yogh;euen to o&thorn;ere men bi here cursed lif god him self curse&thorn; hem in &thorn;e gospel &amp; sei&thorn; &thorn;us: who to &thorn;at man bi whom come&thorn; a sclaundre, &thorn;at is ensaumple to do synne, it spedi&thorn; to him &thorn;at a mylneston of 
<PB REF="00000128.tif" N="62"> assis be hangid in his necke, &amp; &thorn;at he be dreynt in-to<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Matt. xviii. 6.]</NOTE> depnesse of &thorn;e see. &thorn;at is, sei&thorn; gregory, it spedi&thorn; to euyl prelatis &thorn;at &yogh;euen ensaumpele of synne to here sugetis &thorn;at &thorn;ei weren in lowere staat of worldly labour &amp; &thorn;er-wi&thorn; wer dampnyd to depe helle; for &thorn;an &thorn;ei schulden haue lesse peyne &thorn;an to lyue<NOTE PLACE="foot">leve X.</NOTE> euele in &thorn;e he&yogh;e staat &amp; teche o&thorn;ere men do synne, for &thorn;ei ben wor&thorn;i as many de&thorn;es as &thorn;ei &yogh;euen euyle ensaumples of synne to here sugetis. But lord, who is nowe so coueitous abouten worldly lordschipis &amp; temporal goodis as oure prelatis, for comunly alle here visitacion, alle here sacramentis and ordris &yogh;euynge &amp; halwynge of placis &amp; vesty|mentis &amp; blissyng is don<NOTE PLACE="foot">ben X.</NOTE> for coueitise &amp; worldly pride &amp; dignyte; alle here preue spekyng &amp; prechyng &amp; techyng in scolis is for coueitise &amp; magnyfyynge of here worldly staat: who is more idel in goddis seruyce, more in glotonye &amp; wastynge of pore mennus goodis in schynynge vesselis &amp; o&thorn;ere costis? &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ei preien, &thorn;at is wi&thorn;-outen deuocion to plese &thorn;e peple, &amp; comunly for offrynge, &amp; cotidian distri|bucion, &amp; stynkyng lif of lecherie, robberie, pride, coueitise, glotonye; &thorn;at &thorn;ei ra&thorn;ere stiren god to wra&thorn;e &amp; vengaunce &thorn;an to mercy &amp; pite, as goddis lawe, austyn &amp; gregory &amp; o&thorn;ere seyntis witnessen. but, lord, si&thorn; heresie stondi&thorn; most in cursed lif, were ben more heretikes, si&thorn; &thorn;ei ben most synful in opyn &amp; preuy cursed lyuynge; but where schal ony be deppere dampnyd in helle?</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="4" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 4<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Prelatis also robben &thorn;e pore lige men of &thorn;e king bi fals extorisions taken bi colour of holy correccion, &amp; &yogh;euen men leue to dwellen in synne fro &yogh;er to &yogh;er, fro seuene &yogh;er to seuene &yogh;er, &amp; comunly al here lif, &yogh;if &thorn;ei paien bi &yogh;ere twenti shillyngis or more or lesse, and &thorn;us bi sutilte of sathanas &thorn;ei han <MILESTONE N="71" UNIT="page">founde newe peynes orible &amp; schameful to make men paye a gret raunson, to &yogh;eue gold &amp; ba&thorn;e hem in lustis of synne as swyn in feen. And men seyn &thorn;at summe bischopis 
<PB REF="00000129.tif" N="63"> geti&thorn; in o yer two &thorn;ousand mark or poundis; &amp; &yogh;if he laste twenty &yogh;eer bischop wi&thorn; &thorn;is robberie, It wole come to sixti &thorn;ousand mark &thorn;at he robbi&thorn; of &thorn;e kingis lige men. &para; And &thorn;us &thorn;es wickede prelatis sillen cristene mennus soulis to sathanas for money, for whiche soulis crist schedde his precious herte blod vpon &thorn;e cros. And here-fore &thorn;ei ben worse &thorn;an iudas for many skillis, for &thorn;ei sillen crist in a manere as iudas dide wi&thorn; more dispit &amp; more stynkynge coueitise, &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ei hiren lordis to meyntene hem in &thorn;is cursednesse, &amp; &yogh;eue pore mennus goodis to hem for &thorn;is ende, &amp; hiren also iurrouris &amp; o&thorn;ere gentil men of contre to forswere hem wyttyngly on &thorn;e bok &amp; not to putten hem vp for extorsioneris &amp; &thorn;eues; &amp; whanne &thorn;ei schulden be principal dukis in crist oost to fi&yogh;tte &amp; teche o&thorn;ere men bi here ensaumple to fy&yogh;tte a&yogh;enst synnes, as false traitouris &thorn;ei turnen &thorn;e bak &amp; techene cristene men to offre hem redy to &thorn;e deuelys sacrifice. a pore man &thorn;ei constreynem to synne bi manas, chydyng &amp; losse of catel &amp; sclaundrynge, but &yogh;if he wolen consente to hem &amp; fauoure hem in here wrong lif; &amp; &yogh;if he wol do so, &thorn;anne he is an holy sone, &amp; ha&thorn; &yogh;iftis &amp; worldly frendischipe &amp; fauour &amp; anticristis false blissyng &amp; goddis trewe curs. And &thorn;ei flatren lordis whanne &thorn;ei meyntenen &thorn;es anticristis prelatis to robbe here tenauntis, &amp; seyn &thorn;ei worschipen &thorn;anne god &amp; holy chirche, &amp; &yogh;euen lordis grete &yogh;iftis of gold &amp; iuelis &amp; pardons, &amp; licence to synge in oratories &amp; o&thorn;ere veyn &thorn;ingis, and &yogh;if lordis wolen distroie &thorn;es synnes of robberie &amp; sathanas marchaundise, &thorn;anne anticristis prelatis wolen sclaundren hem, curse hem, &amp; entirdite hem &amp; here londis.<NOTE PLACE="foot">here lordis X.</NOTE> And &thorn;us alle men ben conquerid to &thorn;e fend almost, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;es cursed pilatis not prelatis ben verray anticristis, procuratours of sathanas, &amp; traitours of ih&umacr; crist &amp; his peple.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="5" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000130.tif" N="64">
<HEAD>Capitulum 5<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis comunly ben symonyentis in here entre, in processe of here benefis, &amp; in &thorn;e ende of here lif, &amp; &thorn;anne in alle &thorn;es tymes &thorn;ei ben heretikis, so &thorn;at alle o&thorn;ere synnes ben holden for nou&yogh;t in comparison of &thorn;is symonye, as &thorn;e beste part of &thorn;e popis lawe sei&thorn;. for, as gregory &amp; &thorn;e popis lawe sei&thorn;, in &thorn;re maneres is symonye don. First whanne a man come&thorn; to a benefis of &thorn;e chirche bi &yogh;ifte of money or worldly goodis bi hym self or bi o&thorn;ere menes. &para; &THORN;e secunde tyme whanne a man come&thorn; &thorn;er-to bi preiere of lordis or ladies or o&thorn;ere men more than for kunnynge <MILESTONE N="72" UNIT="page">of goddis lawe &amp; holy lif. &para; &thorn;e &thorn;ride tyme whanne a man come&thorn; &thorn;er-to bi worldly seruyce of lordis &amp; ladies, of prelatis, or o&thorn;ere my&yogh;tty men more &thorn;anne for good lif and kunnynge; but who come&thorn; hellis to prelacie? &amp; in processe &thorn;ei mys|penden pore mennus goodis, in wast metis &amp; festis of ryche men &amp; pride of &thorn;is world, &amp; don not here office comunly ne&thorn;ere in good lif ne trewe prechynge, &amp; resignen not here benefis goten &thorn;us by symonye; &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;ei moten algatis do &yogh;if &thorn;ei schullen be saaf vp &thorn;e popis lawe, &amp; neuere in wille to hauen it a&yogh;en but &yogh;if it be bi ri&yogh;t title, &amp; algatis confirma|cion of god bi titel of grace is nedeful to hem. And &thorn;at come&thorn; not but bi verray repentaunce of synne don bi-fore, &amp; bi trewe lif &amp; techynge &amp; meyntenynge of goddis lawe vpon here kunnynge &amp; my&yogh;t. &amp; in here endynge &thorn;ei han not comunly ful contricion for here synnes, as for myspen|dynge of pore mennus goodis, for false extorsions, for sillyng of sacramentis, for norischynge &amp; meyntenynge of o&thorn;ere men in synne, as pride, coueitise, &amp; glotonye &amp; alle o&thorn;ere: for &yogh;if &thorn;ei hadden &thorn;anne contricion &thorn;ei schulden restore &thorn;es wickid extorsions vp here my&yogh;t, &amp; warne o&thorn;ere men of &thorn;e synnes in whiche &thorn;ei hadden norischeden hem; but &thorn;is come&thorn; seldom or neuere, &amp; &thorn;erfore it seme&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ei dien heretikis but &yogh;if god helpe more in the laste poynt of partynge of &thorn;e soule &amp; body, &amp; ellis &thorn;ei dien dampnyd 
<PB REF="00000131.tif" N="65"> fendis of helle. &para; But lordis &amp; ladies here mosten ben wel war, for &yogh;if &thorn;ei &yogh;euen benefis to clerkis fore here worldly seruyces, princypali as for kechene clerkis &amp; countyngge or daunsynge, for palfreis or keuercheris, gold or o&thorn;er worldly seruyce, it is foul symonye &amp; cursed on bo&thorn;e parties, as goddis lawe and &thorn;e chirche &amp; holy seyntis techen. &para; And also &yogh;if &thorn;ei &yogh;euen a benefis for men ben of here kyn, or for fleschly loue, or worldly frendischipe, or ellis for &thorn;e clerk<NOTE PLACE="foot">celrk X.</NOTE> is manly to &thorn;e lord in gay clo&thorn;inge, in grete festis, gret archerie, or ony o&thorn;ere veyn iapis more &thorn;an for &thorn;e worschipe of god &amp; profit of mannes soule, it is stynkynge symonye bi-fore god, as lawes and seyntis techen. &para; And here ben &thorn;re poyntis of treson to god &amp; his peple; &thorn;e first is &thorn;at lordes &amp; ladies ben tratours &thorn;at holden curatis in worldly offices fro &thorn;e soulis &thorn;at &thorn;ei han cure of; for god &yogh;eue&thorn; hym lordi|schipis &amp; presentyngge of chirchis to meyntene goddis lawe &amp; help trewe prestis to teche his peple &thorn;e gospel &amp; maunde|mentis of god, &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ei holden wi&thorn; goddis tresour curatis in here worldly seruyce or chapellis, &amp; letten hem to kepe cristene soulis, &thorn;e whiche crist bou&yogh;t wi&thorn; his precious blod, &thorn;ei ben foul traitours to <MILESTONE N="73" UNIT="page">ih&umacr; crist &amp; to &thorn;e peple &thorn;at &thorn;ei disceyuen &thorn;us; but &yogh;it more treson is in clerkis &thorn;at coueiten &amp; taken &thorn;is worldli office wi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> cure of cristene soulis and may not do hem to-gedre, for &thorn;ei schulden teche &thorn;e lordis &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of goddis lawe &amp; also &thorn;e peril in &thorn;is poynt, &amp; don nou&yogh;t, for ope of grettere benefices or for flaterynge of here lordschipe; but the moost tratourie of alle stondi&thorn; in fals confessouris, &thorn;at schulden telle &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of goddis lawe &amp; don not for lesynge of worldly lordischipe, frendeschipe, fauour or worldly wynnyng, bo&thorn;e of &thorn;e lord &amp; his meyne &amp; of &thorn;e false curat &thorn;er-to; &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;e lord or the lady hire&thorn; costly a fals iudas to his confessour, &thorn;at suffri&thorn; him &amp; ledi&thorn; him &thorn;e hei&yogh;e weie to helle. &para; Also prelatis ben ful of symonye whanne &thorn;ei mynystren here sacramentis or ony gostly office for money or &thorn;ank or preiynge of men of &thorn;e world or for 
<PB REF="00000132.tif" N="66"> ony worldly seruyce. For crist bidde&thorn; hem &yogh;eue al &thorn;is frely as &thorn;ei taken it freely of god, &amp; &thorn;e prophete sei&thorn; he is blissed &thorn;at kepi&thorn; his hondis clene fro alle manere &yogh;ifte, &amp; he is cursed &thorn;at do&thorn; &thorn;e werk of god wi&thorn; necgligence or fraude. &para; And it is a foul fraude to [do] &thorn;is gostly office for worldly reward or for &thorn;anke or preisynge of synful men, whanne &thorn;ei schulden do it for goddis worschipe frely &amp; hel&thorn;e of mannus soule. &para; But &yogh;it symonye of &thorn;e court of rome do&thorn; most harm, for it is most comune &amp; vnder most colour of holynesse, &amp; robbi&thorn; most oure lond of men &amp; tresour; for alle nacions of this cristendom rennen &thorn;ider as to welle of trew&thorn;e and gostly helpe, &amp; &thorn;ei ben most disceyued, for &thorn;ei wenen &thorn;at &thorn;ere is no symonye for holynesse of &thorn;e court of rome. &amp; many kunnynge men &amp; able ben dede bi &thorn;e weie, what wi&thorn; traueile &amp; cold &amp; o&thorn;ere myschefis &amp; enemyes, &amp; ofte raunsonyd, &amp; beren out of &thorn;e lond moche gold to raunson, to spende bi &thorn;e weie&yogh;e; &yogh;e to spende at rome many &yogh;eris &amp; daies, to paie for selis or bullis, to plede for benefices, offryngyus, dymes, &amp; many mo causes, to paie &thorn;e pope &thorn;e first froytys, &amp; cardy|nals &amp; bribouris to spede here nedis, &amp; for pardons, quyenals, priuylegies, for assoilyngis of wowes, &amp; many feyned iapis, &thorn;at men supposen alle &thorn;es passen &thorn;re fiften&thorn;es; &amp; alle go&thorn; out of owre lond comunly in-to enemys hondis, &amp; for al &thorn;is come&thorn; a litel ded lede, &amp; mayntenynge of false plee, &amp; strif, &amp; goddis curs, &amp; symonye, &amp; heresie. for &yogh;if it be symonye a clerk to serue a lord for a benefice &amp; &thorn;e lord to resceyue &thorn;er|fore gold or gold wor&thorn;, bi &thorn;e same skil it is symonye to serue &thorn;e pope in sich a straunge traueile and contre, &amp; &yogh;eue hym gold for his lede, &amp; &thorn;e frystefruytes for &yogh;ifte of a chirche; &amp; &yogh;it whanne a lord ha&thorn; &thorn;e gold for his presentynge &thorn;e gold dwelli&thorn; stille in <MILESTONE N="74" UNIT="page">oure lond, but whanne &thorn;e pope ha&thorn; &thorn;e furste fruytes &thorn;e gold go&thorn; out &amp; come&thorn; neuere a&yogh;en. And so for pardons, &yogh;if &thorn;ei ben ou&yogh;t wor&thorn;i &thorn;ei mosten be free, &amp; to take money for hem is to selle goddis grace and so symonye, &amp; &thorn;an bo&thorn;e parties ben cursed of god &amp; man; &amp; so anticrist ha&thorn; forbarrid &thorn;e fredom of goddis lawe in schriftis, masse, 
<PB REF="00000133.tif" N="67"> syngynge, &amp; o&thorn;ere deuocions &amp; taki&thorn; gold of men to brynge hom sum del to &thorn;is fredom, &amp; so robben hem bi ypocrisye as &yogh;if it were not leful to do profit to<NOTE PLACE="foot">of X.</NOTE> mennus soulis wi&thorn;-out dispensynge of anticrist. But now to schewe &thorn;e malice &amp; cursednesse of symonye; first, almy&yogh;tti god dampne&thorn; it in &thorn;e olde lawe, crist in &thorn;e gospel, &amp; is apostlis after &thorn;e sendynge of &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> holy gost; first, whanne &thorn;e wickid kyng ieroboam made false maunmetis &amp; stockis and worschipide hem for almy&yogh;tty god, bi-cause &thorn;at he selde &thorn;e prest-hode of &thorn;es false goddis for worldly &yogh;iftis god almy&yogh;tty distroied hym &amp; alle his seed. also, for giesy toke money &amp; clo&thorn;is of naaman whanne helise &thorn;e prophete his maistir hadde helid hym, &thorn;e leper of naaman cleuyd to hym &amp; his generacion euere aftir, in tokene &thorn;at gostly lepre, &thorn;at is heresie,<NOTE PLACE="foot">here ne, in both MSS.</NOTE> schulde dwelle wi&thorn; alle syche as taken <SUP>4</SUP>money or <SUP>4</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">4_4 omitted X.</NOTE>money wor&thorn; for gostly offices; &yogh;e, wi&thorn;-outen couenant makynge. also god sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e prophete malachie to &thorn;e iewis &thorn;at his wille is not to hem: "For &thorn;er nys noon &thorn;at shitti&thorn; frely &thorn;e doris of &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Malachi i. 10.</NOTE> temple." &thorn;anne god chargi&thorn; more &thorn;e betre offis as makynge of sacramentis &amp; &yogh;eeuynge of ordris, &thorn;at men plese hym not but &yogh;if &thorn;ei don hem frely. &para; Also crist in &thorn;e gospel drof out of &thorn;e temple hem &thorn;at selden &amp; bou&yogh;ten &thorn;er-inne, &yogh;ee, wi&thorn; his owen hondis, &thorn;at we reden not of many o&thorn;ere synful men &thorn;at he tok so moche vengaunce in his firste comynge, in tokene &thorn;at he scharpliest schal ponysche hem &thorn;at don symonye. Also petir seyde to symon magus; &thorn;i money be<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Acts viii. 20.]</NOTE> wi&thorn; &thorn;e in-to loos of dampnacion, for &thorn;ou gessedest to haue goddis &yogh;iftee &thorn;orou&yogh; money. &para; Also symonye is contrarie to al &thorn;e hole trinyte &amp; to eche persone &thorn;er-of; first to &thorn;e fadir, for whanne god wole not and may not brynge vnable men in-to benefices of &thorn;e chirche for his ri&yogh;twysnesse &amp; vnablete of hem self, &thorn;ei presumen to comen in bi symonye; as &yogh;if &thorn;e peny &amp; falsnesse of &thorn;e fend were more &thorn;an &thorn;e my&yogh;t of &thorn;e fadir of heuene. also ih&umacr; crist is dore bi whiche men schulde entre in-to offices &amp; benefices of &thorn;e chirche, &amp; 
<PB REF="00000134.tif" N="68"> symonyentis wolen come in bi ano&thorn;er weie of falsnesse, as &yogh;if &thorn;ei wolden putte awey ih&umacr; crist, &amp; be more maistris &amp; more witty &thorn;an he. Also symonyentis as <MILESTONE N="75" UNIT="page">myche as in hem is sellen &thorn;e holy gost, &amp; maken him &thorn;ral or bounden to synful men &amp; fendis, whanne &thorn;ei sillen &amp; biggen &thorn;us his &yogh;iftis; &amp; &thorn;erfore &thorn;ei ben worse heretikis &thorn;an &thorn;e cursed heretik arrian &amp; his secte &thorn;at made &thorn;e holy gost lesse in my&yogh;t &thorn;an &thorn;e fadir &amp; &thorn;e sone, &amp; seruant to hem bo&thorn;e as &thorn;e lawe sei&thorn;. For as &thorn;e synne of sodom was moost a&yogh;enst kynde &amp; so most synne in &thorn;o olde lawe, so is symonye as doctours seyn most a&yogh;enst grace &amp; most synne in &thorn;e lawe of grace. And &thorn;er-fore in &thorn;e popis lawe decrees &amp; decretals symony is generaly clepid heresie, &amp; orible peynes ordeyned a&yogh;enst men &thorn;at don symonye on ony manere bi hem self or o&thorn;ere mene persones, bi here wille &amp; consent, &amp; in sum cas hem vnwyttynge. &para; Also generaly prelatis regnen in symonye, as bischopis, munkis, chanons, &amp; freris, &amp; lesse curatis; for bischopis, munkis &amp; chanons sillen &thorn;e perfeccion of cristis pouert &amp; his apostlis, &amp; also trewe prechynge for a litil stynkyng muk or drit, &amp; worldli lordschipe, &amp; wombe ioie and idelnesse, &amp; freris forsaken &thorn;e perfit pouert of crist and his apostlis for pride of &thorn;e worldly staatis &amp; flaterynge &thorn;er-to and ypocrisie &amp; beggynge to geten esely &amp; plen|teuously catel of lordis &amp; ladies &amp; comunes, &amp; to geten &yogh;onge childre to here feyned ordre by symonye, as aplis, purses &amp; o&thorn;ere iapes &amp; false bihestis, &amp; bi false stelynge a&yogh;enst here frendis wille, and a&yogh;enst goddis comaundement. And lesse curatis forsaken holy lif &amp; trewe prechynge of crist &amp; his apostlis for bisynesse &amp; worschipe of &thorn;e world &amp; for glotonye &amp; drunkenesse &amp; lecherie; &amp; ofte bi open symonye comen to here benefices, &amp; dwellen stille in hem whanne &thorn;ei ben vnable to teche goddis lawe in word &amp; dede; &amp; &thorn;us symonye regne&thorn; in alle staatis of &thorn;e chirche, bo&thorn;e in statis groundid of crist &amp; in o&thorn;ere groundid of foolis as &yogh;if &thorn;ei weren statis of holy chirche, but &thorn;ei ben statis of &thorn;e wicked chirche brou&yogh;te in by lesyngis &amp; ypocrisie. 
<PB REF="00000135.tif" N="69"> And si&thorn; &thorn;e kyng &amp; lordis ben chargid of god to distroie &thorn;is synne &amp; o&thorn;ere, &amp; mowen don it &amp; don it not, &thorn;ei ben consenteris &amp; fautouris &thorn;er-of.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="6" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 6<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis halden &thorn;e halwynge of dede stonys or dede er&thorn;e &amp; o&thorn;ere ornamentis of &thorn;e chirche, as vestymentis, clo&thorn;is, chalis, &amp; oile, &amp; crem, more wor&thorn;i &thorn;an &thorn;e halwynge and blissynge of &thorn;e sacramentis of &thorn;e auter, &thorn;at is verray cristis flech &amp; his blood; &amp; so it seme&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ei holden dede stonys &amp; dede er&thorn;e &amp; roten clo&thorn;is more wor&thorn;i &thorn;an cristis owen precious body &amp; his blood. &para; For &thorn;ei holden to hem self halwynge of auter stonys, chirchis &amp; chirche &yogh;erdis &amp; o&thorn;ere clo&thorn;is of &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> chirche as more wor&thorn;i <MILESTONE N="76" UNIT="page">&amp; precious, &amp; suffren pore prestis, be &thorn;ei neuere so vnkunnynge and vicious anemtis god so &thorn;at &thorn;ei speke not a&yogh;enst &thorn;e synne of prelatis, to make &thorn;e sacrament of &thorn;e auter eche day, as &yogh;if &thorn;at were lesse wor&thorn;i &amp; lesse precious. &para; Also &thorn;ei wolen suffre an auter vnhalwedid, or a chirche or a chirche &yogh;erde suspendid &amp; no masse seyd &thorn;er-inne, &yogh;e fourtene ny&yogh;t, &yogh;e a mone&thorn;, &yogh;e longe ynow&thorn;, &yogh;if fourty pens ben bihynden of ten mark or ten pound; &amp; alle &thorn;is &thorn;ei taken bi extorsions, bi &thorn;efte &amp; symonye, &amp; hauen no mercy, be &thorn;e peple neuere so poer, neuere so nedy, &amp; neuere so deuout to here goddis <SUP>2</SUP>word or<SUP>2</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">2_2 omitted X.</NOTE> seruyce; but where ben worse tirauntis &amp; heretikis? &amp; &thorn;us in alle here dedis of gostly offices &thorn;ei cursen hem self &amp; &thorn;e peple also, for &thorn;ei don not &thorn;at &thorn;at longi&thorn; to here office for stynkynge symonye, &amp; maken &thorn;e peple to consente &amp; meynteyne here synne of symonye &amp; heresie, for &thorn;ei don many sotil menys, as graunten pardon &amp; here feyned blissyng to halwyng of chirchis, to make &thorn;e peple wilful to bere hem vp in here synne. &para; And &yogh;if ony man for drede of god &amp; his conscience a&yogh;enstonde &thorn;is extorsion and robberie &amp; symonye he schal be rebukid, dispised, sumned, cursed, lese his catel &amp; in cas 
<PB REF="00000136.tif" N="70"> his bodi to prison or to de&thorn;, &amp; sumtyme be in hate, in strif &amp; enuye, &amp; ful of his wrecchid lif. &amp; &yogh;if he consente wilfully to &thorn;is foule symonye &thorn;anne he is dede in synne, as poul sei&thorn;, &amp; &yogh;if he a&yogh;enstonde it, what bi cautelis of anticrist &amp; malice of &thorn;e fend, he schal be tourmentid bi wra&thorn;&thorn;e &amp; vnpacience &amp; traueile &amp; peyne of his bodi &amp; loos of his catel, &thorn;at vnne&thorn;is schal he be sauyd but nedid to be dampnyd; &amp; &thorn;us it seme&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ei &thorn;at schulden be most principal helperis to cristene mennus soulis &thorn;ei ben most principal procuratours of &thorn;e fend to encombre hem in synne. and &yogh;it it seme&thorn; &thorn;at oure goode god kepi&thorn; &thorn;es veyn offices &amp; feyned sacramentis fro his pore prestis &thorn;at &thorn;ei gon not &thorn;e brode weie to helle for mysusynge of hem.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="7" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 7<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Prelatis also setten more pris bi a litel styngynge<NOTE PLACE="foot">stynkynge AA.</NOTE> drit of worldly goodis &thorn;an &thorn;ei don bi &thorn;e moste holy gospel of ih&umacr; crist; for &thorn;e grete bysynesse &thorn;at &thorn;ei han abouten worldly goodis &amp; &thorn;e litel traueile &amp; studyyng abouten cristis gospel prouen wel &thorn;at &thorn;ei louen more &thorn;is worldly muk &thorn;an &thorn;e gospel of ih&umacr; crist; for &thorn;e dede doynge is proff of loue, as gregory sei&thorn;, &amp; here-fore &thorn;ei preisen &amp; techyn mannus lawis &amp; here owen tradiciouns to gete &thorn;e peny by, but &thorn;ei leuen &amp; dispisen &thorn;e gospel &amp; letten it to be prechid, for &thorn;e gospel techi&thorn; &thorn;e holy lif of crist &amp; his apostlis &amp; dampne&thorn; &thorn;e cursed lif of &thorn;es worldly prelatis, &amp; &thorn;ei commaunden &thorn;at no man schal <MILESTONE N="77" UNIT="page"> preche &thorn;e gospel but at here wille &amp; lymytacion, &amp; forbeden men to here &thorn;e gospel vp peyne of &thorn;e grete curs. but sathanas in his owne persone durste neuere do so myche dispit to crist &amp; his gospel, for he aleid holy writt to crist &amp; wolde haue proued his entente &thorn;er-bi. &amp; si&thorn; it is cristis conseil &amp; comaundement to prestis generaly to preche &thorn;e gospel, and &thorn;is &thorn;ei moten not do wi&thorn;-outen leue of &thorn;es prelatis, &thorn;at in cas ben fendis of helle, &thorn;anne 
<PB REF="00000137.tif" N="71"> prestis may not do cristis conseilis &amp; hestis wi&thorn;-outen leue of fendis. A, lord ih&umacr;! for &thorn;es synful foolis, &amp; in cas fendis of helle, ben more my&yogh;tti &amp; witti &thorn;an &thorn;ou, &thorn;at trewe men may not do &thorn;e wille wi&thorn;-outen auctorite of siche fendis. &para; A, lord god almy&yogh;tty, al witti &amp; alle ful of charite, hou longe wilt &thorn;ou suffre &thorn;es anticristis to dispise &thorn;e in &thorn;yn holy gospel &amp; lette &thorn;e hel&thorn;e of cristene mennus soulis? Endeles ri&yogh;tful lord, &thorn;is &thorn;ou suffredest for synne generaly regnynge among &thorn;e peple, but endeles mercyful &amp; goode lord, helpe &thorn;i pore wrecchide prestis &amp; seruauntis to fore &thorn;i peple to haue loue, drede &amp; reuerence to &thorn;i gospel, &amp; lette not to do &thorn;i worschipe &amp; wille for fals ferynge of anticristis &amp; fendis of helle. &para; Almy&yogh;tti lord god and merciful &amp; endeles witty, si&thorn; &thorn;ou suffredest petir &amp; alle apostlis<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> to haue so grete drede &amp; cowardise in tyme of &thorn;i passion &thorn;at &thorn;ei flowen alle awey for drede of de&thorn; And for a litel pore wommannus vois, and aftirward by confort of &thorn;e holy gost madist hem so stronge &thorn;at &thorn;ei weren afferd of no man, no peyne ne de&thorn;; helpe nowe bi &yogh;eftis of &thorn;e same holy gost &thorn;i pore seruauntis &thorn;at al &thorn;er lif han ben cowardis, &amp; make hem stronge &amp; bolde in &thorn;e cause to meyntene &thorn;i gospel a&yogh;enst anticristis &amp; tirauntis of &thorn;is world. &amp; graunte grace to oure lordis alle to meyntene &thorn;i gospel &amp; &thorn;in ordynaunce, &amp; specialy to seke &thorn;i worschipe &amp; my&yogh;ttily distroie synne; for to &thorn;is office &thorn;ou hast ordeyned lordis. &para; Almy&yogh;tti lord, it seme&thorn; nowe to <NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> foolis of this world &thorn;at &thorn;i cause is ouere|comen and anticrist ha&thorn; &thorn;e victorie, &amp; pore men, lord, doren not abide &thorn;i seruyce; but now lord, for glorie of &thorn;in owe name, &amp; for sauynge of cristene soulis whom &thorn;ou bou&yogh;ttest wi&thorn; &thorn;in precious herte blood, &amp; for distroynge of boost &amp; pride of anticrist &amp; his &thorn;at now ben so hei&yogh;e &amp; my&yogh;tty, graunte &thorn;i seruauntes grace to laste trewe in &thorn;e gospel &amp; preche it trewely in word &amp; dede; &amp; &thorn;i lordis to meyntene it styfly a&yogh;enst anticristis clerkis; &amp; &thorn;i comunes, lorde, to kepe &thorn;in hestis &amp; knowe anticristis 
<PB REF="00000138.tif" N="72"> disceit, &amp; clenly take &thorn;i gospel in reuerence &amp; lette not for false drede of anticrist &amp; o&thorn;ere fendis. so be it, lord.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="8" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 8<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis setten more pris bi &thorn;e roten peny &thorn;anne &thorn;ei don bi &thorn;e precious blood of ih&umacr; crist, for &thorn;e ende of schedynge of <MILESTONE N="78" UNIT="page"> cristis bloode was to saue mannus soulis &amp; it was pris for hem; &thorn;anne as &thorn;ei louen more &thorn;e roten peny &thorn;anne &thorn;e sauynge of cristene soulis, so &thorn;ei louen more &thorn;e roten peney &thorn;an &thorn;e blood of ih&umacr; crist, &amp; in tokene &thorn;er-of &thorn;ei ben besy bo&thorn;e ny&yogh;t &amp; day to gete &thorn;e &thorn;eny wi&thorn; falsnesse, cautelis &amp; tirauntrie, but of mennus soulis is left care; &yogh;if &thorn;e peny fayle &thorn;ei ben woode for wra&thorn;&thorn;e &amp; sorowe, &yogh;if mennus soulis gon to helle bi brekynge of goddis comaundementis no warde, so &thorn;at &thorn;e peny come faste to fille here hondis &amp; coffris. &amp; herefore men seyn &thorn;ei maken marchaundise wi&thorn; money &amp; mennys soulis to sathanas, for &thorn;ei &yogh;euen men licence to dwelle in synne for annuel rente as longe as hem liki&thorn;, &amp; &thorn;us sathanas geti&thorn; soulis to helle for &thorn;e roten peny; for men seyn &thorn;at cayphas bischopis ben sory whanne men forsaken here olde synnes and paien nomore here annuel rente. &para; And seyn &thorn;at &thorn;ei may not holde good hous bi siche men, as &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei wolde sende &thorn;ousande soulis to satanas for to haue moche roten money &amp; a proude name in &thorn;e world of gret housholdyng.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="9" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 9<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis killen men gostly, &yogh;euynge euyl ensaumple &amp; disceyuynge pore men of here almes, &amp; wi&thorn;-drawynge goddis word bi whiche &thorn;ei schulden lyue gostly, for ensaumple of pride, coueitise, wra&thorn;&thorn;e, vnmercy, vanyte, glotonye &amp; lecherie &thorn;ei &yogh;euen to alle men aboute; &amp; manye of &thorn;es synnes ben so open &thorn;at it nedi&thorn; no more to declare hem, but of lecherie men seyn &thorn;at many prelatis ben ful &thorn;er-of &amp; of &thorn;e moste cursed spices &thorn;er-of, &thorn;at it is schame to written it but more to done it in dede; &amp; lowere curatis taken ensaumple at hem 
<PB REF="00000139.tif" N="73"> &amp; seyn, whi may not we haue lemmannus si&thorn; &thorn;e bischop ha&thorn; so manye? &amp; sugetis taken ensaumple at here curatis, bo&thorn;e weddid men &amp; sengle. &amp; &thorn;us prelatis bi &thorn;is cursed ensaumple sleen in als mychel as in hem is alle manere men, for &thorn;ei dorn not for schame of her owen synne sadly amende o&thorn;ere synful, ne wi&thorn;-stonde wronges of souereyns &thorn;at &thorn;ei don to pore men. &para; And here-wi&thorn; prelatis disceyuen<NOTE PLACE="foot">disceyuem X.</NOTE> pore men of here almes, for bi fals pardon &thorn;ei maken men to &yogh;eue here nedi liflode to here cathedral chirches &thorn;at han no nede, &amp; make &thorn;e pore men to hope of more &thorn;ank of goddis mercy to don here almes to riche houses &amp; riche men more &thorn;an to don it to here pore nei&yogh;ebo&thorn;eris &thorn;at ben bedrede, febil, &amp; crokid &amp; blynd, &amp; &thorn;er-wi&thorn; han nou&yogh;t of here owen. And certis &thorn;is is worse &thorn;efte &thorn;an to robbe hem as an owtlawe do&thorn;. For he taki&thorn; comunly gold or siluer, but &thorn;er prelates taken <MILESTONE N="79" UNIT="page">bo&thorn;e of pore men &amp; disceyuen hem in fei&thorn;, hope &amp; charite, &amp; also &thorn;ei suffren o&thorn;ere false pardoneris disceyuen &thorn;e peple for a litel money, &amp; lesse curatis haunten &thorn;is false craft. &para; Also &thorn;es prelates bi extorsions and maistrie taken &thorn;e litel good &thorn;at &thorn;ei schulden lyue bi &thorn;at &thorn;ei geten bi gret swoot of here body, &amp; &thorn;us, as god sei&thorn; of tyrauntis, &thorn;ei taken here skyn <NOTE PLACE="marg">Micah iii. 2.</NOTE> fro &thorn;e bak, &amp; eten &amp; drynkyn mennus blood, whanne &thorn;ei be raueine &amp; ypocrisie disceyuen hem of here goodis bi whiche here bodely lif schulde be susteyned, &amp; whiche goodis &thorn;ei gaten bi hard traueile &amp; wastyng of flech &amp; blood; &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei ben manquelleris &amp; irreguler bi-fore god &amp; his aungelis. &para; Also &thorn;ei prechen not cristis gospel in word &amp; dede bi whiche cristene men schuld lyue holy lif in charite, but blaberen for&thorn;e anticristis bullis to maken cristene men to werre eche wi&thorn; o&thorn;ere in hope to wynne heuene bi siche werris, &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ei letten trewe men to teche treuli &amp; frely cristis gospel &amp; his comaundementis, but &thorn;ei senden newe ypocritis to preche fablis &amp; lesyngis &amp; to flateren men in synne, &amp; to robbe &thorn;e pore peple bi fals beggynge dampnyd of goddis. lawe, &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ei maken &thorn;e peple to erre in bileue &amp; to trowe 
<PB REF="00000140.tif" N="74"> &thorn;at crist beggyd &thorn;us als &thorn;ei don; but certis &thorn;is his an open heresie a&yogh;enst cristis gospel &amp; his lif, &amp; as &thorn;e olde lawe &amp; &thorn;e newe schewyn pleynly; &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;es prelatis killen mennus soulis bi sclaundre of here owen euyl lif, bi disceit of almes, &amp; suffrynge of false techeris &amp; false robberis of &thorn;e peple.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="10" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 10<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Ouere &thorn;is prelatis chargen more here owen cursyng, &thorn;at is many tymys fals, &thorn;an &thorn;e moste ri&yogh;tful curse of god almy&yogh;tty. And here-bi &thorn;ei menen &amp; schewen in dede but falsly &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben more &thorn;an almy&yogh;tty god in trinyte. &para; For &yogh;if a man be acursed of prelatis, &yogh;e wrongly, a-noon alle men ben tau&yogh;t bi hem to flee him as a iew or a sarsyn, &amp; &yogh;if he dwelle fourty daies in here curs he schal be taken to prison. But &thorn;o &thorn;at ben cursed of god for bregynge of his hestis, as proude men, enuyous, coueitous, glotons &amp; lecherouse, ben not ponyschid &thorn;us, but holden vertuous &amp; wor&thorn;i &amp; manly men; &amp; so goddis curs is seit at nou&yogh;t but wrongful mannes curs is chargid aboue &thorn;e cloudis. And &yogh;it &thorn;ou&yogh; a man be cursed of god &amp; of a prelat also trewly, &yogh;if he wole &yogh;eue gold or money at a false mannus wille he schal be assoilid as anemtis men, &thorn;ou&yogh; he dwelle in his synne &amp; &thorn;anne in goddis curs. &para; But see now &thorn;e mysusynge of mannus curs; &yogh;if a trewe man displese a worldly prelat for techynge &amp; meyntenynge of goddis lawe, he schal be sclaundrid for a cursed man &amp; forboden to teche cristis gospel, &amp; &thorn;e peple chargid vp <MILESTONE N="80" UNIT="page">peyne of &thorn;e grete curs to flee &amp; not heren s[i]ch a man for to saue here owen soulis; &amp; &thorn;is schal be don vnder colour of holynesse; for &thorn;ei wolen seie &thorn;at siche a man techi&thorn; heresie &amp; brynge many false witnesses &amp; notaries in his absence, &amp; in presence speke no word, &amp; &thorn;ei feynen &thorn;is false lawe, &yogh;if &thorn;re or four false witnesses hirid bi money seye sich a &thorn;ing a&yogh;enst a trewe man, &thorn;an he schal not be herd, &thorn;ou&yogh; he wolde proue &thorn;e contrarie bi two hundrid or &thorn;re; &amp; &thorn;es false men seye in here doynge &thorn;at crist was lafully don to &thorn;e de&thorn;, &amp; susanne also, for bi sich witnessis 
<PB REF="00000141.tif" N="75"> &thorn;ei weren dampnyd, but cristene men bileue techi&thorn; &thorn;e contrarie. &amp; bi &thorn;is false lawe &thorn;ei may proue heretikis whom euere &thorn;ei wolen; &yogh;e, crist &amp; alle his apostlis &amp; alle his martirs &amp; trewe men in &thorn;is world, &amp; proue eche kyng in cristendom forsworn &amp; no kyng; but certis god techi&thorn; in his lawe &thorn;at o trewe man, as danyel dede, schal conuycte two false prestis; &amp; &thorn;e prophete hely conuycte ei&yogh;te hundrid<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Kings xviii.</NOTE> &amp; mo of false prestis &amp; prophetis of baal. &amp; &thorn;es prelatis wolen distroie al goddis lawe &thorn;at techi&thorn; hou false witnesse schullen be ponyschid, for &thorn;ei wolen not haue hem conuycted of here falsnesse bi mo trewe men; &amp; &yogh;it whanne a man is falsly cursed of a prelat, &yogh;e &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;e prelat be a deuyl of helle, he schal not be assoilid til &thorn;at he swere to stonde to here dom &thorn;ou it be a&yogh;enst goddis lawe &amp; his conscience. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei ben fully contrarie to goddis dom &amp; ry&yogh;twisnesse, for &yogh;if a man haue terespassid neuere so a&yogh;enst god he wole assoile him for verray contricion wi&thorn;-outen siche sweryng or chargyng of vnresonable &thorn;ingis, but &thorn;ei falsly enhaunsen hem aboue god almytti. &para; &THORN;us it stondi&thorn; of mannus curs; apostlis of crist hadden power to take mennys bodyes to<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. v. 5.</NOTE> sathanas to traueilen hem whanne &thorn;ei weren rebelle a&yogh;enst goddis hestis til &thorn;ei weren meke a&yogh;en for peyne &amp; for woo, &amp; so to saue &thorn;e soule; but nowe anticristis clerkis cursen &thorn;e soule in-to helle as &thorn;ei feynen, but &thorn;e body is neuere &thorn;e more traueilid. &amp; certis &thorn;es ben cruel fadris &thorn;at &thorn;us violently cursen here children in-to helle, not for rebelte a&yogh;enst god ne his lawe, but for cristene men wi&thorn;-stonden &thorn;e prelatis coueitise or his pride, or for &thorn;ei techen &amp; meyn|tenen &thorn;e gospel of ih&umacr; crist. &para; Also whanne &thorn;ei cursen for here coueitise &amp; here owen vengaunce &thorn;ei cursen hem self, as &thorn;e lawe sei&thorn;, for &thorn;ei bent out of charite a&yogh;enst god &amp; man. &para; Also whanne &thorn;ei cursen a man &thorn;at meyntene&thorn; goddis lawe paciently &amp; stably god blisse&thorn; a&yogh;enst here cursyng, but &thorn;ei blynden so &thorn;e peple &thorn;at goddis blissyng is sett at nou&yogh;t, but here false curs is drede more &thorn;an god almy&yogh;tty. Also whanne &thorn;ei blissen a man &thorn;at meyntene&thorn; hem in here 
<PB REF="00000142.tif" N="76"> cursed <MILESTONE N="81" UNIT="page">lif god him self curse&thorn; &thorn;at man, as god sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e prophete, but &thorn;ei blyndyn so &thorn;e peple &thorn;at here false blissyng is magnyfied &amp; goddis ri&yogh;tful curs is not dred, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei putten goddis dom &amp; blissynge &amp; cursynge bihynde &amp; setten hem at nou&yogh;t, &amp; magnyfien here owen false dom and blissynge &amp; cursynge aboue god almy&yogh;tty: but in o&thorn;ere placis is more of &thorn;is matere.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="11" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 11<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis disceyuen lordis &amp; alle cristene men bi veyn preieris of mou&thorn;, &amp; veyn knackyng of newe song &amp; costy, for bi title of preire &thorn;ei han many worldly lordschipis &amp; many parische chirchis approprid to hem, &amp; don nei&thorn;er office of prelatis as cristis disciplis diden, nei&thorn;er office of lordis as &thorn;ei owen to do bi goddis lawe, nei&thorn;er &thorn;e office of parsones ne vekeris to here parischenes; but lyuen<NOTE PLACE="foot">lyuem X.</NOTE> in pompe &amp; pride, coueitise, &amp; in wra&thorn;&thorn;e, slou&thorn;e &amp; in ydelnesse, &amp; stenkynge lecherie, glotonye &amp; drounkenesse, &amp; gret ypocrisie, and so techen &thorn;e fendis armys of synne &amp; distroien &thorn;e clennesse of cristis lif as moche as &thorn;ei may. preiere stondi&thorn; principaly in good lif, &amp; of &thorn;is preiere speki&thorn; crist whanne he sei&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel &thorn;at we mosten euere preie; for austyn &amp; o&thorn;ere seyntis seyn as longe as a man dwelle&thorn; in charite so longe he preie&thorn; wel. &para; Also preiere stondi&thorn; in holy desir to do goddis wille, &amp; of &thorn;is speki&thorn; goddis lawe &amp; seyntis ful myche. &para; Also preiere stondi&thorn; in word, as comunly men speken, &amp; &thorn;is is nou&yogh;t wor&thorn; but &yogh;if it be don wi&thorn; deuocion &amp; clennesse &amp; holynesse of lif. &para; For holy writt sei&thorn; &thorn;at his preynge is<NOTE PLACE="marg">Prov. xxviii. 9.</NOTE> abhomynable &thorn;at turne&thorn; awey &amp; heri&thorn; nou&yogh;t &thorn;e lawe; &thorn;at is to seie, &thorn;at fulfilli&thorn; not goddis lawe in his lif. And of siche vikede men sei&thorn; god bi his prophete: whanne &yogh;e schulle<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isaiah i. 15.</NOTE> multiplie &yogh;oure preieris y schal not here &yogh;ou. &para; And god sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e prophete to suche men: y schal warrie or curse to &yogh;oure<NOTE PLACE="marg">Mal. ii. 2.</NOTE> blissynges, &amp; god sei&thorn; bi salamon &thorn;at &thorn;e sacrafices of wicked<NOTE PLACE="marg">Prov. xv. 8.</NOTE> men ben abhomynable, &amp; austyn sei&thorn; in many placis &thorn;at &yogh;if &thorn;ou lyuest in glotonye &amp; dronkenesse, what euere &thorn;i tonge 
<PB REF="00000143.tif" N="77"> sowne&thorn;, &thorn;i lif blaspheme&thorn; god; &amp; gregory sei&thorn; whanne he &thorn;at displese&thorn; is sent for to preie, wi&thorn;-outen doute &thorn;e herte of him &thorn;at is wro&thorn; is stirid to werse wra&thorn;&thorn;e. A lord, si&thorn; prelatis ben so fer fro goddis lawe &thorn;at &thorn;ei wolen not preche hem-self ne suffre o&thorn;ere men to preche &thorn;e gospel trewely &amp; frely, hou abhominable is here preire bi-fore god almy&yogh;tty. lord, si&thorn; prelatis witte not where here preiere be acceptable or dampnable, whi magnyfien &thorn;ei it so moche &amp; sillen it so dere? for a lewid mannus preiere &thorn;at schal be sauyd is wi&thorn;|outen mesure betre &thorn;an &thorn;at prelat &thorn;at schal be dampnyd, &amp; si&thorn; no prelat whot where he schal be dampnyd, whi silli&thorn; <MILESTONE N="82" UNIT="page"> he his cursed preiere to &thorn;e lewid man so dere? &para; And &thorn;er-fore god kepi&thorn; to his owne knowynge &thorn;e wor&thorn;ynesse of mannes preiere, for men schulden not vse marchaundise of symonye &thorn;erby; for god techi&thorn; vs be seynt poul &yogh;if a man resceyue vnwor&thorn;ily &thorn;e sacrament of &thorn;e auter &thorn;at man resceyue&thorn; his<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. xi. 29.</NOTE> dampnacion. And si&thorn; prelatis hondis ben ful of blood, bo&thorn;e of quellyng of men wi&thorn; here owen hondis sumtyme, &amp; bi wille &amp; fals conseilynge to wronge werris, &amp; ful of synne, as symonye, extorsions &amp; robberie, &amp; of meyntenyng in synne for &yogh;er to &yogh;er for money, hou schal god here hem? si&thorn; he sei&thorn; nay hym-self bi &thorn;e prophete: foule ben oure lordis blent to meyntenen open traitours of god, bi gret cost of rentis &amp; lordischipis &amp; &yogh;ifte of grete benefices, for here stynkynge &amp; abhomynable blastis &amp; lowd criynge; for bi &thorn;er grete criyng of song, as deschaunt, countre note &amp; orgene, &thorn;ei ben lettid fro studynge &amp; prechynge of &thorn;e gospel; &amp; here owene fyndynge vp, &thorn;at crist &amp; apostlis spoken not of, as is &thorn;is newe song, &thorn;ei clepen it goddis seruyce, &amp; magnyfien it at &thorn;e fulle, but good lif &amp; techynge of &thorn;e gospel &thorn;ei setten at nou&yogh;t. And &yogh;it crist comaundi&thorn; &thorn;at most of alle &thorn;ingis in &thorn;is world; &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei &thorn;enken it ynow&yogh; to kepe here owene fyndyngis and to traueilen aboute hem, &thorn;ou &thorn;ei leuen &thorn;e ordynaunce of god &amp; studynge of his lawe, &amp; &thorn;us it is verrefyed, but on an euyl manere, &thorn;at seynt poul sei&thorn;: whanne &thorn;e presthod is translatid, it is nede &thorn;at &thorn;e lawe be<NOTE PLACE="marg">Hebrews vii. 12.</NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000144.tif" N="78"> translatid; for whanne presthod stod in holy prestis of<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> lif &amp; studiouse &amp; kunnynge, &thorn;anne was holy writt ynow&yogh; to hem &amp; studied &amp; kept in dede wi&thorn; gret reuerence; but nowe, whanne presthold stonde&thorn; in peny clerkis &amp; stewardis of lordis houses &amp; ladies &amp; ydiotis &amp; symonyentis &amp; proude wrecchis ful of all manere synne, it is nede to haue newe lawes maad of synful foolis to colouren &thorn;is synne by and to gedre gredely ti&thorn;es whanne &thorn;ei don not here office; for goddis lawe helpe&thorn; hem not her-to but dampne&thorn; here pride, symonye, coueytise &amp; o&thorn;ere synnes. &para; And &yogh;it anticristis clerkis feynen &thorn;at &thorn;ou&yogh; synful prelatis &amp; cursed ben not herd in here preiere for here owen holynesse, &yogh;it preiere of<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> siche is herd in vertu of holy chirche; but &thorn;is dremyng nys not groundid in ony place of holy writt, for god sei&thorn; generaly &thorn;at &thorn;is preiere is abhominable &thorn;at turne&thorn; awey &amp; heri&thorn; not goddis lawe; &amp; comunly suche cursed prelatis ben no part of holy chirche, in cas &thorn;at &thorn;ei sullen be dampnyd; also syche cursed prestis dispisen god in his face, hou schulde god here hem &thorn;anne, si&thorn; in cas &thorn;ei ben fendis <MILESTONE N="83" UNIT="page">of helle? &para; Also god heri&thorn; not siche cursed men for hem self, hou schulde he &thorn;anne here hem for o&thorn;ere men, whanne charite schuld bigyne at hem-self. &para; Also in &thorn;e olde lawe god tok gret vengaunce of hem &thorn;at offreden o&thorn;er fier &thorn;an god ordeyned in his sacrafice, &amp; &thorn;is fire was token of charite, &thorn;at who euere dede ony sacrifice to god wi&thorn;-outen charite schulde not ben acceptid, but vengaunce schulde come on him o&thorn;er gostly or bodily; but &thorn;e fend blyndi&thorn; men bi syche false colour to tristen in ypocritis preieris, &amp; sumtyme in preieris of fendis, &amp; not to amende hem of here synne but ra&thorn;ere to meyntene hem &thorn;er|inne; &amp; &thorn;us is oure peple disceyued bi veyn preieris of synful ypocritis, &amp; holy writt not knowen ne kept, but vanyte, pride &amp; o&thorn;ere synnes ben meyntened, &amp; holi lif of prestis &amp; o&thorn;ere men is dispised.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="12" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000145.tif" N="79">
<HEAD>Capitulum 12<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Prelatis also feren cristene men bi here false censures, as suspendynge, cursynge and enterditynge, &thorn;at &thorn;ei kepe not goddis lawe &amp; his ordynaunce; for whanne prestis wolden gladly lyue wel aftir &thorn;e gospel, &amp; preche goddis lawe &amp; dispise &amp; distroie synne, &thorn;anne worldly prelates, for drede of here owen symonye &amp; extorsions of pore men, comaunden prestis to preche not wi&thorn;-outen here leue, &amp; &thorn;anne prestis schullen neuere gete leue or ellis swere &thorn;at &thorn;ei schal not preche a&yogh;enst &thorn;e grete synnes of prelatis. And &yogh;if prestis prechen trewely &amp; frely &thorn;e gospel of crist &amp; reprouen generaly synne, &thorn;es emperours clerkis &thorn;at stryuen a&yogh;enst cristis lyuynge wolen somone hem fro contre to contre; &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ei dwellen wi&thorn; cristene peple &amp; techen<NOTE PLACE="foot">techem X.</NOTE> hem goddis lawe &amp; don not aftir here wrong heest, &para; &thorn;ei wolen suspenden pore prestis fro masse &amp; prechynge &amp; alle goddis seruyce, &amp; curse hem &amp; prisone hem bi &thorn;e kingis power; &amp; so trewe prestis schullen be cursed &amp; prisoned for &thorn;ei don frely werkis of mercy &amp; charite &amp; comaundement of god, &amp; leuen &thorn;e contrarie comaundement of a synful fool &amp; in cas of a maistir deuyl of helle. &para; And &yogh;if lordis wolen helpe pore prestis in ri&yogh;t of goddis lawe, &amp; brynge proude worldly clerkis to mekenesse &amp; pouert, as god comaundi&thorn; hem in his lawe, &thorn;ei schullen be suspendid from alle goddis seruyce and here londis entirditid &amp; &thorn;ei cursed &amp; taken to prison &yogh;if &thorn;ei stonden sadde in goddis cause, &amp; &thorn;es feyned &thorn;eues seruen of &thorn;is, to forbede men to do goddis seruyce &amp; his comaundement &amp; profit of here soulis for feyned drede<NOTE PLACE="foot">dredre X.</NOTE> of anticrist &amp; so maken men more to dreden anticrist &amp; his peynes, &amp; in caas synful foolis &amp; deuelys of helle, &thorn;an <MILESTONE N="84" UNIT="page">almy&yogh;tty god in trinyte &amp; his offense, &amp; to lese &thorn;e blisse of heuene; &amp; &thorn;us anticristis prelatis don more harm to cristene men &amp; maken hem more to breke goddis hestis &thorn;an &thorn;e deuelis in helle, &thorn;at neuere weren men. but a&yogh;enst &thorn;es feyned censures men schulden ben armed wi&thorn; fe&thorn; of &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000146.tif" N="80"> gospel, &thorn;at &thorn;e more &thorn;at &thorn;ei forbeden men do goddis wille, &thorn;e more strong schulden &thorn;ei be to do it; &amp; drede not here curs, for &thorn;anne god blisse&thorn; hem; &amp; a&yogh;enst bodely peyne be armed wi&thorn; pacience &amp; charite &amp; hope of heuenely blisse; &amp; &thorn;an anticristis power schulde soone be brou&yogh;t doun &amp; holy writt knowen &amp; kept &amp; meyntened; but goddis lawe<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> is &thorn;is, &thorn;at prelatis preche to synful men &thorn;e foulnesse of here gretee synnys and horible peynes of helle, &amp; hou soone &thorn;ei may geten mercy of god in &thorn;e blisse of heuene for verrey contricion. And &yogh;if &thorn;ei wolen not leue here opyn synnes for al &thorn;is, &thorn;anne lordis schulden ponysche here bodies in prison or by loos of catel, for &thorn;is is lordis office as petir &amp; poul techen. Sumtyme men weren forboden of trewe prestis to vse &amp; do sacramentis in open cursed lif, &amp; &thorn;at is trewe suspendynge. But nowe goode men ben suspendid fro doyng of goddis hestis til &thorn;at &thorn;ei paien a gret tribuyt to anticrist or his officeris. But &thorn;o&yogh; a man be neuere so openly cursed of god he schal be suffred &yogh;if he wil paie a rente to anticrist or hise, &thorn;ou&yogh; he neuere so foule dispise god &amp; dampne his owne soule &amp; dysceyue &thorn;e peple. &amp; &thorn;us alle &thorn;es feyned censures ben anticristis panter &amp; armes, to lette trewe men fro &thorn;e seruyce of god almy&yogh;tty and to make men to forsake god in his lawe for drede of anticrist and fendis of helle.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="13" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 13<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis disceyuen foule cristene men by feyned in|dulgences or pardons &amp; robben hem cursedly of here money; for &thorn;ei techen men &thorn;at for staciones of rome &amp; for &yogh;euynge of almes aftir synful mennes wille &thorn;ei schullen haue &thorn;ousandis of &yogh;eris of pardon, &amp; also pardon wi&thorn;-outen noumbre to mannys vndirstondynge. &amp; &thorn;is pardon is for&yogh;euenesse or remyssion of peynes whanne men ben verrely contrit of alle here synnes bi vertue of cristis passion &amp; martirdom, &amp; holy meritis of seyntis &thorn;at &thorn;ei diden more &thorn;an was nedful 
<PB REF="00000147.tif" N="81"> for here owene blisse. but &thorn;is crist tau&yogh;te neuere in al &thorn;e gospel &amp; neuere vsed it, nei&thorn;er petir ne poul or ony o&thorn;er apostle of crist; &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ei my&yogh;tten, couden, &amp; weren in most charite to teche &amp; vse &thorn;is pardon &yogh;if &thorn;er had ben any siche, for in crist was alle manere of good lore &amp; good lif &amp; charite, &amp; most aftir in his apostlis; &amp; si&thorn; crist fond &amp; tau&yogh;tte <MILESTONE N="85" UNIT="page">al &thorn;at is nedful &amp; profitable &amp; he tau&yogh;te not &thorn;is pardon, &thorn;ann &thorn;is pardon nys nei&thorn;er nedful ne profitable. &para; Also alle men &thorn;at ben in charite ben partyneris of cristis passion, &amp; of alle goode dedis fro &thorn;e bigynnynge of &thorn;e world til &thorn;e last ende &thorn;er-of, bi &thorn;e most ry&yogh;tful delyng of ih&umacr; crist as moche as it is ry&yogh;tful, &amp; more schal no man haue for no grant of ony<NOTE PLACE="foot">no X.; but corrected in margin.</NOTE> creature of god; &thorn;an for &thorn;is popis graunt or bischopis neuere &thorn;e more of pardon. &THORN;anne men ben grete foolis &thorn;at bien &thorn;es bulles of pardon so dere, &amp; maken hem more bisy to geten hem &thorn;an to kepe &thorn;e hestis of god &amp; to &yogh;eue here almes to &thorn;e most pore &amp; nedi nei&yogh;eboris; for it seme&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben out of fei&thorn;, hope &amp; charite; for &thorn;ei tristen to haue more &thorn;ank to do here almes aftir synful mennus wille &amp; techynge, &yogh;e to ryche houses or ryche men &thorn;at han no nede, &thorn;an for to do here almes aftir cristis techynge &amp; to most nedy men. &para; Also &yogh;if &thorn;e day of doom come bi-fore &thorn;es &thorn;ousand &yogh;eer of pardon come out, &thorn;anne &thorn;es pardons ben false, for aftir &thorn;e dom schal be no purga|torie; but no man wot hou soone &thorn;e doom schal come; ne&thorn;eles &thorn;e pope &amp; his officeris in &thorn;es indulgences presumen to ben euene wi&thorn; god in knowynge certeynly &thorn;e comyng of &thorn;e dom &amp; in departyng of meritis to whom &thorn;at hem liki&thorn;. But bo&thorn;e &thorn;es ben enproprid to god, &amp; &thorn;an it is blasphemye for ony creature to take &thorn;is to hym as do&thorn; &thorn;e pope wi&thorn; his meyne. &para; Also it seme&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;e pope &amp; his ben out of charite &yogh;if &thorn;ere dwelle ony soule in purgatorie, for he may wi&thorn; ful herte wi&thorn;-outen ony o&thorn;er cost delyuere hem out of purgatorie, &amp; &thorn;ei ben able to resceyue suche helpe si&thorn; &thorn;ei ben in grace; &thorn;an &yogh;if he delyuere hem not out 
<PB REF="00000148.tif" N="82"> of purgatorie him lacki&thorn; charite, &amp; &yogh;if he haue not power to delyuere alle &thorn;an is he out of charite &amp; disceyuere of mannus soule, si&thorn; he techi&thorn; &thorn;at his gostly tresour es endles meche, &amp; is neuere &thorn;e lesse &thorn;ou&yogh; he partid it generaly among alle. &para; Also it passe&thorn; mannus knowynge what is goddis dom to suche soulis, &thorn;anne it seme&thorn; a gret pride for a synful man to make hym certeyn &amp; maistire of goddis dom &thorn;at he knowi&thorn; not. &para; Also &thorn;es pardons gon not for charite but for worldly drit as it seme&thorn;, for &yogh;if pardon schulde be grauntid it schulde be graunted for to make pees &amp; charite, &amp; not for to make discencion &amp; werris, &amp; o cristene man to slen his bro&thorn;er; &amp; for to stire men to kepe goddis hestis, not to do aftir singuler wille or worldly profyt of synful men &thorn;at seken here owene worschipe or worldly wynnynge more &thorn;an sauyng of cristene soulis; &amp; for to seie &thorn;e pater noster &thorn;at crist made hym self, &amp; not for singuler preieres made of vs self <MILESTONE N="86" UNIT="page">for loue of an er&thorn;ely kyng; but in al &thorn;is is &thorn;e contrarie don as men seyn in dede, wherfore it is al out of charite &amp; &thorn;an it is nou&yogh;t wor&thorn;. &para; Also &yogh;if &thorn;is pardon be an heuenely &yogh;iefte &amp; gostly it schulde be &yogh;euen frely as crist techi&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel, &amp; not for money ne worldly goodis ne fleshly fauour; but &yogh;if a riche man wol bie dere &thorn;e bulle, he schal haue a bulle of pardon wi&thorn; &thorn;ousand &yogh;eris &thorn;ou&yogh; he be cursed of god for his synful lif, &amp; a pore bederede man &thorn;at ha&thorn; no money &amp; may not traueile to rome or to suche ano&thorn;er place, he schal haue no pardon of &thorn;e pope, &thorn;ou&yogh; he be holy &amp; ful of charite: &thorn;an si&thorn; &thorn;is pardon schulde be frely &yogh;ouen, &yogh;if &thorn;er ony suche be, it is &thorn;efte [&amp;] roberie to take &thorn;us myche gold &thorn;er-fore; but here ypocritis seyn &thorn;at &thorn;ei taken no &thorn;ing for pardon but for &thorn;e bulle &thorn;at is selid: certis a litel deed leed costi&thorn; many &thorn;ousand pond bi &yogh;ere to oure pore lond, sikire &thorn;ei disceyuen &thorn;e peple &amp; iapen hem, for &thorn;ei sillen a faat goos for litel or nou&yogh;t, but &thorn;e garlek costi&thorn; many shillyngis. &para; Also &thorn;is feynd pardon disceyue&thorn; many men, for riche men tristen to flee to heuene &thorn;er-bi wi&thorn;-outen peyne &amp; &thorn;er-fore dreden synne &thorn;e lesse, &amp; of verrey contricion &amp; leuynge of synne &amp; of doynge almes to 
<PB REF="00000149.tif" N="83"> most nedy men is lytil spoken of, for &yogh;if it were so&thorn;ly teld &thorn;is pardon schulde be sette at nou&yogh;t. gret falsnesse is &thorn;is to magnyfie &thorn;e popis power so mychil in purgatorie &thorn;at no man here can teche bi holy writt ne reson, si&thorn; we seen in &thorn;is world &thorn;at a litel harlot dispise&thorn; &thorn;e pope &amp; stroie&thorn; his lordischipe, &amp; &yogh;it he do&thorn; al his my&yogh;t, alle his witt, &amp; alle his wille, to be vengid vpon siche a pore harlot. &thorn;ane it seme&thorn; for many skillis &thorn;at &thorn;is feyned pardon is a sotil marchaundise of anticristis clerkis, to magnyfie her feyned power &amp; to geten worldly goodis, &amp; to make men drede not synne, but sikirly to walwe &thorn;er-inne as hogges; &amp; merueile it is &thorn;at synful foolis doren graunte ony &thorn;ing of meritis of seyntis; for al &thorn;at euere ony seynt dide may not brynge o soule to heuene wi&thorn;-outen grace &amp; my&yogh;t of cristis passion, &amp; alle meritis, &thorn;at ben medeful dedes, of alle seyntis but only cristis ben not euene wor&thorn; to &thorn;e ioie of heuene, as poul sei&thorn;; &amp; si&thorn; god graunti&thorn; to eche man part of alle medeful dedis als mochel as it is wor&thorn;i, no man schal haue more part of &thorn;es dedis for alle &thorn;es bulles, &amp; neuere &thorn;e lasse &thorn;ou&yogh; no man graunte siche part ne siche bullis; &amp; &thorn;es feyned pardons maken men to tristen more in grauntynge of a synful man, &amp; in cas of a deuyl of helle, &thorn;an in &thorn;e ri&yogh;tfuleste graunt of houre lord ih&umacr; crist. almy&yogh;tty god for his endeles mercy distroie&thorn; &thorn;is pride, coueitise, ypocrisie &amp; heresie <MILESTONE N="87" UNIT="page">of &thorn;is feyned pardon, &amp; make men bisi to kepe his hestis &amp; sette fully here triste in ih&umacr; crist. Amen.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="14" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 14<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Prelatis also maken &thorn;e weie to heuene hardere &thorn;an crist made it, &amp; so letten men to go to heuene &amp; &thorn;er-fore ben cursed of god. For &thorn;ei entren not hem self into &thorn;e kyngdom<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. xxiii. 13.</NOTE> of heuene &amp; letten hem &thorn;at wolden, as crist sei&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel, for &thorn;ei make many newe lawes of hem self, &amp; chargen men to studie hem &amp; kepe hem more &thorn;an &thorn;e gospel; &amp; si&thorn; &thorn;e gospel &amp; holy writt is occupacion ynow&yogh; for men 
<PB REF="00000150.tif" N="84"> in &thorn;is lif, &thorn;e more &thorn;at men be<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> occupied abouten mannys lawis &thorn;at expounen not &thorn;e gospel, &thorn;e more &thorn;ei ben drawen fro &thorn;e gospel &amp; &thorn;e lesse knowen &thorn;at &amp; &thorn;e worse kepen it. &para; Also prelatis maken many newe poyntis of bileue, &amp; seyn &thorn;at it<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> is not ynow&yogh; to bileue in ih&umacr; crist &amp; to be cristened, <NOTE PLACE="marg">Mark xvi. 16.</NOTE>as crist sei&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel of mark, But &yogh;if a man bileue &thorn;at &thorn;e bischop of rome be heuyd of holy chirche. And certis &thorn;e apostlis of ih&umacr; crist constreynenden neuere ony man to bileue &thorn;is of hem self, &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ei weren certeyn of here sauynge in heuene; hou schulde &thorn;an ony synful wrecche, &thorn;at wot neuere where he schal be dampnyd or sauyd, con|streyne men to bileue &thorn;at he is heuyd of holy chirche? certis &thorn;ei constreynen men sumtyme to bileue &thorn;at a deuyl of helle is heuyd of holy chirche, whanne &thorn;e bischop of rome schal be dampnyd for his cursed endynge in synne.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="15" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 15<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis magnyfien hem self abouen ih&umacr; crist god and man. For ih&umacr; crist comaundid &amp; tau&yogh;te opynly &thorn;at men schulden not &yogh;eue credence to hym but &yogh;if he dede &thorn;e werkis of &thorn;e fadir of heuene. But oure prelatis chalengen &thorn;at we &yogh;eue credence to hem<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> where &thorn;ei don wel or euyl. Also crist sei&thorn; to &thorn;e iewis of him self &thorn;at &thorn;ei schullen deme a ri&yogh;tful doom &amp; not after &thorn;e face. And in his passion tyme<NOTE PLACE="marg">John vii. 24.</NOTE> crist bade a synful harlot &amp; cursed to bere wittenesse of euyle in cas &yogh;if crist had seid eny euyle. But oure prelatis &thorn;at don euyle bo&thorn;e in dede, speche &amp; &thorn;ou&yogh;t, crien kenely &thorn;at sugetis schullen not deme hem, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei don opynly a&yogh;enst charite. also poul biddi&thorn; &thorn;at his sugetis demen &thorn;at &thorn;ing &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">2 Cor. xii. 2.</NOTE> he sei&thorn; after &thorn;at he was rauyschid in-to &thorn;e &thorn;ridde heuene; but oure prelatis wolen not &thorn;at we deme here seiynge, &thorn;ou&yogh; it be contrarie to goddis lawe opynly, &amp; certis &thorn;is is &thorn;e deuyl cast of helle to distroie &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of holy writt &amp; &thorn;e lif of ih&umacr; crist &amp; his apostlis, and to coloure pride &amp; coueitise 
<PB REF="00000151.tif" N="85"> &amp; symonye &amp; extorsions as moche as euere &thorn;ei wolen, for bi here cast men schullen not reproue hem &thorn;er-of, what synne euere &thorn;ei don.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="16" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 16<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Prelatis also constreynen men to <MILESTONE N="88" UNIT="page"> cesse &amp; do not &thorn;e wille &amp; hestis of god, but &yogh;if &thorn;ei han leue of goddis enemys, &amp; in cas of deuelis of helle. For &yogh;if prestis wolen seie here masse &amp; techen &thorn;e gospel in a bischopis diocise, a noon he schal be forboden but &yogh;if he haue leue of &thorn;at bischop, &amp; he<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> schal paie comunly for &thorn;at leue myche money or ellis swere &thorn;at he schal not speke a&yogh;enst grete synnes of &thorn;at bischop &amp; o&thorn;ere prestis &amp; here falsnesse. And &yogh;it it is a grete werk of charite &amp; mercy to teche men &thorn;e ri&yogh;tte weie to heuene, &amp; &thorn;es men schullen nou&yogh;t doo wi&thorn;-outen leue of &thorn;e bischop, &thorn;ou&yogh; he be neuere so proud, neuere so coueitous &amp; cursed for symonye &amp; extorsions, &amp; many tymes sich a bischop schal be dampnyd, &amp; &thorn;anne, as crist sei&thorn;, he is a deuyl. &thorn;an it is verefied &thorn;at a cristene man schal not do &thorn;e wille of god with|outen leue of goddis enemye, &amp; of a fend of helle; as &yogh;if &thorn;e leue &amp; &thorn;e comaundement of god were not ynow&yogh; to don his wille, but &yogh;if a man haue leue of siche a cursed creature. And &yogh;if siche a cursed creature<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> seie nay, goddis wille schal ben vndon &amp; his lawe &amp; wille vnknowen and not kept. And &thorn;is is don for drede of loos of here worldly pride &amp; coueitise, &amp; of worldly lordischipis &thorn;at &thorn;ei han a&yogh;enst cristis lawe &amp; his techynge &amp; his owen lif and his apostlis; but &thorn;is forbedyng is colourid by holynesse, for, as prelatis feynen, pore prestis wolden teche heresie for &thorn;ei knowen not goddis lawe; but certis &thorn;es prelatis demen heresie alle &thorn;at is a&yogh;enst here lykyng &amp; lustis of here flech; &amp; &thorn;ei ben ful vnable to teche &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of goddis lawe, for &thorn;ei studien not &thorn;er aboute &amp; lyuen contrariously &thorn;er-to; wherefore &thorn;e holy gost techi&thorn; hem not al so&thorn;e, but &thorn;e spirit of lesyngis steri&thorn; hem to lette knowy[n]ge of goddis lawe &amp; sauynge of soulis vnder colour 
<PB REF="00000152.tif" N="86"> of holynesse, for &thorn;ei demen bi-fore &thorn;at men wolen teche heresie; as &yogh;if &thorn;ei weren euene wi&thorn; god knowynge mennys hertis. And &yogh;if pore men seyn &thorn;e so&thorn;e &thorn;at no man may a&yogh;en seie, &thorn;an prelatis seyn &thorn;at it is <NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE>seyd for euyl entent &amp; so hyndren &thorn;e treu&thorn;e &amp; taken vp hem &thorn;e dom &thorn;at is<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> reseruyd to god him self, &amp; &thorn;erfore &thorn;ei ben blasphemes.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="17" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 17<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis distroien most &thorn;e obedience &amp; mekenesse of goddis lawe, for &thorn;ei seie &thorn;at &thorn;ei owen not to be suget to seculer lordis to paien hem taxis in helpe of &thorn;e comunes, &amp; owen not to be amendid bi here sugetis of here opyn synnes, but only of &thorn;e pope &thorn;at is here souereyn; &amp; he of no man in her&thorn;e for he is greteste of alle. for oure lord ih&umacr; crist was suget to &thorn;e he&thorn;ene emperour &amp; paide him tribute for hym &amp; his chirche, &amp; &yogh;it he hadde no seculer lordischipe ne plente of dymes, moche more schulden <MILESTONE N="89" UNIT="page"> &thorn;es riche prestis, &thorn;at han seculer lordischipe a&yogh;enst goddis lawe &amp; grete Iuelis &amp; plente of worldly goodis, helpe &thorn;e kyng &amp; &thorn;e lond to meyntene pore men in reste &amp; charite. &amp; si&thorn; crist was most meke &amp; most obediente to al men, And &thorn;es prelatis ben vikeris of crist to &yogh;eue ensaumple of mekenesse, &thorn;ei owen to be most meke &amp; obedient to alle here sugetis; for bi goddis lawe eche man owe&thorn; to be suget &amp; obedient eche to o&thorn;ere in &thorn;e drede of crist. Also in dede &thorn;ei schewen most rebelte a&yogh;enst god &amp; cristene men, lyuynge in pride, coueitise, idelnesse, extorsions, lecherie, glotyne &amp; wastynge of pore mennus gooddis, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei ben lik to lucifer &amp; ben anticristis, holdynge hem self more wor&thorn;i &thorn;an euere was ih&umacr; crist god &amp; man. And it seme&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ei techen here sugetis heresie bi here false open lif, for here lif schulde be bokis of <SUP>3</SUP>o&thorn;ere sugetis vnder hem, &amp; as bokes ben<SUP>3</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">3_3 This is added at the bottom of the page in a later hand, and sugetis is written sugenes.</NOTE> false &thorn;at techen heresie, so ben &thorn;es prelatis heretikis &thorn;at techen &amp; meyntenen synne bi here cursed ensaumple &yogh;euynge.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="18" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000153.tif" N="87">
<HEAD>Capitulum 18<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Prelatis also ben worse &thorn;an iewis &thorn;at naileden crist on &thorn;e cros, for &thorn;ei pursuen crist in his membris for &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;e treu&thorn;e a&yogh;enst here cursed lif, &amp; sclaundren hem wi&thorn; lesingis, &amp; cursen hem &amp; prisonen hem &amp; slen hem, algatis in wille. And, as crist sei&thorn;, it is all on to dispise &amp; pursue on &thorn;at sei&thorn; &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of crist &amp; to pursue crist god &amp; man. And &thorn;is newe pursuynge of prelatis is don bi more sutil ypocrisie &amp; after more benefice resceyued of cristis passion, &amp; whanne it were most nede to haue helpe in goddis cause a&yogh;enst anticristis clerkis<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &thorn;at destroyen &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of cristis lif &amp; his apostlis in word &amp; dede; &amp; &yogh;it prelatis resceyuen &amp; axen gredely &thorn;at ilke money for whiche iust blood is spilt, &thorn;at &thorn;e iewis wolden not do; &amp; ouer &thorn;is prelatis sillen cristene soulis to sathanas for money, &amp; so in manere defoulen cristis blood &amp; setten it at nou&yogh;t; &amp; bisien hem ny&yogh;t &amp; day hou &thorn;ei may bi anticristis iurdiccion &amp; feyned censures stoppe prestis, &thorn;at &thorn;ei prechen not &thorn;e gospel to delyuere soulis out of &thorn;e deuelis bondis.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="19" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 19<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Prelatis also maken hem self most vnable to kepe &thorn;e gospel of crist bi here grete bysynesse abouten roten goodis, &amp; bi pompe &amp; bost of &thorn;is world, for &thorn;ei ben most bisi of alle men in &thorn;e world to geten worldly goodis bi purchase, &amp; to holden hem bi false plee, &amp; disdeyne to see a pore mannus ri&yogh;t &amp; worche after good conscience, but &yogh;if ony man kaste to helpe pore men in here ri&yogh;t a&yogh;enst grete prelatis he schal haue here enemyte, &amp; be sclaundrid to &thorn;e kyng &amp; grete lordis, &amp; pursued bi false cautelis til he be vndon, &yogh;if &thorn;ei may bi ony lesyng. so &thorn;at whanne &thorn;ei schulden ben most wilful pore &amp; preche &thorn;e gospel <MILESTONE N="90" UNIT="page"> of cristis pouert &amp; his apostlis, &thorn;ei may not for schame, for sclaundryng of hem self, and lest &thorn;ei maken here owen ypocrisie knowen to &thorn;e peple; &amp; herefore &thorn;ei 
<PB REF="00000154.tif" N="88"> hiden cristis pouert fro &thorn;e peple, &amp; lien vpon hym cursedly to coloure here worldly lif; for here &thorn;ou&yogh;t, speche, cost &amp; traueile is more aboute worldly goodis &thorn;an goddis lawe in studynge &amp; techynge &amp; holy lif of hem self &amp; &thorn;e peple. And in worldly aray &amp; wast meyne &amp; grete corseris &amp; clo&thorn;is of gold &amp; worldly armure &thorn;ei passen erlis, &amp; atteynen to kyngis aray in bataile to slee cristene men wi&thorn; here owen cruel &amp; cursed hondis; but hou may &thorn;ei preche &thorn;e gospel of pacience, meknesse, pees and charite in &thorn;is cursed vengaunce takynge? certis &thorn;ei ben sathanas kny&yogh;ttys, turned in-to angelis of li&yogh;t bi name of prestod and religion, to disceyue cristene peple in fei&thorn;, hope &amp; charite. but woo to suche anticristis prelatis, &thorn;us blasphemynge crist &amp; sclaundrynge cristene men.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="20" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 20<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis techen &amp; hiren lordis &amp; comunes &amp; clerkis to blaspheme god &amp; dispise his lawe &amp; ordynaunce; for &thorn;ei techen lordis &amp; alle o&thorn;ere men to meyntene hem in worldly lordschipis, pompe &amp; pride, coueitise, extorsions, piliynge &amp; robbynge of &thorn;e peple vnder colour of holy correccion. &amp; notwi&thorn;stondynge &thorn;at goddis lawe &amp; ensaumple of cristis pore life dampnen<NOTE PLACE="foot">dampnem X.</NOTE> seculer lordschipis in clerkis &amp; coueitise &amp; worldly lif, &yogh;it &thorn;ei graunten pardon wi&thorn;-outen mesure &amp; &yogh;ouen grete benefices &amp; huge tresour of gold &amp; worldly fauour &amp; sathanas blissyng to lordis, clerkis &amp; comineris, for to meyntene anticristis worldly clerkis in &thorn;es synnes a&yogh;enst god &amp; his halwen, &amp; for to pursue &amp; sclaundre &amp; enprisone &amp; slee &amp; brenne pore prestis &thorn;at techen holy writt &amp; cristis gospel of pouert &amp; mekenesse a&yogh;enst here worldly lif. &amp; to &thorn;is ende &thorn;es wickid ydolatrours, worschiperis of false goddis, graunten to &thorn;es manquelleris out of bileue &amp; charite pardons, part of massis &amp; o&thorn;ere preieris, &yogh;e to flee to heuene bi-fore &thorn;e bodi be cold, &amp; &thorn;us blynde anticristis prelatis leden blynde lordis, clerkis &amp; comunes to helle for coueitise &amp; brekynge of goddis comaundementis.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="21" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000155.tif" N="89">
<HEAD>Capitulum 21<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Prelatis also setten more pris bi here owen tradicions, maade for to meyntene here pride &amp; worldly wynnynge, &thorn;an bi &thorn;e gospel of ih&umacr; crist; for &thorn;ei studien faste &amp; techen here owene constitucions, &amp; ponyschen men<NOTE PLACE="foot">more X.</NOTE> sore &yogh;if &thorn;ei don ou&yogh;t a&yogh;enst hem or kunnen hem not, but &thorn;ei studien litel or nou&yogh;t cristis gospel &amp; lesse techen it, &amp; recken lest &thorn;ou&yogh; men kunnen not &thorn;e gospel ne kepen it not; but faste &thorn;ei techen &thorn;e nede &amp; &thorn;e auauntage &amp; trew&thorn;e of here owen lawis, &amp; seyn &thorn;at <MILESTONE N="91" UNIT="page">holy writt is hard, not so nedful as here owen lawes, but it is false to &thorn;e lettere, &amp; men wity&thorn; neuere what it mene&thorn;. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei seyn in dede &thorn;at newe lawes, maade in tyme &thorn;at sathanas is vnbounden of worldly prelatis ful of coueitise symonye &amp; heresie, ben betere &amp; trewere &thorn;an lawe of &thorn;e gospel, maad &amp; tau&yogh;t of ih&umacr; crist god &amp; man; &amp; on &thorn;is ypocrite manere &thorn;ei seyn preuely &thorn;at fonnyd worldly here|tikes ben wiser &amp; trewere &thorn;an &thorn;e holy gost, &thorn;an crist &amp; his apostlis; &yogh;ee &thorn;at &thorn;es worldly clerkis ben wise &amp; trewe &amp; in grete charite, &amp; god &thorn;e trinyte &amp; ih&umacr; crist &amp; his apostlis ben foolis, false &amp; out of charite;<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; X. AA.</NOTE> si&thorn; &thorn;es worldly moldwarpis ful of symonye &amp; heresie maken so open lawis so profitable &amp; so trewe, &amp; god wi&thorn; his helperis make&thorn; derke lawis vnprofitable and vntrewe.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="22" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 22<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis techen &thorn;at &thorn;er nys no &thorn;ing leful in holy chirche in er&thorn;e wi&thorn;-outen leue &amp; confermynge of anticrist, &amp; maken all &thorn;e chirche suget to hym; for &thorn;ei seyn openly &thorn;at &thorn;er is no &thorn;ing leffel among cristene men wi&thorn;-outen leue of &thorn;e bischop of rome, &thorn;ou&yogh; he be anticrist ful of symonye &amp; heresie; for comunly of alle prestis he is most contrarie to crist bo&thorn;e in lif &amp; techynge, &amp; he meyntene&thorn; most synne bi preuylegies, exempcions &amp; longe plees, &amp; he is most 
<PB REF="00000156.tif" N="90"> proud a&yogh;enst cristis mekenesse, most coueitous of worldly goodis &amp; lordschipis a&yogh;enst &thorn;e pouert of crist &amp; his apostlis, &amp; most idel in gostly werkis &amp; occupied in worldly causes a&yogh;enst crist besy traueyle &amp; his apostlis in prechynge of &thorn;e gospel, &amp; most principale sillere of benefices &amp; veyn in|dulgencis &amp; sacramentis where crist comaundi&thorn; men to &yogh;eue frely alle gostli<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &thorn;ingis as &thorn;ei han frely resceyued hem of god. &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;es worldly prelatis feynen &thorn;at it is not lefful to a prest to teche cristis gospel frely wi&thorn;-outen licence of hym or his prelatis vnder hym, &thorn;ou&yogh; god comaunde&thorn; prestis, bi open techynge &amp; his lawe and opyn ensaumple of cristis lif, to teche &thorn;is; &amp; so &thorn;ei menen &thorn;at &yogh;if &thorn;is proude prest &amp; contrarie to crist &amp; his lawe sende not a cristene man<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> bi witnesse of his bullis or letteris of his lowere prelatis he may not fulfil &thorn;e hestis of god ne werkis of mercy; &amp; so &yogh;if &thorn;is principal enemy of crist &amp; his coueitous clerkis wolen lette a cristene man to kepe goddis hestis &amp; poyntis of charite, he mot leue goddis comaundement vndon &amp; obiche to hem at here wille, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei menen &thorn;is ende &thorn;at cristene men may not come to heuene bi kepynge &amp; holdynge of trewe fei&thorn; &amp; charite but &yogh;if anticrist &amp; his worldly clerkis, ful of coueitise, symonye &amp; heresie, ben meyntened in here olde pride &amp; cursednesse a&yogh;enst treu&thorn;e of god almy&yogh;tty; for ellis, as &thorn;ei feynen, &thorn;er may be no bischop no prest <MILESTONE N="92" UNIT="page">ne cristendom ne sacramentis; but certis &thorn;is is foule heresie &amp; blasphemye, for herby cristene men ben suget to anticrist &amp; his symonye &amp; feyned censuris &amp; to sathanas more &thorn;an to ih&umacr; crist &amp; his lawe.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="23" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 23<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Prelatis also ben enemys of pees, conseilouris &amp; meyn|tenouris of werris, &amp; irreguler anemtis god, &amp; here preieris ben cursed; for &thorn;ei dreden &yogh;if lordis weren in reste &amp; pees &thorn;at &thorn;ei schulden perceyue &thorn;e cursednesse of here symonye, 
<PB REF="00000157.tif" N="91"> ypocrisie, coueitise, &amp; robberie of here pore tenauntis, &amp; suffre not prelatis<NOTE PLACE="foot">prestis X.</NOTE> be worldly lordis &amp; tirauntis, as &thorn;ei ben now, &amp; &thorn;er-fore &thorn;ei casten to occupie lordis in werris, and conseilen &thorn;er-to vnder colour of wisdom &amp; charite &thorn;at &thorn;ei may regne in here lustis &amp; coueitise as hem lyke&thorn;. for &yogh;if &thorn;ei weren trewe procuratouris of pees, &thorn;ei schulden gladly &amp; ioiefully coste alle here worldly lordschipis &amp; here flesch &amp; blood &amp; bodily lif to make pees &amp; charite amongis cristene men, &amp; techen lordis and comunes in open sermons and confessions &amp; priue conseillynge &thorn;e peryl of werris, &amp; namely of wrongful werris, &amp; hou harde it is to fi&yogh;tten in charite, &amp; tellen openly &amp; priuely &thorn;e goodnesse &amp; profit of pees &amp; reste, &amp; hou men schulden not haue verray pees but bi holy lif &amp; meyntenynge of treu&thorn;e &amp; ri&yogh;twisnesse &amp; distroiynge of wrong &amp; synnes. but now &thorn;es worldly prelates ben cheef conseilours to werris for pride &amp; coueitise, &amp; ben present in here owene persones in costy array as kyngis, &amp; meyntene many men of armes to slee cristene men in body, &amp; &thorn;ei hem self killen many &thorn;ousand in soule &amp; bodi be cursed ensaumple of euyl lif &amp; meyntenynge in synne for money, &amp; bi cursed conseil priue &amp; apert; &amp; &thorn;er-fore &thorn;ei ben cursed of god &amp; irreguler, &amp; whanne &thorn;ei preien to god &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> holden vp here hondis ful of cristene blood, god sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e prophete ysaie &thorn;at he wole<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isaiah i. 15.</NOTE> not here hem ne resceyue here sacrifices, &amp; bi &thorn;e prophete malachie god curse&thorn; to here blissyngis, &amp; in many places<NOTE PLACE="marg">Malachi ii. 2.</NOTE> of holy writt. for &thorn;ei don not here sacrifices bi mekenesse of herte &amp; mornynge &amp; compunccion for here synnes &amp; &thorn;e peplis, but wi&thorn; knackynge of newe song, as orgen or deschant &amp; motetis of holouris, &amp; wi&thorn; worldly pride of costy vesty|mentis &amp; o&thorn;ere ornementis bou&yogh;t wi&thorn; pore mennus goodis, &amp; suffren hem perische for meschef &amp; laten pore men haue nakid sidis &amp; dede wallis haue grete plente of wast gold.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="24" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000158.tif" N="92">
<HEAD>Capitulum 24<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis distroien &thorn;e ordre &amp; lif of crist &amp; his apostlis bi here worldly lif &amp; array &amp; bost &amp; pride, &amp; bryngen &thorn;e peple in-to heresie of cristis pore lif; for &thorn;ei leuen not as pore prestis aftir crist &amp; his apostlis, but as lordis, &yogh;ee kyngis or emperours, in shynynge vessel &amp; delicat metis &amp; wynes, <MILESTONE N="93" UNIT="page">in fatte hors &amp; precious pellure &amp; ryche clo&thorn;is &amp; proude &amp; leccherous squyeris &amp; meyne, &amp; &thorn;es vanytes wasten pore mennus goodis &amp; suffren hem goo dailes whanne &thorn;ei han nedis to pursue. &amp; wi&thorn; alle &thorn;is &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at &thorn;ei lyuen in &thorn;e staat of cristis apostlis &amp; ben here vikeris &amp; successouris, &amp; maken &thorn;e comune peple bileue &thorn;at crist &amp; his apostlis lyueden &thorn;us; &amp; si&thorn; &thorn;e lif of prelatis is book &amp; in ensaumple to o&thorn;ere sugetis, as lyncolne sei&thorn;, &thorn;es prelates ben heretikes &amp; maistris of heresie, &thorn;at &thorn;ei techen to &thorn;e comunes bi here owen wickid lif &thorn;at is a bok to here sugetis, &amp; &thorn;us for cristis pore lif &amp; meke &amp; traueilous is tau&yogh;t a lordly lif, proud &amp; veyn occupacion of worldlynesse &amp; vanyte of &thorn;is world.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="25" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 25<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Prelatis ouere &thorn;is robben oure lond of mochil tresour, &amp; senden it to aliens &amp; enemys of oure rewme &amp; bryngen a&yogh;en goddis curs &amp; heresie; for &thorn;ei don not here spiritual offis aftir goddis lawe, &amp; &yogh;it gredely gedren dymes &amp; offryngis &amp; procurasies, &amp; senden moche gold coine<NOTE PLACE="foot">senden moche gold to Rome AA.</NOTE> for &thorn;e firste fruytis, &amp; to purchase &amp; apropre to hem moo benefices, preuylegies &amp; indulgences; &amp; &thorn;is is &thorn;efte &amp; symonye &yogh;if goddis lawe &amp; mannus &amp; reson be sou&yogh;t, &amp; &thorn;e sillere of benefices &amp; spiritual &thorn;ingis &amp; &thorn;e &yogh;euere of gold for hem ben cursed of god &amp; man &amp; ben foule heretikis. &amp; sumtyme &thorn;e court of rome his worldly aduersarie to oure lond, &amp; namely in fauour of oure enemys; but more harme is of gostly ennemyte, whanne &thorn;ei enuenymen oure peple wi&thorn; cursed symonye and meyn|tenynge &amp; consent of synne bi blynde obedience. for &yogh;if 
<PB REF="00000159.tif" N="93"> ony worldly prelat wole do ony wrong a&yogh;enst ri&yogh;t &amp; reson, he schal geten a priueilege or exempcion or sentence of curs for his gold sent &amp; spendid at rome, &amp; moche gold go&thorn; out of oure lond bi longe pledynge at rome, &amp; ri&yogh;t born a doun, &amp; synne contyned<NOTE PLACE="foot">conteyned X.</NOTE> &amp; meyntened, &thorn;at vnne&thorn;is dar ony man speke &thorn;era&yogh;enst; and &thorn;us is oure lond robbid of gold, &amp; curs &amp; heresie brou&yogh;t in, and synne longe meyntened, &amp; ri&yogh;twis|nesse stoppid.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="26" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 26<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis seyn &thorn;at holy writt is not sufficient to reule holy chirche, &amp; techeris &thorn;er-of ben not profitable to &thorn;e peple, but here owen statutis maade of synful foolis ben most nedful &amp; techeris &thorn;er-of, And meyntenours of chydynge &amp; strif ben most nedful &amp; profitable to &thorn;e peple. for &yogh;if holy writt were ynow for gouernynge of &thorn;e chirche, it were veyn &amp; vnreson|able to occupie men wi&thorn; moo lawis, si&thorn; men ben now of feblere complexion &amp; lasse wytti &amp; of schortere lif &thorn;an men weren in olde tyme. &amp; it is luciferis pride <MILESTONE N="94" UNIT="page">&amp; more to seie &thorn;at techeris of mannys tradicions maade of synful foolis ben more profitable &amp; nedeful to cristene peple &thorn;an techeris of &thorn;e gospel &amp; goddis comaundementis; but &thorn;er is o cursed cause of alle &thorn;is seiynge; &thorn;ei loue more here owen worldly wynnynge &amp; pride &amp; lustis &thorn;an wynnynge of soulis to blisse by mekenesse &amp; holy lif. And here owen lawes and techeris &thorn;er-of meyntenen &amp; procuren &thorn;is coueitise &amp; lustis, &amp; holy writt &amp; trewe prechours &thorn;er-of dampnen al &thorn;is, &amp; techen wilful pouert &amp; mekenesse &amp; gret traueile &amp; penaunce of clerkis; &amp; &thorn;er-fore &thorn;ei comenden here owen lawes &amp; here techeris, &amp; putten goddis lawe &amp; treue prechouris &thorn;er-of bi|hynde. &amp; heere &thorn;ei putten on crist bo&thorn;e defaute of witt &amp; charite; for si&thorn; crist maade not the beste lawe for holy chirche, as &thorn;ei feynen, &amp; telde not whanne &amp; of whom it schulde be maad, him lackid witt &amp; charite, but certis &thorn;is his foule heresie putt on crist priuely for to meyntene here owen coueitise &amp; pride.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="27" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000160.tif" N="94">
<HEAD>Capitulum 27<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Prelatis constreynen men of symple vnderstondyng to renne in-to errouris &amp; to blaspheme god; for &thorn;ei constreynen suche symple men to assente to here dampnacion of treu&thorn;es of goddis lawe, bi multitude of worldly clerkis blynde &thorn;orou&yogh; coueitise &amp; pride, &amp; bi manas &amp; drede of prisonynge and brennynge, &amp; suffren not men to resten in holy writt &amp; in &thorn;ingis &thorn;at &thorn;ei may understonde, but constreyne hem to assente to nowelries of newe doctours, &thorn;at leuen holy writt &amp; reson &amp; feynen dremes &amp; myraclis to plese coueitous clerkis &amp; to greet veyn glorie for here witt, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei bileuen blyndly in many poyntis a&yogh;enst goddis doom. And &yogh;it &thorn;es prelatis desceyuen lordis &amp; maken hem pursue &amp; prisone trewe men &thorn;at wolen not assente to errouris ouer holy writt and reson. And &thorn;us &thorn;es prelatis ben anticristis turmentours of sathanas for to pursue &amp; sle trewe prestis in goddis lawe, &amp; maken lordis turmentours of &thorn;e fend to ponysche cristene men, for &thorn;ei holden &thorn;e boundes of holy writt &amp; meyntenen &thorn;e trew&thorn;e of cristis lif a&yogh;enst worldly prelatis ful of coueitise &amp; heresie.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="28" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 28<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis closen or stoppen &thorn;e weie to &thorn;e blisse of heuene &amp; open &thorn;e brode weie to helle; for &thorn;ei stoppen &amp; letten men fro kunnynge &amp; kepynge &amp; techynge of holy writt, &thorn;at is entre &amp; ri&yogh;t weie to &thorn;e blisse of heuene, &amp; neden men to bisien hem aboute studiynge &amp; kepynge &amp; techyng of synful mennys tradicions ful of errour, &thorn;at ben maad for pride &amp; coueitise, &amp; also to lerne pride &amp; coueitise &amp; worldly lif &amp; to haunte &amp;<MILESTONE N="95" UNIT="page"> meyntene suche wrecchid worldly lif of clerkys, &amp; &thorn;is is &thorn;e brode weie to helle. Sumtyme men hadden traueile &amp; werke at &thorn;e ful to studie &amp; kepe &amp; teche goddis lawe bi-fore &thorn;at &thorn;es newe lawes of worldly clerkis weren brou&yogh;t vp, &amp; nowe men ben occupied aboute 
<PB REF="00000161.tif" N="95"> lernynge &amp; techyng of hem in alle here lif, &thorn;at vnne&thorn;e may &thorn;ei loke &amp; sauoure holy writt in here laste dayes; &amp; he &thorn;at can not &thorn;es worldly statutis maad for singuler wille and coueitise is hoolden but a fool and vnable to teche &amp; reule cristene peple, &thorn;ou&yogh; he kunne and kepe &amp; teche neuere so wel cristis gospel &amp; goddis comaundementis. &amp; to &thorn;is ende &thorn;es worldly moldwerpis taken keies of helle in stede of keies of &thorn;e kyngdom of heuenes, for &thorn;ei taken ypocrisie &amp; worldly tirauntrie &amp; bostful worldly lif, &amp; meyntenynge of synne bi fals pardon &amp; fals absolucion &amp; cursed preieris, &amp; leuen kunnynge &amp; techynge of holy writt &amp; edefiynge of cristene soules to heuene by good ensaumple of here holy lif.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="29" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 29<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Prelatis also maken lordis turmentouris of sathanas to prisone cristene men for &thorn;ei holden goddis lawe; for &thorn;ei maken lordis to enprisone men whanne &thorn;ei dwellen fourti daies in sentence of curs, &amp; here owene lawe techi&thorn; opynly &thorn;at men schullen dwelle in curs bi al here lif vp peyne of dampnacion, has whanne a man ha&thorn; weddid a womman sibbe to him in degree of consanguinyte or kyn wiche<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> degre is forboden in holy writt, &amp; ha&thorn; not witnesse ynowe to proue &thorn;is in mannus dom, &thorn;ou&yogh; he knowe it neuere so certeynly, he schal be cursed in constorie &amp; may not ryse out of &thorn;is curs, for &thorn;anne he schulde do wyttyngly a&yogh;enst goddis hestis &amp; his conscience, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;is man schal euere in &thorn;is lif be cursed for he wil not wyttyngly do a&yogh;enst goddis comaunde|mentis &amp; his ri&yogh;t conscience. &para; lord, what charite is it to prisone sich a man, &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;es anticristis clerkis cursen men al day for money for techyng of goddis lawe &amp; for werkis of mercy &amp; ri&yogh;twisnesse, &amp; for &thorn;at &thorn;ei wolen not assente to errouris a&yogh;enst holy writt expresly &amp; a&yogh;enst reson. &para; Lord god, hou schullen anticristis mynystris of ri&yogh;twisnesse be 
<PB REF="00000162.tif" N="96"> excused at &thorn;e day of dom, si&thorn; &thorn;ei enprisone falsly trewe men bi fals disceit of worldly heretikys; &thorn;er-fore &thorn;es lordis schulden be certeyn &thorn;at &thorn;e curs were ri&yogh;tful, &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;e man were endurid in synne &amp; drede not god ne his vengaunce, &amp; &thorn;an ponysche&thorn; hym til he wolde drede god and amende his lif, &amp; not til he wolde &yogh;eue money to anticristis clerkis at here wille.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="30" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 30<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis disceyuen cristene men bi licknesse <MILESTONE N="96" UNIT="page">of apis &amp; bi argumentis of glotones til &thorn;e peple breke goddis hestis &amp; meytenen hem in here cursed lustis. For apis whanne &thorn;ei seen a man don ony &thorn;ing bi hem wolen assaie to don &thorn;e same dedis til &thorn;ei ben perischid for defaute of crafte or kunnynge; &amp; glotones arguen &thorn;us, si&thorn; it is good to me to ete or drynke &thorn;us moche, And more mete &amp; drynk is betere, &thorn;an it is betere to me to ete &amp; drynk &thorn;us moche more; &amp; bi &thorn;is colour &thorn;ei cessen not til &thorn;ei heten &amp; drynkyne her legges &amp; hondis out of my&yogh;t &amp; here heuyd out of witt &amp; ben as dede hogges. &THORN;us faren &thorn;e worldly prelatis. &THORN;ei seyn, si&thorn; &thorn;e peple schulden worschipe gregorii, petir &amp; poule, &amp; o&thorn;ere trewe apostlis of crist, &amp; &thorn;ei comen in &thorn;e staat of apostlis, &thorn;anne &thorn;e peple schulden worschipen hem &thorn;us moche. but &thorn;ei taken no rewarde hou &thorn;es apostlis comen to &thorn;is staat, bi ordeynynge &amp; chesynge of god &amp; for holy lif &amp; trewe seruyce &thorn;at &thorn;ei diden to cristene peple, in trewe techynge of &thorn;e holy gospel bo&thorn;e in word &amp; dede; &amp; hou &thorn;ei comen to here staat by symonye, bi chesynge of worldly clerkis, &amp; in cas quyke deuelis in flech &amp; blood, &amp; don<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> not here office but lyuen in pride, coueitise, robberie of &thorn;e peple, &amp; in fleschly lustis &thorn;at cristis apostelis deden not. Also &thorn;ei arguen &thorn;us, si&thorn; petir &amp; poul &amp; o&thorn;ere apostlis of crist hadden keies of heuene &amp; power to bynde &amp; vnbynde synnes, whiche doynge was confermed in heuene, &amp; we ben in &thorn;e staat &amp; 
<PB REF="00000163.tif" N="97"> successouris of hem, &thorn;an we han &thorn;e same power; but &thorn;ei loken litel &thorn;at mannus eleccion maki&thorn; hem not in sich staat, but chesynge of god &amp; kunnynge of holy writt, &amp; souereyn traueile &amp; holy lif, &amp; techynge &amp; meyntenynge of &thorn;e gospel, &amp; brennynge charite to de&thorn;e for goddis loue, &amp; sauynge of cristene soulis; &amp; comunly &thorn;ei ben fer fro alle &thorn;es goodnesse &amp; wlappid in pride &amp; coueitise &amp; moo synnes. Also &thorn;es worldly moldwarpis arguen &thorn;us as glotons; si&thorn; it is good to prestis to haue worldly goodis for here necessarie liflode &amp; helynge, as poul techi&thorn; &amp; reson, &amp; &thorn;anne &thorn;e more &thorn;e betre; til &thorn;ei ben smyten in coueitise &amp; occupacion of &thorn;is world, &thorn;at &thorn;ei sauouren nou&yogh;t of gostly &thorn;ingis, but riot &amp; pride &amp; roten muk of &thorn;is world. &amp; &yogh;if it be good to haue holy writt &amp; presthod and kny&yogh;thod and laboreris to serue god &amp; reule &thorn;e peple; &thorn;an it is betre to make moo newe lawis &amp; moo ordris in &thorn;e chirche, til &thorn;e lawe of god be for&yogh;eten &amp; newe tradicions in excercise &amp; newe ordris magnyfied more &thorn;anne &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> clene ordre &thorn;at crist made himself; &amp; bi &thorn;es iapis &thorn;ei disceyuen &thorn;e peple, &amp; gedren to hem<MILESTONE N="97" UNIT="page"> self &thorn;e goodis of &thorn;is world &amp; magnyfien hemself, here ordris, &amp; here lawes more &thorn;an crist &amp; his lawis, &amp; maken &thorn;e peple to holden vp &thorn;is ypocrisie &amp; heresie.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="31" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 31<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Prelates also spoilen lordis of here rentis bi dowynge of &thorn;e chirche, &amp; lowe curatis bi approprynge of parische chirchis &amp; bi pencions &amp; cost of here officeris, &amp; &thorn;ei robben &thorn;e pore peple bi veyn priueylegies &amp; feyned halwynge of chirches, auteris and chirche&yogh;erdis, &amp; o&thorn;ere sacramentis seld for money and by annuel rentis for lecherie &amp; o&thorn;ere synnes; &amp; here|fore &thorn;ei may be wel licned to swolwis of &thorn;e see &amp; helle, &thorn;at resceyuen al &thorn;at &thorn;ei may &amp; &yogh;elden not a&yogh;en; &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei &thorn;at schulden most forsake &thorn;e worlde &amp; worldly coueitise &amp; vanyte ben most sette in &thorn;e world &amp; leste coueiten heuene 
<PB REF="00000164.tif" N="98"> &amp; gostly goodis; &amp; &thorn;ei &thorn;at schulden most lede &thorn;e peple to heuene, bi trewe techynge of holy writt &amp; ensaumple of wilful pouert &amp; mekenesse &amp; bisy traueile in praieris &amp; deuocions &amp; penaunce, leden &thorn;e peple to helle bi here worldly lawis, coueitise, pride &amp; queyntise of &thorn;e world, &amp; ydelnesse &amp; glotonye &amp; fleschly lustis; &amp; hou &thorn;ei robben &thorn;es parties it is open ynow&yogh;, &thorn;er-fore we moten telle of more ypocrisie lesse knowen.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="32" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 32<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis chargen more here park &amp; br[e]kynge &thorn;er-of &thorn;an goddis hestis &amp; brekynge of hem. &para; For &thorn;ei pursuen more &amp; cruelliere for brekynge of here parkis &thorn;an for brekynge of goddis comaundementis to saue here soulis bi spiritual medecyne; &amp; &thorn;ei ben more bisy to loke &thorn;at here park be wel kepte &thorn;anne to loke &thorn;at goddis hestis<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> ben kepte of goddis peple; &amp; &thorn;ei receruen assoilynge for brekynge of here park to hem self, but &thorn;ei &yogh;euen assoylynge for brekynge of goddis hestis to eche parische prest or curat. For &thorn;ei holden here park more derwor&thorn;i to hem &thorn;an &thorn;e comaundementis of god, &amp; seken more bisily here owen worldly worschipe and<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;an X</NOTE> couetise &thorn;an honour of god &amp; sauynge of cristene soulis; &amp; here is ydolatrie &amp; heresie open ynow&yogh;, &amp; blasphemye of god among worldly &amp; he&thorn;en men.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="33" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 33<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Prelatis also entren vnder colour &amp; studie of cristis apostlis &amp; lyuen &amp; teche contrariously to hem &amp; don most harm to cristendom, &yogh;ee more &thorn;an ony soudon or sarsyn or o&thorn;er men of wrong bileue. &para; For si&thorn; &thorn;is stat is most wort&thorn;i in &thorn;e chirche, &amp; &thorn;ei lyuen so worldly &amp; synfully &thorn;er-inne &amp; turnen it vpsodon, &thorn;ei distroien most &thorn;e goode lif of cristen|dom &amp; techen most perilous heresye. And herefore &thorn;ei 
<PB REF="00000165.tif" N="99"> bicomen &thorn;e deuelis iogelours to blynde mennus gostly ei&yogh;en; &thorn;ei maken men wene &thorn;at here worldly lif &amp; cursed ys &thorn;e holy lif of cristis apostlis, &amp; &thorn;us bryngen in errour &amp; heresie in &thorn;e peple, &amp; ben sathanas transfigurid in-to an aungel of li&yogh;t, &amp; verrefien &thorn;is word of holy writt, &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben made a spectacle to angelis &amp; men, but on euyl manere, where &thorn;ei<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. iv. 9.</NOTE> schulden ben <MILESTONE N="98" UNIT="page">a spectacle of angelis &amp; men to loken onne with ioie for here stronge fi&yogh;ttynge a&yogh;enst enemys of soule bi mekenesse, wilful pouert, &amp; grete traueile in techynge of &thorn;e gospel, &amp; suffrynge of peynes &amp; de&thorn;. &THORN;erfore in en|saumple of cristene men to sue hem in &thorn;es poyntis &thorn;ei ben a spectacle to angelis &amp; men to wonder on here cursed pride, coueitise &amp; ydelnesse in gostly traueile, &amp; cowardise in cristis bataile, &amp; letten charite of cristene men bi here euyl en|saumple, &amp; &thorn;us in stede of cristis apostlis ben comen in viserid deuelis, to disceyuen men in good lif &amp; bryngen hem to sathanas here maister, &amp; in<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &thorn;is manere &thorn;ei pleien &thorn;e pagyn of scottis; for as scottis token &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> skochen of armes of seynt george &amp; here-bi traieden englischemen, so &thorn;es anticristis prelatis taken name &amp; staat of cristis apostlis, as &yogh;if &thorn;ei wolden helpe &amp; lede cristene men &thorn;e ri&yogh;tte weie to heuene as &thorn;ei diden, but here-bi &thorn;ei betraien cristene men in-to synne by suynge of here techynge &amp; cursed lif, &amp; leden hem faste &thorn;e weie to helle.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="34" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 34<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis constreynen prestis to lese charite &amp; blaspheme crist &amp; disceyue his peple; for &thorn;ei neden prestis to fi&yogh;tte &amp; werre in here owen persone a&yogh;enst cristene men, &amp; here abouten spende pore mennys liflode for to hauen a veyn name of hardynesse &amp; &thorn;ank of lordis &thorn;at kunnen nei&thorn;er witt ne reson; for &thorn;ei senden opyn comissions to alle curatis vndir here deuelis iurdiccions bi vertue of mahoundis obedience &amp; bi manas of &thorn;e kyngis power to make hem 
<PB REF="00000166.tif" N="100"> redi wi&thorn; armure to werre iolily a&yogh;enst cristene men. &para; And here-by is armure of pacience and charite and holi preiere &amp; trist in god putt awey, &amp; &thorn;e deuelis lawe of cruelte, enemyte &amp; veyn trist in mannys my&yogh;t brou&yogh;t in. But goddis curs renne&thorn; many &thorn;ousand tyme wi&thorn; al &thorn;is. &amp; here-bi ben half dede men confortid to fi&yogh;tte &amp; slee cristene men &amp; rennen to helle hedly; &amp; so &thorn;es worldly prelatis ben chef capteyns &amp; arraiouris of sathanas batailis to exile good lif &amp; charite, but certis no tonge in &thorn;is lif may telle hou many soulis gon to helle bi &thorn;es cursede capteyns &amp; anticristis iurdiccion &amp; censures.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="35" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 35<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Prelatis also ben weiward ypocritis, blynde lederis, swol|wynge &thorn;e grete cameile al hool &amp; siynge or clensynge a litel gnatte; for &thorn;ei resceyuen &amp; purchasen bi gret ypocrisie seculer lordischipis, a&yogh;enst goddis lawe olde &amp; newe &amp; en|saumple of cristis lif &amp; his apostlis, as lefful, profytable &amp; nedeful; &amp; forsaken as venym matrimonye, &thorn;at is leffel bi holy writt, til newe vowis of contynense of worldli clerkis weren brou&yogh;t in bi disceit of &thorn;e fend. For many prestis now kepen nei&thorn;er matrimonye ne charite, but defoulen wyues, maidenes, widewis &amp; nunnes in eche manere of lecherie, &amp; children ben mor&thorn;erid, &amp; synne a&yogh;enst kynde is not <MILESTONE N="99" UNIT="page">clene fleed. For sathanas caste to purchase worldly honour &amp; plente of worldly goodis &amp; welfare &amp; ydelnesse to &yogh;onge prestis, &amp; dalliaunce wi&thorn; wommen &amp; priue rownyng; &amp; is redy ny&yogh;t &amp; day to stere bo&thorn;e partis to leccherie, &amp; sumtyme to hyden here synne bi fals o&thorn;is &amp; mor&thorn;eryng of children, &amp; sumtyme haunten it opynly &amp; schamen not &thorn;er-of; &amp; her-bi hei&yogh;e prelatis wynnen many &thorn;ousand pondis in fewe &yogh;eris &amp; holden grete housholde as lordis, &amp; &thorn;us by &thorn;is ypocrisie in bo&thorn;e poyntis ben lordis &amp; prestis &amp; comunes encombrid, &amp; goddis lawe dispisid &amp; broken, &amp; synnes gedrid in grete hordis.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="36" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000167.tif" N="101">
<HEAD>Capitulum 36<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis bi sotil ypocrisie horden &amp; meyntenen here synne &amp; o&thorn;ere mennys; for &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at in here absence men may not speke a&yogh;enst here open cursed synnes for synne of bacbitynge &amp; schlaundrynge; &amp; &thorn;ei ben so malicious &amp; my&yogh;tti in worldly power &thorn;at &thorn;ei wolen suffre no man to speke a&yogh;enst her synnes in here presence; &amp; so &thorn;ei wolden bi ypocrisie haue &thorn;is ende, &thorn;at no man schulde speke opynli &amp; sadly a&yogh;enst here cursednesse in no manere, but suffre hem wexe roten in here lustis &amp; robbe &thorn;e peple &amp; disceyue cristendom wi&thorn;-outen ony letting; but certis &thorn;es anticristis clerkis lien falsly a&yogh;enst cristis lore &amp; profite of cristene men. For crist &amp; his apostlis reproueden pharisees &amp; heroude &amp; heretikis in here absence &amp; to &thorn;e peple, as gospillis &amp; pistles witnessen, to oure ensaumple to do so with charite &amp; discrecion, &amp; &thorn;ei ben sclaundrid bi-fore god &amp; his angelis &amp; goode men in er&thorn;e bi here opyn cursed lif; &amp; &thorn;o men &thorn;at reprouen bi charite &amp; discrecion here opyn synnes helpen to amenden here synnes &amp; don awei here sclaundre; but of sclaundre anemptis god &amp; his angelis recken &thorn;ei not, but alle here care is last here ypocrisie bi knowen to lordis &amp; my&yogh;tty men, for drede of takyng awey of here temporal lordischipis &thorn;at ben cause of here synful lyf. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei ben cursed of god; for &thorn;at &thorn;ing &thorn;at is verrey sclaundre &thorn;ei clepen &amp; reckenen as no sclaundre, &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;ing &thorn;at is no sclaundre but remedie &thorn;er a&yogh;enst &thorn;ei crien &amp; clepen sclaundre; but alle &thorn;is is for &thorn;ei wolden dwelle stille in robbyng of &thorn;e peple &amp; here cursed lustis &amp; sclaundre, &amp; disceyue cristen men in good techynge and ensaumple of holy lif.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="37" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 37<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Prelatis also blasphemen god &amp; techen o&thorn;ere men to don &thorn;e same; for &thorn;ei lyuem hem self in pride &amp; coueitise &amp; louen &amp; norischen &amp; meyntenen suche vicious folis, &amp; haten 
<PB REF="00000168.tif" N="102"> &amp; dispisen mekenesse &amp; wilful pouert, &amp; so &thorn;ei don vertuouse men &amp; oppressen hem; &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei conspiren a&yogh;enst crist<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &amp; his vertuous lif &amp; his meke seruauntis, &amp; ben sathanas procuratouris to meyntene synful men in his seruyce. For certis &thorn;ei ben cursed of god &yogh;if &thorn;ei meyntenen wityngly &amp; wilfully <MILESTONE N="100" UNIT="page">proude lordis &amp; leccherours of here owne meynne in here housholde; for &yogh;if &thorn;ei loueden god &amp; &thorn;e soulis of here seruauntis &thorn;ei schulden amende &thorn;is cursed lif or ellis putten hem out of here companye; but now for pride of hem self &amp; wynnyng of drit &thorn;ei holden for&thorn; suche cursed meyne to sclaundre o&thorn;ere men. &para; But as crist and poul witnessen, suche prelatis ben cursed, &amp; forsaken cristis fei&thorn;, &amp; ben werse &thorn;an he&thorn;en men &thorn;at neuere resceyueden cristendom.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="38" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 38<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis disceyuen cristene men in fei&thorn;, hope &amp; charite bi here nouelerie of massis at rome, at scala celi, &amp; newe pardons &amp; pilgrimages; for &thorn;ei maken &thorn;e peple to bileue or triste &thorn;at &yogh;if a prest seye a masse at scala celi for a soule it schal onoon ben out of purgatorie, &thorn;ou&yogh; god of his ri&yogh;twis|nesse ordeyne &thorn;at soule to abide &thorn;ere fourty &yogh;ere or mo, &amp; &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;e prest be cursed for symonye &amp; pride; for as &thorn;ei feynen falsly &thorn;e masse may not be peirid. certis &thorn;e sacra|ment may not be paired for synne of &thorn;e prest; but &thorn;e preiers of cursed prestis in &thorn;e masse ben cursed of god &amp; his angelis, &amp; certis a prest may be so cursed &amp; in heresie &thorn;at he maki&thorn; not &thorn;e sacrament. &amp; god only knowi&thorn; whanne his synne is in &thorn;at degre &amp; whanne in lesse, but euere it is harmful to him &thorn;at make&thorn; &thorn;e sacrament vnwor&thorn;ily. &amp; bi &thorn;es feyned pardons &thorn;e peple leue&thorn; to do here almesse to pore nedy men enprisoned bi god himself &amp; do&thorn; it to ryche men &amp; wasteris, &amp; hopi&thorn; to haue more &thorn;ank of god &thorn;er-by &thorn;an to do it aftyr cristis owne techynge; &amp; &thorn;es prelatis chargen more folye 
<PB REF="00000169.tif" N="103"> avowis of siche pilgrimagis &amp; brekynge of hem, &thorn;an &thorn;e strong comaundementis of god &amp; brekynge of hem, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;e peple dredi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">drawi&thorn; X.</NOTE> more to breke &thorn;is folie avowis maad of here owen errour &thorn;an to breke goddis comaundementis, &amp; louen more here folye avowis to fulfille hem &thorn;an to fulfille goddis hestis; &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei ben disceyued bi &thorn;es nouelries in fei&thorn;, hope &amp; charite bi &thorn;es anticristis prelatis.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="39" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 39<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Prelatis also ben malicious foxis &amp; rauyschynge wolues, oppressynge pore curatis &amp; annuel prestis in here iurdiccion; for whanne &thorn;e kyng &amp; lordis axeden of grete prelatis subsidies &amp; dymes for here temperaltes &thorn;ei graunten hem so &thorn;at pore curatis &amp; annueleris may be taxid at here settyng; &amp; so alle &thorn;e charge falli&thorn; on here pore curatis, &amp; o&thorn;ere &amp; &thorn;e riche prelatis gon free or hellis wynnen a porcion to hem self of goodis of here pore curatis. &amp; &thorn;us whanne &thorn;ei han robbid lordis bi ypocrisie of here temperal lordischipis sotylly &amp; wrongfully &thorn;ei rauyschen &thorn;e goodis of pore prestis vnder hem; &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei don wrong to lordis, wrong to pore curatis, &amp; to pore comunes also; &amp; bi &thorn;es seculer lordischipis &thorn;at &thorn;ei han be ypocrisie &thorn;ei ben <MILESTONE N="101" UNIT="page">emperours &amp; tirauntis of o&thorn;ere prestis. &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ei owen to be most meke of alle o&thorn;ere, and most bisi in studiynge &amp; techynge of holy writt &amp; ensaumple of alle goode manere of lif, bo&thorn;e to cristene men &amp; to he&thorn;ene; but alle &thorn;es gostly goodis ben rauysched &amp; stolen from holy chirche, &amp; contrarie synnes brou&yogh;t in in stede of hem bi &thorn;is dowynge of prestis wi&thorn; seculer lordischipis; &amp; &thorn;is is werse &thorn;an rauyschynge &amp; stelynge of alle worldli goodis &amp; sleynge of many &thorn;ousand of mannus bodies, as soulis &amp; vertues ben betre &thorn;an roten drit.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="40" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000170.tif" N="104">
<HEAD>Capitulum 40<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Also prelatis ben doumbe houndis &thorn;at may not berke in<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isaiah lvi. 10.</NOTE> tyme of most nede but ben traitours to god &amp; his peple; for &thorn;ei ben so chokid wi&thorn; talow of worldly goodis and oc|cupacion abouten hem, &thorn;at &thorn;ei may not preche &thorn;e gospel &amp; warne &thorn;e peple of &thorn;e deuelis disceitis; &amp; si&thorn; &thorn;ei taken &thorn;e charge &amp; offis to lede &thorn;e peple bi so perilous weies &amp; enemyes bi trewe prechynge of &thorn;e gospel &amp; ensaumple of here owne holy lif, &amp; suffren cristene soulis be stranglid wi&thorn; woluys of helle &thorn;orou&yogh; here doumbnesse &amp; occupiynge aboute &thorn;e world, &thorn;ei ben cursed traitours to god &amp; his peple; &amp; &yogh;it to fulfille &thorn;e fendis cruelte &thorn;ei pursuen &amp; cursen &yogh;if ony pore prest wole preche freli cristis gospel &amp; delyuere cristene soulis oute of &thorn;e fendis hondis &amp; leden hem &thorn;e ri&yogh;tte weie to heuene. alle cristene men schulden crie out on &thorn;is false treson &amp; fendis malice &amp;, as crist sei&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel, casten hem out of cristene mennus companye for here olde heresies &amp; cursed disceit of cristene soulis; for &thorn;ei han maad a preue couenaunt wi&thorn; sathanas here maister, &thorn;at he schal haue soulis of here feyned iurdiccion so &thorn;at &thorn;ei haue here worldly pride &amp; coueitise &amp; ydelnesse &amp; fleschly lustis at here wille: but woo to suche traitours of cristene peple.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="41" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 41<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>&YOGH;it worldly prelatis gostly don crist on &thorn;e cros &amp; sleen his prophetis &amp; his apostlis; for &thorn;ei don cristis holy lif &amp; techynge, &amp; so in a manere crist hym self, on &thorn;e cros of lesyngis &amp; bitraien him to he&thorn;ene men whanne &thorn;ei &yogh;euen cure of soulis to worldly foolis, werse &thorn;an ben he&thorn;ene houndis. And so &thorn;ei don crist on &thorn;e cros of vnkyndenesse &amp; dispit, And hereby dispisen hym more &thorn;an diden iewis nailynge crist on bodili cros. and seynt ion crisostom, or wi&thorn; &thorn;e gildene mou&thorn;, &amp; seynt austyn witnessen plenerly &thorn;is sentence; &amp; bernard sei&thorn; &thorn;at a man &thorn;at synne&thorn; opynly 
<PB REF="00000171.tif" N="105"> a&yogh;enst goddis hestis &amp; &yogh;eue&thorn; cursed ensaumple to o&thorn;ere men dispisi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">dispese&thorn; X.</NOTE> more god &amp; do&thorn; more wrong to hym &thorn;an iewis whanne &thorn;ei naileden him bodely on &thorn;e cros. For crist louede more cristene men<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> soulis &thorn;an his owen bodily lif; &amp; &thorn;is cursed man drawi&thorn; fro crist alle soulis als moche as in him is, &amp; &thorn;e iewis drowyn fro him his bodily lif &thorn;at he louede lasse; &amp; &thorn;ei slen his prophetis &amp; apostlis,<MILESTONE N="102" UNIT="page"> whanne &thorn;ei do cursedly a&yogh;enst here techynge &amp; maken it fals as moche as &thorn;ei kunne: &thorn;is sentence witnessi&thorn; ion crisostom vpon &thorn;e gospel of seynt matheu; &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei sillen crist &amp; bitraien hym for money whanne &thorn;ei forsaken &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of holy writt &amp; holy lif for worldly honour &amp; coueitise, &amp; ambrose &amp; bede witnessen &thorn;is poynt.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="42" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 42.</HEAD>
<P>Prelatis blasphemen a&yogh;enst &thorn;e holy gost; for &thorn;ei quenchen his &yogh;iftis &amp; suffren not cristene men to teche goddis peple wi&thorn; siche &yogh;iftis, but maken hem to waste &thorn;es precious &yogh;iftis; and so as to here entent &amp; to here dampnacion &thorn;ei quenchen &thorn;e holy gost. For in here wille &thorn;ei distroien his werkis, &amp; &thorn;e synne is demed bi &thorn;e entent, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;e ende come not for&thorn; but be lettid bi goddis my&yogh;t. For whanne &thorn;ei ben vnable bi ignoraunce &amp; wickid lif to teche cristene peple goddis lawe, &thorn;ei wollen not suffre trewe men teche frely cristis gospel wi&thorn;-outen here leue &amp; lettris, &thorn;ou&yogh; trewe men ben neuere so mochil charged &amp; stired of god to preche his gospel. but &thorn;ei don &thorn;is for &thorn;ei wolden haue money for here lettris &amp; swerynge &thorn;at men not preche a&yogh;enst here synnes, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei ben neuere so opyn cursed traitours of god &amp; his peple; as men gessen &thorn;at veyn religious don to haue leue of &thorn;es goddis traitours to sewe fablis, cronyclis, &amp; lesyngis for to robbe &thorn;e pore peple aftir-ward bi clamouse beggynge, dampnyd bi goddis lawe; &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei &yogh;euen leue to sathanas preschours for to preche fablis &amp; flaterynge &amp; lesyngis, &amp; to 
<PB REF="00000172.tif" N="106"> disceyue &thorn;e peple in fei&thorn; &amp; good lif &amp; robbe hem of here worldly goodis, &amp; to putten blasphemye vpon crist bi here opyn beggynge &amp; letten cristis prechours to preche frely &thorn;e gospel &thorn;at wole not flatere but seyn &thorn;e so&thorn; to eche man &amp; eche staat aftir goddis lawe. but bi suche ypocrisie &thorn;ei letten &thorn;us prechyng of cristis gospel, last lordis &amp; comunes perceyuen here falsnesse, &thorn;ei forbeden not vtterly &thorn;at men schulden not preche &thorn;e gospel, but &thorn;at men schulden not preche wi&thorn;-outen here leue; &amp; si&thorn; &thorn;ei ben ful of coueitise, symonye, pride, extorsions &amp; o&thorn;ere falsnesse, &thorn;ei wolen &yogh;eue to no man leue &thorn;at &thorn;ei supposen wole seie &thorn;e so&thorn;e &amp; not spare, &amp; so in entente &amp; dede &thorn;ei comaunden &thorn;at no trewe man schal preche &thorn;e gospel. &amp; bi &thorn;is &thorn;ei casten to ende in here coueitise, symonye &amp; robberie &amp; meyntenynge of anticristis chirche, &amp; it is to drede last &thorn;ei enden in &thorn;is blasphemye a&yogh;enst &thorn;e holy gost.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="43" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 43<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>&YOGH;it worldly prelatis blasphemen a&yogh;enst god &thorn;e fadir of heuene; for &thorn;ei taken vpon hem power &thorn;at is specyaly &amp; onely reserued to god; &thorn;at is assoilynge of synnes &amp; ful remission of hem; for &thorn;ei taken on hem principal assoilynge of synnes &amp; maken &thorn;e peple to bileue so; whanne &thorn;ei haue only assoilynge as <MILESTONE N="103" UNIT="page">vikeris or massageris to witnesse to &thorn;e peple &thorn;at god assoili&thorn; for contricion, &amp; ellis nei&thorn;er angele ne man ne god hym self assoili&thorn; but &yogh;if &thorn;e synnere be contrit; &thorn;at is fully haue sorowe for his synnes, &amp; haue wille ra&thorn;ere to suffre los of catel &amp; worldly frendischipe &amp; honour &amp; bodely de&thorn; &thorn;an to do wityngly a&yogh;enst goddis comaundement &amp; wille; &amp; &thorn;ei chargen more here owen assoilynge &thorn;an assoillyng of god, for &yogh;if a man come to here schrifte &amp; sacramentis &thorn;ei assoilen hym &amp; maken siker &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;e man lie vpon hym self &amp; be not assoilid of god; &amp; &thorn;ou&yogh; a man be neuere so treuly assoilid of god for his entre sorwe of synne &amp; charite &thorn;at he ha&thorn; now to god, &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at he his 
<PB REF="00000173.tif" N="107"> dampnable but &yogh;if he be assoilid of hem &YOGH;if he haue space &thorn;er-to, pou&yogh; &thorn;ei ben cursed heretikis &amp; enemyes of crist &amp; his peple. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei taken litel reward to god whanne he sei&thorn;, what euere tyme a synful man ha&thorn; so enteire sorowe for his synnes he schal be saaf. &thorn;es prelatis schulden preche &thorn;is contricion &amp; mercy of god &amp; ioies of heuene, &amp; &thorn;e peril of schrifte wi&thorn;-outen repentaunce, &amp; foulnesse of synnes, &amp; grete peynes of helle, &amp; ri&yogh;twissnesse of god to make &thorn;e peple to flee synne &amp; kepe trewly goddis comaundementis, &amp; not disceyuen hem bi here owene power of assoilynge, ne bi fals pardon ne fals preieris &amp; o&thorn;er nouelries bi side goddis lawe. of &thorn;es &thorn;re &amp; fourty errouris &amp; heresies may men see hou euele prelatis disceyuen cristendom. For of hem &amp; non o&thorn;ere is &thorn;is speche, &amp; hou &thorn;ei ben cause of werris &amp; euele lif in &thorn;e peple, and of here dampnacion. God for his endles my&yogh;t and mercy amende &thorn;es errouris and o&thorn;ere, &yogh;if it be his wille. Amen.</P>


</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="5" TYPE="tract"><PB REF="00000174.tif" N="108">
<HEAD>V. SPECULUM DE ANTICHRISTO.</HEAD>
<HEADNOTE><P>I HAVE little doubt that this tract is by Wyclif; it seems to me to bear the stamp of genuineness in style as in matter. The assertion of free|will on p. 110 may surprise some who know how prominent a place was held by predestination in Wyclif's theological system, but it will be seen that in dealing with the next point of Antichrist and his clerks, predesti|nation is treated as a recognized truth. This double-sided assertion of doctrine is usual with Wyclif, who declares in plain terms <I>Cum pr&aelig;desti|natione et pr&aelig;scientia stat libertas arbitrii</I> (see Lechler, I. 509).</P><P>The tract seems to be early in date, belonging to a time when the poor priests were already causing scandal, but when no violent measures had been taken to repress them. It must have been written before Wyclif de|veloped his doctrine of the Eucharist, or he could hardly have mentioned the mass as he does on p. 112, without any reference to the falsity of transubstantiation.</P><P>I have retained the title, though not found in either MS., for the sake of distinction from No. XVII.</P><P>Copied from the Corpus MS. X. and collated with the Dublin MS. AA.</P><P><TABLE>
<HEAD>SUMMARY.</HEAD>
<ROW>
<CELL></CELL>
<CELL>Antichrist and his clerks object to preaching&mdash;</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>I.</CELL>
<CELL>That it causes dissension, and that Christian men should seek peace and charity. To which true men say that Christ has bidden them to preach, and that preaching does more good than harm.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>II.</CELL>
<CELL>That preaching is against charity, because it hardens enemies. It is better to pray for them.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL></CELL>
<CELL>True men cite Christ's example. Some men are saved through preaching; others made better for a time. Besides in all assemblies there are some good men who profit.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>III.</CELL>
<CELL>That preaching can do nothing for men who are ordained by God either to perish or be saved.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL></CELL>
<CELL>True men say that God ordains men to be saved through preaching; that men have free will, and God will give them grace if they desire it.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>IV.</CELL>
<CELL>That prayer is more profitable than preaching.</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL></CELL>
<CELL>True men say that preaching is better than praying by mouth. Christ commanded preaching, but not matins or evensong. It is uncharitable for a man to wrap himself in contemplation when he might be teaching others. Yet priests are to pray devoutly.</CELL>
</ROW>
</TABLE></P></HEADNOTE>


<DIV2 TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000175.tif" N="109">
<HEAD>Speculum de Antichristo. Hou anticrist &amp; his clerkis feren trewe prestis fro prechynge of cristis gospel bi foure disceitis.</HEAD>
<P>First &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at prechynge of &thorn;e gospel maki&thorn; discencion &amp; enemyte, &amp; si&thorn; cristene men schulde make pees &amp; charite, as &thorn;e gospel sei&thorn;, &thorn;ei schulden cesse of prechynge, si&thorn; &thorn;er come&thorn; more harm &thorn;an good &thorn;er-of. Here trewe men seyn &thorn;at crist cam in-to &thorn;is world not to make pees of synful men to lyuen in here fleschly lustis &amp; worldly ioie at here lykyng, but to departe<NOTE PLACE="foot">do parte X.</NOTE> hem fro synful lif bi &thorn;e gospel, &thorn;at is clepid swerd of &thorn;e holy gost. &amp; &thorn;ou&yogh; luciferis children ben wode &amp; sleen hem self bi sterynge of here fadir for enemyte &amp; here owen cruel hertis, &yogh;it cristene men schullen not cesse to do &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> comaundement &amp; honour of god &amp; poyntis of charite to here bre&thorn;ren; for crist &amp; his apostlis leften not prechynge of &thorn;e gospel, &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;e deuelis lyms maden dis|cencion &amp; grucchynge &amp; fi&yogh;ttynge a&yogh;enst hem And goode men resceyuynge cristis gospel, to &yogh;eue vs ensaumple to laste trewe in prechynge &thorn;ou&yogh; anticristis clerkis grucchen. &amp; &thorn;us cristene men schulde make verrey <MILESTONE N="104" UNIT="page">pees bitwene god &amp; cristene soulis bi trewe kepynge of his hestis, &amp; distroie fals pees of cursed men and don here traueile to amende hem for ellis &thorn;ei failleden in charite. For bi &thorn;is sotil ypocrisie anticrist wolde quenche &amp; owtlaue holy writt &amp; make alle men dampnyd; for he wolde heuere stire summe of his seruauntis &amp; stryue &amp; debate for prechynge of goddis word, &amp; &thorn;us schulde no man knowe goddis word bi prechynge. And certis &yogh;if ony man preche in grace &thorn;er come&thorn; more good &thorn;er-of &thorn;an alle fendis lymes may don harm, &thorn;ou&yogh; many &thorn;ousand sathanas children ben deppere dampnyd for here rebelte a&yogh;enst god &amp; his gracious techynge. 
<PB REF="00000176.tif" N="110"> &para; &THORN;e secunde tyme<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at men schulden cesse of prechynge for charite of here enemyes. For bi prechynge here enemyes be stired to hate &amp; mansleynge of holy prechouris &amp; not amendid. for &thorn;ere ben many &thorn;ousand &thorn;at schullen ben dampnyd &amp; not leue here synne for ony prechynge, but more dampnid for &thorn;ei heren goddis word &amp; don not &thorn;er-aftir. And for &thorn;is charite sei&thorn; god to &thorn;e prophete &thorn;at he schal make<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ezekiel iii. 26.</NOTE> his tounge<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> cleue faste to &thorn;e roof of his mou&thorn;, for &thorn;e peple is &thorn;us hard a&yogh;enst god &amp; his techynge. And &thorn;us comaunde&thorn; crist &thorn;at men schullen not &yogh;eue holy &thorn;ingis to hondis &amp;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matthew vii. 6.</NOTE> putten precious perlis to hoggis, &amp; god bidde&thorn; to his prechour &thorn;at he speke not &thorn;ere goddis word where is noon herynge. &para; Here trewe men seyn &thorn;at &thorn;ei schulden loue more god &amp; cristene soulis &thorn;an here owene temporal lif, And &thorn;erfore techi&thorn; goddis lawe to here enemyes &amp; preie for hem hertly til &thorn;ei weren dede, as crist dide on &thorn;e cros &amp; his apostlis to here de&thorn; &amp; namely seynt steuene. And &yogh;it &thorn;ei weren certeyn &thorn;at here enemyes schulden slen hem, &thorn;erfore, to teche vs &thorn;at, &thorn;ei suffreden wilfully to &yogh;eue vs ensaumple to sue hem in &thorn;is. &amp; &thorn;ou&yogh; men schullen algatis be dampnyd &yogh;it it helpi&thorn; hem &thorn;at goddis word is prechid, for &thorn;er-by moo men ben sauyd &amp; fewere dampnyd &amp; so lesse peyne to hem algatis. And &yogh;it sumtyme &thorn;ei han compuncion &amp; leuen here synnes long tyme &amp; ben in grace &amp; charite for a tyme, &thorn;at is betre &thorn;an alle &thorn;is world, &yogh;e to hem; &amp; god &yogh;eue&thorn; to eche man a free wille to chese good or euyl &amp; god is redi to &yogh;eue hem grace &yogh;if &thorn;ei wolen resceyuen it; &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ei done here-by many goode dedis of kynde &amp; for hem schullen haue moche reward in &thorn;is world at &thorn;e laste &amp; lesse peyne in helle, and it<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;it AA.</NOTE> is gret vengaunce of god whanne he wi&thorn;-drawi&thorn; prechynge fro a comynalte. For &thorn;ei ben not wor&thorn;i to here goddis word &amp; &thorn;erfore &thorn;ei schullen be deppere dampnyed; and where a gedrynge of peple is summe comynly ben goode, &amp; for hem principaly men prechen goddis word &amp; not for houndis &thorn;at berken a&yogh;enst god &amp; his lawis, ne for swyn &thorn;at ba&thorn;en hem in 
<PB REF="00000177.tif" N="111"> synne &amp; wolle neuere leuen hem for drede of peyne ne hope<NOTE PLACE="foot">op X. corrected into 'hope' by a later hand.</NOTE> of blisse. And &yogh;if prechours<MILESTONE N="105" UNIT="page"> weren certeyn &thorn;at alle a comynalte wolden not here goddis word &thorn;ei wolden not preche &thorn;ere but goo to o&thorn;er peple, as crist biddi&thorn;, for &thorn;ei schullen not fayle in o place or o&thorn;ere of summe good men til &thorn;e day of dome come.</P>
<P>&para; &THORN;e &thorn;ridde tyme &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at goode men schulden be sauyd &thorn;ou&yogh; no prechynge be, for &thorn;ei may not perische, as god sei&thorn;. And summe wickid men schullen neuere come to blisse for no prechynge in er&thorn;e. &para; Here seyn trewe men &thorn;at as god ha&thorn; ordeyned goode men to blisse, so god ha&thorn; ordeyned hem to come to blisse bi prechynge &amp; kepyng of goddis word; and<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> so as &thorn;ei schullen nedis come to blisse, so &thorn;ei moten nedis here &amp; kepe goddis hestis, &amp; herof serue&thorn; prechynge to hem; and summe wickid men now schullen be conuertid bi goddis grace &amp; herynge of his word. And who knowe&thorn; &thorn;e mesure of goddis mercy, to whom herynge of goddis word schal &thorn;us profite? eche man schal hope to come to heuene &amp; enforce hym to here &amp; fulfille goddis word, for si&thorn; eche man ha&thorn; a free wille &amp; chesyng of good &amp; euyl, no man schal be sauyd but he &thorn;at willefully here&thorn; and endeles kepi&thorn; goddis hestis, and no man schal be dampnyd but he &thorn;at wilfully &amp; endeles breki&thorn; goddis comaundementis, &amp; forsaki&thorn; &thorn;us &amp; blaspheme&thorn; god. &amp; herynge of goddis word &amp; grace to kepen it, frely &yogh;ouyn of god to man but &yogh;if he wilfully dispise it, is ri&yogh;t weie to askape &thorn;is peril &amp; come to endeles blisse; &amp; here-fore synful<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> men owen wi&thorn; alle manere mekenesse &amp; reuerence &amp; deuocion heren goddis word &amp; grucchen not ne stryue a&yogh;enst prechynge of cristis gospel.</P>
<P>&para; &THORN;e fir&thorn;e tyme &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at men schulden cesse of prechynge &amp; &yogh;euen hem<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> to holy preiers &amp; contemplacion for &thorn;at helpe&thorn; more cristene men &amp; is betre. &para; Trewe men seyn boldly &thorn;at trewe prechynge is betre &thorn;an preiynge bi mou&thorn;e, &yogh;e &thorn;ou&yogh; it come of herte &amp; clene deuocioun, &amp; it edifie&thorn; more &thorn;e peple; &amp; &thorn;erfore crist comaundid specialy 
<PB REF="00000178.tif" N="112"> his apostlis &amp; disciplis to preche &thorn;e gospel, &amp; not to close hem in cloistris ne chirchis ne stones to preie &thorn;us. And &thorn;erfore ysaie seied woo is to me for I was stille. And poul sei&thorn;:<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isaiah vi. 8.</NOTE> woo is to me &yogh;if I preche not &thorn;e gospel. &amp; god sei&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> to &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor ix. 16.</NOTE> prophete, &yogh;if he schew not to &thorn;e synful man<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> his synnys he<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ezekiel iii. 17.</NOTE> schal be dampnyd &thorn;er-fore. Jerom sei&thorn; as myche as innocent lif profiti&thorn; bi merit &amp; holynesse, so moche it harme&thorn; &yogh;if it a&yogh;enstonde nou&yogh;t<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> wicked enemys of goddis lawe. And gregori sei&thorn;, &thorn;at men of gret kunnyng &amp; vertuous lif &thorn;at chesen stilnesse &amp; desert for loue of contemplacion ben giltif of as many soulis as &thorn;ei my&yogh;tten saue bi techynge &amp; dwellynge in &thorn;e world; &amp; &thorn;us prechynge is algatis best. ne&thorn;eles deuout preiere of men of good lif is good in certeyn tyme, but it is a&yogh;enst charite for prestis to preie euere more and no tyme to preche; si&thorn; crist chargi&thorn; prestis more for to preche &thorn;e gospel &thorn;an to seie masse or matynes, for he ne speki&thorn; not of matynes ne euensong opynly, <MILESTONE N="106" UNIT="page">ne manere of masse now vsed, but only of &thorn;e sacrament; but he comaundi&thorn; to prestis for to preche &thorn;e gospel bi-fore his de&thorn; and aftir. And &thorn;er-fore &thorn;e grete clerk lyncolne proue&thorn; &thorn;at trewe prechynge of &thorn;e gospel passi&thorn; alle o&thorn;ere goode werkis &thorn;at man do&thorn; in er&thorn;e; &amp; newe doctours, &yogh;e of mannys lawe, seyn &thorn;at prechynge passe&thorn; &thorn;e masse in nyne profites. &amp; &thorn;us sei&thorn; poul &thorn;at god sent hym for to preche &thorn;e gospel &amp; not to<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. i. 17.</NOTE> cristene men; and ion &thorn;e ewangelist sei&thorn;, &yogh;if a man see his<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 John iii. 17.</NOTE> bro&thorn;er haue nede &amp; close his mercy fro him ha&thorn; not charite. moche more &yogh;if men ben in nede of soule &thorn;er is no charite in prestis but &yogh;if &thorn;ei techen hem goddis comaundementis &yogh;if &thorn;ei han kunnynge &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> leiser &thorn;er-to; &amp; ih&umacr; sei&thorn; &thorn;at men schullen be dampnyd &yogh;if &thorn;ei failen in bodily werkis of mercy, &thorn;at is prechynge, ordeyned to hem. &amp; &thorn;us prestis may not cesse of prechynge for suche preiynge, for &thorn;an &thorn;ei leften &thorn;e betre &thorn;ing, &amp; to hem grettere comaundement, &amp; deden &thorn;e lesse &amp; lesse wor&thorn;i, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei weren out of charite; &amp; &thorn;anne here preieris schulden not ben acceptable to god, for &thorn;ei sueden 
<PB REF="00000179.tif" N="113"> not crist &thorn;at cam from heuene to saue soulis bi prechynge of &thorn;e gospel. lord, what charite is it to a kunnynge man to chese his owene contemplacion in reste, &amp; suffre o&thorn;ere men goo to helle for bregynge of goddis hestis, whanne he may ly&yogh;tly teche hem &amp; gete more &thorn;ank of god in litil techynge &thorn;an bi longe tyme in suche preieris. &THORN;erfore prestis schulden studie holy writt &amp; kepe it in here owen lif, &amp; teche it o&thorn;ere men trewely &amp; frely, &amp; &thorn;at is best &amp; most charite. And in certeyn tymes preie most<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> deuoutly &amp; haue sorowe for here synnes &amp; o&thorn;ere mennys. And &thorn;an &thorn;ei schullen be as &thorn;e firmament ouer litel sterris in comparison of o&thorn;ere seyntis in heuene. God brynge vs alle to &thorn;at glorious blisse for his endeles mercy. Amen.</P>


</DIV2>
