</ROW>
</TABLE></P></HEADNOTE>

<PB REF="00000270.tif" N="204">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>&THORN;is is &thorn;e aue maria.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<P><B>Heil</B><NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted SS.</NOTE><B>be &thorn;ou,</B><NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted SS.</NOTE> <B>marie, ful of grace, &thorn;e lord is wi&thorn; &thorn;e. blissed be &thorn;ou among wymmen, &amp; blissed be &thorn;e fruyt of &thorn;i wombe,</B> ih&umacr; crist.<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted SS.</NOTE> amen. so be it. &THORN;e arcangel gabriel sent of god grette oure ladie seynte marie wi&thorn; &thorn;es wordis, <B>heil. be &thorn;ou ful of grace. &thorn;e lord is wi&thorn; &thorn;e. blissed be &thorn;ou among wymmen</B>. &amp; he seide no moo wordis, as &thorn;e firste<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted SS.</NOTE> gospel of seynt luk techi&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot">telli&thorn; SS.</NOTE> but elizebeth, &thorn;e modir of seynt<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke i. 28.</NOTE> ion baptist, seide &thorn;es wordes to oure lady whanne sche hadde conseyued crist; <B>blissed be &thorn;ou among wymmen &amp; blissed be &thorn;e fruyt of &thorn;i wombe.</B> as &thorn;e same gospel techi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">telli&thorn; SS.</NOTE>; but<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke i. 42.</NOTE> cristene men for deuocion adden to &thorn;es tweie wordis, marie &amp; ih&umacr; crist; <MILESTONE N="176" UNIT="page">&amp; men seyn &thorn;at popis graunte moche pardon &thorn;er|fore, but hou euere it be of pardon, &thorn;is addynge to is trewe, for &thorn;e gospel techi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">telli&thorn; SS.</NOTE> vs &thorn;es names &amp; &thorn;ei stiren men to deuo|cion. &para; Here men &amp; wommen, &amp; namely gentil wommen, schulden lerne<NOTE PLACE="foot">lyuen al in SS.</NOTE> mekenesse, chastite, charite, sobirnesse &amp; schamefastenesse, to be aschamyd of eche euyl speche, &amp; namely of lecherie &amp; euyl contenaunce of synne &amp; ribaudrie &amp; vilonye<NOTE PLACE="foot">vilen&thorn;e X.</NOTE> and<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> lerne holy deuocion, &amp; &thorn;anne &thorn;ei worschipen wel ih&umacr; here gostly spouse &amp; seynt marie his modir; &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ei lyuen in pride of herte for nobeleie of blood or<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; X.</NOTE> kyn &amp; rentis &amp; richessis of &thorn;e world, &amp; han indignacion and<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> dispit of o&thorn;ere pore men or wymmen; <SUP>10</SUP>and delyten hem<SUP>10</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">10_10 omitted X.</NOTE> in lecherie in ony degree; or in hate &amp; enuye or glotonye &amp; dronkenesse &amp; boldnesse in synne, &amp; colouren &amp; meyntenen it and lyuen in riot, daunsynge &amp; lepynge in ny&yogh;ttis &amp; slepen out of reson on &thorn;e morwe, &amp; for&yogh;eten god &amp; his drede &amp; deuocion of preieris; what euere here tonge blabre, here euyl lif blaspheme&thorn; &amp; dispisi&thorn; bo&thorn;e ih&umacr; here noble spouse &amp; his modir marie, tresour of clennesse &amp; deuocion. &para; And &yogh;if &thorn;ei 
<PB REF="00000271.tif" N="205"> maken hem more bisi in herte &amp; dede to be <SUP>1</SUP>gaie and costelewe of array<SUP>1</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">1_1 gaie in costelewe array X.</NOTE> of clo&thorn;is &amp; keuerchers and perlis &amp; ribanys, or siche vanytes, to maken here body fresch and<NOTE PLACE="foot">in X.</NOTE> likynge to mennus ei&yogh;en to coueiten hem, &thorn;an to gete vertues in here soule to make it fair to &thorn;e holy trinyte &amp; to ih&umacr; here wor&thorn;ieste spouse, &thorn;ei ben out of charite, &amp; &thorn;e deuelis panter, to kacche men in-to synne of lecherie &amp; many moo synnes<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &amp; holde hem &thorn;er-inne, til sathanas drawe hem bo&thorn;e in<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE>-to helle; &amp; what euere nobleie or dignyte &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &thorn;ei han in &thorn;is world, be &thorn;ei gentil men or wymmen, for &thorn;is cursed lif &thorn;ei ben cherlis or bonde wymmen of synne, &amp; fendis of helle, &amp; gostly spouse brekeris or avoutreris, &amp; lemmans of foule sathanas &thorn;at is foulere &thorn;an ony mesel or leprous in &thorn;is world. &amp; but &yogh;if &thorn;ei amenden hem in &thorn;is world<NOTE PLACE="foot">lyfe SS.</NOTE> &thorn;ei schullen be of hem &thorn;at god speki&thorn; of in iobis bok.<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;e bok of iob SS.</NOTE> &para; &THORN;ei leden, sei&thorn; god, here daies in<NOTE PLACE="marg">Job xxi. 13.</NOTE> lustful goodis &amp; myr&thorn;is of &thorn;is world &amp; in a poynt of tyme fallen doun in-to helle. sumtyme curtesie &amp; genterie was vertuouse<NOTE PLACE="foot">vertues X.</NOTE> lif &amp; honest in word &amp; dede &amp; alle manere of good<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> berynge, &amp; suster of holynesse; but now it is turned in-to vanyte &amp; nysete &amp; knackis &amp; iapis &amp; is &yogh;ate of synne, of pride, of rebaudrie, sleu&thorn;e, coueitise, glotonye, dronkenesse &amp; lecherie &amp; meyntenynge of synne &amp; hordam,<NOTE PLACE="foot">hord X.</NOTE> of wra&thorn;&thorn;e &amp; enuye &amp; bost &amp; cursed swerynge &amp; wast of goodis &amp; robbynge of pore men <SUP>9</SUP>&amp; distroiynge of londis &amp; good cristendom.<SUP>9</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">9_9 omitted SS.</NOTE> &para; O &yogh;e gentil wommen, &thorn;enki&thorn; hou noble wommen &amp; clene &amp; stedefast han be bifore &yogh;ou, as oure lady seynt marie, marie magdaleyne, sussanne, katerine, margare, anneys,<NOTE PLACE="foot">margarete, agnes SS.</NOTE> cicile <MILESTONE N="177" UNIT="page">&amp; many moo, &amp; take what goode ensaumple &yogh;e may of here mekenesse &amp; holynesse; for whanne wymmen ben turnyd fully to goodnesse ful<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> hard it is &thorn;at ony man passe hem in goodnesse. And as<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> hard it<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> is<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &thorn;at ony man passe hem in synne whanne &thorn;ei ben turnyd to pride &amp; lecherie &amp; dronke|nesse. 
<PB REF="00000272.tif" N="206"> I gesse wel &thorn;at &yogh;onge wymmen may sumtyme daunsen<NOTE PLACE="foot">playen hem SS.</NOTE> in mesure to haue recreacion and li&yogh;tnesse, so &thorn;at &thorn;ei haue &thorn;e more &thorn;ou&yogh;t on myr&thorn;e in heuene &amp; drede more &amp; loue more god &thorn;er-by, &amp; synge honeste songis of cristis incarnacion, passion, resurexion &amp; ascencion, &amp; of &thorn;e ioies of oure ladi, &amp; to dispise synne &amp; preise vertue in alle here doynge<NOTE PLACE="foot">cunnyng SS.</NOTE>; but nowe he &thorn;at kan best pleie a pagyn<NOTE PLACE="foot">pagent SS.</NOTE> of &thorn;e deuyl, syngynge songis of lecherie, of batailis and<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> of lesyngis, &amp; crie as a wood man &amp; dispise goddis maieste &amp; swere bi herte, bonys &amp; alle membris of crist, is holden most merie mon<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &amp; schal haue most &thorn;ank of pore &amp; riche; &amp; &thorn;is is clepid worschipe of &thorn;e grete solempnyte of cristismasse; &amp; &thorn;us for &thorn;e grete kyndenesse &amp; goodnesse &thorn;at crist dide to men in his incar|nacion<NOTE PLACE="foot">carnacion X.</NOTE> we dispisen hym more in outrage of pride, of glotonye, lecherie &amp; alle manere harlotrie. &amp; bi &thorn;is doynge &thorn;e fend brynge&thorn; in iolite of body &amp; myr&thorn;e &amp; likynge &amp; newe fyndynge vp of synne, in-stede of holynesse &amp; gostly ioie &amp; herynge of god for his endeles charite, mercy, mekenesse &amp; kyndenesse. lord, where is &thorn;at man or womman &thorn;at maki&thorn; hym so bisi to make his soule fair in vertues<NOTE PLACE="foot">vertuose X.</NOTE> to goddis si&yogh;tte as he maki&thorn; hym bisi aboute atir of body for &thorn;e si&yogh;tte of men? Alas, &thorn;at so gret cost &amp; bisynesse is sette abouten &thorn;e roten body, &thorn;at is wormes mete &amp; a sak of drit &amp; dust &amp; aschis; but aboute &thorn;e soule made to &thorn;e ymage of &thorn;e trinyte, &amp; &thorn;e whiche soule crist bou&yogh;te so dere wi&thorn; his precious herte blood, is no bisinesse to clense it out<NOTE PLACE="foot">ones SS.</NOTE> of synne but to brynge it in-to more synne bo&thorn; ny&yogh;t &amp; day. litel &thorn;enk &thorn;es woode men &amp; wommen on cristis pouert &amp; cold &amp; pouert of his modir &amp; what lif he lyuede in &thorn;is world in so gret penaunce &amp; dispit &amp; wepynge for oure synnys &amp; what schameful de&thorn; he suffrid at &thorn;e laste. &thorn;es lordis &amp; ladies schulden suffre in here presence &amp; courtis no dispisynge of god bi wood<NOTE PLACE="foot">o&thorn;es SS.</NOTE> swerynge, bi wordis of lecherie, ny<NOTE PLACE="foot">be X.</NOTE> o&thorn;ere rebaudrie and vnresonable 
<PB REF="00000273.tif" N="207"> speche; for &yogh;if &thorn;ei suffreden ony of here seruauntis to dispise oure er&thorn;ely kyng moche ponyschynge schulde come <SUP>1</SUP>to hem<SUP>1</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">1_1 omitted X.</NOTE> &amp; &thorn;ei ben holden false &amp; traitour<NOTE PLACE="foot">as false traitours SS.</NOTE> to &thorn;e kyng. o hou moche more traitours &amp; false ben &thorn;es worldly lordis<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> to crist kyng of alle heuene &amp; alle er&thorn;e &amp; helle, whanne &thorn;ei heren sich dispit don to his maieste &amp; refreynen not here seruauntis &thorn;er-of. certis ensaumple of clennesse, honeste &amp; holynesse cam sum|tyme <MILESTONE N="178" UNIT="page">fro lordis courtis to &thorn;e comyns, &amp; &thorn;an was holy lif in worschipe among pore &amp; riche. But now come&thorn; ensaumple of pride, glotonye, lecherie &amp; hal harlotrie fro lordis courtis to &thorn;e comyns. And here-fore regne&thorn; synne in alle manere peple wi&thorn;-outen schame. &thorn;us &thorn;e fend blyndi&thorn; men to clepe &thorn;is cursed hauntynge of arlotrie &amp; synne gret worschipe of god, &amp; to clepe deuocion of preieris &amp; sade mynde of cristis pouert, penaunce &amp; de&thorn; &amp; of &thorn;e day of dome ypocrisie &amp; folie; &amp; suche men ben not wor&thorn;i to dwelle in lordis courtis, laste &thorn;ei dryuen awey &thorn;e deuyl &amp; his scole of synne &amp; vanyte to displesynge<NOTE PLACE="foot">dispisyng SS.</NOTE> of &yogh;onge, nyce folis, &amp; bryngen in crist in-to cristen<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> mennus soulis &amp; his<NOTE PLACE="foot">usen SS.</NOTE> scole of vertues &amp; honeste in &thorn;ou&yogh;t, worde &amp; dede, to<NOTE PLACE="foot">in X.</NOTE> plesynge of god &amp; sauynge of mennus soulis. &para; Heil marie, &thorn;at is wel be to &thorn;e, marie; or ioie be to &thorn;e. for bi <SUP>8</SUP>&thorn;at womman<SUP>8</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">8_8 omitted X.</NOTE> eue cam sorowe, peyne &amp; woo to mankynde for sche tristed not sadly to goddis word but tristed to &thorn;e fendis gabbynge &amp; coueited ouermoche kunnynge &amp; dingnyte; but bi sad bileue &amp; mekenesse &amp; charite of marie cam ioie &amp; saluacion to mankynde, for her bi sche conseyuede crist as &thorn;e gospel sei&thorn;. &thorn;erfore flee lesyngis &amp; pride &amp; holde sadly bileue of goddis word with mekenesse &amp; charite &amp; &thorn;ou schalt haue part of maries <SUP>9</SUP>ioie &amp;<SUP>9</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">9_9 blessyng &amp; &thorn;e SS.</NOTE> blisse of heuene eueremore. marie cristis modir was ful of grace. seynt steuene was ful of grace, as holy writt sei&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Acts vi. 8.</NOTE> but lasse &thorn;an oure lady, &amp; oure swete lord ih&umacr; was ful of grace aboue steuene &amp; oure ladi &thorn;er-to. &amp; so &thorn;er ben &thorn;re 
<PB REF="00000274.tif" N="208"> degrees of plente of grace. &thorn;e leste of &thorn;is plente was in steuene, &thorn;e mydil in oure lady, but &thorn;e most in oure lord ih&umacr; crist. &para; God &thorn;e trinyte is wi&thorn; eche creature bi my&yogh;t, wisdom &amp; goodnesse to kepe it, for ellis it schulde turne to no&yogh;t; but god is wi&thorn; goode men of vertuous lif bi grace to approue &amp; accepte here doyngis &amp; helpe hem &thorn;er-inne, to rewarde hem in blisse &thorn;erfore, &amp; dwelli&thorn; in here soulis as his owen temple, &amp; maki&thorn; hem ioifully dwelle in his seruyce &amp; suffre<NOTE PLACE="foot">suffri&thorn; X.</NOTE> gladly alle dispitis &amp; persecucion for his name; but god is in angelis &amp; seyntis in heuene bi clier schewynge of his godhed to hem &amp; makynge hem to knowe alle &thorn;ingis &amp; haue alle &thorn;at euere &thorn;ei desiren wi&thorn;-outen ony anoye or peyne. &para; Blissed be &thorn;ou among wymmen; &thorn;at is more &thorn;an ony o&thorn;er womman, for noon o&thorn;er was so sad in bileue ne so meke ne so chast ne so goode in alle manere holynesse &amp; namely in brennynge charite. &yogh;if &thorn;ou wilt haue part of maries blisse &amp; goddis blissynge sue marie in &thorn;is holy lif &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">in X.</NOTE> namely in &thorn;es seuene, fei&thorn;, hope, &amp; charite, &amp; mekenesse, chastite, sobirnesse, &amp; brynnynge desir of ri&yogh;twisnesse. And blissed be &thorn;e fruyt of &thorn;i womb: &thorn;at is ih&umacr;, for bi his mercy &amp; grace come&thorn; alle goodnesse, &amp; namely bi his trewe techynge &amp; wilful de&thorn; &amp; endeles my&yogh;t, be whiche he schal reise alle men at domes day &amp; &yogh;if blisse of heuene in bodi &amp; soule to &thorn;o &thorn;at ende in perfit charite. god &yogh;eue vs grace to &thorn;enke on cristis mercy &amp; ri&yogh;twisnesse &amp; maries sadnesse in bileue, &amp; mekenesse to make ende in perfit charite. Amen.</P>


</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="13" TYPE="tract"><PB REF="00000275.tif" N="209">
<HEAD>XIII. HOW SATAN AND HIS CHILDREN, ETC.</HEAD>
<HEADNOTE><P>THE tiresome series of antitheses between Christ and the fiend with which this tract begins are in Wyclif's worst manner, if indeed they are his.</P><P>The characteristic point of this tract is its insistence on the hardships of imprisonment for debt, on the cruelty of those who inflict it unjustly, (pp. 211 and 214), and on the folly of those who fall into it through drunkenness (p. 217). I do not remember any other tract in which this point is pressed so much.</P><P>Whoever the author was, he knew the poor and felt for them; notice, among other things, his description of the bed-rid poor as couching on muck or dust (p. 211), and his complaint that the aged poor had to drink water and fell into fevers. (Did he look upon wine as a febrifuge?)</P><P>Copied from the Corpus MS. X. and collated with the Dublin MS. AA., where the first chapter and part of the second are wanting.</P><P><TABLE>
<HEAD>SUMMARY.</HEAD>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. I.</CELL>
<CELL>The works of bodily mercy are enumerated, and the perversions of them prevalent among bad priests, etc.</CELL>
<CELL>p. 210</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>II.</CELL>
<CELL>Contains a similar list of contrasts as to the works of spiritual mercy</CELL>
<CELL>212</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>III.</CELL>
<CELL>The temptations offered us by the five senses are enumerated and contrasted with the right use of the senses.</CELL>
<CELL>216</CELL>
</ROW>
</TABLE></P></HEADNOTE>

<PB REF="00000276.tif" N="210">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>Hou sathanas &amp; his children turnen werkis of mercy vpsodom &amp; disceyuen men &thorn;er-inne &amp; in here fyue wittis.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<DIV2 N="1" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum primum.</HEAD>
<P><MILESTONE N="179" UNIT="page">First crist comaundi&thorn; men of power to fede hungry pore men; &thorn;e fend &amp; his techen to make costy festis &amp; waste many goodis on lordis &amp; riche men &amp; to suffre pore men sterue &amp; perische for hunger &amp; o&thorn;ere myscheuys; &yogh;e, men &thorn;at feynen hem ful of charite &amp; religion gadren propre goodis to hem seluen &amp; festen delicatly lordis &amp; ladies &amp; riche men &amp; suffre here pore bre&thorn;ren begge for meschef &amp; fare ful harde. crist comaundi&thorn; to &yogh;eue drynk to &thorn;rusty men &amp; wymmen; &thorn;e fend &amp; his techen to purueye hei&yogh; wyn &amp; spised ale &amp; strong for riche men &amp; lordis to make hem dronken &amp; chide &amp; fi&yogh;tte &amp; for&yogh;ete god &amp; his lawe, &amp; to suffre pore &thorn;at han nou&yogh;t of here owene &amp; may not labore for febilnesse or sikenesse &amp; blyndenesse drynke water &amp; falle in feueris or ellis perische. crist comaundi&thorn; to clo&thorn;e nakyd men &amp; wymmen whanne &thorn;ei han no&yogh;t of here owene; &thorn;er-to &thorn;e fend &amp; his techen to &yogh;eue costly clo&thorn;is &amp; manye to riche men &amp; mynstralis or shaualdours for worldly name, &amp; suffre pore men haue nakid sidis &amp; schakynge lippis &amp; hondis for cold &thorn;at woo is hem wi&thorn; &thorn;e lif. &YOGH;e, prelatis &amp; men of singuler religion, &thorn;at taken &thorn;e charge to ben procuratouris &amp; dis|penderis of pore mennus liflode, clo&thorn;en fatte horsis &amp; gaie sadlis &amp; bridlis &amp; mytris &amp; croceris wi&thorn; gold &amp; siluer &amp; precious stonys &amp; suffren pore men &amp; children perische for cold; &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;es prelatis &amp; newe religious comen in staat of cristis pouert &amp; his apostlis, &amp; techen &amp; crien &thorn;at what euere &thorn;ei han is pore mennus goode. &yogh;it riche men clo&thorn;en<NOTE PLACE="foot">closen MS.</NOTE> dede stockis &amp; stonys wi&thorn; precious clo&thorn;is, wi&thorn; gold &amp; siluer &amp; perlis &amp; gaynesse to &thorn;e world, &amp; suffren pore men goo sore a cold &amp; at moche meschefe. Crist techi&thorn; to herbwre pore men &thorn;at han non houses ne peny to peye for here innys; &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000277.tif" N="211"> fend &amp; his techen to herberwe riche men &amp; lordis wi&thorn; gret cost &amp; deyitte for worldly worschipe, &amp; suffre pore men wander in stormys &amp; slepe wi&thorn; &thorn;e swyn, &amp; many tymes suffre not hem come wi&thorn;-inne here &yogh;atis, &amp; to fynde many excusacions &amp; coloure &thorn;is doynge. &yogh;e, ypocritis of priuat religion maken grete houses &amp; costy &amp; gaely peyntid <MILESTONE N="180" UNIT="page">more &thorn;an kyngis &amp; lordis bi sotil beggynge &amp; confessions &amp; trentalis &amp; meyntenynge of synne, [and] herberewe lordis &amp; riche men &amp; namely ladies, &amp; suffre pore men lie wi&thorn;-outen or geten houslewth at pore men or ellis perische for wedris &amp; cold. &para; Crist techi&thorn; to visite sike men &amp; counforte hem &amp; helpe hem of sustenaunce; &thorn;e fend &amp; his techen to visiten riche men, lordis &amp; ladies in here prosperite &amp; lykynge to be holden kynde &amp; curteis, &amp; to counforte eche o&thorn;er in synne &amp; to haue lustis of glotonye, lecherie &amp; o&thorn;ere schrewidnessis, but of pore men &thorn;at ben beddrede &amp; couchen in muk or dust is litel &thorn;ou&yogh;t on or no&yogh;t. &para; &YOGH;it ypocritis of feyned religion visiten not fadirles children &amp; modirles &amp; widewis in here tribu|lacion &amp; kepe not hem self vnbleckid fro &thorn;is world, as seynt iame techi&thorn;: but visete oft riche men &amp; wymmen, &amp; namely<NOTE PLACE="marg">James i. 27.</NOTE> riche widewis, for to gete worldly muk by false disceitis &amp; carien it home to caymes castelis &amp; anticristis couent &amp; sathanas children &amp; marteris of glotonye. &para; Crist teche&thorn; to visite men in prison &amp; helpe to delyuere hem in good manere &amp; counforte hem bi almes &yogh;euynge; &thorn;e fend &amp; his presonen pore men for dette whanne &thorn;ei ben not at power to paie, &amp; traueile ny&yogh;t &amp; day &amp; lyuen ful harde, &amp; to lyue wi&thorn; trew&thorn;e &amp; susteynen<NOTE PLACE="foot">sustevnem MS.</NOTE> wif &amp; children, &amp; on hem is no mercy. &yogh;it feyned religious men pursuen pore prestis to prison &amp; to brennynge bi many cursed lesyngis &amp; sclaundrynge priue &amp; apert, for as mochel as &thorn;ei prechen trewly &amp; frely cristis gospel &amp; goddis hestis &amp; reprouen here ypocrisie, symonye, coueitise &amp; o&thorn;ere disceitis; &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;es ypocritis blenden lordis &amp; prelatis to enprisone siche pore prestis techynge &thorn;e treu&thorn;e bi comaunde|ment &amp; ensaumple of crist &amp; his apostlis, not-wi&thorn;stondynge 
<PB REF="00000278.tif" N="212"> &thorn;at lordis &amp; prelatis ben charged vp peyne of dampnacion to helpe hem &amp; meyntene &thorn;is treu&thorn;e &amp; prechouris of it. &para; It is holden a werk of mercy to birie dede men after &thorn;e techynge of goddis lawe; &thorn;e fend techi&thorn; worldly riche men, clerkis &amp; religious, to make solempnyte whanne riche men ben dede wi&thorn; dirige &amp; messis &amp; wax &amp; rengynge &amp; grete festis, but whanne pore men ben dede vnne&thorn;e wole ony man berie hem or seie derige or masse. &YOGH;it feyned religious wolen come to riche mennus dirige in grete multitude &amp; stire hem to be biried in here chirche, &amp; stryuen &amp; fi&yogh;tten for &thorn;e dede careyne for loue of offrynge &amp; worldly honour, but pore men schullen not lie among hem &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei axen it neuere so faste for charite. &amp; &thorn;us in stede of werkis of bodely mercy &amp; charite is comen in ypocrisie of worldly name &amp; coueitise &amp; norischynge <MILESTONE N="181" UNIT="page">of synne &amp; sotil excusynge &thorn;er-of, &amp; euyl is clepid good &amp; good euyl.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 2<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Werkis of mercy ben worse turned vpsodoun. crist sei&thorn; it is a souereyn werk of mercy &amp; charite to teche vnlernyd men &thorn;e ri&yogh;tte weie to heuene, &thorn;at is &thorn;e gospel &amp; goddis comaundementis; &thorn;e fend &amp; his seyn it is grete charite to teche &yogh;onge men &amp; o&thorn;ere sotil craftis &amp; nedeles &amp; queynte slei&yogh;tis to disceyue schepische men of worldly goodis &amp; make hem self riche &amp; bostful &amp; proude. &amp; &thorn;e fend bi sotil menys of ypocrisie &amp; symonye stire&thorn; lordis &amp; my&yogh;tty men to make an ydiot &amp; fool curatour of cristene soulis, &thorn;at nei&thorn;er may ne kan ne wole, for his opyn synne &amp; worldly lif &amp; ignoraunce of holy writt &amp; necligence &amp; worldly vanyte &amp; drede of worldly shame &amp; loos, teche hem goddis lawe, ne suffre o&thorn;ere to teche hem frely &amp; trewely wi&thorn;-outen flaterynge for drede last his owene falsnesse be knowen; &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;es cursed auaunsynge is clepid charite to helpe &thorn;us a pore man. But an ydiot &amp; a lecherous wrecche schal be sett to kepe &thorn;e soulis for litel pris, &amp; &thorn;e more lorel goo on haukynge &amp; huntyng, 
<PB REF="00000279.tif" N="213"> &amp; serue in lordis courtis, in worldly offices, &amp; &thorn;e deuyl drawi&thorn; wi&thorn; his helpis alle &thorn;at he may to helle &amp; &thorn;is is clepid mercy &amp; charite; but &thorn;is deuelis charite putti&thorn; oute charite &amp; loue of god &amp; bryngi&thorn; in loue of money &amp; synne &amp; hate of vertues &amp; cristene soulis. crist sei&thorn; it is werk of mercy to conseile at perti hou a man schal best lyue in &thorn;is or &thorn;is special poynt. &thorn;e fend &amp; his seyn it is mercy &amp; charite to conseile men to holde for&thorn; craftis &thorn;at &thorn;ei vsen a&yogh;enst here conscience &amp; excusen hem bi almes, as masse syngynge &amp; makynge of nedles houses &amp; costy. &amp; whanne clerkis schullen conseile lordis &amp; o&thorn;ere men hou &thorn;ei may best serue god &amp; saue here soulis in here a-staat, &thorn;is conseil is turned in-to worldly wisdom as bildynge of castellis &amp; arraiynge of housholde in lond of pees &amp; of werre. &amp; whanne it [is] reserued to &thorn;e holy gost to &yogh;eue vtterly conseil in special poyntis &thorn;at ben not expresly comaundid ne forboden in holy writt, worldly clerkis ful of pride, symonye, coueitise &amp; o&thorn;ere synnys &yogh;euen fulbut conseil a&yogh;enst &thorn;e holy gost &amp; a&yogh;enst &thorn;e hel&thorn;e of &thorn;e soule for here owene pride &amp; coueitise; &amp; &thorn;us conseil of &thorn;e holy gost &amp; profit of soulis<NOTE PLACE="foot">AA begins here, the first part of the tract being lost.</NOTE> is putt bihynde &amp; conseil of &thorn;e world &amp; &thorn;e fleisch &amp; of sathanas is putt for&thorn;. god biddi&thorn; &thorn;at lordis &amp; souereyns schulden in resonable manere chastise here sugetis, seruauntis &amp; children whanne &thorn;ei trespassen opynly in word or dede a&yogh;enst goddis comaundementis; &thorn;e fend &amp; his techen &thorn;at suggettis &amp; seruauntis ben cruely beten, pyned, prisoned &amp; sumtyme hangid &amp; drawen for worldly trespas &amp; defaute of here <MILESTONE N="182" UNIT="page">seruyce doynge, &amp; vnreuerence a&yogh;enst worldly souereyns, but of trespas &amp; dispit of god &amp; his lawe no charge but mir&thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">my&yogh;&thorn;e X.</NOTE> &amp; liynge &amp; iapynge. worldly prelatis of anticrist seyn &thorn;at lordis schullen chastise here sugetis of worldly causes, but not of lecherie ne pride ne forswerynge, be it neuere so opyn, for &thorn;at longe&thorn; to iurdiccion of prelatis; ne&thorn;eles &yogh;if &thorn;ei han money of &thorn;es lecherous &thorn;eues &thorn;ei schullen lie in here cursed synne fro &yogh;eer to &yogh;eer, &yogh;e be al here lif &yogh;if 
<PB REF="00000280.tif" N="214"> &thorn;ei paien moche &amp; redily. clerkis seyn &thorn;at lordis ben cursed &yogh;if &thorn;ei chastisen hem, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei ben neuere so foule lecherous &amp; neuere so cursed heretikis, for symonye &amp; coueitise &amp; meyntenynge of synne &amp; robbynge<NOTE PLACE="foot">robben AA.</NOTE> pore tenauntis bi extor|cions for anticristis correccions &amp; veyn halwynge of chirchis &amp; auteris &amp; o&thorn;ere iapis. &para; lord, soone &amp; esely schulde synne be hurlid oute of lond &yogh;if lordis wolden in al here wille, al here witt &amp; power dispise synne &amp; synful wrecchis, &amp; preise &amp; meyntene vertue &amp; vertuous men; &amp; certis &thorn;ei ben holden her-to vp peyne of dampnacion, for ellis &thorn;ei failen in mercy &amp; charite. god techi&thorn; it is mercy to counforten men fallen in myschif &amp; disese. &THORN;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> fend &amp; his techen &thorn;at it is almes to pursuen men<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> to prisonynge &amp; exilynge whanne &thorn;ei ben brou&yogh;t doun bi sodeyne loos, as brennynge &amp; robbynge, for riche men beren hem on honde &thorn;at it is for here synne &amp; mysreulynge of hem self, &amp; ellis o&thorn;ere bro&thorn;elis wolden renne awey wi&thorn; riche mennus good, &amp; &thorn;er-fore &thorn;ei schulden be seet in strong prison til &thorn;ei perische for hungur &amp; myschef &amp; dispeiren &amp; grucchen a&yogh;enst god; &amp; &thorn;us for loue of rotyn dritt &thorn;ei don &thorn;at is in hem to dampne many soulis. &yogh;it worldly clerkis cursen for dymes &amp; offryngis, &thorn;ou&yogh; men ben ful pore &amp; &thorn;ei don no &thorn;ing here offis, &amp; veyn religious cessen not to begge &amp; craue of pore men, &thorn;ou&yogh; here rente be bihynde &amp; here werk<NOTE PLACE="foot">wrek X.</NOTE> bestis in distresse &amp; wif &amp; childe hungry &amp; nakyd, &amp; so &thorn;ei bryngen hem in-to more myschif &amp; counforten hem not but bi lesyngis &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">of X.</NOTE> fals grauntynge of gostly helpe, &thorn;at is not in here power but only in goddis<NOTE PLACE="foot">goode X.</NOTE> delynge. &para; God techi&thorn; &thorn;at it is mercy to for&yogh;eue trespasis &amp; wrongis don a&yogh;enst men hem self &amp; algatis rancor &amp; ewil wille of herte; &thorn;e fend &amp; his seyn &thorn;at it is manlynesse &amp; ri&yogh;twisnesse &amp; almes to betyn gadlyngis &amp; be vengid on hem &thorn;at don hem wrong, for ellis &thorn;eues &amp; lorellis wolden ouerrenne hem &amp; here sugetis wolder not drede hem; but comynly &thorn;is chastysynge is don bi pride, coueitise &amp; out of charite. &amp; &thorn;ou&yogh; lordis &amp; grete men wynnen 
<PB REF="00000281.tif" N="215"> herby worldly name &amp; temperal goodis, &thorn;ei lesen charite &amp; here soule &thorn;at ben wor&thorn;i a &thorn;ousand <MILESTONE N="183" UNIT="page">fold betre &thorn;an alle er&thorn;ely tresour. &para; God sei&thorn; it is mercy &amp; charite to suffre men mekely &amp; wisly whanne &thorn;ei ben out of reson as wro&thorn; &amp; malencolious; &thorn;e fend &amp; his seyn &thorn;at &thorn;is is<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> couwardise &amp; leesynge of worldly name &amp; boldynge of euyl doeris; &amp; &thorn;erfore for o schrewed word a man mot quyte ano&thorn;er or moo, &amp; so of euyl dedis come&thorn; hate &amp; strif, &amp; fi&yogh;ttynge &amp; pledynge be reised &amp; witt &amp; reson &amp; charite exilid, &amp; many men perischid in bodi &amp; soule. god comaundi&thorn; vs to loue oure enemys of oure herte &amp; doo good to men &thorn;at hati&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">haten AA.</NOTE> vs &amp; preie for men &thorn;at pursuen vs wrongfully &amp; falsly; &thorn;e deuyl &amp; his seyn &thorn;at it is ri&yogh;tful to hate oure enemys &amp; don heuyl &amp; harm to hem &thorn;at haten vs &amp; falsly pursuen vs, &amp; axe vengaunce of oure enemys &amp; false pursueris, for ellis we schullen norische oure enemys in here synne &amp; ouerrenne vs &amp; distroie vs, oure wifis &amp; children &amp; goodis, &amp; &thorn;erfore we willen defende vs &thorn;e while &thorn;at we may. trewe men seyn to &thorn;e fend &amp; his disciplis &thorn;at &yogh;if we kepen goddis hestis oure god wole fi&yogh;ten for vs &amp; maken oure enemys afferd, &amp; bi oure goode pacience &amp; charite &amp; herty preiynge for oure enemys<NOTE PLACE="foot">synnys AA.</NOTE> &thorn;ei schulden be goddis grace cesse of here wrong &amp; turne to pees &amp; charite; &amp; &thorn;is is li&yogh;ttere &amp; betere &thorn;an to conquere al &thorn;e er&thorn;e bi dynt of swerid. &amp; &yogh;if oure enemys ben endurid in synne, as was pharaoo, oure godde wolde ordeyne &thorn;e beste for vs bo&thorn;e for body &amp; soule &yogh;if we kepen mekenesse, pacience &amp; charite; &amp; si&thorn; werris comen to men for synnys let men leue here cursed synne &amp; god of mercy &amp; pees wole &yogh;eue vs reste &amp; pees of alle er&thorn;ely enemyes. bi &thorn;es cautelis &amp; many moo the fend &amp; his disciplis distroien werkis of mercy &amp; fallen in-to loos of &thorn;ingis &thorn;at &thorn;ei coueiten mochel &amp; in-to endelis myschefes &thorn;at &thorn;ei wolen to askape, for &thorn;ei wolen not be reulid bi goddis lawe &amp; reson but bi hire wille, &amp; &thorn;er-fore alle &thorn;ingis schal turne a&yogh;enst hem at &thorn;e laste.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="3" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000282.tif" N="216">
<HEAD>Capitulum 3<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>&YOGH;it &thorn;e fend disceyue&thorn; men bi here fyue wittis &amp; make&thorn; hem menys to synne where &thorn;ei schulden be menys to vertue &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">in X.</NOTE> good gouernale of men: first he<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;ei X.</NOTE> stiri&thorn; men to seen vanyte of &thorn;is world &amp; setten here herte &thorn;er-onne &amp; for&yogh;eten god &amp; his werkis; also he stiri&thorn; men to see faire wymmen, &amp; bryngi&thorn; mynde of hem &amp; greet likynge of lecherie in-to mennus hertis til &thorn;ei consenten to synne &amp; fulfillen it in dede. &para; Also whanne men seen lordischipis of &thorn;is world &amp; precious iuelis &amp; gold &amp; siluer, faire hors &amp; scheep &amp; o&thorn;ere goodis, &thorn;e fend stire&thorn; hem to desire hem vnskilfully &amp; sette more here herte on hem &thorn;an on vertues &amp; blisse of heuene; &amp; &thorn;anne &thorn;ei fallen in-to pride &amp; coueitise &amp; o&thorn;ere synnys. but men schulden see <MILESTONE N="184" UNIT="page">goddis werkis, as heuene &amp; er&thorn;e, &amp; goddis creaturis &amp; herbi knowen &thorn;e my&yogh;t, &thorn;e wytt &amp; good|nesse of &thorn;e lord &thorn;at made alle &thorn;ingis of not, &amp; drede hym ouer alle &thorn;ingis &amp; loue him ouer alle creaturis. &para; Whanne men schulden here goddis comaundementis &amp; poyntis of charite &amp; ri&yogh;twisnesse &amp; treu&thorn;e, &thorn;e fend stiri&thorn; hem to heren foul speche of leccherie, of bacbytynge of nei&yogh;eboris &amp; lesyngis for to haue mynde &amp; likynge of synne &amp; to stire men to hate &amp; enuye &amp; pledynge &amp; fi&yogh;ttynge, so &thorn;at meke|nesse &amp; pacience &amp; charite schullen be lost &amp; cursednesse of synne regne&thorn;, &thorn;at vnne&thorn;e can ony man kepe his tonge fro fals &amp; veyn swerynge &amp; schrewid spekynge bo&thorn;e of lecherie &amp; false spekyngis. &para; Whanne men schullen in spirit smelle &thorn;e swettenesse &amp; &thorn;e holynesse of ih&umacr; crist &amp; his lif, &amp; smelle bi bodily witt &thorn;e swettenesse &amp; good odour of herbis &amp; spicis &amp; trees &amp; o&thorn;ere creaturis, to loue god &amp; serue god &amp; herie hym for his goodnesse, &thorn;e fend stiri&thorn; men to sette here lust in smellynge of lekerous metis &amp; drynkis &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> to take ouer|mochil of hem, til &thorn;ei lesen here wittis &amp; for&yogh;eten god &amp; his seruyce &amp; fallen in lecherie &amp; slepen as hooggis, &amp; chiden &amp; fi&yogh;tten as woode houndis, &amp; sweren herte &amp; bonys, &amp; cursen 
<PB REF="00000283.tif" N="217"> &amp; warien &amp; prechen opynly cursed lesyngis, &amp; &yogh;euen en|saumple of synne as cruel fendis of helle. for bi &thorn;is doynge &thorn;ei blasphemen god &amp; styren men to synne more spedly &thorn;an don many &thorn;ousand fendis bi hem self. whanne men schulden taste &amp; take mete &amp; drynk in resonable mesure to sustene here lif &amp; labore, &amp; &thorn;er-fore &thorn;ank god &amp; serue hym mekely &amp; wilfully &amp; loue hym hertly, &thorn;e fend stiri&thorn; men to sewe here owene lustis of flesch, to walwe in glotonye &amp; drounke|nesse as swyn in &thorn;e feen, &thorn;at &thorn;er is nei&thorn;er witt ne reson in hem, ne my&yogh;t to goo on &thorn;e er&thorn;e sumtyme; &amp; to fulfille &thorn;is stynkynge glotonye &amp; dronkenes &thorn;ei seken many stretis &amp; tauernes to seke lekerous morselis &amp; swete drynkis, &amp; borowen o&thorn;er mennus catel &amp; payen not a&yogh;en many tymes; for hereby &thorn;ei wasten here owene goodis &amp; o&thorn;er mennus &amp; comen to pouert &amp; ben casten in prison til &thorn;ei steruen. &amp; bi &thorn;is glotonye &amp; dronkenesse &thorn;ei wasten here owen bodi &amp; wittis &amp; fallen in-to sikenesse<NOTE PLACE="foot">drynkenssis AA.</NOTE> on many maneris &amp; lesen worldly catel &amp; my&yogh;ttis of &thorn;e soule, as vnderstondynge, mynde &amp; reson, &amp; geten peynes of helle in bodi &amp; soule, but &yogh;if &thorn;ei amende hem trewely in &thorn;is world. &amp; &thorn;e fend techi&thorn; glotonys &amp; dronkelewe men to excuse &thorn;is wast on &thorn;is manere: "God made alle goode mete &amp; drynke couenable for men schulden spende it &amp; lyue &thorn;er-by;" but &thorn;ei taken non hede of &thorn;e mesure ne hou falsly &thorn;ei lyuen a&yogh;enst goddis lawe, &amp; hou crist &amp; his seyntis tau&yogh;ten &amp; vseden abstynence &amp; penaunce, &amp; hou cristene men schulden conquere heuene bi brekynge <MILESTONE N="185" UNIT="page">of fleschly lustis, as crist techi&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel, &amp; hou crist &amp; poul &amp; petir comaunden vs &thorn;at we schullen not<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Peter ii. ll.</NOTE> fille &thorn;e desiris of oure flesch, but as gestis or comelyngis &amp; pilgrimes absteynen hem<NOTE PLACE="foot">In AA. 'hem' has been cancelled by underdotting. It should have been corrected to 'us.'</NOTE> fro fleschly desires &thorn;at fi&yogh;tten a&yogh;enst &thorn;e soule. &amp; certis &thorn;e lesse &thorn;at a man spende bo&thorn;e of mete &amp; drynk &amp; clo&thorn;e &amp; alle o&thorn;ere necessaries, so &thorn;at he be strong to serue god &amp; do his labour aftir &thorn;e staat &thorn;at god setti&thorn; him 
<PB REF="00000284.tif" N="218"> inne, so moche &thorn;e betre bo&thorn;e for body &amp; soule &amp; alle o&thorn;ere men. but hou euere we excusen vs we wasten nedeles moche goode bo&thorn;e in mete &amp; drynk &amp; clo&thorn;is, werbi pore men schulden be holpen &amp; we betre serue god &amp; lesse bisi aboute &thorn;e body &amp; more bisy aboute god &amp; hel&thorn;e of oure soulis bi lesse cost &amp; spendynge &yogh;if we holden goode mesure. &para; &THORN;e fend disceyue&thorn; men &amp; wymmen bi touchynge of membris ordeyned for genderure of mankynde, &amp; bi kissyng &amp; clippyng is &thorn;e fier of lecherie kyndlid &amp; norischid in herte til &thorn;e dede sue, &amp; many tymes long custome in<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp;X.</NOTE> &thorn;is cursed synne. &thorn;erfore sei&thorn; &thorn;e wise man, he &thorn;at handli&thorn; pich schal be foulid &thorn;er-of:<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ecclus. xiii. 1.</NOTE> &thorn;at is men handlynge wymmen &amp; kyssynge hem schullen be blickid wi&thorn; lust of lecherie, o&thorn;er in herte o&thorn;er in body or ellis in bo&thorn;e. &thorn;erfore ierom &amp; seyntis seyn &thorn;at fleynge fro suche companye &amp; abstynence &amp; saad traueile is best medecyne a&yogh;enst lecherie; but &thorn;is weiward dalliaunce wi&thorn; wymmen is so comyn &thorn;at vnne&thorn;e can ony man kepe hym clene, or sengle or weddid or men of ordre of<NOTE PLACE="foot">and AA.</NOTE> religion. And &thorn;us it is verrifyed &thorn;at god sei&thorn; by Jeromye; de&thorn; ha&thorn; entrid by &yogh;oure <NOTE PLACE="marg">Jeremiah ix. 21.</NOTE>wyndowis, &thorn;at ben fyue wittes. bi &thorn;es queyntises &amp; many moo &thorn;e fend disceyue&thorn; men &amp; of instrumentis or<NOTE PLACE="foot">of X.</NOTE> menys &amp; armu[r]e of vertue he maki&thorn; instrumentis or menys &amp; armour of synne. God graunte vs grace to haue mynde on &thorn;e peynes &thorn;at crist suffrede in his<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> herte, in his hondis &amp; feet, in his heed, in his si&yogh;tte, &amp; herynge, spekynge, smellynge, &amp; tastynge, &amp; in eche place of his bodi fro &thorn;e heued to &thorn;e sole of &thorn;e foot, &amp; to spende alle &thorn;e my&yogh;ttis of soule &amp; bodi &amp; oure fyue wittis trewely in his seruyce, to seke his worschipe in<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; X.</NOTE> alle &thorn;ingis &amp; distroie synne &amp; falsnesse bo&thorn;e in oure self &amp; o&thorn;ere men, &amp; to holde &amp; meyntene vertuous lif &amp; ri&yogh;twis|nesse &amp; pees &amp; charite. Amen.</P>


</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="14" TYPE="tract"><PB REF="00000285.tif" N="219">
<HEAD>XIV. HOW RELIGIOUS MEN SHOULD KEEP CERTAIN ARTICLES. </HEAD>
<HEADNOTE><P>I SEE nothing in this tract to give us any certainty as to its authorship. It is simply an enumeration of the faults charged against the religious orders, thrown into the form of a wish that they may be avoided.</P><P>The special points for notice are the mention of astronomy among the subjects taught in the religious schools (No. 39), and the complaint that the friars were "too homely with gentlewomen by colour of physic" (No. 38), (cf. Prof. Brewer's preface to Monumenta Franciscana, pp. xliii-xlvi). The same charge is made in the tract Of the Leaven of Pharisees. The abuse of bishoprics <I>in partibus infidelium</I> conferred on men who only desire episcopal orders for the profit to be made of them at home (No. 40) is, I think, mentioned nowhere else in this volume. It is attacked in the Great Sentence of Curse (S.E.W. III. 300).</P><P>We may see from No. 42 the kind of retort made by the friars on the poor preachers.</P><P>The only indication of date is in No. 26, where we learn that one of the points of the poor preachers was the application of the prophecies of Antichrist to the Pope. The preachers are not likely to have begun with arguments of this kind. Still we cannot lay much stress on this argument; such use of prophecy had long been familiar to the Fraticelli.</P><P>Copied from the Corpus MS. X. and collated with the Dublin MS. AA.</P><P>I have omitted the usual summary as useless with a mere list like this.</P></HEADNOTE>

<PB REF="00000286.tif" N="220">
<HEAD>How religious men shoulde kepe certayne Articles.<NOTE PLACE="foot">The title in AA. is "Hou men of priuat religioun schulden loue more &thorn;e gospel, goddis heste and his ordynaunce &thorn;an ony newe lawis, newe reulis and custumes and ordynauncis of synful men." The title given above is inserted in X by a later hand; having been omitted by the scribe. I have left the shorter title for its greater convenience.</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Cristene men preien mekely &amp; deuoutly to almy&yogh;tty god &thorn;at he graunte his grace for his hendeles mercy to oure religious, bo&thorn;e possessioneris &amp; mendynauntis, &thorn;at &thorn;ei assenten to &thorn;is fewe treu&thorn;is. &para; First, &thorn;at &thorn;ei louen more<NOTE PLACE="marg">I.<NOTE PLACE="foot">The numbers at the side are only in AA.</NOTE></NOTE> heuenly &thorn;ingis &thorn;an worldly &thorn;at soone schullen passe. &thorn;e secunde, &thorn;at &thorn;ei setten more pris &amp; deynte bi goddis comaunde|mentis &thorn;an bi tradicions maad <MILESTONE N="186" UNIT="page">of here owene synful hedis.<NOTE PLACE="foot">dedis X.</NOTE> &para; &thorn;e &thorn;ridde, &thorn;at &thorn;ei holden in herte, in word, &amp; dede &thorn;at &thorn;e noble religion maad of <ABBR>ihu</ABBR><NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> crist for prestis in here clennesse &amp; fredom is more perfit &thorn;an ony newe<NOTE PLACE="foot">rewe X.</NOTE> religion maad of synful men &thorn;at ofte erreden in &thorn;ou&yogh;t, word &amp; dede. &para; &thorn;e fir&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei chargen more sixtene condicions of charite &thorn;an here <NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. xiii. 4.</NOTE>bodely abite. &para; &thorn;e fifte, &thorn;at &thorn;ei loue more pouert of &thorn;e gospel, to whiche &thorn;ei ben bounden bi here owene reule &amp; profession, &thorn;an richesse of &thorn;e world, &thorn;at ben clepid drit bi seynt &thorn;oul in <NOTE PLACE="marg">Phil. iii. 8.</NOTE>holy writt, for which richessis &thorn;ei make ofte sacrifice to fendis &amp; honouren false goddis as seynt poul sei&thorn;. &para; &thorn;e sixte, <NOTE PLACE="marg">Col. iii. 5.</NOTE>&thorn;at &thorn;ei loue more resonable abstynence &thorn;an glotonye, wombe ioie &amp; ydelnesse. &para; &thorn;e seuen&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei loue more &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of holy writt &thorn;an ypocrisie &amp; lesyngis of &thorn;e fend. &para; &thorn;e e&yogh;te, &thorn;at &thorn;ei loue more &thorn;e honour of god &amp; saluacion of mennus soulis &thorn;an here owen worldly pride &amp; veyn glorie &amp; singuler profit. &para; &thorn;e neyen&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei setten more prise bi &thorn;e most ri&yogh;tful &amp; most profitable ordynaunce <SUP>6</SUP>of god,<SUP>6</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">6_6 omitted X.</NOTE> bo&thorn;e for clerkis, lordis &amp; comunys, &thorn;an bi &thorn;e wrongful &amp; vnwitty ordynaunce of synful men &thorn;at harmen alle &thorn;es &thorn;re. &para; &thorn;e ten&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei louen more &amp; kepen betre &thorn;e most witti reulis of ih&umacr; crist &thorn;an &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000287.tif" N="221"> vnwitti constitucions of synful &amp; worldly men. &para; &thorn;e elleuen&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei magnyfien more obedience maad to god in cristendom takynge biforme of &thorn;e gospel &thorn;an newe obedience maad singulerly to a synful man, &thorn;at is not comaundid of god nei&thorn;er ensaumplid of ih&umacr; crist &amp; his apostlis but don of here owene synguler ordynaunce. &para; &THORN;e twel&thorn;e, &thorn;at noman be dispised ne ponyschid for good lyuynge in suynge ih&umacr; cristis steppis bi forme of &thorn;e gospel. &para; &THORN;e &thorn;ritten&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei studie &amp; kepe more &thorn;e fredom &amp; priuylegies grauntid of ih&umacr; crist in &thorn;e gospel &thorn;an wrongful priuelegies grauntid of synful men, bi whiche bo&thorn;e pride &amp; coueitise &amp; &thorn;efte &amp; wrongis ben meyntened many tymes. &para; &THORN;e fourten&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben verreyly dede to pompe &amp; pride &amp; coueitise of &thorn;e world &amp; to giotonye &amp; to fleschly synnes, &amp; not ded fro nedful traueile &amp; profitenge to o&thorn;ere men vp &thorn;e &yogh;iftis &thorn;at god<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> ha&thorn; &yogh;ouen hym. &para; &THORN;e fiften&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben not goddis maistris, to dwelle euermore in o place &amp; o manere of lif at here owene lust, but frely &amp; wilfully aftir goddis &yogh;iftis traueilen &amp; dwelle &thorn;er &thorn;at it<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> is most worschipful to god &amp; most nedful &amp; profitable to cristene soulis. &para; &thorn;e sexten&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben verrey bokis &amp; myrrours of mekenesse, wilful pouert &amp; of besi traueile in goddis cause &amp; holynesse to alle men in &thorn;e world, &amp; not bok or myrrour of <MILESTONE N="187" UNIT="page">pride, of coueitise, of ydelnesse &amp; worldly lif to drawe worldly men<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> in-to coueitise &amp; o&thorn;ere synnys &amp; at here laste to helle. &thorn;e seuenten&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei drawen not noble bokis of holy writt &amp; holy doctouris &amp; o&thorn;ere nedeful sciencis fro curatis &amp; clerkis in-to here owene cloistris, &thorn;at ben as castellis or paleicis of kyngis &amp; emperouris, &amp; suffre hem be closed &thorn;ere &amp; waxe rotyn, &amp; nei&thorn;er &yogh;eue hem ne lene hem ne selle hem to curatis &amp; clerkis, &thorn;at my&yogh;tten, couden &amp; wolden lerne holy writt &amp; teche it frely for loue of mennus soulis. &thorn;e ei&yogh;ten&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei louen more comyn profit of cristene men, bo&thorn;e gostly &amp; bodily, &thorn;an here synguler worldly profit &amp; here owene bodily ayse &amp; welfare. &thorn;e neynten&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei 
<PB REF="00000288.tif" N="222"> make not discencion ne gendre strif ne enuye among cristene men bi multipliynge of newe sectis, newe abitis &amp; newe bi|lawis, But drawe to vnyte &amp; charite, as &thorn;er is o god, o bileue, &amp; o cristendom. &thorn;e twenti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei suffre not pore men to be oppressid bi taxis &amp; o&thorn;ere chargis more &thorn;an &thorn;ei may wel bere, &thorn;e while &thorn;at &thorn;ei han plente of richesses &amp; wast iuelis to purchase londis &amp; lordischipis &amp; bilde grete waste houses, si&thorn; alle here goodis ben pore mennus goodis, &amp; &thorn;ei ben but spenderis or keperis of &thorn;e goodis &amp; procura|touris of pore men, as seynt ierom &amp; &thorn;e lawe of &thorn;e chirche witnessen. &thorn;e on and twenti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei conforten not riche men in here false lif, &amp; stoppe not restitucion to be maad to pore men bi sikyrnesse of here perpetual preiere, whanne &thorn;ei witten not where here preiere be wor&thorn; o fer&thorn;ing. &thorn;e two &amp; twenti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei make not comyns so pore bi sotil ypocrisie of gredy beggynge &amp; trentalis, to make grete festis &amp; waste housynge, &thorn;at &thorn;e comyns may not for&thorn;e to paie here tribut to &thorn;e kyng &amp; rentis to lordis &amp; dymes &amp; offrynges to curatis. &thorn;e &thorn;re &amp; twen&thorn;e, &thorn;at in alle &thorn;ingis &thorn;ei ben bisi to seke goddis worschipe &amp; loue hym &amp; his lawe &amp; holde no custome ne tradicion &thorn;at hyndri&thorn; hem<NOTE PLACE="foot">hym X.</NOTE> to serue god, but take goode customes in as moche as &thorn;ei helpen hem to kepe goddis hestis &amp; no more, for lif ne for de&thorn;. god brynge hem to &thorn;is charite. &thorn;e foure &amp; twenti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei hiren not grete men bi gold fees &amp; robees &amp; false gostly helpe to be goddis traitouris, holdynge a&yogh;enst his lawe &amp; his ordynaunce to magnifye anticristis clerkis &amp; synful mennus ordynaunce. &thorn;e fyue &amp; twenti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei quenche not &thorn;e &yogh;iftis of god &amp; so &thorn;e holy gost as moche as is in hem, lettynge trewe prechynge of &thorn;e gospel, laste here pride, coueitise &amp; ypocrisie be knowen. &thorn;e sixe<NOTE PLACE="foot">si&thorn;e X.</NOTE> &amp; twenti&thorn;e, <MILESTONE N="188" UNIT="page">&thorn;at &thorn;ei pursuen not crist in his membris for trewe prechynge of holy writt &amp; trewe schewynge of synne to &thorn;e peple, &amp; of anticrist &amp; his clerkis, bi prophecie of ih&umacr; crist &amp; his apostlis, pleynly tau&yogh;t &amp; 
<PB REF="00000289.tif" N="223"> comaundid of god to be tau&yogh;t trewely &amp; opynly to his peple. &thorn;e seuene &amp; twenti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei blyndyn not &thorn;e kyng &amp; lordis bi ypocrisie &amp; false lesyngis to meyntene wrong ordynaunce of synful men for pride &amp; coueitise, a&yogh;enst goddis lawe &amp; here owene profit &amp; helpe of &thorn;e comyns. &thorn;e ei&yogh;te &amp; twenti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei approprien not parische chirchis to ouer riche houses bi false sugestions &amp; symonye, &amp; putten &thorn;ere an ydiot, &amp; &yogh;euen hym to litel liflode &amp; taken alle &thorn;e profite to hem self, &amp; letten goode curatis of here liflode &amp; trewe techynge of cristene peple &amp; helpe of pore men in<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; X.</NOTE> parischis &amp; goddis seruyce &amp; holdynge vp of &thorn;e chirchis in hilynge &amp; bokis &amp; o&thorn;ere ornamentis. &thorn;e nyne and twenti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei procuren not children to here religion bi sikyrnesse of worldly lordischipe &amp; wombe ioie &amp; ydelnesse, &amp; &thorn;anne make hem bi profession bynde hem to grett pouert &amp; to be dede to worldly myr&thorn;e &amp; likynge; si&thorn; &thorn;o &thorn;at comen more to &thorn;es religious for pride, coueitise, sikyrnesse of bodily welfare &thorn;an for loue of meke|nesse to lyue in pouert &amp; discret abstynence &amp; penaunce, ben cursed &amp; symonyentis in &thorn;e entre. &thorn;e &thorn;ritti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;es mendynauntis disceyuen not children bi lesyngis &amp; ypocrisie &amp; biheste of worldly honour &amp; welfare as wel as gret prelatis &amp; bischopis to come &amp; lyue herby in here priuat secte, preisynge it more &thorn;an &thorn;e noble &amp; free religion maad &amp; kept of ih&umacr; crist &amp; his apostlis. &thorn;e on &amp; &thorn;ritti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei stelen not riche mennus children &amp; pore, &amp; leden hem to ferre contres fro here frendis &amp; holde hem cloos til &thorn;ei ben professid a&yogh;enst here wille, &amp; &thorn;an suffre hem not to goo out &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei ben vnable to kepe &thorn;is religion; si&thorn; &thorn;ei sillen in a manere &thorn;es children to &thorn;is priuat ordre for worschipe &amp; worldly wynnyng &amp; constreyne hem to here dampnacion. &thorn;e two &amp; &thorn;ritti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei sende not gold out of &thorn;e rewme in-to aliens hondis for to gete priuylegies &amp; dispensacions a&yogh;enst &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> poyntis of here reule &yogh;if it be resonable &amp; profitable, &amp; &yogh;if it be vnresonable &amp; vnprofitable late no man bynde hym 
<PB REF="00000290.tif" N="224"> &thorn;er-to; But lyue frely vnder clene religion &thorn;at crist maade in whiche may noon errour be. &thorn;e &thorn;re &amp; &thorn;ritti&thorn;e, &thorn;at, si&thorn; &thorn;ei preisen so mochil obedience maad to man, &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben not exempt fro obedience to bischopis &amp; to &thorn;e comyn lawe bo&thorn;e of &thorn;e chirche &amp; of &thorn;e lond. &thorn;e foure &amp; &thorn;ritti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei &yogh;euen not a pencion of moche gold to &thorn;e pope for to be exempt fro visitacions of bischopis &amp; iust correccion, si&thorn; &thorn;ei holden <MILESTONE N="189" UNIT="page">mannus obedience so medful, last herby &thorn;ei waxen rotyn in synne &amp; &thorn;e ordynaries doren not amende hem bi forme of &thorn;e gospel for &thorn;es weiward exempcions, si&thorn; robert grosted clepi&thorn; siche exempcion &thorn;e deuelis nettis. &para; &thorn;e fyue &amp; &thorn;ritti&thorn;e, si&thorn; it is a grete sentence of &thorn;e chirche &thorn;at who euere do&thorn; a&yogh;enst &thorn;e ri&yogh;tful wille of a dede man is cursed, late it be enquired where &thorn;es religious, myspendynge here goodis in pompe &amp; worldly plees &amp; newe purchasynge, &amp; leuynge &thorn;e noumbre of prestis &amp; helpynge of pore men, a&yogh;enst here foundouris wille, &amp; getynge priuylegies &amp; dispensynge a&yogh;enst here reulis maad of holy men as &thorn;ei seyn, where &thorn;ei ben cursed or not; &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ei ben late alle men helpe &amp; make hem kepe &thorn;e friste ri&yogh;tful wille of here<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> foundour &amp; patron. &thorn;e sixe &amp; &thorn;ritti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei make not enuye, strif &amp; plee bitwixe curatis &amp; hem and<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> bitwixe curatis &amp; here sugetis for here priueleygies of confession &amp; sepulture &amp; mortuaries &amp; false lesyngis makynge. &thorn;e seuene &amp; &thorn;ritti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei norischen not men &amp; wommen in lecherie, in wrong disceit of fals chaffarynge &amp; extorcion doynge, lettynge verrey resti|tucion of euyl goten goodis &amp; &thorn;e schame of grete synneris &yogh;if &thorn;ei were schryue at here owene curatis, for to haue part of &thorn;is<NOTE PLACE="foot">his X.</NOTE> robberie, &amp; make worldly festis &amp; wast houses a&yogh;enst here pouert &amp; profession, bi colour of trentalis &amp; longe preieris in si&yogh;tte of men. &thorn;e ei&yogh;te &amp; &thorn;ritti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben not in lordis courtis reuleris of here householdis &amp; worldly officis, &amp; to homly wi&thorn; gentil wymmen bi colour of fisik, for drede of sclaundrynge &amp; mysdoynge, si&thorn; &thorn;ei lyuen in reste &amp; 
<PB REF="00000291.tif" N="225"> welfare of body &amp; ben &yogh;onge &amp; stronge of complexion, &amp; sathanas is redi to tempte hem. &para; &thorn;e nyne &amp; &thorn;ritti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei studien bisily holy writt &amp; techen it more &thorn;an veyn sophistrie &amp; astronomye &amp; more &thorn;an &thorn;e popis decretalis &amp; fablis &amp; cronyclis; si&thorn; &thorn;at it<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> is best &amp; most nedeful &amp; &thorn;ei han grete wittes of kynde &amp; grete leiser to studien &thorn;us. &thorn;e forti&thorn;&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben not maad bischopis of he&thorn;ene men &amp; sweren to goo &thorn;ider &amp; conuerte hem, &amp; &thorn;anne meyntened to be suffragans &amp; sellen sacramentis &amp; robben &thorn;e peple &amp; maken hem haue goddis curs for here money. &thorn;e on &amp; fourti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;es newe religious blasphemen not god in holdynge a prest of here ordre apostata &amp; cursed &yogh;if he lyue among cristene peple where he ha&thorn; resonable euydence to profit most bi good ensaumple of holy lif &amp; trewe &amp; free prechynge wi&thorn;-oute flaterynge &amp; beggynge &amp; lesyngis sewynge. &para;&thorn;e two &amp; fourti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei blasphemen not god, takynge vp-on hem self knowynge approprid to god, &thorn;at &thorn;is prest coueiti&thorn; fredom of &thorn;e <MILESTONE N="190" UNIT="page">gospel for his eise &amp; lustis in synne of bodi; &thorn;at &thorn;is child schal betre serue god in &thorn;is newe ordre than in clene ordre &thorn;at crist maade; &thorn;at it is betre to begge of pore men &amp; do aftir o foolis styrynge &thorn;an do mercy to cristene soulis aftir stirynge of god. &thorn;e &thorn;re &amp; fourti&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei preise not more obedience to synful men bi synguler profession, not ensaumplid<NOTE PLACE="foot">ensaumplis in both MSS.</NOTE> of crist &amp; his apostlis, &thorn;an medful obedience of children to fadir &amp; modir &amp; of seruauntis to here lordis &amp; maistris; si&thorn; god techi&thorn; &amp; com|aunde &thorn;is obedience &amp; &thorn;e merit &thorn;er-of, last mannus folie be hei&yogh;ed more &thorn;an goddis ordynaunce. &thorn;e laste, &thorn;at alle clerkis of religion &amp; o&thorn;ere examynen wel whiche is &thorn;e beste ordre for prestis, where it be possessioneris ordre or mendynauntis or ellis &thorn;e mene &thorn;at crist made &amp; kepte &amp; his apostlis alle; &thorn;at is presthod bi fredom &amp; clennesse of cristis reule in &thorn;e gospel. &amp; late alle prestis kepe &thorn;e beste &amp; leue &thorn;e lesse profit. god for his<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> endeles mercy brynge alle prestis her-to &amp; make lordis &amp; comyns to constreyne hem to &thorn;is. Amen.</P>


