<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>Of seruauntis &amp; lordis hou eche schal kepe his degree.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<P>First, seruauntis schullen trewely &amp; gladly serue to here lordis or maistris &amp; not be fals ne idel ne grucchynge ne heuey in here seruyce doynge, but holde hem paied of &thorn;e staat of seruauntis, in whiche god ha&thorn; ordeyned hem for here beste to holde hem in mekenesse a&yogh;enst pride, &amp; besi traueile a&yogh;enst ydelnesse &amp; slou&thorn;e. for seynt poul biddi&thorn; &thorn;at &yogh;if &thorn;ou<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. vii. [21.]</NOTE> be clepid a seruaunt, recke &thorn;ou not &thorn;er-of; &thorn;at is to seie be not grucchynge ne heuy &thorn;erfore. &para; Also poul techi&thorn; &thorn;us: "&yogh;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ephes. vi. [5.]</NOTE> seruauntis obeische to fleschly lordis wi&thorn; drede &amp; quakynge or tremelynge, in sympilnesse of &yogh;oure herte, as to crist; not seruynge at &thorn;e ei&yogh;e, as plesynge to men, but as seruauntis of crist, doynge &thorn;e wille of god of herte, wi&thorn; goode wille seruynge as to &thorn;e lord of alle lordis &amp; not to men; wittynge &thorn;at eche man what euere good &thorn;ing he do schal resceyue &thorn;at of &thorn;e lord, be he seruaunt or bonde or free man;" &thorn;at is to seie reward of god for &thorn;at good doynge. &para; Also poul techi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Col. iii. [22.]</NOTE> &thorn;us seruauntis; "obeche, &yogh;e seruauntis, bi alle &thorn;ingis to fleschly lordis. what &thorn;ing euere &yogh;e don worche &yogh;e of herte, &thorn;at is wisdom &amp; wille, as to &thorn;e lord &amp; not to men, witynge &thorn;at of &thorn;e lord &yogh;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">he X.</NOTE> schulle take<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> retribucion, &thorn;at is mede or reward, of heritage in heuene. serue &yogh;e to &thorn;e lord crist; for who &thorn;at do&thorn; wrong or iniurye schal resceyue &thorn;at &thorn;ing &thorn;at he ha&thorn; wickydly don, &amp; anemptis god is not accepcion or takynge of personys." &thorn;at is o man schal not be sparid in goddis dom for his richessis or lordschipis or hei&yogh; blood, &amp; a pore man be ponyschid for a litel trespas, as men don in &thorn;is wickid world, but eche man schal be ponyschid after his owene gilte, &amp; <MILESTONE N="191" UNIT="page">eche man rewardid after his owene goode lif. but here &thorn;e fend moue&thorn; summe men to seie &thorn;at cristene men schullen not be seruauntis or &thorn;rallis to he&thorn;ene lordis, si&thorn; &thorn;ei ben false to god &amp; lasse wor&thorn;y &thorn;an cristene men; nei&thorn;er to cristene lordis, for &thorn;ei ben bre&thorn;eren in kynde, &amp; ih&umacr; crist bou&yogh;te cristene 
<PB REF="00000294.tif" N="228"> men on &thorn;e crois &amp; made hem fre; but a&yogh;enst &thorn;is heresie poul writi&thorn; &thorn;us in<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; X.</NOTE> goddis lawe: "what kynne seruauntis ben vnder<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Tim. vi. [1.]</NOTE> &yogh;ook of seruage deme &thorn;ei here lordis wor&thorn;i alle manere honour or worschipe, &thorn;at &thorn;e name &amp; techynge of &thorn;e lord be not blasphemyd," &thorn;at is, holden wrongful &amp; dispised; &amp; &thorn;is word is vndirstonden of he&thorn;ene lordis. "but &thorn;o seruauntis &thorn;at han trewe or cristene lordis, dispise &thorn;ei not to serue hem for &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben bre&thorn;eren bo&thorn;e in kynde &amp; in fei&thorn;, but more serue &thorn;ei for &thorn;e lordis ben cristene &amp; louyd, &thorn;e whiche ben partyneris of good dede. teche &thorn;ou &thorn;es &thorn;ingis," sei&thorn; poul to bischop thymothe, "bo&thorn;e to men &thorn;at ben vnlerned, And stire men &thorn;at ben lerned &amp; necligent in doynge. &yogh;if ony man techi&thorn; o&thorn;er wise, &amp; accordi&thorn; not to &thorn;e hoole wordis of oure lord ih&umacr; crist &amp; to &thorn;at lore &thorn;at is after pitee, he is proude, no &thorn;ing kunnynge, but weilynge or languyschynge aboute questiouns &amp; fi&yogh;ttynge of wordis, of whiche ben gendred enuyes<NOTE PLACE="foot">enemyes X.</NOTE> st[r]yues &amp; blasphemes, &thorn;at ben dispisyngis of god, euyl suspescions &amp; fi&yogh;ttyngis to-gedre of men &thorn;at ben corupt in herte or soule, &thorn;at ben priued fro treu&thorn;e." &para; Also poul<NOTE PLACE="marg">Titus ii. [8. 10.]</NOTE> techi&thorn; &thorn;at generaly cristene men &amp; wymmen schullen be so holy of lif, &thorn;at men out of bileue be aschamed &amp; haue noon euyl to seie of cristene men, &amp; chargi&thorn; seruauntis to be suget, or vnderlout,<NOTE PLACE="foot">under lout X.</NOTE> to here lordis, &amp; plesynge in alle &thorn;ingis, &amp; not a&yogh;en seiynge, not doynge fraude, but in alle &thorn;ingis schewynge good fei&thorn; or fidelite or treu&thorn;e, to worschipe, or to make fair in alle &thorn;ingis &thorn;e techynge of god oure saueour. And &thorn;erfore techi&thorn; petir &thorn;at cristene men schullen haue so<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Peter iii. [16.]</NOTE> good conscience &amp; so good lif &thorn;at enemys of oure fei&thorn; &thorn;at bakbiten or myspeken of vs ben confounded, &amp; also &thorn;ei &thorn;at falsly chalengen oure goode lif in crist be stoppid; &amp; petir speki&thorn; more pleynly of &thorn;is matir, &amp; comaundi&thorn; cristene men<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Peter ii. [12.]</NOTE> to haue goode lyuynge amonge he&thorn;ene men, &thorn;at in &thorn;at &thorn;ing &thorn;at &thorn;ei myspeken of vs, as of mysdoeris, &thorn;at &thorn;ei beholden &amp; see vs of oure goode werkis, &amp; glorifie god in &thorn;e tyme of 
<PB REF="00000295.tif" N="229"> visitacion. &para;But &yogh;it summe men &thorn;at ben out of charite sclaundren pore prestis wi&thorn; &thorn;is errour, &thorn;at seruauntis or tenauntis may lawefully wi&thorn;holde rentis &amp; seruyce<NOTE PLACE="foot">servyces AA.</NOTE> fro here lordis whanne lordis ben opynly wickid in here lyuynge. &amp; &thorn;ei maken &thorn;is false <MILESTONE N="192" UNIT="page">lesyngis vpon pore prestis to make lordis to hate hem, &amp; not to meyntene treu&thorn;e of goddis lawe &thorn;at &thorn;ei techen opynly for worschipe of god &amp; profit of<NOTE PLACE="foot">on X.</NOTE> &thorn;e reume and stablynge of &thorn;e kyngis pouer &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">in X.</NOTE> distroynge of synne. for &thorn;es pore prestis distroien most bi goddis lawe rebelte of seruauntis a&yogh;enst lordis, &amp; charge seruauntis to be suget &thorn;ou&yogh; lordis bi tirauntis, for seynt petir techi&thorn; &thorn;us: "Be ye ser|uauntis<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Peter ii. [18.]</NOTE> suget to lordis in alle manere of<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> drede, not only to goode lordis &amp; bonere,<NOTE PLACE="foot">honoure X.</NOTE> but also to tirauntis, or siche &thorn;at drawen fro goddis scole." for, as seynt poul sei&thorn;, eche<NOTE PLACE="marg">Romans xiii. [1.]</NOTE> man owi&thorn; to be suget to hei&yogh;ere potestatis, &thorn;at is to men of hei&yogh;e power, for &thorn;er is no power but of god; &amp; so he &thorn;at a&yogh;enstondi&thorn; power, stondi&thorn; a&yogh;enst &thorn;e ordynaunce of god; but &thorn;ei &thorn;at a&yogh;enstonden geten to hem self dampnacion. &amp; &thorn;erfore poul biddi&thorn; &thorn;at we be suget to princes bi nede, &amp; not only for wra&thorn;&thorn;e but also for conscience; &amp; &thorn;erfore we paien tributis to princis, for &thorn;ei ben mynystris of god; &amp; poul biddi&thorn; vs paie dettis to alle men, tribut to hym &thorn;at we owen tribut, &amp; so of taliage for &thorn;ingis boren aboute in lond, &amp; so drede &amp; also worschipe or honour. &amp; &thorn;us seruauntis schulden trewely &amp; wilfully seruen lordis &amp; here maistris, &amp; lyue in reste, pees &amp; charite, &amp; stire lordis, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei weren he&thorn;ene lordis, to good cristene fei&thorn; &amp; holy lif bi here pacience &amp; opyn trewe lif &amp; meke. &amp; &thorn;is is a feyned word of anticristis clerkis &thorn;at, &yogh;if sugetis may leffully wi&thorn;drawe ti&thorn;es &amp; offryngis fro curatis &thorn;at openly lyuen in lecherie or grete o&thorn;ere synnes &amp; don not here office, &thorn;an seruauntis &amp; tenauntis may wi&thorn;|drawe here seruyce &amp; rentis fro here lordis &thorn;at lyuen opynly a cursed lif. for to &thorn;e first sugetis han &thorn;e auctorite of goddis lawe &amp; mannus lawe also, but not to wi&thorn;drawe 
<PB REF="00000296.tif" N="230"> seruyce &amp; rentis fro wickid lordis; but ben chargid of god bi petir &amp; poul to be &thorn;us suget to wickid lordis; &amp; &thorn;erfore crist paiede for hym &amp; his apostlis tribut to &thorn;e he&thorn;ene<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. xvii. [27.]</NOTE> emperour. &amp; we reden not &thorn;at he or ony apostle paide ti&thorn;es to &thorn;e wickid hei&yogh;e prestis after tyme &thorn;at he began to preche. &para; Also lordis han power of mennus bodies &amp; catel in resonable<NOTE PLACE="marg">Rom. xiii. [1-7.]</NOTE> maner, &amp; temperale swerd &amp; worldly power bi goddis lawe to compelle men to do here seruyce &amp; paie rentis, but bi &thorn;e gospel &amp; cristis lif &amp; his apostlis, prestis han not siche power to constreyne men to paie hem dymes, &amp; principaly whanne &thorn;ei don not here gostly office, but harmen here sugetis in fals techynge &amp; euyl ensaumple of lif. but &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei deden wele here office &amp; men wolden not paie dymes, &thorn;ei schulden suffren mekely &amp; not curse, as ih&umacr; crist dide.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke ix. [55.]</NOTE></P>
<P>See we now hou lordis schulden lyue in here astaat. first, &thorn;ei <MILESTONE N="193" UNIT="page">schulden knowe goddis lawe &amp; studie it &amp; meyntene it, &amp; distroie wrong &amp; meyntene pore men in here ri&yogh;t to lyue in reste, pees &amp; charite, &amp; suffre no<NOTE PLACE="foot">not X.</NOTE> men vnder colour of hem to do extorcions, bete men, &amp; holde pore men out of ri&yogh;t bi streng&thorn;e of lordischipis. &para; For &thorn;us speki&thorn; holy writt in &thorn;e fifte<NOTE PLACE="foot">first AA.</NOTE> bok of goddis lawe; "whanne &thorn;e kyng is ordeyned bi<NOTE PLACE="marg">Deut. xvii. [16.]</NOTE> &thorn;e chesynge of god &amp; of his peple, he schal not multiplie to hym self many hors, he schal not haue many wyues to drawe his herte to lustis, &amp; he schal not haue oute of mesure grete wei&yogh;ttis of siluer &amp; gold, but after &thorn;at he schal sitte in sege of his regne, he schal writte to him &thorn;e bok of goddis lawe in a volym, takynge ensaumplerie of prestis of &thorn;e kynrede of leuy, &amp; haue it wi&thorn; him, &amp; he schal rede &thorn;at alle &thorn;e daies of his lif, &thorn;at he kunne drede &thorn;e lord his god &amp; kepe his wordis, &thorn;e whiche ben comaundid in &thorn;e lawe, &amp; his herte schal not be lift vp in-to pride vpon his bre&thorn;eren, &amp; he schal not croke in-to &thorn;e ri&yogh;tte side ne in-to &thorn;e left side, &thorn;at he &amp; his children regne long tyme vpon Israel." &para; Also kyngis &amp; lordis schulde axe of god, bi gret desir &amp; holy lif, wisdom of 
<PB REF="00000297.tif" N="231"> heuenely &thorn;ingis &amp; kunnynge of er&thorn;ely &thorn;ingis to reule goddis peple bi, &amp; not richessis, ne worldly substaunces,<NOTE PLACE="foot">sustenaunces X.</NOTE> ne worldly glorie, ne vnresonable vengaunces of here enemys, ne long lif in &thorn;is world, as kyng samon<NOTE PLACE="foot">salamon AA.</NOTE> dede, &amp; &thorn;erfore god &yogh;af him wisdom of heuenely &thorn;ingis &amp; of er&thorn;ely &thorn;ingis &amp; richessis &amp; substaunce &amp; glorie, &thorn;at neuere kyng bi-fore hadde so moche ne aftir. &para; Also so<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> kyngis &amp; lordis schulden be clo&thorn;id wi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Job xxix. [14 etc.]</NOTE> ri&yogh;twisnesse &amp; ri&yogh;tful dom as wi&thorn; a diademe, &amp; be ei&yogh;e to a blynd man &amp; foot to &thorn;e crokid or haltynge, &amp; be fadir of pore men, &amp; wi&thorn; most diligence sike &thorn;e cause &thorn;at &thorn;ei knowe not, &amp; defoule &amp; distroie &thorn;e power of a wickid man, &amp; take a-wey &thorn;e prey out of his tee&thorn;; &amp; whanne &thorn;ei sitten as kyngis<NOTE PLACE="foot">lyngis X.</NOTE> &amp; compaynes stonden aboute &thorn;ei schulden [be] confortours of mornynge men &amp; men ful of myscheyf, &amp; delyuere pore men criynge, &amp; fadirles children &amp; moderles &thorn;at han noon helpe, &amp; so haue blyssynge of him &thorn;at was in poynt to perische, &amp; conforte &thorn;e widwis herte. &thorn;es goodnessis &amp; many moo vsed &thorn;e holy kyng iob, &amp; ben in holy writt for ensaumple of kyngis &amp; lordis. Also god him self sei&thorn; bi ieromye &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jerem. xxii. 3. 5.</NOTE> he schal take vengaunce on hem &thorn;at demeden not ri&yogh;thfully &thorn;e cause<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> of widwe, &thorn;e cause of fadirles &amp; modirles, &amp; &thorn;e cause of pore men. Also god hym self sei&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> by ysaie, &thorn;at princes<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isaiah i. [16.]</NOTE> schullen cesse to don euele &amp; lerne to do wel, &amp; seke dom, &amp; helpe men oppressid wrongly, &amp; &yogh;eue dom to fadirles &amp; modirles, &amp; meyntene &thorn;e widwe, &amp; come &amp; reproue him; &thorn;at is to seie, but &yogh;if he &thorn;an helpe hem. &amp; &thorn;erfore sei&thorn; holy writt<NOTE PLACE="marg">Prov. xx. [28.]</NOTE> &thorn;at mercy &amp; trew&thorn;e kept of kyngis, &amp; his trone is maade strong bi mekenesse<MILESTONE N="194" UNIT="page">&amp; mercy, &amp; &thorn;e kyng &thorn;at sitti&thorn; in sete of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Prov. xx. 8.</NOTE> dom distroie&thorn; alle euyl in his lokynge, &amp; so it plesi&thorn; more to god to do mercy &amp; dom &thorn;an to do sacrifices; &amp; &thorn;us salamon<NOTE PLACE="marg">Prov. xxv. 5.</NOTE> sei&thorn;, &thorn;at &thorn;ei &thorn;at don wickedly ben abhominable to &thorn;e kyng, for his sete is maade stable bi ri&yogh;twisnesse; &amp; &thorn;us sei&thorn; dauid,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Psalm xcix. 4.</NOTE> &thorn;at &thorn;e honour of &thorn;e kyng loue&thorn; dom; &amp; for &thorn;e ri&yogh;tful &amp; witti dom &thorn;at salamon dide bitwixen tweie comyn wymmen, alle 
<PB REF="00000298.tif" N="232"> &thorn;e lond of israel drede hym. &amp; &thorn;erfore techi&thorn; poul &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">Rom. xiii. [3.]</NOTE> princes ben not to drede of good werk but of euyl, &amp; a man sette in grete power beri&thorn; not wi&thorn;-oute grete cause &thorn;e swerd, &thorn;at is worldly power, for he is a mynystre of god to do vengaunce to him &thorn;at do&thorn; euyle. &amp; seynt petir techi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Peter ii. [13.]</NOTE> generaly cristene men to be suget to eche man for god, &amp; to &thorn;e kyng as to souereyn bifore o&thorn;ere, &amp; to dukis as seynt of &thorn;e kyng<NOTE PLACE="foot">lyng X.</NOTE> to vengaunce of mysdedis or mysdoeris &amp; to preisynge<NOTE PLACE="foot">preiynge X.</NOTE> of goode dedis or goode doeris. &para; Also poul techi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Col. iv. [1.]</NOTE> lordis &thorn;us: "&yogh;e lordis, &yogh;eue to seruauntis &thorn;at &thorn;ing &thorn;at is ri&yogh;tful &amp; equite &amp; euene, witynge &thorn;at &yogh;e also han a lord in heuene." also poul sei&thorn; in a-pistel of ephesyns: "&amp; &yogh;e lordis, do to<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ephesians vi. [9.]</NOTE> seruauntis &thorn;e same &thorn;ingis, &thorn;at is goode ri&yogh;twisnesse &amp; equyte of herte, &amp; wi&thorn; goode wille, for&yogh;euynge manasse; witynge &thorn;at bo&thorn;e &yogh;oure lord &amp; hern is in heuenes, &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">in X.</NOTE> accepcioun<NOTE PLACE="foot">excepcion X.</NOTE> of persones is not anemptis god;" &thorn;at is, god sparet not for richesse ne lordischipe ne worldly frendischipe to ponysche synnes, &amp; sparet not for pouerte to rewarde good lyuynge of pore seruauntis.</P>
<P>&para; Si&thorn; &thorn;is is &thorn;e office of kyngis &amp; lordis, to venge &thorn;us synnys &amp; to preise &amp; rewarde goode dedis, &yogh;if lordis leuen &thorn;is office, &amp; meyn|tenen synful men &amp; wrong doeris, &amp; helpen not pore men in here ri&yogh;t, &thorn;ei may drede &thorn;at here kyngdom &amp; lordischipis schullen be translated in-to ano&thorn;er folk, as &thorn;e wyse man sei&thorn;: "a kyngdom<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ecclus x. [8.]</NOTE> is<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> translated from o peple in-to ano&thorn;er for vnri&yogh;twisnesse, &amp; iniuries or wrongis, &amp; contekis or debatis, &amp; for dyuerse giles or disceitis." for men dreden<NOTE PLACE="foot">dredem X.</NOTE> &thorn;at vnri&yogh;twisnesse a&yogh;enst god regne&thorn; in oure lond; for men dreden more to displese an er&thorn;ely dedly wrecche for lesynge of worldly frendischipe &thorn;an to displese god almy&yogh;tty &amp; to lese his moste blissed frendischipe; &amp; loue more to performe a wrong comaundement of proude luciferis children &thorn;an to performe &thorn;e moste ri&yogh;tful comaunde|ment of god, &thorn;at is esy &amp; sikirere; &amp; louen more a litel stynkynge drit of worldly goodis &thorn;an &thorn;ei louen &thorn;e blisse of 
<PB REF="00000299.tif" N="233"> heuene; for many men maken hem more bisy to geten worldly muk &thorn;an to geten vertues &amp; holy lif, &amp; maken more sorowe whanne &thorn;ei fallen fro worldly catel in-to pouerte &thorn;an whanne &thorn;ei fallyn fro grace &amp; charite &amp; o&thorn;ere vertues in-to many orble<NOTE PLACE="foot">orrible AA.</NOTE> synnys. Also men<MILESTONE N="195" UNIT="page"> louen more to venge wrongis &amp; dispites don to here owene personys or lordischipis &thorn;an to venge wronggis or dispitis don a&yogh;enst &thorn;e mageste of god almy&yogh;tty; as &yogh;if a man speke a word of litel reprof or vilonye of a lord or a grete man of &thorn;is world he schal be pursued &amp; peyned &thorn;er-fore &thorn;at alle &thorn;e world or many men schullen wondere vpon hym, but &yogh;if men speken falsnesse bi oure god, seiynge &thorn;at crist beggede<NOTE PLACE="foot">begge X.</NOTE> as men don now nedles, or dispisen his name bi cursid swerynge, or speken vilonye of lecherie or of o&thorn;ere foule synnys to foule cristene soulis &thorn;erbi, &thorn;ei ben not pursued ne hurlid out, but chirischid &amp; holde goode felawis, &amp; summe &yogh;it ben holden holy men, for goddis lawe is not knowen &amp; here ypocrisie is &yogh;it hid, &amp; &thorn;us vnri&yogh;twis|nesse regne&thorn; vpon many sidis.</P>
<P>iniuries or wrongis ben don to pore men many weies; for prelatis techen hem not treuely goddis lawe, nei&thorn;er in word ne ensaumple of holy lif, &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ei cursen faste for here dymes &amp; offryngis of pore men, whanne &thorn;ei schulden ra&thorn;ere &yogh;eue hem worldly goodis &thorn;an take of hem; for prelatis wasten in pride, glotonye,<NOTE PLACE="foot">gloterie AA. and so generally through the tract.</NOTE> worldly plees &amp; grete festis of lordis and riche men &thorn;e tresor of pore men, &thorn;e while &thorn;ei ben in moche peyne &amp; wrecchidnesse in bodi &amp; soule; &amp; &yogh;it prelatis wolen not do sacramentis &amp; here gostly office to here sugetis, as halwynge of chirchis and auteris &amp; chirche&yogh;erdis &amp; o&thorn;ere ornementis, but<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &yogh;if men bien hem for moche money; &amp; &thorn;anne comynly &thorn;e biere &amp; &thorn;e sellere ben cursed of god. also lordis many tymes don wrongis to pore men bi extorscions &amp; vnresonable mercy|mentis &amp; vnresonable taxis, &amp; taken pore mennus goodis &amp; paien not &thorn;erfore but white stickis, &amp; dispisen hem &amp; 
<PB REF="00000300.tif" N="234"> manassen hem &amp; sumtyme beten hem whanne &thorn;ei axen here peye. &amp; &thorn;us lordis deuouren pore mennus goodis in glotonye &amp; wast &amp; pride, &amp; &thorn;ei perischen for myschief, &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">as X.</NOTE> hungur &amp; &thorn;rist &amp; colde, &amp; &thorn;ere children also; &amp; &yogh;if here rente be not redily paied here bestis ben stressid &amp; &thorn;ei &thorn;ursued wi&thorn;outen mercy, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei be neuere so pore &amp; nedi &amp; ouerchargid wi&thorn; age, febilnesse &amp; loos of catel &amp; wi&thorn; many children. &amp; &yogh;it lordis wolen not mekely here a pore mannus cause &amp; helpe hym in his ri&yogh;te, but suffre sisouris of contre to distroie hem, but ra&thorn;ere wy&thorn;holden pore men here hire, for whiche &thorn;ei han spendid here fleisch &amp; here blood. &amp; so in a manere &thorn;ei eten &amp; drynken pore mennus fleisch &amp; blood &amp; ben manquelleris, as god pleyne&thorn; bi his prophetis. where-fore god sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e prophete ysaie, &thorn;at siche lordis ben felawis of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isaiah i. [15. 23.]</NOTE> &thorn;euys &amp; here hondis ben ful of blood, &amp; &thorn;erfore whanne &thorn;ei preien many preieris bi mou&thorn; &amp; holden vp <MILESTONE N="196" UNIT="page">here hondis, god wole not here hem ne resceyue here offryngis &thorn;at ben wrong|fully geten of pore mennus goodis bi extorcions &amp; raueyne &amp; robberie. &amp; &yogh;it men of lawe, &thorn;at schulden distroie siche falsnesse bi here offices &amp; don eche man ri&yogh;t &amp; reson,<NOTE PLACE="foot">X inserts &amp;.</NOTE> meyn|tenen wrong for money &amp; fees &amp; robis, &amp; forbaren pore men fro<NOTE PLACE="foot">for X.</NOTE> here ri&yogh;t, &thorn;at it is betre to hem to pursue not for here ri&yogh;t, be it neuere so opyn, &thorn;an to pursue &amp; lese more catel for disceitis of delaies and cauellacions &amp; euele wilis<NOTE PLACE="foot">willes X.</NOTE> &thorn;at &thorn;ei vsen; &amp; &thorn;us wrong is meyntened &amp; trew&thorn;e &amp; ri&yogh;t outlawid in many statis.</P>
<P>&para; Also stryues, contekis &amp; debatis ben vsed in oure lond, for lordis stryuen wi&thorn; here tenauntis to brynge<NOTE PLACE="foot">brynke X.</NOTE> hem in &thorn;raldom more &thorn;an &thorn;ei schulden bi reson &amp; charite; &amp; &thorn;ei grucchen a&yogh;en, &amp; cursen &amp; warien ny&yogh;t &amp; day, &amp; grete men of &thorn;is world<NOTE PLACE="foot">worldly AA.</NOTE> debaten, &amp; meyntenen debatis at louedaies; &amp; who so may be strengere wil haue his wille don, be it wrong be it ri&yogh;t, &amp; ellis make debate among many hundrid &amp; &thorn;ousand men &amp; sumtyme many countres, &amp; by<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> sich debatynge many men holden grete houses &amp; grete araies &amp; 
<PB REF="00000301.tif" N="235"> grete costis. &amp; summe lordis, seme &thorn;ei neuere so holy &amp; deuout in here preieres, wolen to meyntene name of here lordischipe beten men of contre, &amp; meyntenen o&thorn;ere mysdoeris &thorn;er-to, &thorn;ou&yogh; men pursuen ri&yogh;t &amp; reson in good manere, &amp; &thorn;is is for falsnesse of a liere &amp; coueitise &amp; worldly pride. &amp; clerkis striuen for holy writt &amp; seyn &thorn;at it is most trewe &amp; best to reule cristene mennus soulis bi, but ypocritis seyn &thorn;at holy writt is fals, &amp; newe lawis maad of worldly clerkis ben betre for cristene men &thorn;an holy writt, &amp; &thorn;erfore &thorn;ei studien mannus lawis &amp; techen hem to coloure bi here pride &amp; coueitise; &amp; leuen &thorn;e gospel &amp; goddis lawe, for it dampne&thorn; pride &amp; coueitise of clerkis, &amp; techi&thorn; mekenesse &amp; wilful pouerte &amp; bisynesse in preiere &amp; gostly occupacion. trewe clerkis seyn &thorn;at &thorn;at religion &amp; ordre &thorn;at crist, god &amp; man, maade is most perfit, most li&yogh;t &amp; most siker for my&yogh;t, wisdom &amp; charite of &thorn;e lord; but ypocritis seyn &thorn;at newe religion, founden of synful men &amp; gadrid of many errouris, of foolis &amp; worldly, proude &amp; coueitise wrecchis, is best; &amp; &thorn;erfore &thorn;ei leuen cristis religion in his owene fredom, &amp; bynden<NOTE PLACE="foot">byndem X.</NOTE> hem bi singuler profession to synful foolis. &amp; &yogh;it crist &amp; his apostlis tauten neuere ne vseden siche profession. &amp; herfore many children ben brou&yogh;t to siche newe religion for loue of worldly pride &amp; welfare of body more &thorn;an for holy lif to serue god in penaunce &amp; clennesse of soule, &amp; sum ben stolen &thorn;efly fro here frendis, &amp; summe bi false lesyngis &amp; false bihestis brou&yogh;t &thorn;er-to, &amp; for-&thorn;inke it after, &amp; be not suffred to turne to cristis clene religion, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei ben vnable to &thorn;is newe religions maade of synful mennus <MILESTONE N="197" UNIT="page">ordynaunce; &amp; so in summe manere &thorn;ei ben nedid to be dampnyd for ypocrisie &amp; grucchynge of conscience, &amp; leuynge of betre &thorn;ing &amp; holdynge for&thorn; of &thorn;e worse wyttyngly. &para; Trewe clerkis seyn also &thorn;at cristis lyuynge &amp; his apostlis in wilful pouert, wi&thorn;|outen fals &amp; nedeles beggyng &amp; whi&thorn;-outen worldly lordischipis, is most perfit in itself &amp; best for alle clerkis, si&thorn; crist god &amp; man chees &thorn;is<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> lif for &thorn;e beste; &amp; he my&yogh;tte not erre nei&thorn;er in 
<PB REF="00000302.tif" N="236"> &thorn;ou&yogh;t ne in word ne dede, but summe ypocritis seyn a&yogh;enst &thorn;is in worde or dede or bo&thorn;e, &thorn;at it his best to feyne holy pouert aftir crist &amp; his apostlis, &amp; &thorn;er-wi&thorn; lyuen in lustis of worldly gaynesse, of costy<NOTE PLACE="foot">gostly X.</NOTE> housynge &amp; grete more &thorn;an lordis don, &amp; in costy clo&thorn;ing for ony lord, &amp; in cost of mete or drynke &amp; makynge of grete festis of riche men. &amp; &thorn;is lif &thorn;ei holden vp bi fals beggynge of pore men, &thorn;at may not wel paie here rentis to lordis &amp; here dymes &amp; offryngis to curatis &amp; meyntene here wif &amp; children &amp; leue out of dette, traueile &thorn;ei neuere so besily ny&yogh;t &amp; day. &amp; be &thorn;ei neuere so pore &amp; in grete dette &thorn;es ypocritis ceessen not to robbe hem bi fals beggynge, dampned of goddis lawe. o&thorn;ere ypocritis seyn in dede &thorn;at it is betre for clerkis to haue worldly rentis &amp; lordischipis dowid to hem &amp; parische chirchis approprid to hem<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> bi symonye &amp; lesyngis &thorn;an to lyue in wilful &amp; honest pouert as crist &amp; his apostlis diden. &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ei reulen not wele &thorn;e peple, as lordis schulden, but seyn &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben dede to &thorn;e world; &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> techen not &thorn;e peple goddis lawe in word &amp; ensaumple as prestis schulden, but seyn it falle&thorn; not to hem to preche; &amp; &thorn;ei traueile not for here liflode, as god enyoyned adam for his penaunce, &amp; poul traueiled wi&thorn; his hondis in nede for his sustenaunce, but &thorn;ei lyuen comynly in ydelnesse &amp; glotonye &amp; enuye &amp; many o&thorn;er synnys, &amp; feynen holy|nesse in syngynge, in preynge of mou&thorn; &amp; customes maad of mannus errour, more &thorn;an in lyuynge after cristis gospel. &amp; whanne trewe clerkis meyntenen here trewe part bi holy writt &amp; reson &amp; ensaumple of cristis lif &amp; his apostlis, &amp; newe ypocritis meyntenen here fals part bi ground of synful men &amp; bi ypocrisie &amp; worldly power &amp; &yogh;iftis of money &amp; censures, as suspendynge, cursynge &amp; prisonynge, &amp; &thorn;anne is debat &amp; strif reised at &thorn;e fulle. for many lordis &amp; grete men ben disceyued bi &thorn;e multitude of ypocritis, &amp; many blente bi &yogh;iftis of money &amp; worldly profitis &thorn;at &thorn;ei geten of &thorn;es ypocritis, &amp; summe bi fleschly loue &amp; worldly frendi|schipe, &amp; for &thorn;at fewe stonden wi&thorn; &thorn;e trew&thorn;e &amp; but fewe 
<PB REF="00000303.tif" N="237"> lordis or riche cristene men stonden bi goddis lawe &amp; profit of cristene mennus soulis for to wynne &thorn;e blisse of heuene; &amp; &thorn;erfore pore clerkis ben sclaundrid for heretikis, for &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of holy writt, &amp; hurlid &amp; cursid &amp; prisonyd &amp; lettid to preche &thorn;e gospel, for drede laste &thorn;ei warne &thorn;e peple after cristis techynge of &thorn;e <MILESTONE N="198" UNIT="page">false disceitis of anticrist &amp; his worldly &amp; proude &amp; coueitouse clerkis. &amp; &thorn;us str[i]ues &amp; debatis ben reised &amp; meyntened in oure lond.</P>
<P>&para; Also diuerse gilis or disceitis &amp; falsnesses rengnen moche in oure lond; for prelatis hiden &thorn;e gile of here symonye &amp; ypocrisie, &thorn;at vnne&thorn;is come&thorn; ony to ony grete benefice wi&thorn;outen symonye, priuy or apert; &amp; &thorn;us alle prestis &amp; lordis &amp; comyns also ben enuenymed wi&thorn; heresie of cursid symonye, &amp; prelatis &thorn;at schulden distroie synne &amp; chasse it<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> out of londe wolen meyntene men in synne of leccherie &amp; o&thorn;ere fro &yogh;eer to &yogh;eer for a pencion bi &yogh;ere, &amp; clepen &thorn;is holy correction; &amp; &thorn;ei ben wode &yogh;if ony lord or o&thorn;ere my&yogh;tty man lette hem of &thorn;is correction, &thorn;e whiche is roberie &amp; extor|sion. In confessouris regne&thorn; moche gile for &thorn;ei conforten &amp; norischen grete men of &thorn;is world in here synnys for to gete a benefice, worldly wynnynge or frendischipe or lustis of<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> here stynkynge bely, &amp; vnder colour of holynesse leden men to &thorn;e &yogh;atis of helle &amp; sellen soulis to sathanas for drit of worldly goodis &amp; wombe ioie for a while; for &thorn;ei doren not telle hem &thorn;e so&thorn;e &amp; gretnesse of here foule synnys &amp; horiblite of peynes of helle, &amp; forsake here companye whanne &thorn;ei wolen dwelle stille in here synne, leste &thorn;ei lese worldly<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> worschipe &amp; lustis &thorn;at &thorn;ei seken more &thorn;an to saue cristene soulis. In men of lawe regne&thorn; moche gile, for &thorn;ei meyntenen <SUP>4</SUP>falsnes for wynnynge &amp; maken lordis to<SUP>4</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">4_4 omitted X.</NOTE> meyntene wrongis &amp; don wrongis whanne lordis hopen to do ri&yogh;t &amp; plese god, &amp; bi here coueitise &amp; falsenesse &thorn;ei purchasen londis &amp; rentis ynowe and don many extorsions &amp; beren don &thorn;e ri&yogh;t bo&thorn;e of pore &amp; riche, &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ei maken it so<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X</NOTE> holy in signes outward, 
<PB REF="00000304.tif" N="238"> as &yogh;if &thorn;ei weren angelis of heuene, to colour here falsenesse &amp; blynde &thorn;e peple &thorn;erby. &para; In marchauntis regne&thorn; gile in ful grete plente, for &thorn;ei sweren falsly be alle grete membris of crist &amp; bi alle my&yogh;tty god in trinyte &thorn;at here chaffere cost so moche &amp; is so trewe &amp; profitable, to bigile &thorn;e peple &amp; to teche &yogh;onge prentis &thorn;is cursed craft, &amp; preisen hym most &thorn;at most bigile&thorn; &thorn;e peple, &amp; hiden here vsure &amp; colouren it bi sotil cautelis of &thorn;e fend &thorn;at fewe men may proue &thorn;is vsure &amp; amende hem &thorn;er-of bi-fore &thorn;e day of dom. &para; In seruauntis regne&thorn; gile, for &thorn;ei traueilen faste awhile in presence of here maister, &amp; in absence ben ydel &amp; iapen &amp; don litel good, &amp; sweren faste &thorn;at &thorn;ei may not labore treweliere &amp; bisiliere &thorn;an &thorn;ei don. &amp; &yogh;it generaly in clerkis regne&thorn; most gile, for &thorn;ei disceyuen men bi here veyn preieris &amp; pardons &amp; indulgencis, for &thorn;ei knowen not &thorn;e goodnesse of here preieris ne abilnesse of men &thorn;at &thorn;ei preien fore, but &thorn;ei owen to drede sore &thorn;at &thorn;ei stiren god to vengaunce for here owene wickid lif; &amp; &thorn;er come&thorn; no pardon but of god for good lyuynge &amp; endynge in charite, &amp; &thorn;is schal not be bou&yogh;t <MILESTONE N="199" UNIT="page">ne solde as prelatis chafferen &thorn;es dayes; for who is in most charite is beste herde of god, be he schepeherde or lewid man, or in &thorn;e chirche or in &thorn;e feld; &amp; who kepi&thorn; wel &thorn;e hestis of god schal haue pardon &amp; &thorn;e blisse of heuene, &amp; noon o&thorn;ere for creature vnder god. &amp; &thorn;us gile regne&thorn; in many statis &amp; personys &thorn;at oure lond may drede sore a conquest, But &yogh;if synne &amp; gile be chasid out &amp; treu&thorn;e &amp; charite meyntened soone.</P>
<P>but nowe be lordis wel war &thorn;at &thorn;ei don mercy &amp; charite &amp; good conscience to her seruauntis, for ellis &thorn;ei schulle gete no mercy ne loue of god, for wrong oppressynge of pore men axi&thorn; vengaunce of god, as do&thorn; wrong mansleynge; &amp; loke lordis &thorn;at &thorn;ei reule wel seruauntis &amp; tenauntis, &thorn;at &thorn;ei drede god &amp; his wra&thorn;&thorn;e &thorn;e more, &amp; flee synnys &amp; lyue vertuously &amp; in treu&thorn;e anemtis god &amp; man; for lordis owen to &yogh;eue holy ensaumple of lif to seruauntis &amp; sugetis, &amp; ponysche hem for here wickid lif anemtis god more &thorn;an for falsnesse of dispit 
<PB REF="00000305.tif" N="239"> don a&yogh;enst here owene persone or worldly profit; &amp; to preise, cherische<NOTE PLACE="foot">chirch X.</NOTE> &amp; loue &amp; rewarde hem for here holy lif &amp; treu&thorn;e more &thorn;an for pleisynge of here owene persone or for doynge of here worldly auauntage or profit. &amp; &thorn;us schullen lordis &thorn;at ben vertuous in hem self norische vertuous seruauntis &amp; trewe to god &amp; man, &amp; reproue &amp; ponysche wickid trecchouris<NOTE PLACE="foot">treccherous X.</NOTE> &amp; cursed of lif; &amp; &thorn;us schulde synne among hem &amp; o&thorn;ere be hurlid out &amp; trou&thorn;e &amp; vertuous lif meyntened &amp; cherischid. &para; Also lordis schullen don non extorsions to here pore seruauntis bi ne worldly lawe ne customes, for alle &thorn;es lawes &amp; customes ben no&thorn;ing wor&thorn; but &yogh;if &thorn;ei ben reulid bi charite &amp; good conscience; &amp; lordis owen to procure good &amp; reste &amp; pees to here seruauntis as goode fadris &amp; helperis, &amp; suffre not here stiwardis or ony officeris to don hem wrong. for si&thorn; &thorn;ei may distroie &thorn;is wrong<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &amp; don not, &thorn;ei ben fautoris &amp; meyntenors of &thorn;is wrong, &amp; schulle be ponyschid as &thorn;e doeris, as seynt<NOTE PLACE="marg">Rom. i. [32.]</NOTE> poul sei&thorn;, &amp; in many cas more scharply, for here meyntenynge do&thorn; more harm &amp; wrong &thorn;an &thorn;e wickid stiwardis bi hem-self;<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Timothy v. [8.]</NOTE> for seynt poul sei&thorn; pleynly &thorn;at he &thorn;at ha&thorn; not cure or kepynge of his owene, &amp; most of his owene homly meyne,<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> ha&thorn; for|saken &thorn;e fei&thorn; &amp; is worse &thorn;an an he&thorn;ene man. of &thorn;is it seme&thorn; opynly &thorn;at &thorn;at lord &thorn;at chargi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">chargid X.</NOTE> not what wrong or extorsions his officeris don vnder hym forsaki&thorn; &thorn;e ri&yogh;te fei&thorn; &amp; is worse &thorn;an an he&thorn;ene man; for he do&thorn; more harm to a cristene man, &amp; distroie&thorn; more cristene religion, &amp; maki&thorn; hate &amp; grucchynge &amp; discencion bitwixe pore &amp; riche, &amp; anemtis god; for &thorn;ei my&yogh;ten soone enquere of trewe men of &thorn;e contre &thorn;e falsnesse of here officeris &amp; amende hem, &yogh;if &thorn;ei loueden treu&thorn;e of god <MILESTONE N="200" UNIT="page">&amp; ri&yogh;tful helpe of pore men as moche as &thorn;ei louen hel&thorn;e of here body &amp; holsumnesse of here bodily mete; &amp; but &yogh;if &thorn;ei don &thorn;us &thorn;ei fallen out of charite as it seme&thorn;, for &thorn;ei louen more ellis here bely &amp; hem self &thorn;an &thorn;e honour of crist &amp; ri&yogh;tful gouernaile of goddis peple. &amp; lordis schulden warne here officeris &thorn;at &yogh;if &thorn;ei don wrong to here pore 
<PB REF="00000306.tif" N="240"> tenauntis &thorn;ei schulden be put out of here offices &amp; lese here frendischipe &amp; lordischipe, &amp; &thorn;anne wolden officeris of lordis ben war of extorsions &amp; wrong meyntenaunce. &amp; lordis ben foule disceyued to dwelle att home in lustis of glotonye &amp; lecherie &amp; ydelnesse, &amp; to seie here matynes &amp; o&thorn;ere deuocions in mou&thorn; &amp; not in herte ne dede, &amp; to suffre pore men distroied bi euyl officeris; for god sei&thorn; bi salamon it is betre to do mercy &amp; ri&yogh;tful dom &thorn;an to offre sacrifies. for &thorn;e presence of &thorn;e ri&yogh;tful lord schulde more distroie wrongis &amp; euyl meyntenaunce &thorn;an many letteris sent to euyl officeris, for &thorn;ei charge not to do ri&yogh;t after &thorn;e letteris, for &thorn;er is no more pursuet don after &thorn;e deed lettre. &para; What is it wor&thorn; a lord to crie bi word to god, whanne many pore men axen ri&yogh;tfully vengaunce a&yogh;enst him for extorsions &amp; wrongis &thorn;at he &amp; his officeris don or suffren<NOTE PLACE="foot">suffre&thorn; X.</NOTE> to be don in his name, whanne he may letten hem; for &thorn;an he is consentour or autor of siche wrongis. for god wole sonere here many pore ri&yogh;tfully criynge vengaunce &thorn;an a lord &amp; many ypocritis axynge vnri&yogh;tfully helpe &amp; wynnynge of worldly goodis; for god sei&thorn; &thorn;at he wole not here synful men criynge to him in tyme of here nede whanne &thorn;ei wolen not here pore men &amp; helpe hem in here wrongis &amp; myscheues &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben inne. &para; Also a grete vnri&yogh;twisnesse regne&thorn; among lordis whanne &thorn;ei wolen not distroie pride, coueitise &amp; worldly lif of clerkis &thorn;at harmen so moche cristene peple. for &yogh;if lordis wolden dispise &thorn;e pride of coueitouse clerkis &amp; not conferme hem ne<NOTE PLACE="foot">no X.</NOTE> meyntene here worldly lordischipe &amp; symonye, &thorn;at is opynly dampnyd bi holy writt &amp; cristis lyuynge, &thorn;es proude worldly clerkis ful of coueitise &amp; lecherie &amp; o&thorn;ere synnes schulden sone ben abatid, &amp; holy lif &amp; trewe techynge schulde be brou&yogh;t a&yogh;en. but here renne&thorn; moche gile &amp; ypocrisie of anticrist &amp; his clerkis, for &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at seculer lordis han no power vpon clerkis, but &yogh;if prelatis clepen hem to chastise clerkis whanne &thorn;ei ben rebel &amp; wolen not ben amendid bi here prelatis. for 
<PB REF="00000307.tif" N="241"> salamon putte adoun on hei&yogh; prestis &amp; ordeyned ano&thorn;er in his<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Kings ii. [27.]</NOTE> place, &amp; owtlawid &thorn;e firste wi&thorn;-outen axynge helpe of clerkis for traiterie don to salamon &amp; his peple; &amp; treson a&yogh;enst crist &amp; his lawe &amp; his peple is more &thorn;an treson a&yogh;enst an er&thorn;ely kyng &amp; more schulde be ponyschid. &amp; as petir &amp; poul techen, lordis ben ordeyned of god to venge mysdedis and mysdoeris &amp; to preise goode dedis &amp; goode doeris; &thorn;anne &thorn;e more &thorn;at<MILESTONE N="201" UNIT="page"> a synne is, &thorn;e more howen lordis to ponysche it; but &thorn;e synne of clerkis is more &thorn;an &thorn;e synne of o&thorn;ere lewid men, &thorn;anne lordis owen more to ponysche synne of clerkis &thorn;anne &thorn;e synne of o&thorn;er men. &amp; it is more synne &amp; perilous to goddis peple whanne lowere clerkis meyntenen here synne &amp; grete prelatis suffren hem &thorn;er-inne, &amp; consenten &thorn;er-to for necligence or coueitise, &thorn;an whanne prelatis don here bisynesse to distroie synne &amp; pursue wickid clerkis. &thorn;er-fore lordis owen to ponysche more wickid clerkis whanne prelatis slepen &amp; fauouren hem in synne for moneye,<NOTE PLACE="foot">meney X.</NOTE> for ellis my&yogh;tten kyng|domes ben conquerid for<NOTE PLACE="foot">to X.</NOTE> necligence of coueitouse prelatis, as it was in &thorn;e lond of israel. &amp; herefore whanne crist was preised of &thorn;e peple, he wente in-to &thorn;e temple &amp; wi&thorn; his hondis droof out symonyentis, to &yogh;eue ensaumple to lordis to do &thorn;e same; &amp; &thorn;erfore petir &amp; poul outaken not clerkis fro ponyschynge of lordis. &thorn;anne si&thorn; goddis lawe &yogh;eue&thorn; general power to seculer lordis for to ponysche mysdoeris, whi schulden &thorn;ei not ponysche euyl clerkis, &thorn;at most drawen o&thorn;ere men to synne &amp; so to disturblynge of rewmes? si&thorn; crist suffred paciently wrongful de&thorn; of pilat, &thorn;at was a seculer iustise, moche more schulden clerkis suffren ri&yogh;tful ponyschinge of here synnys bi seculer lordis; for poul forsok<NOTE PLACE="marg">Acts xxv. 11.</NOTE> not to take de&thorn; of seculer domes men &yogh;if he hadde deserued it, &amp; also appelid to &thorn;e he&thorn;ene emperour of rome; &amp; &thorn;us it seme&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;o clerkis &thorn;at wolen not be amended bi seculer lordis dom ben out of mekenesse &amp; pacience &amp; charite, &amp; hi&yogh;en hemself aboue crist &amp; his apostlis a&yogh;enst goddis ordy|naunce bi luciferis pride, &amp; ben cursed anticristis. &amp; &yogh;it 
<PB REF="00000308.tif" N="242"> lordis don gret wrong &amp; gile, for &thorn;ei auaunsen lewid men of kunnynge &amp; lyuynge to benefices wi&thorn; care of many<NOTE PLACE="foot">mennys AA.</NOTE> soulis, &amp; taken to hem self &thorn;e profit of &thorn;e grete benefices for many &yogh;eris, &amp; holden many benefy[c]ed men in here chapelis for nouelrie of newe song, &amp; maken summe prestis stiwardis of here housholde, &amp; summe prestis clerkis of here kechene,<NOTE PLACE="foot">lecherie X.</NOTE> &amp; summe prestis here auditours, &amp; summe prestis tresoreris, &amp; summe aumeneris, &amp; summe stiwardis of here courtis, &amp; summe conseileris &amp; reuleris of here worldly plees, arraies &amp; worldly dedes, as &thorn;ou&yogh; no man coude worldly office but &thorn;ei; &amp; wolen not suffre hem goo teche &thorn;e soulis for whiche &thorn;e schullen answere at domes day, &amp; for whiche crist schedde his precious herte blood, but suffren &amp; meyntenen &thorn;e wolues of helle to slee cristene mennus soulis bi<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> synne, &amp; letten almes dede bo&thorn;e gostly &amp; bodily, &amp; so &thorn;ei ben cursed traitours to god &amp; to his prestis &amp; his pore peple. &amp; more traitorie of god &amp; his peple is in &thorn;es prestis &thorn;at<MILESTONE N="202" UNIT="page"> wilfully &amp; costly procure to haue &thorn;is worldly offices &amp; dwellen &thorn;er-inne &amp; leuen here gostly office vndon.<NOTE PLACE="foot">undir AA.</NOTE> but most traiterie of god &amp; his peple is in fals confessouris &thorn;at schulden telle lordis &thorn;e grete peril of &thorn;is synne &amp; o&thorn;ere, &amp; wolden not for drede of loos of worldly frendschipe &amp; lordischipe &amp; worldly worschipe &amp; wynnynge; for &thorn;ei sette more<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> bi a litel stynkynge dritt of &thorn;is world &thorn;an bi helpe of cristene soulis &amp; frendischipe of god &amp; &thorn;e blisse of heuene. Also many ietteris of contre &thorn;at wolen make hem self gentel men &amp; han litel or nou&yogh;t to lyue onne, &amp; o&thorn;ere lordis also wolen preise a worldly prelat or curat &amp; bere him vp, &thorn;ou&yogh; he be neuere so vicious in lecherie, pride &amp; coueitise &amp; o&thorn;ere synnes, so &thorn;at &thorn;is worldly curat maki&thorn; hem grete festis &amp; wasti&thorn; pore mennus almes in &yogh;iftis of wyn &amp; vanytes; &yogh;e, &thorn;ou&yogh; he be a market betere, a marchaunt, a meyntenour of wrongis at louedaies, a fals suerere, a man|quellere &amp; inreguler. but &yogh;if &thorn;er be a gostly curat or prest &thorn;at lyue&thorn; a good lif in mekenesse &amp; doynge almes to pore 
<PB REF="00000309.tif" N="243"> men, &amp; not wastynge pore mennus almes in veyn feste or suche getteris, but holde hym in his preieris deuoutly &amp; in techynge of goddis lawe trewely &amp; in his trewe stondynge of holy writt, he schal be holde a nyggard, an hound, or an hoog, an ypocrite &amp; an heretik; namely &yogh;if he reproue hem of here wickid lif &amp; teche hem &thorn;e beste weie to heuene bo&thorn;e in word &amp; dede, &amp; so be hurlid &amp; pursued priuely or apertly, &amp; so hatid amonge hem &thorn;at he schal be fayn to sette his chirche to ferme to suche a gettere nerehonde for nou&yogh;t, or ellis for fals sclaundre putt on him lese his chirche, or for schame or anoy flee &thorn;e contre, &amp; bi &thorn;is wrong ben many men lettid fro goddis seruyce &amp; trewe techynge. And &yogh;it lordis don many wrongis &amp; giles in here offices, for &thorn;ei wasten here tyme in slou&thorn;e &amp; ydelnesse, &amp; wasten here goodis in bost &amp; pride &amp; glotonye; &amp; he &thorn;at best can do &thorn;is is holden of worldly men best lord &amp; most worschipful, principaly &yogh;if he meyntene his men to bete pore men &amp; do wrongis bi loue daies, holdynge &amp; meyntenynge of causes &thorn;at ri&yogh;t &amp; lawe may not haue his cours. &amp; &thorn;us whanne &thorn;ei schulden haue hous|hold of ri&yogh;twise men &amp; vertuous of lif, &thorn;ei meyntenen proude luciferis children, extorsioneris, robberies, &amp; reuers, to distroie here pore nei&yogh;ebores &amp; maken here hous a den of &thorn;eues, &amp; ben procuratours of &thorn;e fend to holde vp falsnesse &amp; o&thorn;ere synnes, &amp; to putte doun goddis lawe<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &amp; his seruauntis. for lordis schulden traueile als faste to kunne holy writt, &amp; do treu&thorn;e &amp; equyte, &amp; meyntene ri&yogh;t of pore men<MILESTONE N="203" UNIT="page"> &amp; reste &amp; pees vp here kunnynge &amp; power, as pore men ben bisi to labore for here owene liflode &amp; to paye here rentis to lordis; for god sei&thorn; bi dauyd: "&amp; now, &yogh;e kyngis, vnderstonde; be &yogh;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Psalms ii. 10.</NOTE> lerid &thorn;at demen &thorn;e er&thorn;e; serue &yogh;e to &thorn;e lord wi&thorn; drede of herte, &amp; enyoie &yogh;e to hym wi&thorn; quakynge." &amp; &thorn;e wise man<NOTE PLACE="marg">Wisdom vi. 6.</NOTE> sei&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;e most hard dom schal ben to hem &thorn;at ben aboue o&thorn;ere, &amp; ih&umacr; sei&thorn; &thorn;at to whom is moche bitokene, of hym schal<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke xii. 48.</NOTE> moche ben axid. god stire&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">stire AA.</NOTE> lordis to distroie synne &amp; norische vertues &amp; holy lif of clerkis &amp; alle o&thorn;ere<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;ere AA.</NOTE> sugetis. Amen.</P>


</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="16" TYPE="tract"><PB REF="00000310.tif" N="244">
<HEAD>XVI. WHY POOR PRIESTS HAVE NO BENEFICE.</HEAD>
<HEADNOTE><P>THIS tract, whoever may be its author, is vigorously written. It has a special interest as a full statement and defence of the motives which led Wyclif to institute his order or company of poor priests.</P><P>As evidence in favour of Wyclif's authorship, we may notice the phrase "moo sacraments than Christ used and his apostles." In the Trialogus we find complaints that sacraments are multiplied so as to be a burden to the Church, and Confirmation and Extreme Unction are said not to have enough ground in Scripture to be necessary to salvation (<I>Trial</I>, book iv. chapters xi., xiv., xxv.). His doctrine of dominion is brought in on p. 247. Perhaps we may see a touch of personal feeling in the statement that a curate cannot get leave of absence to study God's law without payment. Had Wyclif found it necessary to buy leave to absent him|self from Fillingham in 1368?</P><P>On the other hand, the tone of several passages would lead us to attri|bute them to one of the poor priests rather than to Wyclif. It seems unlikely that the rector of Lutterworth would speak of a man who accepted a cure as binding himself "to o synguler place as a tey dogge," p. 252.</P><P>Copied from the Corpus MS. X. and collated with the Dublin MS. AA.</P><P><TABLE>
