<PB REF="00000311.tif" N="245">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>Whi pore prestis han none benefice.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<DIV2 N="1" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum primum.</HEAD>
<P>Summe causes meuen summe pore prestis to resceyue not benefices; &thorn;e friste for drede of symonye, &thorn;e secunde for drede of myspendynge pore mennus goodis, &thorn;e &thorn;ridde for drede of lettynge of bettre occupacion &thorn;at is more li&yogh;t or eisy, more certeyn, &amp; more profitable on euere side. for &yogh;if men schulde come to benefices be &yogh;ift of prelatis &thorn;er is drede of symonye; for comynly &thorn;ei taken the friste fruytis or o&thorn;ere pensions, or holden curatis in office in here courtis or chapelis or o&thorn;ere veyn offices, fer fro prestis lif tau&yogh;t &amp; ensaumplid of crist &amp; his apostlis; so &thorn;at comunly siche benefices comen not frely, as crist comaundi&thorn;, but ra&thorn;ere for worldly wynnynge or flaterynge or preisynge &amp; &thorn;ank of my&yogh;tty men &amp; lordis, &amp; not for abilnesse of kunnynge of goddis lawe<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &amp; trewe techynge of &thorn;e gospel &amp; ensaumple of holy lif. &amp; here-fore comynly &thorn;es prelatis &amp; resceyueris ben foulid wi&thorn; symonye, &thorn;at is cursed heresie as goddis lawe &amp; mannus lawe techen opynly &amp; many seyntis. &amp; grete merueile it is now &thorn;at, si&thorn; seynt gregory sey&thorn; in pleyn lawe of &thorn;e chirche &amp; o&thorn;ere bokis &thorn;at siche men as desiren benefices schulden not haue hem, but men &thorn;at fleen hem for drede of vnabilnesse of hemself &amp; grete charge, as dide moyses, ieromye, austyn, gregory &amp; holy seyntis; &amp; now who can faste renne to rome &amp; bere gold out of &thorn;e lond &amp; paie it for deed leed &amp; a litil writynge, &amp; stryue &amp; plede &amp; curse for ti&thorn;es &amp; o&thorn;ere temperal profitis, &thorn;at ben clepid wi&thorn; anticristis clerkis ri&yogh;ttis of holy chirche, schal haue grete benefices of cure of many &thorn;ousand soulis; &thorn;ou&yogh;<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;ei X.</NOTE> he be vnable of kunnynge of holy writt, not in wille to teche &amp; preche his sugetis, but of cursed lif &amp; wickid ensaumple of pride, of coueitise, glotonye, lecherie &amp; o&thorn;ere grete synnys. but &thorn;ere be ony symple man &thorn;at desire&thorn; to lyue wel &amp; teche 
<PB REF="00000312.tif" N="246"> treuely goddis lawe &amp; dispise pride &amp; o&thorn;ere synnys, bo&thorn;e of prelatis &amp; o&thorn;ere men, he<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> schal ben holden an ypocrite, a newe techere, an heretik, &amp; not suffred to come <MILESTONE N="204" UNIT="page">to ony benefice. but &yogh;if <SUP>2</SUP>he have<SUP>2</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">2_2 omitted X.</NOTE> ony litel pore place to lyuen a pore lif onne, he schal be so pursued &amp; sclaundrid &thorn;at he schal be putt oute bi wiles, cautelis, fraudis &amp; worldly violence, &amp; enprisoned, disgratid or brent, &yogh;if anticristis clerkis may for ony gold &amp; cursed lesyngis. &para; And &yogh;if lordis schullen presente clerkis to benefices &thorn;ei wolen haue comynly gold in grett quantite, &amp; holden &thorn;es curatis in here worldly office, &amp; suffren &thorn;e wolues of helle to stranglen mennus soulis, so &thorn;at &thorn;ei haue moche gold &amp; here office don for nou&yogh;t, &amp; here chapelis holden vp for veyn glorie or ypocrisie; &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ei wolen not presente a clerk able of kunnynge &amp; of<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> good lif &amp; holy ensaumple to &thorn;e peple, but a kechen clerk or a penne clerk or wis of<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> bildynge of castelis or worldly doynge, &thorn;ou&yogh; he kunne not rede wel his sauter &amp; knowe&thorn; not &thorn;e comaundementis of god ne sacramentis of holy chirche. &amp; &yogh;it summe lordis to colouren here symonye wole not take for hem self, but keuer|chiefs for &thorn;e lady, or a palfray, or a tonne of wyn; &amp; whanne summe lordis wolden presente a goode man &amp; able for loue of god &amp; cristene soulis, &thorn;an summe ladies ben menys to haue a daunsere, a trippere on tapitis, or huntere or haukere, or a wilde pleiere of someres gamenes for flaterynge &amp; &yogh;iftis goynge bitwixe, &amp; &yogh;if it be for daunsynge in bedde so moche &thorn;e worse. &amp; &thorn;us it seme&thorn; &thorn;at bo&thorn;e prelatis &amp; lordis comynly maken a cursed anticrist &amp; a quyk fend to be maister of cristis peple, for to leden hem<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> to helle, to sathanas here maistir, &amp; suffre not cristis disciplis to teche cristis gospel to his children for to saue here soulis; &amp; so &thorn;ei traueilen to exile crist &amp; his lawe out of his heritage, &thorn;at is cristene soulis, &thorn;at he bou&yogh;te not wi&thorn; roten gold ne siluer but wi&thorn; his precious herte blood &thorn;at he schedde on &thorn;e crois bi most brennynge charite. but in &thorn;is presentynge of euyl curatis and holdynge 
<PB REF="00000313.tif" N="247"> of curatis in worldly office, lettynge hem fro here gostly cure, ben &thorn;re degrees of traiterie a&yogh;enst god &amp; his peple. &para; &THORN;e friste is in prelatis &amp; lordis &thorn;at &thorn;us holden curatis in here worldly office; for &thorn;ei han here hei&yogh;e statis in &thorn;e chirche &amp; lordischipis for to purueie treue curatis to &thorn;e peple, &amp; to meyntene hem in goddis lawe &amp; ponyschen hem &yogh;if &thorn;ei failen in here gostly cure, &amp; bi &thorn;is &thorn;ei holden here lordischipis of god. &THORN;an &yogh;if &thorn;ei maken euyl curatis &amp; holden hem in here worldly office, &amp; letten hem to lede goddis peple &thorn;e ri&yogh;tful weie to heuene, but helpen hem &amp; constreynen hem to lede &thorn;e peple to helle ward bi wi&thorn;-drawynge of goddis word &amp; bi euyl ensaumple &yogh;euynge, &thorn;ei ben weiward traitours to god &amp; his peple, &amp; vikeris &amp; procuratours of sathanas. &YOGH;it more traiterie is in false curatis &thorn;at &yogh;euen mede <MILESTONE N="205" UNIT="page">or hire to comen in-to siche worldly offices, for to spare here muk &amp; leie it in tresor, &amp; to gete lordischipe &amp; mauntenaunce a&yogh;enst ordynaries, &thorn;at &thorn;ei doren not clepen hem to residence &amp; saue here soulis, but couchen in lordis courtis, in<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; X.</NOTE> lustis &amp; aise of here flech for to gete moo fatte benefices, &amp; purposen not spedly to do here gostly office. woo is to &thorn;o lordis &thorn;at ben leed wi&thorn; suche cursed heretikis &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> anticristis, traitours of god &amp; his peple, &amp; namely traitours to lordis hem self. where lordis my&yogh;tten not fynde in alle here lordischipe trewe worldly men to reule here houshold &amp; worldly offices, but &yogh;if &thorn;ei taken &thorn;er-to curatis &thorn;at ben opynly false traitours to god &amp; his peple? where lordis ben so blyndid<NOTE PLACE="foot">byndid AA.</NOTE> &thorn;at &thorn;ei perceyuen not &thorn;at siche traitours, &thorn;at opynly ben false to god, &thorn;at &thorn;ei wolen moche more ben false to hem? but &thorn;e most traiterie is in fals confessouris, &thorn;at schulden bi here office warne prelatis &amp; lordis of &thorn;is grete peril, &amp; clerkis also, &thorn;at &thorn;ei holden none siche curatis in here worldly offices; for &thorn;ei don not &thorn;is last &thorn;ei losen lordischipe &amp; frendischipe &amp; &yogh;iftis &amp; welfare of here stynkynge bely; &amp; so &thorn;ei sillen cristene soulis to sathanas for to haue lykyngis of here stynkynge bely, &amp; maken prelatis &amp; 
<PB REF="00000314.tif" N="248"> lordis &amp; curatis to lyue in synne &amp; traiterie a&yogh;enst god &amp; his peple. &amp; so a&yogh;enst &thorn;e hire &thorn;at lordis &yogh;euen here confessouris &thorn;ei disceyuen hem in here soulis hel&thorn;e, &amp; meyntenen hem in cursed traiterie of god &amp; his peple, &amp; &thorn;us almost al &thorn;e world go&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">aboute has been inserted in X. but crossed out.</NOTE> to helle for &thorn;is cursed symonye &amp; false confes|sours. for comynly prelatis, lordis &amp; curatis ben enuenymed wi&thorn; &thorn;is heresie of symonye, &amp; neuere don verey repentaunce &amp; satisfaccion &thorn;er-fore; for whanne &thorn;ei han a fat benefice geten by symonye &thorn;ei forsaken it not, as &thorn;ei ben bounden bi here owene lawe, but wittyngly vsen for&thorn; &thorn;at symonye, &amp; lyuen in riot, coueitise, pride, &amp; don not here office nei&thorn;er in good ensaumple ne trewe techynge. &amp; &thorn;us anticristis clerkis, enemyes of crist &amp; his peple, bi money &amp; flaterynge &amp; fleschly loue gedrynge to hem ledynge of &thorn;e peple, &amp; forbarre trewe prestis to teche hem goddis lawe; &amp; &thorn;erfore &thorn;e blynde ledi&thorn; &thorn;e blynde &amp; bo&thorn;e partis rennen in-to synne, &amp; ful many to helle. &amp; it is huge wonder &thorn;at god of his ri&yogh;twisnesse dis|troie&thorn; not &thorn;e housis of prelatis &amp; lordis &amp; curatis, as sodom &amp; gomor, for &thorn;is heresie, extorsions &amp; o&thorn;ere cursednesses &thorn;at &thorn;ei haunten, &amp; for drede of &thorn;is synne &amp; many moo summe pore wrecchis resceyue no benefices in &thorn;is world.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 2<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>&YOGH;it &thorn;ou&yogh; pore prestis my&yogh;tten frely geten presentacion of lordis to haue benefices wi&thorn; cure of soulis, &thorn;ei dreden for<NOTE PLACE="foot">of X.</NOTE> myspendynge of poore mennus goodis; &amp; &thorn;is is more drede &thorn;an <MILESTONE N="206" UNIT="page">&thorn;e first as<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> anemtis here owene personys. for prestis owen to holde hem paied wi&thorn; fode &amp; hilynge, as seynt poul<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Tim. vi. [8].</NOTE> techi&thorn;; &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ei han more it is pore mennus goode, as here owene lawe &amp; ierom &amp; goddis lawe seyn, &amp; &thorn;ei ben kepers &thorn;er-of &amp; procuratours of pore men. But for institucion &amp; induccion he schal &yogh;eue moche of &thorn;is god &thorn;at is pore mennus to bischopis officers, archdekenes &amp; officialis &thorn;at ben to riche, 
<PB REF="00000315.tif" N="249"> &amp; not frely comen &thorn;er-to.<NOTE PLACE="foot">of X.</NOTE> And whanne bischopis &amp; here officeris comen &amp; feynen to visite, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei norischen men in open synne for annuel rente, &amp; don not here office but sillen soulis to sathanas for money, wrecchid curatis ben nedid to festen hem richely &amp; &yogh;eue procuracie &amp; synage; &yogh;e, a&yogh;enst goddis lawe &amp; mannus &amp; reson &amp; a&yogh;enst here conscience. &amp; also &thorn;ei schullen not be suffrid to teche treuly goddis lawe to here owene sugetis &amp; warne hem of false prophetis, &amp; disceyuen <NOTE PLACE="foot">disseyuen AA. Perhaps it should be disseruen. If not we must read "that" for "and" just before.</NOTE>hem bo&thorn;e in bileue &amp; techynge &amp; good lif &amp; er&thorn;ely goodis, as crist do&thorn;e in &thorn;e gospel, &amp; comaundi&thorn; curatis to do &thorn;e same vp peyne of here dampnacion; for &thorn;anne &thorn;ei mosten crie to &thorn;e peple &thorn;e grete synnys of prelatis &amp; o&thorn;ere newe feyned religious, as god biddi&thorn;; but &thorn;ei demen &thorn;at siche sadde reprouyngis of synne is enuye, sclaundrynge of prelatis, &amp; distroiynge of holy chirche. &amp; &thorn;ei schullen not be suffrid to do scharp execucion of goddis lawe a&yogh;enst here sugetis, ben &thorn;ei neuere so opynly cursed of god &amp; sclaundris of cristene religion, &yogh;if &thorn;e hei&yogh;e clerkis of anticrist han &yogh;iftis &amp; pensions bi &yogh;ere to sufre cursed men in opyn avoutrie &amp; o&thorn;ere synnys. for whanne &thorn;ei ben falsly amendid bi officialis &amp; denes no man be hardy to waken hem out of here lustis of synne, for &thorn;at schulde distroie iurdiccioun &amp; wynnynge of<NOTE PLACE="foot">for X.</NOTE> prelatis, &amp; &thorn;is cursed extorsion is clepid bi ypocrisie &thorn;e grete almes of anti|cristis clerkis<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE>; but here-by &thorn;ei maken large kechenes, holden fatte hors &amp; houndis &amp; haukis &amp; strompetis gaiely arraied, &amp; suffren pore men to sterue for myschief, &amp; &yogh;it suffren &amp; constreinen hem to goo &thorn;e brode weie to helle. &para; Also many tymes here patrons &amp; o&thorn;ere getteris of countre &amp; ydel schaueldouris willen loke to be festid of siche curatis, &amp; ellis maken hem lese &thorn;at litel &thorn;ing &thorn;at &thorn;ei &amp; pore men schulden lyue bi; so &thorn;at &thorn;ei schullen not spende &thorn;e dymes &amp; offryngis after good conscience &amp; goddis lawe but waste 
<PB REF="00000316.tif" N="250"> hem on suche my&yogh;tty &amp; riche men &amp; ydel, &amp; ellis, for traueile, cost &amp; enemyte &amp; dispisynge &thorn;at &thorn;ei schullen suffre &amp; on &thorn;e to&thorn;er side for drede of conscience, hem is betre to forsake al &thorn;an to holde it for&thorn;. &para; Also eche good day comynly &thorn;es smale curatis schullen haue letteris fro here ordynaries to summone<MILESTONE N="207" UNIT="page"> &amp; to curse pore men for nou&yogh;t but for coueitise of anticristis clerkis; &amp; but &yogh;if &thorn;ei somonen &amp; cursen hem, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei knowe no cause whi anemtis god &amp; his lawe, &thorn;ei ben hurlid &amp; somnyd fro day to day, fro fer place to fer&thorn;ere, or cursed <SUP>1</SUP>or lese here benefices or profitis<SUP>1</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">1_1 omitted AA.</NOTE> &thorn;er-of; for elles as prelatis feynen &thorn;ei<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;er AA.</NOTE> bi here rebelte schulden soone distroie prelatis iurisdiction, power &amp; wynnynge. &para; Also whanne pore prestis first holy of lif &amp; deuout in here preieris ben benefised, but &yogh;if &thorn;ei ben worldly &amp; bisy aboute &thorn;e world to make grete festis to riche personys &amp; vikeris &amp; riche men &amp; costy &amp; gaily arraied, as<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; X.</NOTE> here staat axi&thorn; bi fals dom of &thorn;e world, &thorn;ei schullen be hatid &amp; hayned doune as houndis, &amp; eche man redi to peiere hem in name &amp; worldly goodis. &amp; so many cursed disceitis ha&thorn; anti|crist brou&yogh;t vp bi his worldly clerkis to make curatis to<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> myspende pore mennus goodis &amp; not don<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> trewely here office, or ellis to forsaken al &amp; late anticristis clerkis, as lordis of &thorn;is world, &yogh;e more cruely &thorn;an o&thorn;ere tirauntis, robbe &thorn;e pore peple bi feyned sensures &amp; teche &thorn;e fendis lore bo&thorn;e bi open prechynge &amp; ensaumple of here cursid lif. &para; Also &yogh;if siche curatis ben stired to gone lerne goddis lawe &amp; teche here parischenys &thorn;e gospel, comynly &thorn;ei schullen gete no leue of bischopis but for gold; &amp; whanne &thorn;ei schullen most profite in here lernynge &thorn;an schulle &thorn;ei be clepid hom at &thorn;e prelatis wille, &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ei schullen haue ony hei&yogh;e sacramentis or poyntis of &thorn;e hei&yogh;e prelatis, comynly &thorn;ei schulle bie hem wi&thorn; pore mennus goodis wi&thorn; hook or wi&thorn; crok; &amp; so &thorn;ere is ful gret peril of euyl spendynge of &thorn;os goodis, bo&thorn;e a&yogh;enst hei&yogh;e prelatis, anemtis riche men of contre, as patrones, persones &amp; o&thorn;ere gettouris of contre, &amp; here owene kyn for fame of &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000317.tif" N="251"> world &amp; for schame &amp; euyl demynge of men. &amp; certis it is gret wonder &thorn;at god suffri&thorn; so longe &thorn;is synne vnponyschid opynly, namely of prelatis courtis &thorn;at ben dennys of &thorn;eues &amp; larderis of helle; &amp; so of here officeris &thorn;at ben sotil in malice &amp; coueitise; &amp; of lordis &amp; my&yogh;tty men, &thorn;at schulden distroie &thorn;is wrong &amp; o&thorn;ere &amp; meyntenen treu&thorn;e &amp; goddis seruauntis, &amp; now meyntenen anticristis falsenesse &amp; his clerkis for part of &thorn;e wynnynge. &amp; hou symple prestis durren take siche benefices, but &yogh;if &thorn;ei weren my&yogh;tty of kunnynge &amp; goode lif &amp; herty to a&yogh;enstonde &thorn;es wrongis &amp; moo &thorn;an<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;at X.</NOTE> we may now touche for &thorn;e multitude of hem &amp; sotil colourynge bi ypocrisie. but certis god suffri&thorn; siche ypocritis &amp; tirauntis to haue name of prelatis for grete synnys of &thorn;e peple &amp; vnwor&thorn;inesse &thorn;er-of, &thorn;at eche part lede o&thorn;er<NOTE PLACE="foot">open X.</NOTE> to helle bi blyndnes of &thorn;e fend; &amp; &thorn;is is a &thorn;ousand fold more vengaunce &thorn;an &yogh;if god distroie bodely bo&thorn;e partis &amp; alle here goodis <MILESTONE N="208" UNIT="page">&amp; er&thorn;e &thorn;er-wi&thorn;, as he dide bi sodom &amp; gomor; for &thorn;e lengere &thorn;at &thorn;ei lyuen &thorn;us in synne, &thorn;e grettere peynes schullen &thorn;ei haue in helle but &yogh;if &thorn;ei amenden hem. &amp; &thorn;is drede &amp; many moo maken summe pore prestis to resceyuen non benefices.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="3" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 3<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>But &yogh;it &thorn;ou&yogh; pore prestis my&yogh;tten haue frely presentacion of lordis, &amp; ben holpen bi meyntenynge of kyngis &amp; helpe of goode comyns fro extorsions of prelatis &amp; o&thorn;ere myspendynge of &thorn;es goodes, &thorn;at is ful hard in &thorn;is grete regnynge of anti|cristis clerkis; &yogh;it &thorn;ei dreden sore &thorn;at bi &thorn;is singuler cure ordeyned of synful men &thorn;ei schulden be lettid fro betre occupacion &amp; fro more profit of holy chirche, &amp; &thorn;is is &thorn;e moste drede of alle as anemtis here personys. for &thorn;ei han cure &amp; charge at &thorn;e fulle of god to helpe here bre&thorn;eren to heuene ward, bo&thorn;e bi techynge, preiynge &amp; ensaumple &yogh;euynge; &amp; it seme&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ei schullen most esily fulfille &thorn;is bi general cure of charite, as dide crist &amp; his apostlis, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei bynden hem 
<PB REF="00000318.tif" N="252"> not to o synguler place as a tey dogge, &amp; bi &thorn;is &thorn;ei may most sikirly saue hem self &amp; helpe here bre&thorn;eren; for now &thorn;ei ben free to flee fro o cite to a no&thorn;er whanne &thorn;ei ben pursued of <NOTE PLACE="marg">Matthew x. 23.</NOTE> anticristis clerkis, as biddi&thorn; crist in &thorn;e gospel. Also nowe &thorn;ei may best wi&thorn;-oute chalyngynge of men goo &amp; dwelle among &thorn;e peple where &thorn;ei schullen most profite, &amp; in couen|able tyme come &amp; goo aftir stirynge of &thorn;e holy gost, &amp; not be bounden bi synful mennus iurdiccion fro &thorn;e betre doynge. &para; Also now &thorn;ei suen crist &amp; his apostlis neer, in &thorn;us takynge almes wilfully &amp; frely of &thorn;e peple &thorn;at &thorn;ei techen, &thorn;anne in takynge dymes &amp; offryngis bi customes &thorn;at synful men ordeynen &amp; vsen now in &thorn;e tyme of grace. &para; Also &thorn;is is more medeful in bo&thorn;e sidis as &thorn;ei vnderstonden bi cristis lif &amp; his apostlis; for &thorn;us &thorn;e peple &yogh;eue&thorn; hem almes more wilfully &amp; deuoutly, &amp; &thorn;ei taken it more mekely &amp; ben more besy to lerne, kepe &amp; teche goddis lawe, &amp; so it is &thorn;e betre for bo&thorn;e sidis. &para; Also bi &thorn;is manere my&yogh;tte &amp; schulde &thorn;e peple &yogh;eue frely here almes to trewe prestis &thorn;at trewely kepten here ordre &amp; frely &amp; opynly tau&yogh;ten &thorn;e gospel, &amp; wi&thorn;-drawen it fro wickede prestis, &amp; not be constreyned to paie here ti&thorn;es &amp; offringis to open cursed men &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">X inserts not.</NOTE> meyntene hem in here opyn cursednesse; &amp; &thorn;us schulde symonye, coueitise &amp; ydelnesse of worldly clerkis be leid doun, &amp; holynesse &amp; trewe techynge &amp; knowynge of goddis lawe be brou&yogh;t in, bo&thorn;e in clerkis &amp; lewid men. &para; Also &thorn;us schulde stryuynge, pledynge &amp; cursynge for dymes &amp; offryngis &amp; hate &amp; discord among prestis &amp; lewid men be endid, &amp; vnyte, pees &amp; charite meyntened &amp; kept. &para; Also &thorn;es benefices bi &thorn;is cours &thorn;at men vsen nowe bryngi&thorn; in worldlynesse &amp; nedeles bisynesse aboute worldly officis, &thorn;at crist &amp; his apostlis wolden neuere <MILESTONE N="209" UNIT="page">take vpon hem; &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ei weren more my&yogh;tty, more witti, &amp; more brennynge in charite to god &amp; to &thorn;e peple, bo&thorn;e to lyue &thorn;e best manere in hem self &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> to teche o&thorn;ere men. &para; Also coueitise &amp; worldly bisynesse<NOTE PLACE="foot">sikirnesse X.</NOTE> of clerkis &amp; occasion of coueitise &amp; worldlynesse of &thorn;e peple 
<PB REF="00000319.tif" N="253"> schulden be don awey, &amp; cristis pouert &amp; his apostlis bi ensaumple of pore lif of clerkis &amp; triste in god &amp; desirynge of heuenely blisse schulde regne in cristene peple. &para;Also &thorn;an schulde prestis studie holy writt &amp; be deuout in here preieris, &amp; not be taried wi&thorn; newe offices, as newe songis &amp; moo sacramentis &thorn;an<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;at X.</NOTE> crist vsede &amp; his apostlis, &thorn;at tau&yogh;ten vs alle treu&thorn;e &amp; spedly sauynge of cristene peple. &para;Also mochil blasphemye of prelatis &amp; o&thorn;ere men of feyned obedience &amp; nedles sweryngis maad to worldly prelatis schulden &thorn;an cessen, &amp; souereyn obedience to god &amp; his lawe &amp; eschewynge of nedles o&thorn;es &amp; forswerynge schulde regne among cristene men. &para;Also &thorn;an schulde men eschewe comynly alle &thorn;e perilis seid bifore in &thorn;e first chapitre &amp; &thorn;e secunde &amp; many &thorn;ousand mo, &amp; lyue in clennesse &amp; sikernesse of conscience. &para;Also &thorn;an schulde prestis be bisy to syke<NOTE PLACE="foot">seke AA.</NOTE> goddis worschipe &amp; sauynge of mennus soulis, &amp; not here owene worldly glorie &amp; wynnynge of worldly drit. &para;Also &thorn;an schulden prestis lyue lich to angels,<NOTE PLACE="foot">an angel X.</NOTE> as &thorn;ei ben angelis of offices, where &thorn;ei lyuen now as swyn in fleschly lustis, &amp; turnen a&yogh;en to here formere synnes as houndis to here sp[e]wynge, for habundaunce of worldly goodis &amp; ydelnesse in here gostly office &amp; ouere moche bisynesse aboute &thorn;is wrecchid lif. for &thorn;es dredes &amp; many &thorn;ousand mo, &amp; for to be more lich to cristis lif &amp; his apostlis, &amp; for to profite more to here owene soules &amp; o&thorn;ere mennus, summe pore prestis &thorn;enken wi&thorn; goddis helpe<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> to traueile aboute where &thorn;ei schulden most profiten by euydence &thorn;at god &yogh;eue&thorn; hem, &thorn;e while &thorn;ei han tyme &amp; litel bodily streng&thorn;e &amp; &yogh;ou&thorn;e. ne&thorn;eles &thorn;ei dampnen not curatis &thorn;at don wel here office, so &thorn;at &thorn;ei kepen liberte of &thorn;e gospel, &amp; dwellen where &thorn;ei schullen most profite, &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;ei techen trewly &amp; stabely goddis lawe a&yogh;enst false prophetis &amp; cursed fendis lymes. Crist for his endeles mercy helpe his prestis &amp; comyn peple to be war of anticristis disceitis, &amp; goo euene &thorn;e ri&yogh;tte weie to heuene. Amen, ih&umacr; for &thorn;in endeles charite.</P>


</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="17" TYPE="tract"><PB REF="00000320.tif" N="254">
<HEAD>XVII. HOW ANTICHRIST AND HIS CLERKS TRAVAIL TO DESTROY HOLY WRIT.</HEAD>
<HEADNOTE><P>THIS tract should be compared with a short fly-leaf printed by Mr. Arnold, S. E. W. III. 186.</P><P>I cannot pretend to any sure judgment as to the authorship, but there is nothing in it at variance with Wyclif's teaching. It seems to have been written when the controversy with the poor priests had been carried on some time, and when they found it necessary to justify their constant appeals to God's law (Talem enim habebant terminum in omnibus suis dictis, semper pr&aelig;tendendo legem Dei; Goddis lawe, Knighton 2664.) It is possible that the need of such a justification would be soon felt even among the popular preachers, as it must certainly have been discovered very early in the schools. We need not, therefore, assign a very late date to this composition.</P><P>Copied from the Corpus MS. X. and collated with the Dublin MS. AA.</P><P><TABLE>
<HEAD>SUMMARY.</HEAD>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. I.</CELL>
<CELL>As Christ ordained four Gospels, so Satan has four devices to set men's authority above that of the Gospel. These devices are specially used by friars for the glory of their orders</CELL>
<CELL>p. 255</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>II.</CELL>
<CELL>The first false pretence is that the Church is of more authority than the Gospel, since it decreed which gospels should be received</CELL>
<CELL>256</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>III.</CELL>
<CELL>The second, that Austin says he would not believe the Gospel, unless the Church told him</CELL>
<CELL>258</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL></CELL>
<CELL>Austin's meaning is misrepresented</CELL>
<CELL>258</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL></CELL>
<CELL>Duty of maintaining the truth</CELL>
<CELL>259</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>IV.</CELL>
<CELL>The third, that men only know the Gospel by the Church</CELL>
<CELL>259</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL></CELL>
<CELL>The true ground of faith is Christ himself</CELL>
<CELL>260</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>V.</CELL>
<CELL>The fourth, that men believe the Gospel without knowing why</CELL>
<CELL>260</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL></CELL>
<CELL>Faith is given by God; its power</CELL>
<CELL>261</CELL>
</ROW>
</TABLE></P></HEADNOTE>

<PB REF="00000321.tif" N="255">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>Hou anticrist &amp; his clerkis traueilen to distroie holy writt &amp; to make cristene men vnstable in &thorn;e fei&thorn; &amp; to sette here ground in deuelis of helle.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<DIV2 N="1" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum primum.</HEAD>
<P>As houre lord ih&umacr; crist ordeynede to make his gospel sadly knowen &amp; meyntened a&yogh;enst heretikis &amp; men out of bileue bi writtynge of his foure euaungelistis, so &thorn;e deuel sathanas casti&thorn; bi anticrist &amp; his worldly false clerkis to distroie holy <MILESTONE N="210" UNIT="page">writt &amp; cristene mennus bileue bi foure cursed weies or fals resons. &para;&THORN;e first, &thorn;at &thorn;e chirche is of more auctorite &amp; more credence &thorn;an is ony gospel. &para; &THORN;e secunde, &thorn;at austyn sei&thorn; &thorn;at he wolde not bileue to &thorn;e gospel but &yogh;if &thorn;e chirche tau&yogh;te hym so. &para;&THORN;e &thorn;ride, &thorn;at no man now on lyue wote whiche is &thorn;e gospel but &yogh;if it be bi approuynge of &thorn;e chirche. &para; &THORN;e four&thorn;e, &yogh;if men seyn &thorn;at &thorn;ei bileuen &thorn;at &thorn;is is &thorn;e gospel of matheu or ion, &thorn;ei axen, whi bileuest &thorn;ou &thorn;at &thorn;is is &thorn;e gospel; as who sei&thorn;, &thorn;er is no cause but for &thorn;e chirche conferme&thorn; it &amp; teche&thorn; so. &THORN;es foure euydences &amp; many moo maki&thorn; &thorn;e fend to blynde men in bileue, &thorn;at &thorn;ei schulden not knowe whiche is synne, which is vertu, which is treu&thorn;e, which is falsnesse, which is good, which is euyl, &amp; which is goddis heste, &amp; which is lesynge of &thorn;e fend for to brynge alle men blyndly to helle. &amp; &thorn;es newe religious &amp; principaly freris prechen &thorn;es euydences &amp; sowen hem among lewid men <SUP>1</SUP>in contres to stoppe pore prestis &amp; lewid men,<SUP>1</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">1_1 omitted X.</NOTE> &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben not hardy to speke of &thorn;e gospel &amp; holy writt &amp; goddis comaundementis &amp; ioies of heuene &amp; of<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> synnes &amp; peynes of purgatorie &amp; of helle, lest &thorn;ei stiren men to rise out of synnys for drede of peynes, &amp; to lyfe in vertuous lif for to haue &thorn;e blisse of heuene. &amp; &thorn;is disceit in bileue is maad &amp; coniected of &thorn;es cursed pharisees for to magnyfie here newe feyned ordres, founden of synful men, not only wi&thorn; cristis clene religion but 
<PB REF="00000322.tif" N="256"> more &thorn;an it or ony part of holy writt; &amp; for<NOTE PLACE="foot">herfore X.</NOTE> &thorn;ei willen not be conuyct of here pride &amp; ypocrisie &amp; forsake here coueitise &amp; lustis of here bely &amp; here propre wille. &THORN;erfore &thorn;ei wilen ra&thorn;ere renne to helle fullire,<NOTE PLACE="foot">fulbere AA.</NOTE> &amp; drawe alle men after hem heedly bi distroiynge of cristene fei&thorn;, &thorn;an to come to cristis clene religion wi&thorn; fredam of &thorn;e gospel &thorn;at is ordeyned of god of endeles wisdom wi&thorn;-outen errour of ony synful man; for &thorn;ei mosten &thorn;an knoweleche here falsenesse &amp; ypocrisie, bi &thorn;e whiche &thorn;ei disceyueden cristene men fro &thorn;e bigyngne of here nouelries til &thorn;is tyme. but luciferis pride &amp; coueitise of worldly muk &amp; of hei&yogh; astatis and<NOTE PLACE="foot">of X.</NOTE> worldly worschipe may not suffre &thorn;is mekenes, as men dreden ful sore, for old enuye of sathanas &amp; hard rotynge in synne.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 2<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>See we now hou &thorn;ei bryngen in &thorn;e first cursed ground, &thorn;at &thorn;e chirche is of more autorite &amp; credence &thorn;an is &thorn;e gospel. &THORN;ei seyn &thorn;at nychodeme &amp; many moo writen &thorn;e gospellis of cristis lif &amp; his techynge, &amp; &thorn;e chirche putte hem awey &amp; approued &thorn;es foure gospellis of matheu, mark, luk &amp; ion. &THORN;an &thorn;e chirche my&yogh;te as wel haue putt out &thorn;es foure &amp; approued &thorn;e to&thorn;ere gospelleris; si&thorn; it was in free wille &amp; power of &thorn;e <MILESTONE N="211" UNIT="page">chirche to reproue &amp; dampne whiche &thorn;ei wolden &amp; approue &amp; accepte whiche hem lykede; &amp; &thorn;erfore men schulden bileue more to &thorn;e chirche &thorn;an to<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> ony<NOTE PLACE="foot">our X.</NOTE> gospel. &para;First &thorn;es fercastynge heretikis vnderstonden bi &thorn;e chirche &thorn;e pope of rome &amp; his cardynalis, &amp; &thorn;e multitude of worldly clerkis assentynge to his symonye &amp; worldly lordischipe aboue alle kyngis &amp; emperours of &thorn;is world; for ellis it were not to here purpos to magnyfye &thorn;e chirche as &thorn;ei now don. &THORN;anne trewe men seyn &thorn;at &thorn;e clergie &thorn;at first was kunnynge &amp; holy of lif was stirid bi &thorn;e holy gost to take &thorn;es gospellis &amp; charge not cristene peple wi&thorn; mo; si&thorn; &thorn;es ben ynowe &amp; 
<PB REF="00000323.tif" N="257"> profitable<NOTE PLACE="foot">perfyt AA.</NOTE> at &thorn;e fulle, &amp; ben figured in many prophecies of goddis lawe; &amp; &thorn;es foure witnessis weren acceptid of &thorn;e holy gost to &thorn;is writynge for many skillis &thorn;at we may not telle now; but certes &thorn;e chirche my&yogh;tte not haue putt awey &thorn;es gospellis &amp; acceptid &thorn;e o&thorn;ere. for &thorn;an it hadde don a&yogh;enst &thorn;e dom of god &amp; a&yogh;enst &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of ih&umacr; crist &amp; a&yogh;enst charite of &thorn;e holy gost, for to putte awey &thorn;es witnesses &thorn;at knewen more of goddis preuyte &amp; weren holiere of lif, &amp; to take witnessis not so kunnynge of goddis dom ne so holy of lif ne so meke ne so stable in fei&thorn; &amp; in loue of ih&umacr; crist. but &thorn;es sotil heretikis traueilen ny&yogh;t &amp; day to ensaumple &thorn;e multitude of worldly clerkis, &thorn;at ben ful of symonye, pride, coueitise, glotonye, lecherie &amp; o&thorn;ere synnes, aboue ih&umacr; crist &amp; his gospel, for to haue here worldly lif, pride &amp; lustis meyntened, &thorn;at no man schulde lette hem in here worldly glorie ne dis|trurble hem of here lustis, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei neuere so foule lien of<NOTE PLACE="foot">on AA.</NOTE> god &amp; sclaundren his peple. for &thorn;ei wolen make here cursed lif &amp; heresies to be gospel &amp; bileue of cristene men; but where ben more cursed traitouris to god &amp; his lawe &amp; more perilous &amp; false prophetis to cristene peple? for god com|aundi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Rev. xxii. 18.</NOTE> vp peyne of his grete curs &amp; deep dampnynge in helle &thorn;at no man schal wi&thorn;-drawe fro his lawe ony poynt of treu&thorn;e, ne adde &thorn;er-to ony nouelrie &thorn;at is not approued of &thorn;e trinyte, &amp; ih&umacr; crist sei&thorn; &thorn;at his gospel is euerlastynge testament. But &thorn;ei wolen for-don it wi&thorn; a stynkynge blast of anticristis cursed mou&thorn;. lord, hou doren cristene men meyntene siche heretikis, a&yogh;enst goddis techynge &amp; pees of cristene peple? siche weiward heretikis ben ful vnable to reule prelatis &amp; lordis &amp; comyns in schrifte, in prechynge &amp; preynge &amp; o&thorn;ere poyntis of here soule hel&thorn;e, for &thorn;ei disceyuen hem in fei&thorn; &amp; good lif, for to haue here owene pride &amp; coueitise &amp; lustis born vp, &amp; so drawen alle men to helle &thorn;at ben reulid bi suche false confessours, false prechours &amp; false conseilours.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="3" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000324.tif" N="258">
<HEAD>Capitulum 3<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>See now &thorn;e secunde wheel in &thorn;is deuelis wayn; &thorn;ei bere vpon austyn &thorn;at he sei&thorn; &thorn;us, <MILESTONE N="212a" UNIT="page">&thorn;at he wolde not bileue to &thorn;e gospel but &yogh;if &thorn;e chirche seide it. so trewe men answeren &thorn;us: suppose<NOTE PLACE="foot">suppo X.</NOTE> &thorn;at austyn sei&thorn; &thorn;is word, he seide to &thorn;is entente, &thorn;at but &yogh;if crist, heuyd of holy chirche, &amp; seyntis in heuene &amp; &thorn;e apostlis of crist, &thorn;at ben holy chirche, seiden &amp; approueden &thorn;is gospel, ellis he wolde not bileue &thorn;er-to; &amp; &thorn;is vnderstondynge is ful trewe &amp; resonable &amp; accordynge to &thorn;e lettere of austyn. but &thorn;ei vnderstonden &thorn;us, but &yogh;if &thorn;e multitude of cursed worldly clerkis approue &thorn;is for &thorn;e gospel, ellis austyn wolde not bileue to &thorn;e gospel of ih&umacr; crist; &amp; si&thorn; austyn was &amp; is so gret a doctour of holy chirche, no man schulde bileue to &thorn;e gospel but &yogh;if &thorn;e chirche of &thorn;es prelatis confermen &thorn;at &thorn;is is &thorn;e gospel of crist. &THORN;anne<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;an X.</NOTE> &yogh;if &thorn;e multitude of anticristis clerkis approuen not &thorn;e gospel ne treu&thorn;e of holy writt, no man schulde holde<NOTE PLACE="foot">olde X.</NOTE> &thorn;e gospel ne ony comaundement of god, ne meyntene ony treu&thorn;e a&yogh;enst anti|crist &amp; his worldely prelatis. but what heresie my&yogh;tte soonere distroie cristene mennus bileue? &amp; god forbede &thorn;at austyn were in &thorn;is<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> perilous heresie, or ony cristene man. &THORN;er-fore it is cursed lesynge to sclaund[r]e seynt austin wi&thorn; &thorn;is cursed errour, to<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> coloure here owene false vnderstondynge &amp; heresie bi &thorn;is holy doctour. for bi &thorn;is cursed wheel, &yogh;if anticristis clerkis dampne cristene mennus fei&thorn; &amp; &thorn;e comaundementis of god &amp; poyntis of charite, &amp; bryngen in here owen weiward lawis to holden vp here pride &amp; coueitise, &amp; to curse men for &thorn;ei don werkis of charite, men moten vp peyne of dampnacion receyue here cursed dedis as bileue, &amp; forsake &thorn;e gospel of ih&umacr; crist, &amp; take fendis lesyngis in stede of goddis lore; &amp; moo cursednesse to distroie cristene fei&thorn; &thorn;an wole sue of &thorn;is cursed vnderstondynge may no man ne fend ymagyne til &thorn;e day of dom. &THORN;erfore cristen men<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> schulden stonde to &thorn;e de&thorn; 
<PB REF="00000325.tif" N="259"> for meyntenynge of cristis gospel, &amp; trewe vnderstondynge &thorn;er-of geten bi holy lif &amp; gret studie, &amp; not sette here fei&thorn; ne triste in synful prelatis &amp; here cursed clerkis, ne in here vnderstondynge of holy writt, for &thorn;ei ben vnable wi&thorn; &thorn;is worldly lif ful of pride, coueitise, glotonye &amp; ydelnesse, as<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; X.</NOTE> haukynge &amp; huntynge, &amp; pleiynge at &thorn;e chees &amp; tablis, &amp; riot &amp; daunsynge, &amp; festis makynge, dronkenesse &amp; lecherie, to perceyue &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of holy writt &amp; hei&yogh;e preuytees of god. for crist sei&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel &thorn;at &thorn;e fadir of heuene hidi&thorn; &thorn;es<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. xi. 25.</NOTE> treu&thorn;es fro worldly wise men &amp; queynte, &amp; schewi&thorn; hem to meke men as weren cristis disciplis. &amp; &thorn;e wise man sei&thorn; &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">Prov. ix. 10.</NOTE> &thorn;e wisdom schal not entre in-to an euyl willid man, for &thorn;e drede of god is bigynnynge &amp; plente of wisdom, &amp; &thorn;ei han not &thorn;is drede; &thorn;an &thorn;ei han not &thorn;is wisdom. &THORN;erfore it is luciferis pride, &amp; passe&thorn; it, to constreyne men to take vnder|stondynge of holy writt after &thorn;e witt &amp; dom of siche worldly <MILESTONE N="212b" UNIT="page">clerkis, &thorn;at ben enemys of crist &amp; his lawe &amp; his seruauntis, for &thorn;ei ben blynde in goddis lawe &amp; good lif, &amp; leden blynde men to helle, as crist sei&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel; for in steed of keies of heuene, &thorn;at ben kunnynge of holy writt &amp; power to distroie synne &amp; saue cristene soulis bi trewe techynge &amp; good ensaumple, &thorn;ei han ignoraunce of goddis lawe, &amp; no wil<NOTE PLACE="foot">wel X.</NOTE> to studie &amp; lyue &thorn;er-aftir, but kunnynge &amp; practisynge in here owene wickede lawis for pride &amp; coueitise, &amp; feynen hem power of tirauntrie to stoppe treue men fro prechynge of &thorn;e gospel, &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ei prechen a&yogh;enst here wille to curse hem &amp; prisone hem &amp; brenne hem<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE>; &amp; certis &thorn;es ben keies of helle.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="4" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 4<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>See now &thorn;e &thorn;ridde wheel of sathanas chaar. &THORN;es cautelous clerkis &amp; religious of lucifer seyn &thorn;at no man wot whiche is the gospel but bi approuynge &amp; confermynge of &thorn;e chirche. but trewe men seyn &thorn;at to here vnderstondynge &thorn;is is ful of 
<PB REF="00000326.tif" N="260"> falsed; for cristene men ben certeyn of bileue, bi gracious &yogh;ifte of ih&umacr; crist, &thorn;at &thorn;is treu&thorn;e tau&yogh;t bi crist &amp; his apostlis is &thorn;e gospel, &thorn;ou&yogh; alle anticristis clerkis crien neuere so faste &thorn;e contrarie vp peyne of curs &amp; prisonynge &amp; brennynge. &amp; &thorn;is bileue is not groundid on &thorn;e pope &amp; his cardinalis, for &thorn;anne it moste faile &amp; ben vndon, as &thorn;ei failen &amp; ben sumtyme distroied, but on ih&umacr; crist, god &amp; man, &amp; on &thorn;e holy trinyte; &amp; so it may neuere faile but in defaute of him &thorn;at schulde loue god &amp; serue him &amp; faile&thorn; in &thorn;es two poyntis, for almy&yogh;tty god &amp; his treu&thorn;es ben foundement of cristene mennus fei&thorn;. And as poul sei&thorn;, foundement may no man sette biside &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">l Cor. iii. 11.</NOTE> &thorn;at is sette, &thorn;at is ih&umacr; crist. &THORN;erfore &thorn;ou&yogh; anticrist &amp; alle &thorn;es<NOTE PLACE="foot">his X.</NOTE> worldly clerkis ben biried depe in helle for here cursed symonye, pride, &amp; coueitise &amp; o&thorn;ere synnys, &yogh;it cristene fei&thorn; faile&thorn; not; for &thorn;ei ben not ground &thorn;er-of but ih&umacr; crist is ground &thorn;er-of. for he is oure god &amp; oure beste maistre, euere redy to teche trewe men alle &thorn;inge &thorn;at is profitable &amp; nedful to here soulis; &amp; he may not faile in &thorn;is techynge but for vnablete of him &thorn;at schulde resceyue &thorn;is techynge.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="5" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 5<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>&THORN;e four&thorn;e whel of belialis carte is &thorn;is: &yogh;if cristene men seyn &thorn;ei knowen bi bileue &thorn;at &thorn;is is cristis gospel, &thorn;es malicious heretikis axen whi &thorn;ei bileuen &thorn;at &thorn;is is gospel. but trewe men axen of hem a&yogh;enward whi &thorn;ei bileuen &thorn;at god is god; &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ei tellen a good sufficient cause, telle we &thorn;e same cause whi we bileuen &thorn;at &thorn;is is cristis gospel. but &thorn;es heretikis wolden haue &thorn;is cause: for &thorn;es prelatis techen &thorn;at &thorn;is is cristis gospel; &amp; &thorn;anne<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &thorn;ei wolden haue of &thorn;is cause alle here false purpos, &thorn;at what euere &thorn;es prelatis techen opynly &amp; meyntenen stedfastly, were of as gret autorite or more &thorn;an is cristis gospel; <MILESTONE N="212c" UNIT="page">&amp; so &thorn;ei wolden distroie holy writt &amp; cristene fei&thorn;, &amp; meyntenen &thorn;at what-euere &thorn;ei don were no synne. but cristene men taken here fei&thorn; of god bi his 
<PB REF="00000327.tif" N="261"> gracious &yogh;ifte, whanne he &yogh;eue&thorn; to hem knowynge &amp; vnder|stondynge of treu&thorn;es nedful for to saue mennus soulis bi, &amp; grace to assente in here herte to suche treu&thorn;es; &amp; &thorn;is men clepen fei&thorn;. &amp; of &thorn;is fei&thorn; cristene men ben more certeyn &thorn;an ony man is of ony<NOTE PLACE="foot">only X.</NOTE> worldly &thorn;ing bi ony bodily witt; &amp; &thorn;er|fore crist reproue&thorn; most defaute of bileue, bo&thorn;e in &thorn;e iewis &amp; in his disciplis, &amp; &thorn;erfore cristis apostlis preieden<NOTE PLACE="foot">preiseden X.</NOTE> most to haue stabilnesse in fei&thorn;; for it is unpossible &thorn;at ony man plese god wi&thorn;-outen fei&thorn;, &amp; so crist preide principaly &thorn;at &thorn;e fei&thorn; of petir &amp; o&thorn;ere disciplis schulden not faile endeles; &amp; goddis lawe telli&thorn; hou bi fei&thorn; seyntis wrou&yogh;ten alle here grete wondris &amp; meruailis &thorn;at &thorn;ei diden. &amp; &yogh;if anticrist seie here &thorn;at eche man may<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> feyne &thorn;at he ha&thorn; ri&yogh;t fei&thorn; &amp; goode vnderstondynge of holy writt &yogh;ouyn of god whanne he is in errour, late a man seke in alle &thorn;ingis trewely &thorn;e honour of god &amp; lyue iustly to god &amp; man, &amp; &thorn;anne god wole not faile to him in ony &thorn;ing &thorn;at is nedful to hym, nei&thorn;er in fei&thorn; ne vnderstondynge ne in answere a&yogh;enst his enemyes. &amp; for fei&thorn; is scheld of cristene men a&yogh;enst alle temptacions of &thorn;e fend &amp; ground of alle vertues, &thorn;erfore sathanas ordeyned &thorn;es newe sectis to be so manye &amp; haue name of kunnynge &amp; holynesse bifore alle o&thorn;ere, &amp; groundi&thorn; in hem pride, enuye, coueitise, glotonye, lecherie &amp; ypocrisie to walwe among &thorn;e peple &amp; stire hem bi word &amp; ensaumple to be vnstable in &thorn;e fei&thorn;; &amp; stire&thorn; hei&yogh;e worldly prelatis to be fauourable to hem &amp; meyntenen hem in &thorn;is ypocrisie to coloure here owene synne &thorn;er-bi, &amp; to lette treue men to preche pleynly &amp; frely cristis gospel &amp; &thorn;e hestis of god for sauynge of mannus soule. &amp; here-bi &amp; [bi] many moo disceitis schulden cristene men knowe how &thorn;es newe religious ben false prophetis &amp; cursed sectis, of whiche crist &amp; his apostlis prophecieden bifore, &amp; tau&yogh;ten men to knowe hem bi here werkis,<NOTE PLACE="foot">clerkis AA.</NOTE> &thorn;at ben ypocrisie, coueitise &amp; meyn|tenynge of synne bi fals prechynge, flaterynge, fals conseilynge &amp; sclaunderynge of trewe men,<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &amp; makynge<NOTE PLACE="foot">maken X.</NOTE> men siker of 
<PB REF="00000328.tif" N="262"> gostly helpe bi fals letteris of fraternyte &amp; many o&thorn;ere nouel|ries brou&yogh;t vp bi ypocrisie &amp; coueitise. &amp; as ion &thorn;e euaungelist<NOTE PLACE="marg">2 John 10.</NOTE> comaundi&thorn;, cristene men schulden not resceyue hem in-to here houses ne seie to hem, heil. &amp; poul biddi&thorn; &thorn;at men schulden<NOTE PLACE="marg">2 Thess. iii. 14.</NOTE> not comune wi&thorn; hem, &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben confoundid &amp; schamed of here false heresie &amp; turne to cristis clene religion wi&thorn;-outen errour of synful mennus tradicions. God almy&yogh;tty streng&thorn;e his litil flok<NOTE PLACE="foot">folk X.</NOTE> a&yogh;enst &thorn;es foure whelis of sathanas chaar, a&yogh;enst <MILESTONE N="213" UNIT="page">anticristis clerkis &amp; helperis, &amp; make hem stronge in ri&yogh;tful fei&thorn;, hope &amp; charite, to seke trewely &thorn;e worschipe of ih&umacr; crist &amp; sauynge of mennus soulis; to dispise anticristis bost &amp; feyned power; &amp; wilfully &amp; ioiefully suffre peyne &amp; reproue<NOTE PLACE="foot">reprof AA.</NOTE> in &thorn;e world for &thorn;e name<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;anne AA.</NOTE> of ih&umacr; &amp; his gospel, to &yogh;eue sade ensaumple to o&thorn;ere for to folowe &amp; conquere &thorn;e hei&yogh;e blisse of heuene bi glorious martirdom as o&thorn;ere seyntis diden bifore. Ih&umacr; for &thorn;in endeles my&yogh;t, endeles wisdom, endeles goodnesse &amp; charite, graunte to vs synful wrecchis &thorn;is bone. Amen.</P>


</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="18" TYPE="tract"><PB REF="00000329.tif" N="263">
<HEAD>XVIII. HOW SATAN AND HIS PRIESTS, ETC.</HEAD>
<HEADNOTE><P>I SEE no reason to deny the authenticity of this tract. In complaining of the manner in which Scripture was wrested to all ends by setting aside its literal sense, Wyclif was insisting on a favourite topic. It is curious, however, to find him maintaining the right of preaching against wicked men by name, since, so far as I know, there is no personal attack in any of his works; the nearest approach to it being his allusions to Spencer's action in heading the Flanders Crusade. It is possible, having regard to the context, to suppose that he means only class names (such as 'prelates,' 'friars,' etc.). He may have been taxed with want of charity in attacking special classes, instead of confining himself to a general denunciation of sin. It seems that in any case his attacks were returned.</P><P>Copied from the Corpus MS. X. and collated with the Dublin MS. AA.</P><P><TABLE>
<HEAD>SUMMARY.</HEAD>
<ROW>
<CELL>CHAP. I.</CELL>
<CELL>Three heresies prevalent. 1. That holy writ is false. 2. That it is lawful to lie. 3. That it is uncharitable to denounce sins of great men</CELL>
<CELL>p. 264</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL></CELL>
<CELL>The first two are upheld in schools of divinity; the third by pre|lates and great men</CELL>
<CELL>265</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>II.</CELL>
<CELL>They say that holy writ is false, since against both testaments they maintain that the clergy may hold secular lordship</CELL>
<CELL>265</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL></CELL>
<CELL>They advocate a false mode of interpretation, refusing the literal sense</CELL>
<CELL>266</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL></CELL>
<CELL>Reasons for such advocacy</CELL>
<CELL>267</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>III.</CELL>
<CELL>Lies are brought in, because prelates and new religious are false, having forsaken the way in which they are bound to live</CELL>
<CELL>268</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL></CELL>
<CELL>Abuses of the orders; child-stealing, etc.</CELL>
<CELL>269</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL></CELL>
<CELL>Lying in act has led to lying in word</CELL>
<CELL>270</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL>IV.</CELL>
<CELL>Prelates and false religious say that it is against charity to expose their sins</CELL>
<CELL>271</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL></CELL>
<CELL>It is a priest's duty to warn men of their sins</CELL>
<CELL>271</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL></CELL>
<CELL>Prelates and religious attack other men in their sermons</CELL>
<CELL>273</CELL>
</ROW>
<ROW>
<CELL></CELL>
<CELL>But they wish to shut the mouths of reprovers, lest they should lose influence and wealth</CELL>
<CELL>273</CELL>
</ROW>
</TABLE></P></HEADNOTE>

<PB REF="00000330.tif" N="264">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q>Hou sathanas &amp; his prestis &amp; his feyned religious casten bi &thorn;re cursed heresies to distroie alle good lyuynge &amp; mayntene<NOTE PLACE="foot">meyntenynge X.</NOTE> alle manere of synne.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<DIV2 N="1" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum primum.</HEAD>
<P>As almy&yogh;tty god in trinyte ordeyne&thorn; men to come to &thorn;e blisse of heuene bi &thorn;re groundis, bi knowynge of &thorn;e trinyte bi sad fei&thorn;, bi treue kepynge of goddis hestis, &amp; bi perfit charite &amp; endeles, so sathanas &amp; his worldly clerkis &amp; his feyned religious ful of sotil ypocrisie casten to distroie alle vertuous lif &amp; iustise, &amp; meyntene alle manere of synne bi &thorn;es &thorn;re cursed groundes. &THORN;e first is &thorn;at holy writt is fals; &thorn;e secunde &thorn;at it<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> is lefful &amp; medful to lie; &thorn;e &thorn;ridde &thorn;at it is a&yogh;enst charite to crie opynly a&yogh;ens prelatis synnes &amp; o&thorn;er my&yogh;tty mennys. for as &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;is is bacbitynge or detraction &amp; sclaundrynge, to brynge men out of deuocion to god &amp; holy chirche, &amp; make men of religion of euyl name where &thorn;ei weren bifore holden goode &amp; holy; &amp; &thorn;is prechynge stire&thorn; lordis &amp; o&thorn;ere men to wi&thorn;drawe worldly goodis fro men of holy chirche, &amp; so hyndri&thorn; goddis seruyce &amp; preieris for &thorn;e pees &amp; maken<NOTE PLACE="foot">sic in both MSS.</NOTE> discencion &amp; enuye. for &yogh;if holy writt be fals men may haue noon autorite &thorn;er-bi to reproue synne &amp; preise vertues &amp; vertuous lif. &amp; &yogh;if it be leffel &amp; meritorie to leie, &thorn;an no man ha&thorn; ground to stire men fro synne bi grete peynes bihi&yogh;te bi cristis word, ne stire men to vertues bi grete ioies of heuene. for si&thorn; it is medful to lie, as &thorn;ei seyn, crist vsed &thorn;is medful craft at &thorn;e fulle, &amp; no man may &thorn;anne wite in whiche autorite he seide so&thorn; &amp; in whiche he lei&yogh;ede. &amp; &yogh;if it be a&yogh;enst charite to preche &amp; crie openly a&yogh;enst synne of prelatis &amp; men of &thorn;e chirche &amp; o&thorn;ere my&yogh;tty men, &thorn;an cristis lif &amp; his techynge &amp; his apostlis &amp; prophetes in &thorn;e olde lawe &amp; his comaundementis to his prophetis weren a&yogh;enst charite, 
<PB REF="00000331.tif" N="265"> ful of detraccion &amp; sclaundrynge. but what heresies my&yogh;tte more blaspheme god, more distroie holy writt &amp; vertuous lif, &amp; more norische synne &amp; cursed men in here lustis? &amp; certis wi&thorn;-inne &thorn;is seuene &yogh;eer worldly coueitouse clerkis &amp; feyned religious<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> meyntened in scolis of dyuynite two &thorn;e firste heresies, &amp; &yogh;it holden it a noble dede to susteyne hem; <MILESTONE N="214" UNIT="page">&amp; &thorn;e &thorn;ridde heresie regnyd<NOTE PLACE="foot">regne&thorn; X.</NOTE> &thorn;an &amp; &yogh;it do&thorn; more &amp; more among prelatis, feyned religious &amp; lordis &amp; comyns for &thorn;e more part. hou stiren suche heretikis &amp; blasphemes god of treu&thorn;e to mercy bi here preieris, si&thorn; god curse&thorn; to here blyssyngis, as he sei&thorn; bi prophete malechie, &amp; here preiere is abhominable &amp;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Malachi ii. 2.</NOTE> cursed, for &thorn;ei turnen awey &amp; heren not goddis lawe &amp; fulfillen it in dede. hou<NOTE PLACE="foot">and AA.</NOTE> meyntenen lordis &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of &thorn;e gospel &amp; holy writt, si&thorn; &thorn;ei meyntenen siche blaspheme heretikis to be dowid in seculer lordischipe a&yogh;enst goddis comaundement &amp; ensaumple of cristis lif &amp; his apostlis? hou doun prestis here office &thorn;at schulde witnesse &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of goddis lawe to suffre peyne &amp; de&thorn; &thorn;erfore? hou don comunes here trewe seruyce to god, &thorn;at meyntenen siche heretikis &amp; worschipen hem in word &amp; dede whanne &thorn;ei owen to knowen here opyn falsnesse? it is grett meruaile &thorn;at god of his endles ri&yogh;twisnesse<NOTE PLACE="foot">mercy X.</NOTE> distroie&thorn; not alle &thorn;is cursed peple to helle for &thorn;es cursed blasphemyes &amp; erresies<NOTE PLACE="foot">heretikis X.</NOTE> &amp; wickid meyntenynge; but certis &thorn;e lengere &thorn;at he spare&thorn; bi mercy, &thorn;e sorere schal &thorn;e vengaunce be but &yogh;if men amenden hem.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 2<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>See now hou &thorn;es cursed heretikis bryngen in &thorn;e firste blasphemye. first &thorn;ei seyn &amp; meyntenen &thorn;at clerkis may leffully haue seculer lordischipis &amp; lyue in pompe &amp; worldly welfare as lordis. &amp; holy writt old &amp; newe &amp; cristis<NOTE PLACE="foot">crist X.</NOTE> lif &amp; his apostlis dampnen &thorn;is pride &amp; wrecchednesse in clerkis. &amp; neden hem to mekenesse &amp; wilful traueile &amp; pouert. &amp; 
<PB REF="00000332.tif" N="266"> many men aleggen faste holy writt a&yogh;enst &thorn;e worldly lif of clerkis; &thorn;erfore &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at holy writt is fals, for trewe men schulden haue noon auctorite a&yogh;enst here cursed lif. &THORN;e secunde tyme &thorn;ei fynden vp a newe manere of speche or logik, &thorn;at is contrarie to &thorn;e speche of holy writt; &amp; for &thorn;ei wolen meyntenen here owen fyndynge as good &amp; trewe, &thorn;erfore &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at &thorn;e speche of holy writt is fals &thorn;at reuersi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">resceyueth X.</NOTE> here owene fonnydnesse. &amp; here &thorn;ei maken god a fool &amp; fals, in as moche as in hem is, &amp; schewen hem self wise men &amp; trewe; &amp; algatis feynen hem self wisere &amp; treuere &thorn;an god almy&yogh;tty. &para;&THORN;e &thorn;ridde tyme &thorn;ei coueten name of wisdom &amp; worschipe of &thorn;is world &amp; here owene excellence more &thorn;anne goddis honour, &amp; &thorn;erfore &thorn;ei disdeynen to sue mekely &thorn;e speche of goddis lawe &amp; &thorn;e lif of crist &amp; his apostlis, but maken newe lawis &amp; logik &thorn;at maken holy writt derk &amp; fals to &thorn;e comyn vnderstondynge of hem &amp; here folweris. &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ei schame sumdel to seie to cristene lordis &thorn;at holy writt is fals, but &thorn;ei don worse bi sotel ypocrisie &thorn;at holy writt is fals to &thorn;e wordis but &thorn;e vnderstondynge &thorn;er-of is trewe; &amp; &thorn;is vnderstondynge hangi&thorn; in determinacion of worldly prelatis, &thorn;at kunnen not holy writt &amp; ben not able to <MILESTONE N="215" UNIT="page">haue inspiracion of &thorn;e holy gost bi here holy lif, for &thorn;ei ben comynly ful of symonye, pride, coueitise, glotonye, lecherie, manquellynge &amp; o&thorn;ere synnys, &amp; open heretikis &amp; enemys of crist &amp; his lawe &amp; his trewe seruauntis. &amp; ih&umacr; crist sei&thorn; &thorn;at siche ben blynde &amp; leden blynde men in-to &thorn;e lake of synne &amp; at &thorn;e laste to helle; for &yogh;if &thorn;ei han money &amp; gold at here lykynge bi extorsion &amp; robberie, &thorn;ei recken not of cristene soulis hou foul deuelis deuouren hem. &amp; &thorn;e holy gost dwelli&thorn; not in siche proude &amp; coueitouse clerkis, for &thorn;ei ben templis of &thorn;e fend &amp; &thorn;ei worschipen fals goddis &amp; dwellen in<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> ydolatrie, hou schulde god teche hem &thorn;e precius treu&thorn;es of his lawe? but certis bi &thorn;is ypocrisie &thorn;ei wolen brynge in what heresie &thorn;at hem liki&thorn; &amp; meyntene it for good treu&thorn;e &amp; profitable. 
<PB REF="00000333.tif" N="267"> for &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at here sentence &amp; dom is vnderstondynge of holy writt; &amp; &thorn;es worldly prelatis wolen make a congregacion of hem self &amp; clerkis assentynge to hem, summe for worldly drede &amp; worldly fauour, summe for gold &amp; hope of beneficis, &amp; summe for drede of curs, priuynge of beneficis &amp; sclaundre &amp; prisonynge &amp; brennynge. but se now &thorn;e wodnesse of &thorn;is blasphemye. first &yogh;if holy writt be fals, certis god autor<NOTE PLACE="foot">autorite AA.</NOTE> &thorn;er-of is fals, &amp; si&thorn; &thorn;ei graunten &thorn;e friste errour, &thorn;ei moten graunte al &thorn;at sue&thorn; &thorn;er-of. also &thorn;ei feynen &thorn;at a fool &amp; a cursed deuyl is wisere &amp; trewere &thorn;an ih&umacr; crist god &amp; man, si&thorn; here speche is wittiere &amp; trewere &thorn;an &thorn;e speche of god in holi writt, &amp; &thorn;is reson is pleyn. suppose &thorn;at &thorn;is clerk writynge or techynge contrarie speche to holy writt schal be dampnyd, for &thorn;an he is a deuyl as crist sei&thorn; of iudas, &amp; as &thorn;ei feynen his writynge &amp; techynge is wittiere &amp; trewere &thorn;an techynge &amp; writynge of god almy&yogh;tty; &thorn;an it sue&thorn; opynly &thorn;at a fool &amp; a cursed deuyl is wittiere &amp; trewere &thorn;an ih&umacr; crist, kyng of wisdom &amp; treu&thorn;e. Lord, si&thorn; &thorn;e holy gost is autour &amp; welle of witt &amp; treu&thorn;e, whe&thorn;er he tau&yogh;tte not goddis prophetis &amp; cristis apostlis to write &amp; speke treu&thorn;e; whe&thorn;er &thorn;e fend sathanas techi&thorn; proude &amp; coueitouse clerkis, ful of symonye &amp; o&thorn;ere synnys, more witt &amp; treu&thorn;e &thorn;an &thorn;e holy gost techere of alle treu&thorn;e tau&yogh;te cristis apostlis &amp; euaunge|listis, &thorn;at weren sad in bileue &amp; charite &amp; holy &amp; trewe in lif &amp; techynge. &amp; whanne al &thorn;e ground is sou&yogh;t of &thorn;is heresie it stondi&thorn; in &thorn;is poynt, &thorn;at holy writt, goddis owene word, is fals for &thorn;is cursed heretik mysvnderstondi&thorn; it, or for it dis|plese&thorn; &thorn;is heretik &amp; reproue&thorn; &thorn;is synne. but certis bi &thorn;is skille he&thorn;ene men &amp; fendis maken god most false of alle &thorn;ingis, for &thorn;ei vnderstonden &thorn;at god is most fals &amp; wrongful &amp; dampne&thorn; hem most for here synnys. but it fari&thorn; bi holy writt &amp; cursed clerkis &amp; foolis as it fari&thorn; bi drounken men &amp; &thorn;e mone <MILESTONE N="216" UNIT="page">And candel; &thorn;ei demen of o mone or candel to be two, for &thorn;ei ben vndisposid to deme &amp; knowe &thorn;e treu&thorn;e bicause of here 
<PB REF="00000334.tif" N="268"> dronkenesse, so &thorn;es foolis, bi here pride, coueitise &amp; o&thorn;ere synnys, ben vnable to conseyue<NOTE PLACE="foot">conceyue AA.</NOTE> &thorn;e hei&yogh;e trew&thorn;is of goddis word; &amp; &thorn;erfore &thorn;ei seyn &thorn;at it is fals, for &thorn;ei han not witt ne grace to traueile aboute trewe vnderstondynge &thorn;er-of for worldly occupacion &amp; ydelnesse.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="3" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 3<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Now see whi meyntenynge of lesyngis is brou&yogh;t in. god sei&thorn; &thorn;at no &thorn;ing plesi&thorn; to a fool but folie; so no &thorn;ing plesi&thorn; comynly to a false man but falsnesse; &amp; for &thorn;es worldly prelatis &amp; newe pharisees ben groundid in lesyngis, &thorn;erfore &thorn;ei comenden lesyngis &amp; meyntenen hem. for prelatis comen in &thorn;e staat of cristis apostlis to lyue in pouert, mekenesse &amp; traueyle of &thorn;e gospel as &thorn;ei deden, but &thorn;ei ben turned to coueitise, worldly lordischipis, pride, ydelnesse &amp; vanyte, &amp; turnen cristis lif and<NOTE PLACE="foot">"in" in both MS.</NOTE> techynge vpsodom. Also newe religious ben brou&yogh;t in-to &thorn;e chirche to reise up cristis mekenesse, pouert &amp; penaunce, &amp; to ben a bok of &thorn;is pouert &amp; dispisynge of &thorn;e world to alle men to loken on, &amp; &thorn;ei ben turned to ypocrisie, pride, coueitise, glotonye &amp; slou&thorn;e &amp; bisynes<NOTE PLACE="foot">lesyngis AA.</NOTE> of &thorn;e world more &thorn;an o&thorn;ere worldly men, &amp; ben fals bokis ful of synne &amp; heresie; &thorn;at, as ierome &amp; anseml<NOTE PLACE="foot">sic in both MS.</NOTE> witnessen, here croune, here tonsure, here abitis ben ful of lesyngis &amp; &thorn;ei ben but feyned &amp; peyntid men of religion, &amp; not only lesyngmongeris but pure lesyngis. &amp; si&thorn; god sey&thorn; in &thorn;e sauter &thorn;at alle &thorn;at speken lesyngis schullen ben lost, hou<NOTE PLACE="marg">Psalm v. 6.</NOTE> moche more schullen &thorn;ei ben lost &thorn;at ben pure lesyngis. &THORN;e secunde tyme, crist sei&thorn; to &thorn;e iewis, &yogh;if &yogh;e weren<NOTE PLACE="marg">John viii. 39.</NOTE> abrahamus children &yogh;e schulden do werkis of abraham; &amp; &thorn;er-fore sei&thorn; austyn wi&thorn; o&thorn;ere seyntis &thorn;at &thorn;ou art his soone whoos werkis &thorn;ou dost. &THORN;an si&thorn; &thorn;e fend is fadir of lesyngis, as crist sei&thorn;, &thorn;es worldly clerkis, &amp; namely feyned religious, comenden lesyngis, for to witnesse in word &amp; dede &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben 
<PB REF="00000335.tif" N="269"> &thorn;e fendis children. for &yogh;if &thorn;ei weren cristis children &thorn;ei schulden holde treu&thorn;e in word &amp; wille &amp; dede &amp; meyntenen &thorn;at, and dispisen alle manere of lesyngis &amp; falsnesse &amp; synne vp here kunnynge &amp; power; &amp; as ion &thorn;e euaungelist sei&thorn;, &thorn;ei schulden wilfully putte hem to de&thorn; for to distroie lesyngis, si&thorn; lesyngis stondi&thorn; more in false dedis &thorn;an in wordis, as<NOTE PLACE="foot">of X.</NOTE> holy writt, ambrose &amp; o&thorn;ere seyntis witnessen pleynly. &para; &THORN;e &thorn;ridde tyme, &thorn;es newe ordris &amp; flaterynge my&yogh;tte not be susteyned wi&thorn;-oute lesyngis, bo&thorn;e in word &amp; dede, in &thorn;is manere as &thorn;ei now ben; &amp; for to schewe<MILESTONE N="217" UNIT="page"> &thorn;at &thorn;is veyn religious louen more here owene inuencions &amp; here owene lustis<NOTE PLACE="foot">both MSS. repeat "more" here.</NOTE> &thorn;an &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> clene religion of cristis ordynaunce &amp; gret pouert &amp; peynful lif after crist &amp; his apostlis, &thorn;ei preisen lesyngis for to beren vp &thorn;es veyn nouelries &amp; haunte here lustis. for &yogh;if cristis owene ordre &amp; ensaumple of his lif &amp; his apostlis ben betere &amp; profitere &thorn;an ony newe maad of synful men, it is a foul lesynge to chese wityngly &amp; meyntene &thorn;e lesse perfit,<NOTE PLACE="foot">profit X.</NOTE> &amp; forsake &thorn;e li&yogh;ttere, sikerere &amp; perfitere. &para; Also it is a cursed lesyng to drawe children, &thorn;at han but litil discrecion, to &thorn;es newe feyned religious bi &yogh;eftis &amp; bi behestis<NOTE PLACE="foot">hestis AA.</NOTE> of worldly lordischipe, honour &amp; sikernesse of bodily welfare, more &thorn;an to holde wilful pouert &amp; penaunce &amp; dispit &amp; forsakynge of alle worldly &thorn;ing, for al &thorn;is is symonye &amp; heresie &yogh;if it be wel sou&yogh;t; but it is a cursedere lesyng to stele &yogh;onge children fro here frendis &amp; bi false disceitis make hem to be professed, sumtyme a&yogh;enst here wille, &amp; suffre hem not to gon out of &thorn;is veyn ordre, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei knowen hem self vnable &thorn;er-to. &para; For sumtyme &thorn;es children frendis fallen in mornynge to de&thorn;; &amp; sumtyme bi myschef ben dede where here children &thorn;us stolen schulden ellis helpe hem; &amp; sumtyme &thorn;es children schulden be goode techeris &amp; reuleris of &thorn;e peple, &amp; now ben cursed ypocritis, ful of coueitise, lecherie, enuye &amp; grucchynge a&yogh;enst god; &amp; now &thorn;ei ben nedid to rob &thorn;e pore peple bi fals beggynge, &amp; sclaundren crist wi&thorn; &thorn;is clamose beggynge 
<PB REF="00000336.tif" N="270"> dampned of goddis lawe, &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;es open &thorn;efte is stifly meyn|tened a&yogh;enst goddis lawe, reson &amp; charite bi sotil ypocrisie, &amp; no chasti&yogh;ynge don &thorn;er-onne. for men wenen &thorn;at &thorn;es stronge &thorn;eues ben vnder no kyngis lawe ne prelatis lawe in oure lond. for men vnderstonden &thorn;at fewe men of discrecion comen to &thorn;es nouelries but siche &yogh;onge bi stelynge or disceyuynge, or ellis bi coueitise of worldly honour &amp; sikernesse of wombe ioie. &amp; herefore &thorn;es veyn religious preisen lesyngis, dampnyd bi holy writt old &amp; newe, for cristis treu&thorn;e. &amp; &thorn;e deuel is lesyngis fadir &amp; disceyued mankynde bi lesynge &amp; brou&yogh;t it in-to sorowe &amp; peyne, as &thorn;e gospel &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">of X.</NOTE> &thorn;e first part of holy writt schewi&thorn;; &amp; &thorn;erfore sei&thorn; ambrose &thorn;at alle men &thorn;at louen lesynges ben &thorn;e deuelis children. ion &thorn;e euaungelist sei&thorn; &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="marg">1 John ii. 21 (?).</NOTE> no lesyng is of god; &thorn;anne it is of &thorn;e deuyl si&thorn; he is fadir of lesyngis. &THORN;erfore &thorn;e wise man sei&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;e mou&thorn; &thorn;at lei&thorn; slee&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Wisdom i. 11.</NOTE> &thorn;e soule; &amp; a &thorn;ef is more wor&thorn;i to be suffrid &thorn;an &thorn;e lastynge of a lesyngmongere; &amp; dauid sei&thorn; &thorn;at god<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> schal dampne alle<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ecclus. xx. 27.</NOTE> men &thorn;at speken lesyngis, &amp; &thorn;e prophete zacharie sei&thorn; &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">Zech. v. 4.</NOTE> goddis curs come&thorn;<MILESTONE N="218" UNIT="page"> to &thorn;e hous of lieris, &amp; seynt austyn declare&thorn; in many bokis &thorn;at of<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> ei&yogh;te manere lesyngis &thorn;e leste is synne, &amp; who euere techi&thorn; &thorn;e contrarie disceyue&thorn; &thorn;e peple. but for &thorn;es veyn religious forsaken<NOTE PLACE="foot">forsakynge X.</NOTE> &thorn;e techynge &amp; lif of crist, mene persone in trinyte, &thorn;erfore &thorn;ei kunnen no mene bitwixe seiynge so&thorn;e in eche tyme &amp; bitwixe lesynge. sumtyme it harme&thorn; men to seie &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> so&thorn;e out of couenable tyme &amp; euere it harme&thorn; to lie, but sumtyme it profiti&thorn; to be stille &amp; abide a couenable tyme to speke, as dide crist &amp; his apostlis, &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;es veyn religious knowen &thorn;is &thorn;ei schulde haue no colour to make lesyngis. but &thorn;er is o gret cause whi &thorn;ei comenden so lesyngis. &thorn;ei maken profession to lyue bi labour of here hondis, bi benetis reulis &amp; fraunseis &amp; austynes, &amp; to be deed to &thorn;e world, &amp; to be ensaumple &amp; bok of wilful pouert, mekenesse &amp; grete penaunce &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> abstynence; &amp; now &thorn;ei ben turned to alle manere of schrewdnesse, harlotrie &amp; synne; &amp; 
<PB REF="00000337.tif" N="271"> &thorn;erfore &thorn;ei forsaken cristis scole of<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; AA.</NOTE> treu&thorn;e &amp; magnyfien &thorn;e deuelis scole of lesyngis; as &thorn;ei first token lesyng of lif, so &thorn;ei meyntenen now lesyng in word to coloure &thorn;er-bi here olde cursed lif, &thorn;at no man may bryngen hem out &thorn;er-of.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="4" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 4<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>See nowe &thorn;e &thorn;ridde heresie &thorn;at may hoold of olde synnys.<NOTE PLACE="foot">AA reads &thorn;at ma&thorn; hoord of olde synnes. I suspect both readings are corrupt.</NOTE> &THORN;es worldly prelatis &amp; peyntid religious, beried in here olde synne,<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> symonye, coueitise &amp; pride &amp; robberie, seyn &thorn;at it is a&yogh;enst charite to crie opynly here cursed disceitis to lordis &amp; comyn peple, &amp; namely in here absence. but see &thorn;e waiward|nesse &amp; cursednesse of &thorn;es deuelis ypocrisie &amp; sheld of synne. Almy&yogh;tty god, ful of charite, comaundi&thorn; to &thorn;e prophete ysaie<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isaiah lviii. 1.</NOTE> to crie &amp; cesse not, &amp; to schewe to his peple here grete synnes. synne of comyns is grete, synne of lordis &amp; my&yogh;tty men &amp; wise is more, but synne of prelatis is most, &amp; most blynde&thorn; &thorn;e peple. &THORN;an treue men ben holden bi goddis heste to crie most a&yogh;enst &thorn;e synne of prelatis, si&thorn; it is most &amp; harme&thorn; most &thorn;e peple. Also crist sei&thorn; who<NOTE PLACE="foot">wo AA.</NOTE> to hym &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke xvii. 1.</NOTE> sclaundri&thorn; a litel child of hem &thorn;at ben cristene. but prelatis of &thorn;e world &amp; peyntid foolis of religion, bi here opyn pride, coueitise, glotonye, lecherie, extorsions &amp; meyntenynge of synne, sclaundren most &thorn;e peple; for her-bi &thorn;ei ben bolde to walwe in synne preue &amp; apert; &thorn;anne a&yogh;enst &thorn;is synne schulden trewe men crie most. &para; Also god sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e prophete ezechiel &thorn;at &yogh;if a synful man lie in synne &amp; &thorn;e prophete<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ezekiel iii. 18.</NOTE> schewe hym not &thorn;e peril of his synne ne vengaunce of god, &thorn;er-fore &thorn;e synful man schal die in his synne &amp; &thorn;e prophete schal answere for hym, &amp; so bo&thorn;e schullen be dampnyd. &amp; si&thorn; eche prest is an angel &amp; prophete bi his presthod, <MILESTONE N="219" UNIT="page">as seynt gregory sei&thorn;, eche prest is in dette to telle synful men here synnes &thorn;at &thorn;ei may amende hem. &para; Also god sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000338.tif" N="272"> prophete ezechiel &thorn;at god ha&thorn; &yogh;ouen a prest to be a spie to<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ezekiel iii. 17.</NOTE> aspie &thorn;e sotil disceitis of &thorn;e fend &amp; warne &thorn;e peple of hem; but among alle &thorn;e helpis of &thorn;e fend a wickid prelat or a fals religious is &thorn;e moste. &THORN;anne a trewe prest owi&thorn; most to warne &thorn;e peple of hem. &amp; &thorn;erfore gregory sei&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> &amp; lawe of &thorn;e chirche &thorn;at no man harme&thorn; more cristene peple &thorn;anne he &thorn;at ha&thorn; name of ordre or holynesse &amp; &thorn;er-wi&thorn; lyue&thorn; wickidly; for his synne is taken to ensaumple of o&thorn;ere. &amp; &thorn;erfore sei&thorn; gregory in<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; X.</NOTE> his pastoralis &thorn;at prelatis ben wor&thorn;i to haue as many de&thorn;es as &thorn;ei senden ensaumples of synne to here sugetis &amp; to men &thorn;at comen after hem. and ysidre &amp; &thorn;e lawe sei&thorn; &thorn;at he &thorn;at consenti&thorn; &amp; fauoure&thorn; a man in synne schal be reproued bi most greuous reprofe. &amp; austyn sei&thorn; in &thorn;e lawe, &thorn;at a bischop &thorn;at consenti&thorn; to o&thorn;er mennus synnes schulde ra&thorn;ere be clepid an vnchastised hound &thorn;an a bischop. &amp; in token of &thorn;is crist purged &thorn;e temple &amp; noon o&thorn;ere place bi vengaunce bodily take in his owene persone. &amp; gregory &amp; o&thorn;ere seyntis seyn &thorn;at euele prestis ben cause of synne of &thorn;e peple. &THORN;erfore men schulden most ponysche &thorn;is most synne of prelatis &amp; religious &thorn;at is cause of o&thorn;ere &amp; of distruction of rewmes. Also crist sei&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel &thorn;at false prophetis &amp; false cristis<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. xxiv. 24.</NOTE> schullen ryse &amp; disceyue manye, &amp; biddi&thorn; vs bewar of hem &amp;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. vii. 16.</NOTE> flee hem &amp; knowe hem bi here werkis, &amp; telli&thorn; what condi|cions &amp; werkis &thorn;at &thorn;ei schullen haue. &THORN;anne &yogh;if prestis knowen &thorn;es false anticristis &amp; false prophetis bi tokenes of goddis lawe &amp; warne not &thorn;e peple of hem, &thorn;ei ben giltif of loos of cristene soulis. Also ion &thorn;e euaungelist sei&thorn;: &yogh;if ony<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 John iii. 17.</NOTE> man see his bro&thorn;er haue nede &amp; schitte his purs &amp; mercy fro hym, charite dwelli&thorn; not in hym; moche more &yogh;if prestis knowen &thorn;at mennus soulis ben in myschief of fals bileue brou&yogh;t in bi anticristis clerkis, &thorn;ei ben out of charite but &yogh;if &thorn;ei helpen hem out of &thorn;is myschief, si&thorn; &thorn;is<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> is most myschief in &thorn;is world. &amp; &thorn;erfore crist sei&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> in &thorn;e gospel &yogh;if it be<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke xiv. 5.</NOTE> mercy to helpe a beste falle in &thorn;e lake, moche more mercy is 
<PB REF="00000339.tif" N="273"> it to drawe mennus soulis out of errour &amp; peril of soule; &thorn;at is disceit in bileue brou&yogh;t in bi coueitouse clerkis &amp; luciferis children. but anticristis prelatis &amp; veyn religious seyn &thorn;at it is a&yogh;enst charite to nemne hem bi name in open sermon &amp; in here absence. trewe men seyn here &thorn;at ih&umacr; crist reproued scribis &amp; pharisees bi name &amp; in here absence, as &thorn;e gospel<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. xxiii.</NOTE> <NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke xi. 44.</NOTE> witnessi&thorn; in many placis, &amp; ei&yogh;te tymes bi name cursed hem &amp; cleped hem ypocritis, &amp; telde<NOTE PLACE="foot">telle X.</NOTE> to &thorn;e comune peple here <MILESTONE N="220" UNIT="page">false coueitise, ypocrisie &amp; pride. &amp; ih&umacr; clepid herode a fox in his absence &amp; in his presence spak no word to him, as<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke xiii. 32.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke xxiii. 8, 9.</NOTE> diuerse gospellis seyn. &amp; &yogh;it anticristis clerkis tellen false lesyngis in open sermons vpon certeyn personys &amp; in here absence, so &thorn;ei don openly a&yogh;enst here owene techynge; but anticrist wolde haue &thorn;is ende, &thorn;at in absence of his cursed worldly prelatis &amp; heretikis men schulden not reproue here cursed synnes for drede of lesyngis of charite &amp; for bacbitynge. &amp; anticrist make&thorn; hem so my&yogh;tty &thorn;at in here presence no man dar speke a&yogh;enst here opyn synnes but &yogh;if he wole be dede anoon. And so anticrist wolde &thorn;at no man schulde speke a&yogh;enst here synne in no manere, but suffre hem<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted X.</NOTE> to robbe &thorn;e peple &amp; brynge in heresies &amp; distroie cristen-dom. But o principal cause is whi &thorn;ei sey &thorn;us; &yogh;if it be charite to crie &thorn;us a&yogh;enst synnys of worldly prelatis &amp; veyn religious, si&thorn; many of hem ben kunnynge &amp; reulen lordis &amp; prelatis &amp; my&yogh;tty men in confession, &thorn;ei mosten warne hem &thorn;at clerkis schulden lyue in pouert &amp; mekenesse, &amp; not in worldly lordischipis ne in pompe &amp; vanyte as &thorn;ei now don; &amp; warne lordis &thorn;at &thorn;ei amende wickid clerkis of here opyn symonye &amp; robbynge of here tenauntis; &amp; warne lordis &amp; comyns hou god curse&thorn; to blissyngis &amp; preieris of men of cursed lif, &amp; &thorn;at here preiere turne in-to synne, as god hym self &amp; gregory &amp; &thorn;e lawe witnessen, &amp; hou prestis &amp; religious &thorn;at ben out of charite &amp; lyuen a&yogh;enst goddis comaundementis, as in glotonye, dronkenesse &amp; enemyte &amp; pride, stiren god bi here veyn 
<PB REF="00000340.tif" N="274"> preiynge to vengaunce ra&thorn;ere &thorn;an mercy. &amp; as austyn sei&thorn;, whateuere heryyngis of god here tounge blabere here lif blaspheme&thorn; god; &amp; as god sei&thorn; him self here preynge is cursed &amp; abhomynable. &amp; certis &thorn;anne schulde lordis knowe ypocrisie, heresie &amp; disceit of worldly prelatis &amp; feyned religious; &amp; &thorn;anne schulden cristene men wite &thorn;at who euere lyue&thorn; best preie&thorn; best; &amp; a symple pater noster of a plou&yogh;man &thorn;at his in charite is betre &thorn;an a &thorn;ousand massis of coueitouse prelatis &amp; veyn religious ful<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted AA.</NOTE> of coueitise &amp; pride &amp; fals flaterynge &amp; norischynge of synne. And for &thorn;es anticristis clerkis louen more here owene heynesse &amp; pride &amp; worldly ioie &amp; welfare &thorn;an cristis honour &amp; vertuous lif of cristene peple, &thorn;er-fore &thorn;ei ratellen &thorn;at it is a&yogh;enst charite to tellen opynly here cursed disceitis &amp; synnes; last lordis &amp; comyns taken fro hem here wast worldly goodis, &amp; constreynen hem to kepe mekenesse &amp; pouert &amp; pennaunce, as god techi&thorn; &amp; here owene profession. &THORN;us almy&yogh;tty <MILESTONE N="221" UNIT="page">god in trinyte distroie&thorn; &thorn;es &thorn;re nestis of anticrist &amp; his clerkis, &amp; stire&thorn; alle manere of men to meyntene &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of holy writt &amp; distroie lesyngis &amp; openly preche a&yogh;enst ypocrisie, heresie &amp; coueitise, bo&thorn;e in word &amp; dede, of alle euyl prelatis &amp; prestis &amp; peyntid reli|gious; for &thorn;an schal goode lif &amp; treu&thorn;e &amp; pees &amp; charite regne among cristene men. Ihesu crist for &thorn;in endeles mercy graunte vs &thorn;is ende. Amen.</P>


