<PB REF="00000413.tif" N="347">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q><MILESTONE N="124" UNIT="page">Sicut enim corpus sine spiritu moritur ita opera sine fide.</Q>
<BIBL>iacobi 3<SUP>o</SUP>.</BIBL>
<Q>fides sine operibus mortua est.<NOTE PLACE="foot">no text in CC.</NOTE></Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<DIV2 N="1" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>[Capitulum primum.]</HEAD>
<P>For it is seide in holdynge of oure haly-day &thorn;at we schulde ocupie &thorn;e tyme in prechynge <SUP>2</SUP>and preiynge<SUP>2</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">2_2 omitted CC.</NOTE> and deuoute herynge of &thorn;e lawe of god, and ouer &thorn;is<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted CC.</NOTE> many freris, as bastardis to goddis lawe, tellen iapes or lesyngis &amp; leeuen &thorn;e gospel; herfore schulden men lerne of &thorn;re good<NOTE PLACE="foot">goddis CC.</NOTE> vertues, &thorn;at &thorn;e gospel of poule clepi&thorn; fei&thorn;, hope, &amp; charite. ffei&thorn; is &thorn;e ground of alle o&thorn;er vertues; &amp; &thorn;er-fore poule clepi&thorn; it schelde of alle<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted CC.</NOTE> cristen men. ffor amonge sixe armures noon is more nedeful. but fei&thorn; may be taken on manye maneres. &para; Sum tyme fei&thorn; is clepid &thorn;e truthe &thorn;at men<NOTE PLACE="foot">we CC.</NOTE> trowen, &amp; so &thorn;er is a comune fei&thorn; to alle cristen men. &para; Sum tyme fei&thorn; is clepid vertu &thorn;at maken<NOTE PLACE="foot">maki&thorn; CC.</NOTE> trewe men, &amp; so eche trewe man ha&thorn; diuerse fei&thorn;. and sum tyme fei&thorn; is clepid oure trowynge in werkys. and by &thorn;es &thorn;re membris may<NOTE PLACE="foot">maist CC.</NOTE> &thorn;ou knowe goddis lawe &thorn;at speki&thorn; of fei&thorn; on<NOTE PLACE="foot">in CC.</NOTE> diuerse maneres. seynt poule clepi&thorn; fei&thorn; ground of goostly &thorn;ingis &thorn;at men schulden hope to haue in heuen; and here men <SUP>10</SUP>seen hem not, but trowen bi word of god, if &thorn;ei<SUP>10</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">10_10 omitted CC.</NOTE> seruen him treuly, to haue hem in heuen. and so specialye by fei&thorn; ben men made trewe <MILESTONE N="124b" UNIT="page">to god; and whos[o] fayli&thorn; in fei&thorn; he is fals to god, &amp; tristi&thorn; not to hijs treuthe, as he&thorn;en men don not. and herfore seith seynt poule &thorn;at cristen mennus fei&thorn; is mene of alle here gode werkis<NOTE PLACE="foot">werlkis Q, vertues CC.</NOTE> &thorn;at &thorn;ei here don. ffor seyntis by fei&thorn; discoumfiteden rewmes, &yogh;he &thorn;e rewmes of &thorn;e fende; &amp;<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Heb. xi. 33.]</NOTE> &thorn;at is more maistri &thorn;an wyn rewmes of men, for enemyes ben moo &amp; more koynte<NOTE PLACE="foot">queynt CC.</NOTE> in &thorn;er dedis bi wylis of here capteyns. 
<PB REF="00000414.tif" N="348"> <SUP>1</SUP>&amp; &thorn;us seyntis han wrou&yogh;t faire &amp; iust dedis,<SUP>1</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">1_1 omitted Q.</NOTE> for noman may laste in harde lif for god but if he haue fei&thorn;, bi whiche he lasti&thorn; so; ne noman may serue blis of god but if he haue fei&thorn;, bi whiche he serui&thorn; it; and schortly noman synni&thorn; a&yogh;enus god but if<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted Q.</NOTE> he fayle in fei&thorn;, &thorn;at groundi&thorn; goddis werkis. &para; as if &thorn;ou haddist a lettre &thorn;at &thorn;i kynge sent &thorn;ee seelid wi&thorn; hijs priuey seele, &amp; worschipid &thorn;ee myche &amp; hi&yogh;t &thorn;ee greet eritage to be at<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted Q.</NOTE> hijs retenu &amp; serue hym treuly, &thorn;ou woldest don of &thorn;in hoode and kisse hijs seel for hope of rewarde. god is miche more &thorn;an any lord of erthe; he sent a lettre to man by moyses hijs messangere, &thorn;at is more wor&thorn; &thorn;an any pope or cardynal. hijs lettre is hijs mawndementis, &amp; grace in moyses soule is hijs priue seel, better &thorn;en eny kyngis signe. &para; hijs seruice is li&yogh;t &amp; hijs eritage is myche, for it is &thorn;e blis of heuen lastynge <SUP>4</SUP>wi&thorn;-outen ende,<SUP>4</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">4_4 for euere CC.</NOTE> and here-of schulden men not fayle wi&thorn;-outen greet forfeture. take<NOTE PLACE="foot">Q. inserts we.</NOTE> hed to mennus fei&thorn; how bisily &thorn;ei traueylen for godes &amp; worschip of &thorn;e worlde, &amp; leeue traueyle to god, &amp; &thorn;ou mayst wel see &thorn;at fei&thorn; feili&thorn; hem.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 2<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>1<SUP>o</SUP>. But in &thorn;re maneres may mennus fei&thorn; fayle. Sum faylen in fei&thorn; for defaute of it; as<NOTE PLACE="foot">of KK.</NOTE> men &thorn;at trowen not to god &thorn;at he wil reward hem of &thorn;e blis of heuen for her trewe seruice. 2<SUP>o</SUP>. &para; sum men faylen in fei&thorn;, for it is so &thorn;ynne, &amp; <SUP>7</SUP>eke li&yogh;t<SUP>7</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">7_7 ee&thorn; CC.</NOTE> to perische wi&thorn; dart by sau&yogh;t of &thorn;in enemye; as men &thorn;at ben assaylid by her flesche or by &thorn;e world, or in lustis or in peynes &yogh;yuen it vp to<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted Q.</NOTE> sone, for litil trist &thorn;at &thorn;ei han in mede of her lord. and herfore crist often tymes reprouyde hys apostlis for litilnesse of her fei&thorn;, whan &thorn;ei fayleden to trist on hym. 3<SUP>o</SUP>. &para; and sum<NOTE PLACE="foot">summen CC.</NOTE> faylen in 
<PB REF="00000415.tif" N="349"> here fei&thorn; &thorn;at han her scheld holid,<NOTE PLACE="foot">holde Q.</NOTE> &amp; by spere of here enemye &thorn;ei ben often kylde; &amp; ben suche men &thorn;at trowen many trow&thorn;es, &amp; in sum <MILESTONE N="125" UNIT="page">&thorn;ei faylen as men out of here fei&thorn;; for as he &thorn;at byndi&thorn; hym to kepe goddis hestis mut kepe hem alle, as seynt Iames sei&thorn;, so he &thorn;at byndi&thorn; him to fei&thorn; of hijs<NOTE PLACE="marg">[James ii. 10.]</NOTE> god, mut kepe it al hoole stifly &amp; in ordre. ffor if &thorn;i schelde were at &thorn;i backe, &thorn;ou my&yogh;tist sone be kilde. for &thorn;e fendes of helle trowen alle &thorn;at we trowen, but hem failen charite to bynde her schelde in ordre, &amp; herfore ben &thorn;ei dampned by<NOTE PLACE="foot">for CC.</NOTE> her defourmed scheeld. &para; &amp; herfore schulden we trowe alle &thorn;e lawe of god, &amp; trowe &thorn;at it is trewe by euery part of it;<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;er-of CC.</NOTE> for if &thorn;ou trowe myche of it, &amp; trowist &thorn;at sum is fals, by &thorn;is hoole of &thorn;i schelde art &thorn;ou deed to god; &para; as freris &thorn;at trowen many articlis of &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted Q.</NOTE> treuthe &amp; faylen in &thorn;e treu&thorn;e of &thorn;e sacrid hoost, schal be dampnyd herfore But if &thorn;ei turne a&yogh;en &amp; trowe in wordes of crist, &thorn;at sei&thorn;: "&thorn;is is my bodye." but nowe freris trowen no&thorn;er &thorn;at &thorn;is oost is brede ne &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted CC.</NOTE> bodye of crist, ne ne&thorn;er of &thorn;is may be; but crist sei&thorn; surely:<NOTE PLACE="foot">so&thorn;li CC.</NOTE> "&thorn;is breed is my bodye." but hou ar &thorn;ei not heretikis &thorn;at trowen a&yogh;en crist here? &para; and &thorn;us eueryche man ha&thorn; a maner of fei&thorn;, syn eche man trowi&thorn; &thorn;at god &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">in Q.</NOTE> alle &thorn;ingis ben, but hijs fei&thorn; is rente in particuler erroures &thorn;at trowi&thorn; fals of &thorn;e fei&thorn;, by any part of it. and so oure good god byndi&thorn; vs not to euermore trowen &amp; specyaly eche article of &thorn;e treu&thorn;e, for sum ben so sutil &thorn;at first in blis of heuen seyntis schulen knowe hem &thorn;at now g[e]neraly trowen hem. for if &thorn;ou trowist in &thorn;i god, &thorn;at trow&thorn;e wil suffice &thorn;ee; but noman trowi&thorn; in god but he &thorn;at loue&thorn; him &amp; hope&thorn; by his good lif to haue <SUP>8</SUP>&thorn;e blis of heuen.<SUP>8</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">8_8 blisse of god CC.</NOTE></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="3" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>[Capitulum 3<SUP>m.</SUP>]</HEAD>
<P>HOpe is &thorn;e secounde vertu &thorn;at god himself axi&thorn;, &amp; is ful diuerse fro fei&thorn; &thorn;at we han spokun of. ffor fei&thorn; is of &thorn;ingus &thorn;at was &amp; ben &amp; schul be, but hope is al only of &thorn;inges &thorn;at 
<PB REF="00000416.tif" N="350"> ben to come. as we trowen &thorn;at god made &thorn;e world of nou&yogh;t, &amp; we trowen &thorn;at crist is now bodily in heuen, &amp; schal euermore be after &thorn;e <SUP>1</SUP>day of<SUP>1</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">1_1 omitted CC.</NOTE> dom. &para; also fei&thorn; is bo&thorn;e of gode &thorn;ing &amp; euyl, bo&thorn;e of him &thorn;at ha&thorn; fei&thorn; &amp; of o&thorn;er creaturis, but hope is al only of hym &thorn;at ha&thorn; hope and only of good &thorn;inge in &thorn;e blis of heuen. as we trowen &thorn;at many men schul <MILESTONE N="125b" UNIT="page">be dampned in helle, &amp; &thorn;at many o&thorn;ur schul be saued in heuen; but no&thorn;ur we hopen &thorn;is damp|nacion ne &thorn;is saluacion, for we hopen al only &thorn;at towchi&thorn; oure owne blis. and so trowthe of cristen men putti&thorn; hem owte of dowte, &amp; maki&thorn; hem so surely trowe<NOTE PLACE="foot">thorowe Q.</NOTE> here bileue, &thorn;at &thorn;ei schulden stonde for &thorn;is treu&thorn;e, to dee&thorn; of here bodye. &para; but so it is not of hope if we looken wel, as ne&thorn;er we witen ne we trowe now to be sauyd, &amp; &yogh;hit we hopen it wi&thorn;-outen ony dowte. and so hope is werke of soule bi-ne&thorn;e oure bileue, &amp; so by-nethe knowynge but a-bouen doutinge. and so hope of er&thorn;ely &thorn;inge is not vertu of hope, but comunely it smacchi&thorn; synne, for it letti&thorn; hope of heuen. and so it is all diuerse to hope and to trowe; but &thorn;is is a sutil mater to clerkis for to knowe, but comune <SUP>3</SUP>sentence here-of<SUP>3</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">3_3 speche CC.</NOTE> suffici&thorn; to o&thorn;ure men.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="4" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 4<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>[B]vt si&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted CC.</NOTE> philosopheres seyn &thorn;at contraries han oon lore, fei&thorn; and hope techen vs to knowe contraries of hem. ffei&thorn; ha&thorn; in fidelite contrarie to him, and hope ha&thorn; desperacion as his contrarie. and as fei&thorn; is ground of alle o&thorn;ur vertues, so in-fidelite is ground of alle o&thorn;ur synnes. &para; and herfor<NOTE PLACE="marg">[John xvi. 8.]</NOTE> sei&thorn; crist &thorn;at god schal reproue &thorn;e worlde first of &thorn;is synne, for it groundi&thorn; alle o&thorn;ere. <NOTE PLACE="foot">Q inserts for.</NOTE>wan-hope of men is a greet synne, for noman is dampned wi&thorn;-outen &thorn;is wanhope. for he &thorn;at lasti&thorn; in &thorn;is<NOTE PLACE="foot">hys Q.</NOTE> synne to his lyues ende, and ha&thorn;e no sorowe 
<PB REF="00000417.tif" N="351"> of hijs synne ne hope to haue for&yogh;yu[n]es, he synne&thorn; a&yogh;en &thorn;e holy goost; &thorn;at neuer schal be for&yogh;ifen him, no&thorn;er in &thorn;is worlde ne in &thorn;e to&thorn;ur, as crist him silf sei&thorn;. and many &thorn;er<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Matt. xii. 31.]</NOTE> ben &thorn;at synnen in &thorn;is synne longe bifore &thorn;ei dien. &para; but &thorn;anne it lasti&thorn; euere, as eche man &thorn;at god knowi&thorn; to be dampned in helle, beri&thorn; euere-lastinge synne a&yogh;en &thorn;e holy gost; for as &thorn;e holy gost is &thorn;e laste persone of god, after whom come&thorn; noon o&thorn;ur, so it is of &thorn;is synne. ffor no <MILESTONE N="126" UNIT="page">man may synne after &thorn;is last<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted Q.</NOTE> synne. &para; and so by two weyes fallen men in despeyre. 1<SUP>o</SUP>. Sum for &thorn;ei trowen not in &thorn;e mercy of god; &amp; &thorn;es ben cayms childire &amp; seyn her synne is more &thorn;an her dissert is to serue blis or ellis goddis mercy. 2<SUP>o</SUP>. and sum synnen in dispeyre a&yogh;enus ri&yogh;twisnes<NOTE PLACE="foot">ri&yogh;tfulnesse CC.</NOTE> of god; as &thorn;es &thorn;at seyn in her lif: "late me synne ynowe, for god wole neuere lese &thorn;at he ha&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted Q.</NOTE> dere bou&yogh;t." and so alle &thorn;at schul ben dampned ben euere more in synnyng a&yogh;en &thorn;e holy gost, &amp; euere in despeyringe. &para; as if a man drof continuely in-to &thorn;e er&thorn;e a stake, til he were in dispeire &thorn;at he my&yogh;t drawe it vp. &thorn;e stake is &thorn;e synne hardud in mannus hert; &thorn;e malle &thorn;at he driue&thorn; it wi&thorn; is newe rehersynge of synne; and suche at &thorn;e ende of her lif lacken power &amp; grace to trist in helpe of &thorn;er god and hope to be sauyd.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="5" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>[Capitulum 5<SUP>m.</SUP>]</HEAD>
<P>[&THORN;]E &thorn;ridde vertu of god is loue or<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; Q.</NOTE> charite, and it ha&thorn; two braunchis, as loue of god &amp; loue of man. &amp; beste mene to kepe &thorn;is loue were man forto lerne &amp; loue forto kepe two tables of goddis lawes,<NOTE PLACE="foot">hestis CC.</NOTE> for bi &thorn;es &amp; ellis not kepi&thorn; man him in charite. and &thorn;is vertu clo&thorn;is man at domus-day wi&thorn; bride-clo&thorn;is, &amp; &thorn;is clo&thorn;e may neuere be lost in &thorn;is world ne in &thorn;e to&thorn;ure. ffor noman may come to heuene but he haue &thorn;is clo&thorn;inge, ne no man may haue &thorn;is clothe, but if he come to heuen; &amp; so men &thorn;at schulen be dampned han but 
<PB REF="00000418.tif" N="352"> feyned charite. But lyue wele after goddis lawe &amp; hope to haue &thorn;is<NOTE PLACE="foot">CC. inserts last.</NOTE> loue, for no man schal knowe ne trowe to haue it but if god wole telle him priueyly. &para; and so freris, &thorn;at louen more her habite &thorn;at &thorn;ei han ordeyned hem &thorn;an &thorn;e clo&thorn;e of charite &thorn;at god ha&thorn; schapen his sones, ben yuel disposid to haue &thorn;is<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;e Q.</NOTE> clo&thorn;e of charite; Si&thorn; &thorn;er loue is turned amys to charge more here habite, to lesyn it or leeuen it, to clo&thorn;e &thorn;er|wi&thorn; &thorn;er bodye, &thorn;an to lese &thorn;is charite to clo&thorn;e &thorn;er-wi&thorn; &thorn;er soule; for often &thorn;ei lese charite in presens of man, but if &thorn;ei losten &thorn;is habite &thorn;us, as &thorn;ei falsly feynen, &thorn;ei were opyn apostates and losten &thorn;e luf of god, for as &thorn;ei feynen falsly god <MILESTONE N="126b" UNIT="page">loue&thorn; more &thorn;is clo&thorn;inge &thorn;an clo&thorn;inge of &thorn;er soule wi&thorn; &thorn;is clo&thorn;e of charite; and &thorn;is is open heresie by many kyn skylles. but here men douten comunly where men schuld loue &thorn;es heretikys, but it is no drede &thorn;at ne men schulde loue &thorn;er kynde &amp; hate &thorn;e same kynde in &thorn;at &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben so yuel, and so &thorn;e persones bi hem-silf schulden be loued in charite, &amp; here synnes by hemsilf schulden men hate for goddis loue.<NOTE PLACE="foot">sake CC.</NOTE> ffor he is not frend to crist &thorn;at loue&thorn; &thorn;us hijs enemye; and &thorn;us he is frend to &thorn;e frere &thorn;at hati&thorn; &thorn;us his synne &amp; worchi&thorn; to distrie it &amp; purge him &thorn;er-fro. &para; and &thorn;is moue&thorn; manye men to speke of &thorn;re heresies &thorn;at many freres be smyttid inne, &amp; contrarien &thorn;es &thorn;re<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted Q.</NOTE> vertues. ffor who my&yogh;t more contrarie fei&thorn; &thorn;an sey &thorn;at crist sei&thorn; fals whan he sei&thorn; &thorn;at "&thorn;is brede is myn owne bodye," for &thorn;is may ne&thorn;er be<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted Q.</NOTE> brede ne &thorn;e bodi of crist, but it is accident or nou&yogh;t, as freres feynen falsly. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei chesen hem a place to falsen crist in hijs visage, and ierom wi&thorn; o&thorn;ur seyntis &thorn;at tellen &thorn;is wit of crist. ffreres seyn priueyly &thorn;at &thorn;ei spake here eresie, si&thorn;en anticrist &thorn;er mayster sei&thorn; euen &thorn;e contrarie. &para; &thorn;e secounde vertu of &thorn;es &thorn;re <SUP>6</SUP>many freres reuersen,<SUP>6</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">6_6 moue&thorn; freres to reuersen Q.</NOTE> for crist tau&yogh;t in hijs lawe &thorn;at men schulde not begge, but holde euen his ordre, &amp; &thorn;ei schulde come to heuen; &thorn;es<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;e Q.</NOTE> freres seyn &thorn;e contrarie, &amp; grownden 
<PB REF="00000419.tif" N="353"> hem an ordre of &thorn;er wilful beggyng, bi men &thorn;at han no nede; and herbi schulde men hope to sitt hye in heuen, for, as &thorn;ei lien falsly, crist beggid<NOTE PLACE="foot">CC. inserts 'not.'</NOTE> &thorn;us. &para; &thorn;e &thorn;ridde of &thorn;es vertues is contraried bi freres, si&thorn;en it is no charite to falsly passe crist. for crist sei&thorn; to hijs cosyns &thorn;at by hijs manhed he had<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Matt. xx. 23.]</NOTE> no power to &yogh;yue hem leue to sit on hijs ri&yogh;t<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted CC.</NOTE> side, but to &thorn;e godhed in hijs fadure is propred &thorn;is power; but freres seyn opunly by letteres of here fraternite &thorn;at &thorn;ei &yogh;yuen &thorn;er bre&thorn;eren leue to haue part of &thorn;er blis; and &thorn;is my&yogh;t &thorn;ei not do but if &thorn;ei &yogh;ouen men leue to sitt on &thorn;e ri&yogh;t hond of crist as if &thorn;ei passed him. &amp; &thorn;is sownes not charite but luciferes pride.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="6" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>[Capitulum 6<SUP>m.</SUP>]</HEAD>
<P><MILESTONE N="127" UNIT="page">Bvt si&thorn; clo&thorn;inge of &thorn;is loue is myche loued of god, &amp; more wor&thorn;e to man &thorn;an al &thorn;is worldes richessis, man schuld ful bisily knowe propirtees of &thorn;is loue. but poule, &thorn;at was rauesched vnto &thorn;e &thorn;rid heuen, &amp; herde derne wordes of god,<NOTE PLACE="marg">[2 Cor. xii. 2.]</NOTE> &thorn;at ben not here leful vs forto speke, telli&thorn; sixtene propirtes<NOTE PLACE="marg">[1 Cor. xiii. 4.]</NOTE> &thorn;at suen &thorn;is charite. &thorn;e first is &thorn;at charite is patient of wronges. for al oure charite mut be ensaumpled of crist; but crist was so patient, as seynt petre sei&thorn;, &thorn;at whan he was<NOTE PLACE="marg">[1 Peter ii. 23.]</NOTE> mys-said he cursid not a&yogh;en, ne when he suffrid wronges he manassid not a&yogh;en. O what charite ha&thorn; he to suffre wronge for cristis loue &thorn;at wol not suffre a li&yogh;t word, but &yogh;eld a worse a&yogh;en? &para; &thorn;e secounde propirte is &thorn;is: &thorn;at charite is benyngne. for it is not ynow to suffre, for so don &thorn;efis, but do good in soule a&yogh;enus yuel suffrid; for &thorn;at is good loue of &thorn;e fire of charite, &amp; is clepid benignite by propirte of word. and here-fore clerkis seyn &thorn;at &thorn;er ben &thorn;ree lawes; &thorn;e first is lawe of oure good<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted Q.</NOTE> god to do good for yuyl; &thorn;e to&thorn;ure is lawe of &thorn;e worlde, to do good for good &amp; yuel for yuel, as mannus maner is; &thorn;e &thorn;rid is &thorn;e deuelis lawe, to do yuel for good, &amp; &thorn;is is maner of men whan &thorn;ei ben turned to deuelis. &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000420.tif" N="354"> &thorn;rid propirte &thorn;at sue&thorn; &thorn;is secounde is &thorn;at charite ha&thorn;e noon enuye to noon kyn &thorn;inge, for it loue&thorn; wel god &amp; alle goddis creatures. &para; &thorn;e four&thorn;e propirte &thorn;at sue&thorn; of &thorn;is riche vertu is &thorn;at charite wi&thorn;-outen for&thorn;e wirchi&thorn; not schrewidly for as &thorn;is first &yogh;ock bigynni&thorn; wi&thorn; paciens, &amp; si&thorn;en goi&thorn; into worchinge of a mannus soule, so mut &thorn;is o&thorn;ur &yogh;oc forsake yuel wi&thorn;-inne, &amp; <SUP>1</SUP>also wi&thorn;-oute<SUP>1</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">1_1 si&thorn; yuel dede wi&thorn;oute CC.</NOTE> bi ordre of god. &thorn;e fyue&thorn; maner of charite stonde&thorn; in &thorn;is, &thorn;at it bolne&thorn; not wi&thorn; pride, syn it is &thorn;us patient. &amp; &thorn;e sixte sue&thorn; here-of, &thorn;at it coueiti&thorn; not worldly worschip; for al worschipe of charite sche putti&thorn; oonly<NOTE PLACE="foot">hoolly CC.</NOTE> in god. &thorn;e seue&thorn; condicion &thorn;at sue&thorn; &thorn;is<NOTE PLACE="foot">in Q.</NOTE> charite is &thorn;at it seki&thorn; not propre godes to hir silf, but seki&thorn; worschip to god &amp; profyte to his chirche. &para; &thorn;e ey&yogh;t propirte of charite stondi&thorn; in &thorn;is, &thorn;at charite wrathi&thorn; &thorn;er<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted Q.</NOTE> not al if it suffre wronge, and &thorn;erfore it is li&yogh;t to men to stande with pees &amp; charite. &thorn;e neynt propirte of charite is deppere &thorn;an &thorn;es o&thorn;ere, &thorn;at it &thorn;enki&thorn; not yuel, for siche &thorn;ou&yogh;t turne&thorn; to yuel; as iob maad couenaunt to &thorn;enke not on a virgyne. &para; &thorn;e <MILESTONE N="127b" UNIT="page">tente&thorn; propirte &thorn;at sui&thorn; &thorn;is vertu of charite is &thorn;at sche ioyethe not of wickidnesse, as aungelus in heuen ioyen of payn of fendis but not of here wickidnesse. &amp; &thorn;er-fore &thorn;is condicion sue&thorn; after charite, &thorn;at it ioye&thorn; wi&thorn; god of trow&thorn;e &thorn;at he loue&thorn;. &para; &thorn;e twel&thorn;e condicion &thorn;at sue&thorn; &thorn;is charite is &thorn;at sche take&thorn; mekely what euere &thorn;ing &thorn;at come&thorn; hir to. &thorn;e &thorn;rittente condicioun stondi&thorn; in &thorn;is, &thorn;at charite trowi&thorn; al &thorn;at euere god sei&thorn;; and si&thorn; no &thorn;inge is good but &thorn;at god sei&thorn;, charite trowi&thorn; alle good &thorn;ing,<NOTE PLACE="foot">omitted Q.</NOTE> &yogh;he profyte of synnes. ffor men &thorn;at dreden god, if &thorn;ei fallen in synne, &thorn;ei ben more ware &thorn;at &thorn;ei synnen not eft,<NOTE PLACE="foot">ofte Q.</NOTE> &amp; &thorn;anken more god of hijs gracious helpe, &amp; alle medeful dedis haue &thorn;ei part off. &para; &thorn;e fourtene&thorn; condicion &thorn;at sue&thorn; after charite stondi&thorn; in &thorn;is poynt, &thorn;at sche hopi&thorn; alle &thorn;inge turne&thorn; to good of goddis childur &thorn;at dreden him in loue. &thorn;e fiftente condicion 
<PB REF="00000421.tif" N="355"> &thorn;at sue&thorn; &thorn;is charite is &thorn;at sche susteyne&thorn; wi&thorn; wille alle harmes &thorn;at come&thorn;, &yogh;he<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;hit Q.</NOTE> sche is not discounfortid if goddis helpe bidi&thorn; longe. &para; and so &thorn;e laste condicion &thorn;at sue&thorn; &thorn;is blessid vertu is &thorn;at sche falli&thorn; neuer doun, but lasti&thorn; for&thorn;e for euere in &thorn;is world &amp; in &thorn;e to&thorn;ure, as loue of god faili&thorn; not. &amp; if a man knewe<NOTE PLACE="foot">koude CC.</NOTE> no more of goddis lawe but &thorn;ise sixtene condicions &amp; bisyede him to kepe hem, he my&yogh;t li&yogh;tly come to heuen &amp; wite who went amys.<NOTE PLACE="foot">only in CC.</NOTE></P>
<TRAILER>Expliciunt ffei&thorn; hope &amp; charite.</TRAILER>


</DIV2>
