<DIV2 N="1" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>[Capitulum primum.]</HEAD>
<P>&thorn;er ben two offisis &thorn;at fallen to purging of &thorn;e chirche. &thorn;e toon falli&thorn; to kny&yogh;tis &amp; kyngis wi&thorn; o&thorn;ere lordis, &thorn;at shulde defende wi&thorn; streng&thorn;e &thorn;e lawe of crist in his boundis; &amp; in &thorn;is seruyss &thorn;ei holden of crist al &thorn;e lordchip &thorn;at &thorn;ey han, &amp; herfore &thorn;ey shulden be war &thorn;at &thorn;ey forfete not a&yogh;enus &thorn;is lord. for &yogh;if &thorn;ei ceessen of &thorn;is seruyss bi lesse tyme or more bi ony slou&thorn;e, god may not for&yogh;ete &thorn;is trespas but punysshe it in his tyme; &amp; bi &thorn;is cause ben lordchipis chaungid, nou encreessid &amp; nou destried. &THORN;e to&thorn;er offiss to purge &thorn;e chirche falli&thorn; to prestis, &thorn;at crist ha&thorn; ordeyned to telle generally his lawe to lordis &amp; comyns what &thorn;ey shulden do, &amp; to stonde for goddis lawe to bodily de&thorn; &yogh;if it be nede. &amp; &thorn;us fi&yogh;ting of &thorn;es cristis kny&yogh;tis stondi&thorn; in paciense &amp; passioun. &amp; &thorn;us it is to saye shortly heere of &thorn;e offiss of goostly herde. &THORN;er ben two &thorn;ingis &thorn;at fallen to &thorn;e offiss of &thorn;is herde, &amp; &thorn;es ben hoolynesse of lif &amp; hoolsumnesse of his lore. A curat shulde preche to &thorn;e puple treu&thorn;is of goddis lawe &thorn;at euere ben grene, for &thorn;anne he ledi&thorn; his sheep wel in hool pasture &thorn;at wole not rote; &amp; for hoolynesse of lif techi&thorn; rude men by groos ensaumple, it is nede-ful to &thorn;is herde &amp; to his floc to lyue hoolily. &amp; herfore seyen hooly doctours &thorn;at &thorn;e lif of &thorn;is herde is a bok to lewyd men, &amp; a marke &thorn;at &thorn;ei shulden sue aftir. &amp; herfore si&thorn;en crist is &thorn;e beste herde &thorn;at may not fayle in &thorn;is offiss, no cristenman shulde sue his prelate but in as myche as he sue&thorn; crist. &amp; &thorn;us an herde shulde passe in vertues his floc as &thorn;e herde passi&thorn; his sheep, for he shulde be so sad in vertues &amp; in suynge of &thorn;e firste herde &thorn;at ne&thorn;er for coueytise ne fauoure ne drede of de&thorn; he shulde not fayle; for &thorn;is herdis offiss is &thorn;e hierste &thorn;at criste &yogh;yue&thorn; to ony man. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ey moten lerne &thorn;e craft of loue, to loue crist bifore alle o&thorn;ere, &amp; &thorn;anne a man 
<PB REF="00000475.tif" N="409"> loue&thorn; &thorn;us crist whanne he kepi&thorn; wel his biddingis; &amp; ellis he is not wor&thorn;y to haue siche a maystir, as &thorn;e gospel sei&thorn;. &amp;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. x. [37.]</NOTE> &thorn;us &thorn;is herde mut nedis knowe bileue, hope &amp; charite. For &yogh;if he fayle in ony of &thorn;ese he techi&thorn; not wel his floc, <MILESTONE N="1b" UNIT="page">ne putti&thorn; his lif for his sheep a&yogh;enus &thorn;e wolf whanne myster is.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>[Capitulum] 2<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>si&thorn;en a prest shulde be a mene bitwixe god &amp; &thorn;e puple &amp; teche &thorn;e puple &thorn;e wille of god, it is knowen &thorn;ing bi skile &thorn;at whanne he erri&thorn; in &thorn;is offiss he sinne&thorn; more &thorn;an o&thorn;ere men; &amp; &thorn;us synnede scarioth more &thorn;an o&thorn;ere comyn men. it is knowun bi bileue &thorn;at a man shulde not synne for to wynne al &thorn;is world, were it neuere so li&yogh;t a synne; for ellis &thorn;is man synnede wel, &amp; synnede not in synnynge &thorn;us. &amp; &thorn;us a man shulde not synne al &yogh;if god bade hym synne, but god may not bidde man synne, as god hym silf may not synne. &amp; si&thorn;en it mut nedis be synne to fayle fro suynge of crist, man shulde not fayle in &thorn;is suyt for god ne for ony creature. &amp; it is knowun bi opyn skile &thorn;at it mut nedis be synne to fayle in suynge of crist for many resouns &thorn;er ben herof. for suynge of crist in vertues is so good &thorn;at it may not be yuel; and it is so li&yogh;t a suyt &thorn;at no man is excuside bi noun power; &amp; crist chees siche a lif to teche men to sue hym, &amp; no man may come to heuene but &yogh;if he sue crist on sum maner. &amp; &thorn;us al synne of man-kynde stondi&thorn; in defaute of suyt of crist; &amp; &thorn;us si&thorn; ech cristenman ha&thorn; power of god to sue crist, he dissusi&thorn; to myche his power &thorn;at vsi&thorn; it not to sue &thorn;is lord. &amp; heere men shulden be ware wi&thorn; &thorn;e fend &thorn;at &thorn;ey be not blyndid bi hym to seye who may be euene wi&thorn; crist, &amp; &thorn;us to allegge crist is but foly. &THORN;is is &thorn;e lewiderste fendis skile &thorn;at euere cam out of his leesingis; for men wolen not be euene wi&thorn; crist ne go bifore hym as petre wolde, but sue crist neer or ferrere, &amp; ellis &thorn;ey moten go amys. &amp; &thorn;is may ech man do o&thorn;er more ny&yogh; or ferrere. &amp; &thorn;us summe gon bifore crist &amp; summe contrarien hym in &thorn;er weye. &THORN;es men 
<PB REF="00000476.tif" N="410"> gon bifore crist &thorn;at feynen hem an hid power for pride or for couetyise, al&yogh;if &thorn;is power be not groundid in crist, &amp; &thorn;us don prelatis nou-a-dayes in asoyling &amp; priuylegies. &amp; o&thorn;ere men gon bifore crist &thorn;at trowen &thorn;at &thorn;ey ben mouyd bi pite to stire a man to do a dede, &amp; &yogh;it it is a&yogh;enus goddis wille; &amp; &thorn;us it semy&thorn; &thorn;at petre was mouyd to lette crist to die for men, &amp; herfore was petre clepid satanas &amp; bedun go bihynde crist; for no drede petre hadde be dampnyd &yogh;if he hadde not sorowid for &thorn;is synne. &THORN;es men reuersen crist bi his godhed &amp; his manhed &thorn;at han power of cristis godhed to do a &thorn;ing vpon resoun, &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ey letten to do it, doynge <MILESTONE N="2" UNIT="page">&thorn;e contrarye her-of. &amp; si&thorn;en god is &thorn;e firste resoun many men in omissioun synne a&yogh;enus crist, &amp; &thorn;ey moten nedis contrarie to hym. &amp; &thorn;us men of &thorn;es newe ordris reuersen crist as satanas, for &thorn;ey leeuen &thorn;at crist biddi&thorn; &amp; don newe biddingis vndir his power.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="3" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 3<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>of &thorn;is goldun bileue shulden prestis take &thorn;is reule of crist &thorn;at poul &yogh;yue&thorn; to tymothe, &amp; in hym to alle cristen<NOTE PLACE="marg">[1 Tim. vi. 8.]</NOTE> prestis: "hauynge fode &amp; o&thorn;ere &thorn;yngis bi whiche we ben skilefuly keuerid, be we payed wi&thorn; &thorn;es two," &amp; do we werk &thorn;at prestis shulden do. for ech prest shulde sue crist bi &thorn;e power &thorn;at crist ha&thorn; &yogh;ouyn hym; but ech prest may li&yogh;tly &thorn;us sue crist &yogh;if he lette not hym silf, &amp; &thorn;us synne excusi&thorn; hym not &thorn;at he synne not in &thorn;is noun suyt. &amp; &thorn;us crist lyuede a comyn lif &thorn;at ech cristenman may sue, &amp; noon of hem may be euene wi&thorn; crist, for nedis cristis godhed mut be bifore. &amp; &thorn;us ech cristenman may renne faste &amp; he shal ay fynde crist bifore hym; be he pore, be he riche, be he feble, be he witty, he may not fayle in his good wille &thorn;at ne he shal sue crist in &thorn;at. &amp; &thorn;us shal ech cristenman do, be he herde, be he sheep; but &yogh;if he take to be herde he shulde passe in witty suyng; &amp; &thorn;is reule &thorn;at poul &yogh;yueth mouyde apostlis &amp; o&thorn;ere prestis, til &thorn;at &thorn;e chirche of rome was dowid, to sue 
<PB REF="00000477.tif" N="411"> crist in &thorn;e gospels pouert, &amp; what &thorn;ing &thorn;at a prest ha&thorn; more he ha&thorn; his meede heere but not in heuene. &amp; &thorn;us poul vndirstondi&thorn; bi fode, mete &amp; drynk &thorn;at ben couenable to do betere &thorn;e seruyss of god; &amp; not lustly deyntees of prestis, ne&thorn;er to make &thorn;er body wantoun, ne gete hem worchip in ouer-greet meyne. two maner of hiling ben nedeful to prestis &thorn;at shulden do &thorn;is offiss; hiling of resonable clo&thorn;is, &amp; eke hiling of skileful housis. but be war heere &thorn;at synne of curatis brou&yogh;t in bi custom in &thorn;es two be not cause of &thorn;y synne to spende to myche in o&thorn;er of hem. &amp; si&thorn;en we shulden be pilgryms heere &amp; rowe wisely in &thorn;is boot to heuene, &yogh;if we passen &thorn;is fode &amp; hiling we chargen vs silf wi&thorn;|outen fruyt. &amp; &thorn;us prestis shulden be war &thorn;at coueytise ouer &thorn;is reule of crist lette not prestis to holde poulis reule, for &thorn;anne &thorn;ey synne in auerise. &amp; &thorn;us prestis may bi &thorn;re enemyes be temptid to breke &thorn;is apostlis reule; bi &thorn;er fleys, &amp; bi &thorn;e world, &amp; bi pride of &thorn;e fend. &THORN;at prest &thorn;at fedi&thorn; <MILESTONE N="2b" UNIT="page">hym silf to lustfuly to plese his fleys mut passe resoun in his dispensis; &amp; &thorn;at bringi&thorn; in robbing of curatis. &amp; &thorn;at prest synne&thorn; bi &thorn;e world &thorn;at passi&thorn; &thorn;is reule in to greet meyne or in to costly dispensis, &amp; sei&thorn; &thorn;e world nedi&thorn; herto. he synne&thorn; bi tempting of &thorn;e fend, &thorn;at bi pride or worldly worchip coueyti&thorn; more of siche godis &thorn;an resoun axi&thorn; to his offiss. &amp; &thorn;us onest pouert is best, moost sure, &amp; moost li&yogh;t to prestis heere; &amp; bi &thorn;is cause crist helde &thorn;is meene bitwixe begging &amp; worldly richees. &amp; heere ben &thorn;re excusaciouns &thorn;at ben seyd to excuse prestis synne. summe seyen &thorn;at for worldly worchip &thorn;ey moten passe &thorn;is reule of poul; &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei desiren more worldly worchip &thorn;an worchip of heuene in staat of blis bi &thorn;e holding of goddis reule. but where is more foly of man? &THORN;e secound excusacioun of synne sei&thorn; &thorn;at prestis moten do bodily almes, &amp; algatis helpe folc of &thorn;er kynd. but &thorn;is telli&thorn; an opyn blasfemye, &thorn;at crist was vnwiss in &thorn;is, si&thorn; he vside not &thorn;is in word ne dede, for goostly almes is myche betere &thorn;an deling of &thorn;is worldly drit. &THORN;e &thorn;ridde excusacioun of prestis is &thorn;at &thorn;ey moten nedis gedere godis for sekenesse &amp; eelde 
<PB REF="00000478.tif" N="412"> &amp; o&thorn;ere caassis to helpe hem in tyme of nede. &THORN;is is a&yogh;enus &thorn;e lore of crist, to triste in help of worldly muc, &amp; leeue to triste in god almy&yogh;ti for keping of his comaundementis.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="4" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 4<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>but heere anticrist argue&thorn; a&yogh;enus &thorn;is lawe of god &thorn;at bi &thorn;is same skile lordis &thorn;at lyuen worldlily shulden holde hem payed of &thorn;er fode &amp; &thorn;er hiling, but where were &thorn;anne &thorn;er lordchip &amp; &thorn;er tresour to helpe reumes?</P>
<P>many siche ape resouns han men herd a&yogh;enus crist, as &yogh;if an ape wolde argue &thorn;us: "a mannus eye is in his hed of sutil fode &amp; vnhilid, bi &thorn;e same skile shulde his foot." &THORN;is fend mut lerne arguyng, &amp; wite to what ende god ha&thorn; ordeyned dyuerse lemes of hooly chirche, &amp; &thorn;eraftir shapun hem godis. prestis shulden be in &thorn;e hierste staat, &amp; sue crist in sure pouert. kyngis &amp; lordis shulden be byne&thorn;e &amp; shewe &thorn;e godhed of crist; &amp; so hem falli&thorn; to &thorn;er offyss to haue lordchip &amp; worldly richees, &amp; bi &thorn;is shulden &thorn;ey shewe cristis power in his godhed. &amp; cristis prestis shulden be pore &amp; pacient bi cristis manhed. But hou ben worldly godis nedeful to kepe siche offiss of <MILESTONE N="3" UNIT="page">prestis? clerkis shulden shame of siche resouns, &amp; algatis hou &thorn;ey passen crist in taking of worldly lordchipis &amp; hauyng of er&thorn;ely tresour, &thorn;at shulden be proper to worldly men. crist wolde not in his persone ne in his apostlis haue siche richessis, but kepte lordchipis &amp; worldly godis to kyngis &amp; lordis of &thorn;is world; &amp; certis &thorn;ese axen bodily trauel &amp; my&yogh;ti defense of goddis lawe &thorn;at shulden not acorde to prestis; wherfore shulden &thorn;ei haue &thorn;es godis? &amp; so worldly lordis shulden knowe wherfore god &yogh;af hem &thorn;es godis, &amp; serue god bi &thorn;es godis in my&yogh;ti defending of his lawe; for wite &thorn;ey wel &thorn;at for &thorn;is defaute may &thorn;ey be blamed of &thorn;is cheef lord. prestis shulden not lette &thorn;is ordenaunse, but helpe &thorn;at it were kept of &thorn;e chirche; for so dide crist in word &amp; dede, why shulden not his prestis do so? auerous gedering of tresour is to blame in ech staat.
<PB REF="00000479.tif" N="413"></P>
<P>&YOGH;it argue&thorn; anticrist a&yogh;enus &thorn;is lawe &thorn;at poul ha&thorn; teld; apostlis as &thorn;ei weren tau&yogh;t of god chesiden to hem seuene dekenes to serue folc at &thorn;er mete &amp; to do bodily almes. Why shulden not prestis do so, si&thorn;en &thorn;ei kunnen wiseliere do &thorn;is?<NOTE PLACE="marg">Acts [vi.]</NOTE> but heere men seyen as bifore &thorn;at &thorn;is smacchi&thorn; an ape skile. for we graunten to &thorn;es spekeris &thorn;at bo&thorn;e lowere prestis &amp; dekenes may serue trewe men &amp; pore in departing of mete to hem; but &thorn;ey shulen not bi &thorn;is offiss leeue ay to preche cristis gospel. &amp; so men shulden take heere good hede hou apostlis gederide not &thorn;es godis, but seculeris puttiden hem at &thorn;er feet; &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ei leften not to preche for departing of &thorn;es godis. &amp; &thorn;us a clerk or spenser of a curat may parte &thorn;es godis in &thorn;e name of hym. what lewid skile shulde moue of &thorn;is &thorn;at prestis shulden be seculer lordis, or haue worldly godis in propre, si&thorn;en apostlis kepten hem fro &thorn;es two. &amp; heere men answeren to &thorn;e &thorn;ridde skile &thorn;at anticrist maki&thorn; heere; poul techi&thorn; hou &thorn;at bishops shulden ordeyne wel for &thorn;er hous &amp; herbore men wi&thorn;-oute grucching, but herto &thorn;ei moten haue wherof ouer &thorn;er fode &amp; &thorn;er hiling. We graunten wel &thorn;at siche bishops as ben keperis of parischis shulden wel ordeyne for her housis bo&thorn;e in prestis &amp; o&thorn;er meyne, so &thorn;at &thorn;ey hadden not to manye ne to ydil ne to synful. &amp; si&thorn;en &thorn;ey shulden haue ynow bo&thorn;e of fode &amp; of hiling, &thorn;ey shulden not euere be so nedy &thorn;at ne &thorn;ey my&yogh;ten helpe pore pilgryms. but heere &thorn;ei hadden need to be war of herboringe <MILESTONE N="3b" UNIT="page">of stronge beggeris &amp; of my&yogh;ti men of &thorn;e world to haue heere &thorn;ank of worldly manhed. &THORN;ey shulden kepe pore pilgryms for tyme &thorn;at &thorn;ei hadden wher-of, &amp; fede hem bi apostlis fode &amp; not bi deyntees for worldly worchip. &amp; &thorn;is shulde teche siche persones to take more hede to &thorn;er pary&yogh;shis to fede her soulis goostly, al &yogh;if &thorn;ey shulden do &thorn;is sumtyme. &amp; &thorn;is were litil charite in persouns to spare hem silf for a ny&yogh;t for to helpe &thorn;er euene cristen, whanne &thorn;ey sawen &thorn;at &thorn;ei hadden nede; &amp; algatis to take siche gestis &thorn;at helden hem payed wi&thorn; siche godis, &amp; weren of &thorn;e noumbre of hem &thorn;at poul biddi&thorn; to holde hem payed.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="5" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000480.tif" N="414">
<HEAD>Capitulum 5<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>of &thorn;is may men se ouer &thorn;at alle herdis of crist shulden lyue of &thorn;e almes of sheep &thorn;at &thorn;ey techen. for &yogh;if &thorn;ey han rentis bifore or worldly richees, &thorn;ei shulden leeue hem bifore or lyue on hem bi-syde &thorn;er sheep. &amp; &thorn;us apostlis leften &thorn;er godis whanne &thorn;ey weren chosun to cristis disciplis. for ech persoun shulde bi charite sue crist as lichy as he my&yogh;te, but crist lyuede of almes of &thorn;e puple &thorn;at he tau&yogh;te; why shulde a prelat shame to lyue &thorn;us on siche almes? &THORN;e gospel of luk<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke viii. [3.]</NOTE> sei&thorn; hou marye maudelen &amp; cusees wif &amp; many o&thorn;ere mynys|triden to crist of &thorn;e godis &thorn;at weren herne; &amp; &thorn;us as crist was nedy for men, so he wolde take of &thorn;er almes; hou shulde a prelat shame to take &thorn;us godis of pore men? Also ech prelat shulde lyue moost parfit lif &amp; moost sikire, but it is more parfit &amp; sikire to lyue on siche almes &thorn;an bi ony o&thorn;er maner, &amp; &thorn;erfore prelatis shulden mekely holde hem payed of &thorn;is title. &YOGH;if &thorn;ei hadden bi anticristis lawe weye to plete for &thorn;es godis, &thorn;ey wolden stryue &amp; curse for hem &amp; wrongly disturble &thorn;er sugetis, &amp; &thorn;us to haue bi title of almes as crist hadde is more worchipful, for lawe of &thorn;e lord is betere, &amp; &thorn;us prestis ben more lik to crist. &amp; &thorn;us prelatis shulden bi title of almes &yogh;yue lore &amp; leding to &thorn;er sugetis; &amp; si&thorn;en &thorn;is &yogh;yuyng is myche betere &thorn;an bodily &yogh;yuyng &thorn;at &thorn;e puple &yogh;yue&thorn;, it is more worchipful to prelatis to &yogh;yue &thorn;us goostly almes &thorn;an to take bodily almes, &thorn;at is so litil &amp; so myche dette, &amp; herfore sei&thorn; poul so&thorn;ely &thorn;at it is more blessid condicioun for to &yogh;yue<NOTE PLACE="marg">Acts xx. [35.]</NOTE> betere &thorn;ing &thorn;an to take &thorn;ing lesse wor&thorn;. &amp; &thorn;us &yogh;if title of almes renne bi-twixe &thorn;is herde &amp; his sheep, it is more willeful to &thorn;es sheep &amp; so more meedeful to hem, &amp; herfore wolde poul take willefuly &thorn;e &yogh;ifte &thorn;at philemon shulde <MILESTONE N="4" UNIT="page">&yogh;yue hym.<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Philemon v. 15.]</NOTE> &amp; on &thorn;e to&thorn;er syde anentis &thorn;e herde it turne&thorn; hym to more mekenesse, &amp; stiri&thorn; hym by skyle &amp; shame to &yogh;yue a&yogh;en betere &yogh;ifte. Also god is so skileful &thorn;at he wole not &thorn;at men chaffere but in &thorn;ingis whoos valu &thorn;ei knowen; but lore &amp; 
<PB REF="00000481.tif" N="415"> preyour of prestis may not be taxid bi mannus wit, &amp; &thorn;erfore god wolde not &thorn;at it were seld bi dymes ne offeringis. &amp; &thorn;erfore sei&thorn; crist in matheus gospel to his disciplis &thorn;at techen<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. x. [8.]</NOTE> &thorn;e puple: "&yogh;ee token frely &yogh;oure wit of god, &amp; &yogh;yue &yogh;ee it frely to &thorn;e puple." &amp; &thorn;is sentense shulden prestis take as a reule of bileue, for myche wit &amp; myche streng&thorn;e ben in goddis reules &thorn;at semen rude.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="6" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 6<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>of &thorn;is it semy&thorn; to many men &thorn;at ne&thorn;er persoun ne prelat shulde wringe out &thorn;e godis of his sugetis bi cursis ne worldly ple. for &thorn;ey ben pure almes as we supposen, on which almes shulde renne no ple; for &thorn;ei shulden be willeful &amp; &yogh;ouyn wi&thorn;-oute resoun of mannus dette. Also crist &amp; his apostlis ne&thorn;er cursiden ne pletiden for &thorn;er dette, &amp; &thorn;ey shulden be ensaumple to vs; why shulden we curse or plete for hem? &amp; in tokene here-of god telde in his newe lawe litil or nou&yogh;t of &yogh;yuyng of dymes. &amp; it semy&thorn; to trewe men &thorn;at god wolde &thorn;at dymes weren partid bi-twixe prestis &amp; o&thorn;ere pore men &thorn;at weren feble, lame or blynd. &amp; therfore telli&thorn; luk in his<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke ix.</NOTE> gospel hou crist cam &thorn;oru&yogh; samary wi&thorn; his disciplis, &amp; &thorn;ey wolden ne&thorn;er &yogh;yue fode ne herbore for hym &amp; hise; &amp; ioon &amp; iames axiden of crist &thorn;at fier shulde come doun fro heuene &amp; destrie hem, as ely dide; but crist answeride to &thorn;es apostlis &amp; tau&yogh;te &thorn;at he wolde not curse &thorn;us: "&yogh;ee witen not," sei&thorn; crist, "whoos spiritis &yogh;ee ben, &amp; hou y loue mekenesse &amp; paciense; for mannus sone cam not in-to &thorn;is world to lese mennus soulis but to saue hem." &amp; iurisdiccioun of crist was largere &amp; freere &thorn;an &thorn;e popis. si&thorn;en crist wolde not curse for &thorn;es wrongis, &amp; &thorn;ei weren more &thorn;an oure wrongis, bi what lawe shulden we haue title to curse &thorn;us for oure lesse wrongis? no drede crist hadde more ri&yogh;t to &thorn;es dymes &thorn;an ony cristen|man may haue to dymes or to offeringis or to ony good by mannus lawe; &amp; si&thorn;en crist tau&yogh;te in &thorn;is dede not to plete for 
<PB REF="00000482.tif" N="416"> his dette, why shulden not prestis sue crist heere, si&thorn;en cristis dedis ben myrour to hem?</P>
<P>&amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ey taken of &thorn;e olde lawe &thorn;at dymes ben <MILESTONE N="4b" UNIT="page"> due vn-to prestis, myche more in &thorn;e newe lawe whanne prestis ben more wor&thorn;y bi crist. so&thorn; it is &thorn;at dymes weren due to prestis in &thorn;e olde lawe, but &thorn;ey weren holdun to do a&yogh;en sleyng of beestis &amp; hard seruyss. but god forbede &thorn;at oure prelatis oblische hem to trauele &thorn;us, for &thorn;anne &thorn;ei abiden a&yogh;enus bileue, sleyng of crist &thorn;at was &thorn;anne figurid. Also no man shulde plete an o&thorn;er, &amp; algatis &thorn;e curat his sheep, but for charite to &thorn;e pleted man; si&thorn;en poul sei&thorn; &thorn;at alle oure dedis shulden be don in charite, &yogh;e &thorn;at shulde strecche to oure enemyes. &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ou seyst &thorn;at charite moue&thorn; &thorn;ee to plete &thorn;us for dymes, for&yogh;yue &thorn;ou hem as crist dide; for &thorn;at is more li&yogh;t &amp; of more loue. &amp; &yogh;if a man plete in goddis cause &amp; alegge &thorn;at &thorn;ou hast synned in doyng of &thorn;yn herdis offiss, in &thorn;ingis &thorn;at &thorn;ou shuldist &yogh;yue &thorn;i sheep; no drede &thorn;ou maist not answere heere ne iustefie &thorn;y part bi goddis lawe. &amp; &thorn;us in &thorn;e newe lawe si&thorn;en prestis bi-gunnen to plete &thorn;us, &thorn;ei han left to do &thorn;er offiss, as &thorn;ei leften in &thorn;e olde lawe; &amp; so in-stode of siche plees &thorn;e curat shulde moue his sheep bi paciense &amp; o&thorn;ere vertues &amp; trewe trauel in his offiss. &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;is wole not moue &thorn;e puple to &yogh;yue hym &thorn;ingis &thorn;at ben nedeful, turne &thorn;is prelat to o&thorn;er puple; for so dide crist, &amp; god faili&thorn; not; or ellis lyue he on his bodily trauel or o&thorn;ere mennus almes as poul dide.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="7" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 7<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>of &thorn;is ground may men se ouer, &thorn;at &yogh;if an hye prelat charge a persoun to &yogh;yue hym godis &thorn;at is not groundid bi lawe of god for to &yogh;yue, &thorn;ys persoun shulde not &yogh;yue &thorn;es godis, ne&thorn;er for cursing ne o&thorn;ere censuris. for a man shulde not asente to synne for no&thorn;ing as it is seyd; &amp; no drede &thorn;is persoun assentide to &thorn;e wrong of his prelat aboue, whanne he &yogh;yue&thorn; 
<PB REF="00000483.tif" N="417"> &thorn;us pore mennus godis bi &yogh;ifte &thorn;at goddis lawe techi&thorn; not. for al treu&thorn;e is in goddis lawe, &amp; dettis feyned wi&thorn;-outen it ben pure robbery of &thorn;e puple; but who shulde not a&yogh;en-stonde &thorn;is? &amp; it is all oon to an hye prelat to curse &thorn;is persoun for &thorn;is cause &amp; to seye: "robbe &thorn;ou pore men, &amp; take of hem so myche good, &amp; y shal mayntene &thorn;i robbery, &amp; ellis y shal curse &thorn;ee in &thorn;yn hed &amp; suspende &thorn;ee &amp; &thorn;e puple &thorn;at &thorn;ey here not goddis seruyss." Who wolde not fle fro siche spuyling for siche feyned censuris of prelatis? but heere ha&thorn; &thorn;e fend shapun a sharp cautel to streng&thorn;en &thorn;is robbery. &THORN;ey wolen bi process of &thorn;er lawe priue a man of his benefiss &amp; putte in an-o&thorn;er fend &thorn;at wole blely robbe pore men &amp; &thorn;us &yogh;yue &thorn;is robbery to &thorn;is prelat of anticrist. &amp; &thorn;is astonye&thorn; many persouns to stonde for ri&yogh;t a&yogh;enus &thorn;e fend. but heere shulden alle &thorn;re <MILESTONE N="5" UNIT="page">partis of &thorn;e chirche helpe ech o&thorn;er a&yogh;enus &thorn;e deuel, &amp; wite wel first &thorn;at suche cursing or censuris ben vnskileful; &amp; so men shulden quenche hem si&thorn; &thorn;ei ben a&yogh;enus goddis lawe. &amp; trewe persouns wi&thorn; &thorn;er pari&yogh;schis shulden not lette for siche manass to stonde algatis for &thorn;is treu&thorn;e, ne&thorn;er for dispensis ne peyne; for si&thorn;en persouns shulden haue no godis to &yogh;yue &thorn;er prelatis but of &thorn;er sheep, what persoun shulde for al &thorn;is world make &thorn;is robbing of pore men? &amp; &yogh;if manye wolden holde togedere in &thorn;is bileue a&yogh;enus &thorn;e fend, it were a triacle a&yogh;enus venym &thorn;at emperour prelatis sowen in &thorn;e folc. for no drede ne&thorn;er persouns ne puple shulden assente herto for ony man. &amp; &thorn;anne bischops &amp; archidekenes wi&thorn; &thorn;er officials &amp; denes shulden not amersy pore men; for &thorn;is is worse &thorn;an comyn robberye, si&thorn;en ipocrisie is feyned ouer wrong-taking of &thorn;es godis. a prest shulde ra&thorn;ere leeue &thorn;is offiss &amp; suffere de&thorn; or he assentide by ony of sixe maner of consentis to siche piling of pore men. for it is in many caasis as myche synne to rob a wedewe or a pore fadirles child of a peny or an halpeny as it were to robbe a riche man of an hundrid markis wor&thorn; godis. &amp; no drede siche cowarde prestis ben cause of al siche spuyling; &amp; it is shewid by &thorn;is &thorn;efte &thorn;at &thorn;ei louen more &thorn;er shepis godis &thorn;an &thorn;ey don heel&thorn;e of &thorn;er soule, &amp; &thorn;anne &thorn;ay 
<PB REF="00000484.tif" N="418"> faylen of gode herdis, &amp; ben hirid hynes or woluys, &amp; &thorn;e puple shulde crye out on siche.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="8" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 8<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>cristenmen of &thorn;is ground &thorn;enken &thorn;at pari&yogh;schens shulden drawe fro persouns offeringis &amp; dymes &amp; o&thorn;ere godis whanne &thorn;ey faylen opynly in &thorn;er offiss, for siche assent is to blame &thorn;at nurshi&thorn; persouns in siche synne. but what meede were it to pari&yogh;shens to &yogh;yue her almes to siche a prelat to werre a&yogh;enus crist &amp; his chirche &amp; mayntene &thorn;e fendis part a&yogh;enus crist? si&thorn;en crist ha&thorn; tau&yogh;t cristenmen hou &thorn;ey shulden wisely do &thorn;er almes; not a&yogh;enus &thorn;er oune hed, ne a&yogh;enus &thorn;er modir hooly chirche. Also bileue in ioons epistle techi&thorn; &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">2 John [10].</NOTE> men shulden not grete siche; but it is more to &yogh;yue hem almes &thorn;an to grete hem bi nakid word; myche more men shulden not grete hem wi&thorn; almes, but fle fro hem as fro false prophetis. Also &thorn;e popis lawe biddi&thorn; men to not here &thorn;e massis of prestis &thorn;at ben comyn lechours. &THORN;anne &yogh;if prestis ben in more synne &thorn;at is more knowun to &thorn;e puple, &thorn;ey shulden not take &thorn;es prestis seruyss; hou shulden &thorn;ey herfore &yogh;yue hem almes? Also poul <MILESTONE N="5b" UNIT="page">biddi&thorn; drawe men to dele not wi&thorn; siche men &thorn;at ben contrarie to goddis lawe, but sich prestis ben contrarie<NOTE PLACE="marg">[1 Cor. v. 11.]</NOTE> to god &amp; to his puple as wolues of raueyn; hou shulden men &thorn;anne &yogh;yue hem godis to peruerte so myche puple? for what euere &thorn;ei don, in masse or mateyns or o&thorn;er dedis of &thorn;er lif, &thorn;ey harmen hem silf &amp; &thorn;er pari&yogh;s &amp; o&thorn;er puple<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. pupple.</NOTE> &thorn;at is aboute hem. &amp; bi &thorn;e same skile [they are] foolis &thorn;at &yogh;yuen &thorn;er godis as almes to siche prelatis; for siche &yogh;ifte is not almes but &yogh;ifte of helle to streng&thorn;e &thorn;e fend. &amp; &thorn;e fend shulde shame heere to seye &thorn;at pari&yogh;schens shulden not iuge of &thorn;e lif of &thorn;er prelat whe&thorn;er &thorn;at he be good or yuel; for &thorn;ey shulden iuge to sue hym in as myche as he sue&thorn; crist. &amp; &thorn;us si&thorn; crist biddi&thorn; 
<PB REF="00000485.tif" N="419"> iuge his werkis, why shulden not men iuge &amp; fle false prelatis? it is al oon to seye &thorn;is feynyng &amp; to lette men to fle fro fendis &amp; blesse hem fro &thorn;er wickid werkis, but teche men to assente to hem. lord, si&thorn; crist biddi&thorn; men &thorn;at &thorn;ey shulden not trowe to hym but &yogh;if he dide his fadirs werkis, what priuylegie ha&thorn; anticrist heere &thorn;at men shulden trowe &amp; susteyne hym in doyng of &thorn;e deuels werkis? Also crist techi&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. v. [13.]</NOTE> &thorn;at &yogh;if salt vany&yogh;sche awey it is not wor&thorn; aftir but to be castun out &amp; be defoulid of men; &amp; &thorn;is salt shulde be &thorn;es prelatis. lord, wher &thorn;is casting out &amp; &thorn;is defouling &thorn;at crist speki&thorn; of be &yogh;yuyng of godis to siche curatis, &amp; mayntenyng of hem in &thorn;is staat. lord, si&thorn;en men doren not mayntene an opyn traytour of &thorn;e kyng, hou doren &thorn;ey mayntene a more traytour &amp; more harmful of ihesu crist? &THORN;e harme &thorn;at wolde sue of &thorn;is lore semy&thorn; to stonde in &thorn;is good, &thorn;at prestis shulden shewe bi &thorn;er werkis &thorn;at &thorn;ey weren wor&thorn;y to be helpid; but &thorn;is lore is tau&yogh;t of crist, &amp; blessid be &thorn;e weye &thorn;at techi&thorn; it. &YOGH;if men iugen vndiscretly &thorn;ey don hem more harm &thorn;an prestis, for laste prestis in vertuous lif &amp; drede &thorn;ey not of sustenaunse.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="9" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 9<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>&thorn;is sentense of almes shulde strecche to plasis &thorn;at han chirchis approprid; as ben munkis &amp; chanouns &amp; seculer collegies. &THORN;er ben &thorn;re maner of collegies &thorn;at vsen &thorn;is craft of appropring. &THORN;e firste ben cathedral chirchis &thorn;at han pro|uendris approprid to hem; &thorn;e secounde ben chapels of prinsis &thorn;at han chirchis more approprid; &thorn;e &thorn;ridde ben collegies of studies &thorn;at vsen &thorn;is same craft; bi &thorn;es may men knowe o&thorn;ere &thorn;at han appropring of chirchis. For alle acorden in &thorn;is, &thorn;at &thorn;ey han almes of pari&yogh;schens &amp; <MILESTONE N="6" UNIT="page">&yogh;it dwellen not on &thorn;e pari&yogh;s as herdis for to teche hem; &amp; &thorn;ey blasfemen in god. for &thorn;ey moten nedis seye &thorn;at god ordeynede &thorn;is; &amp; si&thorn; no cause is of &thorn;is almes, &thorn;ei seyen &thorn;at god shoop &thorn;is wi&thorn;-oute cause. Also 
<PB REF="00000486.tif" N="420"> god ha&thorn; ordeyned heere in er&thorn;e almes to be delid as he deli&thorn; reyn; but he deli&thorn; reyn as it is nede, bi smalle dropis where er&thorn;e is drye; hou shame&thorn; not anticrist heere to make siche dichis &amp; waste drye er&thorn;e? no drede he is an yuel god, &thorn;at &thorn;us reuersi&thorn; goddis ordeynaunse. &amp; &yogh;if siche collegies feynen &thorn;at &thorn;ey preyen &amp; o&thorn;ere weyes profiten to &thorn;er pari&yogh;schis, men shulden not &thorn;us chaffere wi&thorn; preyere; for &thorn;ey witen nere wher &thorn;ey ben dampnyd. &amp; preyour of siche fendis is litil wor&thorn;, &yogh;e to hemsilf, hou feden &thorn;ey sheep? Also almes shulde be fre &amp; discreet as goddis lawe techi&thorn;, for ellis it were not meedeful, &amp; god &yogh;aue no leeue to do it; what meede shal a pore man haue &thorn;at he sufferi&thorn; a&yogh;enus his wille his almes be borun to cayms castel to fede a floc of anticristis? certis &thorn;ey don &thorn;es pari&yogh;schis no good ne to general hooly chirche, but &yogh;if &thorn;ei don good as &thorn;e fend &thorn;at reuersi&thorn; goddis ordenaunse. men shulden seke ground of siche collegies, whe&thorn;er god ha&thorn; ordeyned hem to be, &amp; &thorn;e floc fed bi hem &thorn;at ben so fer &amp; so lewid. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;es nouelries of collegies semen to tempte crist as &thorn;e fend, for &thorn;ey gon not to heuene bi greesis &thorn;at god ha&thorn; ordeyned to lede &thorn;idur, but &thorn;ey wolen fle bi &thorn;e fendis craft &amp; leeue &thorn;e weye &thorn;at crist ha&thorn; set. crist ordeynede &thorn;at his herdis shulden dwelle wisely vpon his sheep, &amp; teche hem bo&thorn;e bi lif &amp; word hou &thorn;ey shulden lyue to come to heuene; but anticrist casti&thorn; an-o&thorn;er gile, &thorn;at his herdis dwelle afer in castels &amp; be doump of lore of lif &amp; lore of word to helpe &thorn;er sheep, &amp; so it is nedeful &thorn;at &thorn;e puple be dis|seyued in body &amp; soule. &THORN;ey ben disseyued in &thorn;er body, for &thorn;ei ben robbid of bodili good &amp; it is clepid almes bi ipocrisie. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ey ben goostly disseyued, bo&thorn;e for hem wanti&thorn; teching to wende to heuene bi cristis weye, &amp; for &thorn;ey ben led to helle bi errour of &thorn;e fendis weye. crist sei&thorn; &thorn;at he is weye, &amp; grounde &thorn;ou &thorn;is apropring in crist, for &yogh;if crist grounde it not, it is &thorn;e brode weye to helle; it is a newe foundun weye <MILESTONE N="6b" UNIT="page">for sutilte a&yogh;enus charite, but &thorn;e kyngis weye is crist &thorn;at ledi&thorn; surely to heuene.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="10" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000487.tif" N="421">
<HEAD>Capitulum 10<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>Ant &thorn;us seyn summen heere &thorn;at, as lordis of &thorn;e world shulden wi&thorn;drawe &thorn;er lordchip fro clerkis dowid a&yogh;enus goddis lawe, so comyns of &thorn;e pari&yogh;s shulden wi&thorn;drawe &thorn;er almes &amp; &yogh;yue it aftir &thorn;e lore of crist, for ellis &thorn;ey reuersiden crist &amp; dispisiden hym &amp; chosun &thorn;e fend. &amp; &yogh;if a prelat, as pope or bishop, streyne &thorn;e puple a&yogh;enus &thorn;er wille to &yogh;yue &thorn;er almes to siche plasis, certis &thorn;ei ben &thorn;e fendis proctours. for crist koude neuere make an almes &thorn;ing &thorn;at were not willeful to men &amp; he koude not ordeyne siche buschementis to robbe men &amp; to wounde hem. &THORN;es men ben woundid in soule &thorn;at ben smytun wi&thorn; errour of vertues; &amp; &thorn;us can anticrist bi many mylis sende his arowis to wounde &thorn;e puple, &amp; moue con|sciense of men &thorn;at &thorn;ey leeue goddis lore &amp; take &thorn;e lore &thorn;at &thorn;e pope biddi&thorn;, as &yogh;if &thorn;e pope were hyed ouer crist. for crist biddi&thorn; men &thorn;us to do almes to pore feble &amp; lame &amp; blynd, but anticrist biddi&thorn; to leeue &thorn;is, and to do it to stronge &amp; idil men, &thorn;at ben nurschid in &thorn;e fendis nest to be an oost a&yogh;enus crist. Also pride &amp; coueytise of my&yogh;ti men of &thorn;e world weren ground of siche nestis wi&thorn;outen autorite of crist; &amp; &thorn;us men moten nedis assente to &thorn;e fend a&yogh;enus crist &thorn;at assenten to siche propring of chirchis bisyde cristis leeue, for crist sei&thorn; &thorn;at who so is not wi&thorn; hym he mut nedis be a&yogh;enus hym. &amp; &thorn;us coueytise of popis &amp; bishops assenti&thorn; to siche appropringis, &amp; coueytise of &thorn;er messangeres &thorn;at ben hirid to helpe hem; &amp; pride of men of &thorn;e world &thorn;at wolen make hem siche poondis, is an o&thorn;er rote of consense a&yogh;enus crist lord of &thorn;is world. but ech man shulde &thorn;enke wisely &thorn;at his oune synne is to myche, al &yogh;if he procure not to be parsener of o&thorn;ere mennus synnes bi consent. &amp; &thorn;is consent of my&yogh;ti men bi streng&thorn;e &amp; cautels of &thorn;e fend ha&thorn; maistry of pore sheep of crist, &amp; autorisi&thorn; siche wrongis in er&thorn;e. Also crist techi&thorn; in &thorn;e pater noster to preye god to &yogh;yue vs oure breed, &amp; it shulde be maad oure breed bi oure trewe seruyss &thorn;at god 
<PB REF="00000488.tif" N="422"> biddi&thorn;; but al &thorn;es &thorn;at han chirchis aproprid faylen of &thorn;is trewe seruyss herfore, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei ben vnhable to preye, but preyen a&yogh;en &thorn;er oune hed. &amp; to &thorn;is purpos speki&thorn; poul, &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">[2 Thess. iii. 10.]</NOTE> &thorn;is man &thorn;at traueli&thorn; not ete he not; for &yogh;if he dide, he eet as a priue &thorn;ef mete of o&thorn;ere pore men. siche sutiltees of priue resouns &thorn;at ben hid in goddis lawe shulden moue men on goddis syde to holde cristis ordenaunse in his boundis; for certis a priuey errour &amp; an hid wole bringe in <MILESTONE N="7" UNIT="page">a grettere errour, as o defaute &thorn;at is contynued wolle bringe in a more defaute. as defaute of keping of o pari&yogh;s wole turne hem to &thorn;e fendis children, &amp; &thorn;ey wolen infecte cuntreys, &amp; cuntreys wolen infecte reumes; &amp; &thorn;us it falli&thorn; to kyngis &amp; bischops to stoppe &thorn;is errour for more perel.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="11" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 11<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>but heere moue&thorn; &thorn;e fend men to feyne falsly a&yogh;enus treu&thorn;e. many men taken as bileue &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben lordis of &thorn;er oune godis, &amp; &thorn;anne it is leeueful to hem to do &thorn;er almes where euere &thorn;ey wolen. but where shulden &thorn;ey do &thorn;er almes but to &yogh;yue &thorn;er dymes &amp; &thorn;er offeringis, &amp; to siche curatis &thorn;at &thorn;e pope &amp; bischops lymiten hem, for ellis my&yogh;te a man be dampnyd wi&thorn;-outen ony defaute of hym; for hou shulde a lewid man do but as his prelat techi&thorn; hym?</P>
<P>Heere men seyn bi goddis lore &thorn;at ech man &thorn;at ha&thorn; dis|crecioun shulde be tau&yogh;t wi&thorn;-ynne bi god of grete articlis of bileue; but oon article of bileue next aftir &thorn;e hooly goost is to trowe hooly chirche &thorn;at is cristis spouse &amp; oure modir. &amp; &thorn;is is a foul errour to take &thorn;e spouse of &thorn;e fend &amp; worchipe here as cristis spouse bo&thorn;e in word &amp; in dede. we may not &yogh;it wite for certeyn which persone is of cristis spouse of alle &thorn;e men &thorn;at wandren heere, but we may gesse &amp; &thorn;at is ynow. As we gessen &thorn;at &thorn;is man &thorn;at holdi&thorn; wel cristis lawe is a leme of hooly chirche, &thorn;e which chirche is oure modir, So we gessen of an-o&thorn;er man &thorn;at reuersi&thorn; cristis lawe, &thorn;at he is a leme of &thorn;e fend &amp; no part of hooly chirche; &amp; we shulden 
<PB REF="00000489.tif" N="423"> not &yogh;yue dymes ne offeringis to siche men as to hooly chirche, as we shulden not loute &thorn;e fend al &yogh;if he shewide hym in ymage of crist. &amp; herfore crist &amp; his apostlis weren not gredy of worldly godis, but helden hem payed of fode &amp; hiling, &amp; so don prestis of cristis chirche. &amp; &thorn;us si&thorn; crist is cheef lord, men moten dispende cristis godis on &thorn;at maner &thorn;at crist ha&thorn; lymyted, &amp; not hou euere a man wole, &amp; it is not ynow to do good but &yogh;if a man do it wel. for &thorn;e gospel of ioon telli&thorn; &thorn;at crist sei&thorn; of summe foolis &thorn;at &thorn;ei shulen deme<NOTE PLACE="marg">[John xvi. 2.]</NOTE> to obesche to god in pur-suyng of his apostlis; as poul wente &thorn;at he dide wel to drawe cristenmen to ierusalem. &amp; &thorn;us it is ny&yogh; &thorn;e perel to &yogh;yue bodily almes to men but &yogh;if men knowen hem betere, &amp; &thorn;anne in litil quantite. &amp; herfore crist tau&yogh;te not his apostlis to bisie hem abou<MILESTONE N="7b" UNIT="page"> te siche almes but aboute goostly almes, &thorn;at is preching of &thorn;e gospel; but bodily almes is brou&yogh;t yn bi freris &amp; o&thorn;ere stronge beggeres. &amp; &thorn;es fendis clerkis feynen almes whanne it is noon almes but synne. &amp; &thorn;us errour in bileue, to trowe to &thorn;e pope &amp; to bischops as men shulden trowe goddis lawe, maki&thorn; many men blamed of god. for men shulden trowe to &thorn;es prelatis aftir &thorn;er dedis groundid in goddis lawe; but men shulden trowe to cristis lawe ouer &thorn;is as bileue. but &yogh;it &thorn;e fend disseyue&thorn; men &thorn;at &thorn;ey &yogh;yuen not &thorn;is almes vnto ioon or to robert, but to god &amp; in his name bi good entent, &amp; &thorn;at is ynow; for a man shulde paye his dette to hym &thorn;at is traytour to god. Heere is myche for to seye, for &thorn;e fend taki&thorn; fals &thorn;at foolis &yogh;yuen not &thorn;er almes to robert &thorn;at is a leme of &thorn;e fend. &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ei &yogh;yuen &thorn;is &thorn;us to god, &thorn;ei &yogh;yuen it on an yuel maner; but men witen &thorn;at it is dampnable to &yogh;yue to god &thorn;er seruyss yuele as ech fend &thorn;at is in helle &yogh;yue&thorn; to god his dampnyng. &amp; &thorn;us men moten ri&yogh;te &thorn;er entent, &amp; &yogh;yue discretly goddis godis, for wenyng to do wel in many caasis is not ynow. &amp; as anentis worldly dette &thorn;er is an-o&thorn;er resoun &thorn;er-of; for a man may meedefuly &yogh;yue it to hym &thorn;at shal aftir be dampnyd; for &thorn;is is no willeful almes but &yogh;ilding of dette bi mannus lawe.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="12" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000490.tif" N="424">
<HEAD>Capitulum 12<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>&yogh;it &thorn;e fend blyndi&thorn; many curatis &thorn;at wenen &thorn;at wenen &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben not holdun to residense bi leeue of &thorn;e pope or of &thorn;er bischop or of seculere lordis bi priuylegie, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei taken fruytis of &thorn;er chirchis &amp; seruen not &thorn;er puple &thorn;erfore. but heere trewe men shulden knowe &thorn;at ne&thorn;er pope ne o&thorn;er man ha&thorn; power to kepe a man in his benefiss &amp; to do nou&yogh;t &thorn;erfore; for god wole not do &thorn;is dede but axi&thorn; due seruyss for &thorn;is offiss. &amp; as an ymage is not &thorn;e man al &yogh;if it be lik to hym, so siche leeue of a persoun maki&thorn; hym not herde but wolf to god; &amp; &yogh;if an herde haue bullis of &thorn;e pope &thorn;at he dispensi&thorn; heere wi&thorn; hym, alle siche bullis excusen not bifore &thorn;e iugement of god; but &thorn;ey accusen more &thorn;e pope to take part of mennus dampnyng &thorn;at tristen so myche in &thorn;e popis bullis more &thorn;an in lawe or skile of god. &amp; bi &thorn;e same skile bischops leeue, &thorn;at is of a persoun, excusi&thorn; hem not bifore god, but te[lli&thorn;]<NOTE PLACE="foot">Illegible from the margin being rubbed.</NOTE> hou &thorn;ey bien &amp; sillen &thorn;er peyne; &thorn;is chaffere pas[si&thorn;]<NOTE PLACE="foot">Illegible from the margin being rubbed.</NOTE> symonye, for it is more ny&yogh; to wrong to &yogh;yue a man leeue for money to serue not god but to serue &thorn;e fend. For certis no man may haue &thorn;is power,<MILESTONE N="8" UNIT="page"> &yogh;e not anticrist hym silf. &amp; as anentis seculer lordis, as kyngis &amp; prinsis &amp; o&thorn;ere lordis, men shulden sharply telle to hem &thorn;at &thorn;ei han no power a&yogh;enus god, but &thorn;ei moten nedis for siche dedis &thorn;at men clepen priuelegies dampne hem silf, wi&thorn; &thorn;es persouns &thorn;at &thorn;ey letten fro goddis offiss. &amp; wolde god &thorn;at trewe prestis wolden telle sharply &thorn;is perel to lordis; for man my&yogh;te not more opynly bicome traytour to his god &thorn;an to drawe his kny&yogh;tes fro his seruyss, &amp; bringe in fendis &amp; sle his soulis. but &yogh;it &thorn;e fend ha&thorn; founden cautels to bringe in vikeris in persouns stede, &amp; bi colour of siche vikeris he sei&thorn; &thorn;at propring of chirchis is leeueful, &amp; noun residense is excusid bi siche a viker &thorn;at holdi&thorn; his stede. Heere men &thorn;enken &thorn;at it were good to haue a viker &thorn;at were nedy to take bodily almes of men whanne &thorn;e persoun trauelide 
<PB REF="00000491.tif" N="425"> not &thorn;erfore; but &thorn;ey ben not in &thorn;is &thorn;er vikeris, but in bodily trauel &amp; spuyling of men. but bo&thorn;e &thorn;is persoun &amp; &thorn;is viker moten be puny&yogh;shid for &thorn;er trespas, si&thorn; ech man is holdun to serue god bi al &thorn;e power &thorn;at he ha&thorn;; for &yogh;if &thorn;is viker my&yogh;te serue ynow, what nede were it of siche a persoun? certis but to spuyle &thorn;e pore folc, &amp; make more synne in hooly chirche. &amp; bringing in of siche vikeris, &thorn;at oftetyme ben vnhable herdis, maki&thorn; hem pore &amp; nedy, &amp; sharpi&thorn; hem to spuyle pore puple; &amp; it maki&thorn; persouns aboue more hardy to walowe in synne, &amp; many tymes &thorn;ei ben vnhable to haue trewely &thorn;e name of curat. &amp; siche false names &thorn;at ben &thorn;us feyned excusen not bifore crist, si&thorn; crist is &thorn;e firste treu&thorn;e &amp; &thorn;e firste resoun of alle &thorn;ingis. We graunte wel &thorn;at it were good many prestis to haue felowis in keping of a floc, oon to do o &thorn;ing, an-o&thorn;er an-o&thorn;er; as oon to trauele bodily in mynistring of sacramentis, an-o&thorn;er to trauele in preching &amp; o&thorn;er teching of &thorn;e puple; but loke &thorn;at &thorn;es bo&thorn;e be hooly &amp; lyue in pouert as apostlis diden &amp; ech of hem helpe mekely o&thorn;er as felowis drawinge in goddis &yogh;oc. but &thorn;is axi&thorn; residense on sheep &thorn;at man is herde of. god may not be bigilid bi siche names &amp; excusing, for &thorn;is lord wole rikene wi&thorn; &thorn;es seruauntis fully aftir &thorn;at resoun axi&thorn;. &YOGH;if &thorn;ou feynest &thorn;ee an ordre &thorn;at &thorn;ou preyest &amp; &thorn;enkist on god, &amp; &thorn;erwi&thorn; &thorn;ou hast cure bi &thorn;y viker &thorn;at kepi&thorn; &thorn;e chirche, loke &thorn;at &thorn;ou bere not falsly &thorn;e name, but lyue in pouert as baptist dide, not in hye castels of caym &amp; lustful fode as boris in sty; <MILESTONE N="8b" UNIT="page">for preyours &thorn;at siche booris maken don to many more harm &thorn;an good. for bi &thorn;is fallas my&yogh;te a fend or a soutere be an herde ouer a &thorn;ousynd men in englond &amp; excuse residense bi a fool.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="13" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 13<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>&yogh;it argue&thorn; &thorn;e fend to colour siche appropringis, &thorn;ey ben con|fermed of &thorn;e pope &amp; approuyd of &thorn;e court, who may im|pungne &thorn;is dede but &yogh;if he impungne &thorn;e pope; &amp; of &thorn;is it wolde sue &thorn;at &thorn;e pope &amp; hise ben opyn heretikis, but where were &thorn;is fi&yogh;tinge chirche &yogh;if &thorn;is were so&thorn; of &thorn;e pope, &yogh;if &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000492.tif" N="426"> pope &amp; alle his clerkis weren dyuydid fro cristis chirche. for holding of cristis religioun shulde stonde moost in &thorn;e clergye, &amp; algatis in &thorn;es newe ordris as ben freris, munkis &amp; chanouns.</P>
<P>heere seyen trewe men in god more hardily &thorn;an &thorn;ey weren wont &thorn;at &thorn;is is a lewid skile, &yogh;if &thorn;e pope approue &thorn;is &thorn;ing &thorn;anne &thorn;is &thorn;ing mut nedis be trewe, for herby &thorn;e contrarye is &thorn;e more licly. for si&thorn; &thorn;e pope is more tempted &thorn;an o&thorn;ere men &amp; more led bi &thorn;e fend, it semy&thorn; bi &thorn;e popis confermyng &thorn;at &thorn;is is &thorn;e fendis werk. &amp; heere is more coloure in &thorn;is resoun &thorn;an in resouns &thorn;at aristotle telli&thorn; &thorn;at &yogh;if a man haue a kempt hed &thorn;anne he is a leccherous man. sumtyme it may falle so &amp; sumtyme &thorn;e contrarye may falle, as &thorn;e pope may sumtyme falle on &thorn;e so&thorn;e &amp; sumtyme discorde &thorn;erfro, as he may bi fauoure or money approue fi&yogh;ting of prestis &amp; ful asoyling of men &thorn;at fi&yogh;ten faste in his cause. but trowe we herfore &thorn;at god wole folde fro ri&yogh;twesnesse of his lawe? for god is moost mersiful al &yogh;if he suffere siche blasfemyes, &amp; &thorn;us he wolde &thorn;at mersy were in men &amp; for&yogh;yuenesse of &thorn;er wrongis; &amp; not &thorn;at men shulden fi&yogh;te to-gidere for siche lordchip of anticrist. &YOGH;if it be treu&thorn;e of goddis lawe god in &thorn;at conferme&thorn; it, &amp; &yogh;if it be falsed a&yogh;enus god, &yogh;it it is treu&thorn;e as austyn sei&thorn;, &amp; so god conferme&thorn; it to be puny&yogh;schid bi his wille; but &thorn;e fend is autour &thorn;er-of &amp; stiri&thorn; men to trowe to it. &amp; &thorn;us men &thorn;at han kunnyng &amp; knowen &thorn;e errours of &thorn;e pope shulden wi&thorn; mekenesse &amp; obediense telle &thorn;es errouris to hym &amp; o&thorn;ere. For &thorn;us dide poul for li&yogh;t synne &thorn;at petre did a&yogh;en &thorn;e chirche, &amp; ellis men loueden not &thorn;e pope ne iesu crist ne his chirche. &THORN;us bi cautels of &thorn;e fend is hate turnyd to name of loue &amp; loue turnyd to name of hate, <MILESTONE N="9" UNIT="page">&amp; &thorn;us ben many men disseyued. &amp; men trowen as bileue &thorn;at &thorn;e pope ha&thorn; no power but to edifie &thorn;e chirche bi &thorn;e lawe &thorn;at god ha&thorn; &yogh;ouyn; for poul sei&thorn; he ha&thorn; noon o&thorn;er, &amp; he hadde as myche as &thorn;e pope. &amp; si&thorn; &thorn;er is no power but of god, &amp; god &yogh;yue&thorn; no power to destrie his spouse; ne&thorn;er pope ne o&thorn;er man ha&thorn; power but to helpe &thorn;e chirche bi goddis lawe. &amp; &thorn;us feynyng of anticristis powere, &thorn;at is fals a&yogh;enus &thorn;is 
<PB REF="00000493.tif" N="427"> treu&thorn;e, come&thorn; of &thorn;e fadir of lesingis &amp; disseyue&thorn; many men. &amp; as anentis heresies of &thorn;e pope &amp; his clerkis supposen many trewe men &thorn;at he &amp; hise ben heretikis, for &thorn;ei holden a&yogh;enus goddis lawe worldly lordchipis in prestis hondis, &amp; &thorn;is is a&yogh;enus crist &amp; his lawe, &amp; maynteynen<NOTE PLACE="foot">mayntenyd MS.</NOTE> wrong a&yogh;enus worldly lordis. crist wole puny&yogh;sche &thorn;is heresie &amp; make it more knowun her-aftir, al &yogh;if anticrist &amp; hise seyn nou &thorn;at noone ben heretikis but &thorn;ei &thorn;at seyen &thorn;us. mennus diffynyng of heresie is litil wor&thorn; but to blame men &thorn;at don &amp; speken a&yogh;enus goddis lawe, for siche ben mooste heretikis. &amp; &thorn;us appropring of chirchis, newe brou&yogh;t in bi &thorn;e fend, sowe&thorn; symonye &amp; lesingis to make &thorn;is propring to be grauntid. &amp; &thorn;us algatis ben pore men robbid of worldly godis &amp; goostly help, &amp; &thorn;e fend ha&thorn; an entre to ouercome helples men, as ben men of siche pari&yogh;schis &amp; o&thorn;ere &thorn;at assenten herto.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="14" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 14<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>&yogh;it argue&thorn; &thorn;e fend &thorn;at bi &thorn;is foly &thorn;at heere is spokun alle col|legies &thorn;at ben in studies shulden be destried; but where were &thorn;anne cristendom? for &yogh;if philosofie &amp; dyuynite wantiden in &thorn;e reume of englond, where were &thorn;anne bileue of men or goddis lawe in englond? for collegies in oxneford &amp; caumbrige ben foundid on siche appropringis, &amp; collegians wenden out &amp; prechen &amp; quykenen many partis of englond; &amp; degre takun in scole maki&thorn; goddis word more acceptable, &amp; &thorn;e puple trowi&thorn; betere &thorn;erto whanne it is seyd of a maistir.</P>
<P>heere men seyn &thorn;at many goodis han comun bifore of siche studies, but neuere so myche si&thorn;en collegies weren dowid as dide bifore &thorn;er rentis weren proprid; &amp; &thorn;erfore it were good &thorn;at &thorn;es studies &amp; collegies &thorn;at ben in hem stooden in as myche as &thorn;ei acorden to goddis lawe &amp; lyuen wel, &amp; as myche as &thorn;ei discorden fro cristis lawe &thorn;at &thorn;ey weren mendid. but si&thorn; &thorn;at 
<PB REF="00000494.tif" N="428"> apostlis token no siche degre &amp; crist forfendide hem to be clepid maystris, it seme&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;is he&thorn;en maner brou&yogh;t in in<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. xxiii.</NOTE> studies discordi&thorn; fro &thorn;e gospel; &amp; as preching of apostlis was betere &thorn;an is preching of &thorn;es maystris, so prestis wi&thorn;-oute degre of scole may profite more &thorn;an don &thorn;es maystris. <MILESTONE N="9b" UNIT="page">take &thorn;e good fro &thorn;e yuel, &amp; holde &thorn;e good &amp; leeue &thorn;e yuel; &amp; moue it not &thorn;ee &thorn;at of siche yuel come&thorn; myche good to men &amp; reumes, for god wole suffere noon yuel be don but &yogh;if good come &thorn;erof. &amp; &thorn;us &yogh;if comyng of good &thorn;at springi&thorn; of yuel bi goddis grace shulde moue men to do &thorn;at yuel, &amp; continue it &amp; holde it, ech yuel shulde be don &amp; a man shulde fle noon yuel; for yuel of fendis doi&thorn; myche good, as adam &amp; eue diden good in synnyng, but it was don on yuel maner &amp; &thorn;erfore &thorn;e maner shoulde be fled. &amp; &thorn;us &yogh;if dyuynite were lernd on &thorn;at maner &thorn;at apostlis diden, it shulde profite myche more &thorn;an it doi&thorn; nou bi staat of scole, as prestis nou wi&thorn;-oute siche staat profiten more &thorn;an men of siche staat; &amp; contynue &thorn;ey in good lif &amp; in boundis of goddis lawe, &amp; &thorn;is shal make &thorn;e folc more trowe &thorn;an doi&thorn; degre takun in scole. &amp; manye sciensis ben vsid in scole &thorn;at profiten not to goddis lawe, but tarien &amp; letten fro &thorn;is lawe, as poul techi&thorn; opynly. &amp; &thorn;us mannus lawe tau&yogh;t in scolis letti&thorn; goddis lawe to growe, &amp; no drede god is &thorn;at maistre &thorn;at wole teche nou as redily as he wolde bifore &thorn;is tyme, &yogh;if prestis lif be shapun &thorn;erto. &amp; &thorn;at semy&thorn; no good mene to passe ouer cristis ordenaunse &amp; his lawe for good &thorn;at god sendi&thorn; herof, for &thorn;anne men shulden [not] drede to synne. &amp; &thorn;us men of scole trauelen veynly for to gete newe sutiltees, &amp; to magnefie &thorn;er name for &thorn;er worchip &amp; &thorn;er wynnyng, &amp; &thorn;e profit of hooly chirche bi &thorn;is weye is put abac. &amp; in making of &thorn;es maystris ben pore mennus godis ofte wasted, &amp; &thorn;e kyng of pride is hied &amp; cristis mekenesse is put bihynde. many siche synnes &thorn;at stiren to stryues comen of siche partis in studies; &amp; &thorn;us bi propring of chirchis come&thorn; ri&yogh;tly noon help to &thorn;e chirche.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="15" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000495.tif" N="429">
<HEAD>Capitulum 15<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>ant heere &thorn;e freris wi&thorn; &thorn;er fautours seyn &thorn;at it is heresye to write &thorn;us goddis lawe in english, &amp; make it knowun to lewid men. &amp; fourty signes &thorn;at &thorn;ey bringen forto shewe an heretik ben not wor&thorn;y to reherse, for nou&yogh;t groundi&thorn; hem but nygromansye.</P>
<P>it semy&thorn; first &thorn;at &thorn;e wit of goddis lawe shulde be tau&yogh;t in &thorn;at tunge &thorn;at is more knowun, for &thorn;is wit is goddis word. whanne crist sei&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel &thorn;at bo&thorn;e heuene &amp; er&thorn;e shulen passe but his wordis shulen not passe, he vndirstondith bi his woordis his wit. &amp; &thorn;us goddis wit is hooly writ, &thorn;at may on no maner be fals. Also &thorn;e hooly gost &yogh;af to apostlis wit at wit-sunday for to knowe al maner langagis to teche &thorn;e puple goddis lawe &thorn;erby; &amp; so god wolde &thorn;at &thorn;e puple were tau&yogh;t goddis lawe in dyuerse tungis; but what <MILESTONE N="10" UNIT="page">man on goddis half shulde reuerse goddis ordenaunse &amp; his wille? &amp; for &thorn;is cause seynt ierom trauelide &amp; translatide &thorn;e bible fro dyuerse tungis into lateyn &thorn;at it my&yogh;te be aftir translatid to o&thorn;ere tungis. &amp; &thorn;us crist &amp; his apostlis tau&yogh;ten &thorn;e puple in &thorn;at tunge &thorn;at was moost knowun to &thorn;e puple; why shulden not men do nou so? &amp; herfore autours of &thorn;e newe law, &thorn;at weren apostlis of iesu crist, writen &thorn;er gospels in dyuerse tungis &thorn;at weren more knowun to &thorn;e puple. Also &thorn;e wor&thorn;y reume of fraunse, not-wi&thorn;-stondinge alle lettingis, ha&thorn; translatid &thorn;e bible &amp; &thorn;e gospels wi&thorn; o&thorn;ere trewe sentensis of doctours out of lateyn in-to freynsch, why shulden not engli&yogh;sche men do so? as lordis of englond han &thorn;e bible in freynsch, so it were not a&yogh;enus resoun &thorn;at &thorn;ey hadden &thorn;e same sentense in engli&yogh;sch; for &thorn;us goddis lawe wolde be betere knowun &amp; more trowid for onehed of wit, &amp; more acord be bi-twixe reumes. &amp; herfore freris han tau&yogh;t in englond &thorn;e paternoster in engli&yogh;sch tunge, as men seyen in &thorn;e pley of &yogh;ork, &amp; in many o&thorn;ere cuntreys. si&thorn;en &thorn;e pater|noster is part of matheus gospel, as clerkis knowen, why 
<PB REF="00000496.tif" N="430"> may not al be turnyd to engli&yogh;sch trewely, as is &thorn;is part? specialy si&thorn;en alle cristenmen, lerid &amp; lewid, &thorn;at shulen be sauyd, moten algatis sue crist &amp; knowe his lore &amp; his lif. but &thorn;e comyns of engli&yogh;schmen knowen it best in &thorn;er modir tunge, &amp; &thorn;us it were al oon to lette siche knowing of &thorn;e gospel &amp; to lette engli&yogh;sch men to sue crist &amp; come to heuene. Wel y woot defaute may be in vntrewe translating, as my&yogh;ten haue be many defautis in turnyng fro ebreu in-to greu, &amp; fro greu in-to lateyn, &amp; from o langage in-to an|o&thorn;er. but lyue men good lif &amp; studie many persones goddis lawe; &amp; whanne chaungyng of wit is foundun amende &thorn;ey it as resoun wole. summen seyn &thorn;at freris trauelen &amp; &thorn;er fautours in &thorn;is cause for &thorn;re chesouns, &thorn;at y wole not aferme, but god woot wher &thorn;ey ben so&thorn;e. first &thorn;ey wolden be seun so nedeful to &thorn;e engli&yogh;schmen of oure reume &thorn;at singulerly in her wit lay&yogh; &thorn;e wit of goddis lawe, to telle &thorn;e puple goddis lawe on what maner euere &thorn;ey wolden. &amp; &thorn;e secound cause herof is seyd to stonde in &thorn;is sentense; freris wolden lede &thorn;e puple in techinge hem goddis lawe &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei wolden teche sum, &amp; sum hide, &amp; docke sum. For &thorn;anne defautis in &thorn;er lif shulden be lesse knowun to &thorn;e puple, &amp; goddis lawe shulde be vntreweliere knowun bo&thorn;e bi clerkis &amp; bi comyns. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde cause &thorn;at men aspien stondi&thorn; in &thorn;is as &thorn;ey seyn; alle &thorn;es newe ordris dreden hem &thorn;at &thorn;er synne shulde be knowun, <MILESTONE N="10b" UNIT="page">&amp; hou &thorn;ei ben not groundid in god to come in-to &thorn;e chirche, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ey wolden not for drede &thorn;at goddis lawe were knowun in engli&yogh;sch, but &thorn;ey my&yogh;ten putte heresye on men &yogh;if engli&yogh;sch toolde not what &thorn;ey seyden. god moue lordis &amp; bischops to stonde for knowing of his lawe.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="16" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 16<SUP>tum.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>it were to speke ouer &thorn;is of dymes &amp; of offeringis &thorn;at ben hire to prestis &thorn;at don trewely &thorn;er seruyss; &amp; dymes ben clepid goddis part in goddis lawe for greet wit. many causis men tellen comynly why dymes ben clepid 
<PB REF="00000497.tif" N="431"> goddis part. nyne partis ben of creaturis &amp; god is in &thorn;e ten&thorn;e degre; &amp; in tokene &thorn;at god is lord general ouer alle creaturis, men &yogh;yuen god &thorn;e ten&thorn;e part in tokene of his general lordchip. &thorn;e werkes of &thorn;e sixe dayes in whiche god made &thorn;e world holden sixe kyndis of &thorn;ingis in &thorn;is ordre of ten; &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;er ben nyne ordris of aungels, al &yogh;if &thorn;e firste bok of &thorn;e bible specifie not &thorn;es nyne ordris, as poul doi&thorn; in his bokis. &thorn;e ey&yogh;the maner of creaturis ben comyn &thorn;ingis &thorn;at god ha&thorn; maad, &amp; hooly writ speki&thorn; of hem in many bokis of goddis lawe. &thorn;e nyne&thorn;e maner of creaturis, &amp; &thorn;e hierste of alle o&thorn;ere, is &thorn;e manhed of crist: &amp; on &thorn;is sue&thorn; his godhed, &amp; &thorn;is ten&thorn;e &thorn;ing is hierst lord of al maner of creaturis. &amp; god moue&thorn; al maner of tungis to clepe &thorn;is firste noumbre of ten bi symple name &amp; aftirward &thorn;ei clepen it bi a gederid name; &amp; &thorn;is may men se in many tungis. &amp; &thorn;is mouyde men in many agis to paye to god &thorn;e ten&thorn;e part, so &thorn;at bi &thorn;is &thorn;ey confessiden to hym &thorn;e generalte of his lordchip; &amp; &thorn;is cause is ynow to moue men to paye dymes. but it were for-to wite whiche men shulden reseyue dymes. &thorn;e firste bok of &thorn;e olde lawe telli&thorn; of abel &amp; caym, hou &thorn;ey brenten &thorn;er ty&thorn;is to god, &amp; &thorn;e smoke wente up to heuene. &amp; it is licly &thorn;at &thorn;is maner lastide vn-to &thorn;e tyme of moyses; but god lymytide in moysees lawe &thorn;at prestis &amp; dekenes shulden lyue on dymes, &amp; semelily &thorn;is maner lastide vn-to &thorn;e comyng of crist. but nou in &thorn;e &thorn;ridde tyme of grace prestis &amp; prelatis chalengen to hem dymes &amp; mennus offeringis bi autorite of &thorn;e olde lawe, &amp; &thorn;is semy&thorn; skileful, so &thorn;at men trauele wel wi&thorn; hem, for men shulden paye &thorn;er dymes &yogh;it as &thorn;ey diden in &thorn;e olde lawe, but &thorn;ey shulden not brenne hem nou, for &thorn;er ben many pore goddis seruauntis. &amp; &thorn;us lawe &amp; skile chacchi&thorn; men to &yogh;yue to trewe prestis &thorn;es dymes, for &thorn;is were moost li&yogh;t &amp; resonable &yogh;if &thorn;at prestis lyuen wel. &amp; men neden not to rikene heere hou ofte &thorn;e olde lawe biddi&thorn; &thorn;at prestis shulden haue hem; but for crist &amp; hise apostlis weren fewe &amp; lyueden on litil almes, <MILESTONE N="11" UNIT="page">y can-not se bi goddis lawe &thorn;at ne dymes may be partid among cristis pore men, &thorn;e whiche crist 
<PB REF="00000498.tif" N="432"> telli&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel, as pore feble &amp; pore lame &amp; pore blynde.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke xiv. [13.]</NOTE> &amp; prestis ben &thorn;e firste for &thorn;ei shulden be pore as crist, &amp; feble &thorn;ey ben to do &thorn;er seruyss &amp; to gete &thorn;er-wi&thorn; fode &amp; hiling. crist koude bi weye of myraclis &amp; weye of almes gete ynow, but &yogh;it crist was pore &amp; feble &amp; figuride prestis aftir to come.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="17" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 17<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>it were to shewe aftir &thorn;is &thorn;at &thorn;e lawe &thorn;at god &yogh;yue&thorn; bi seynt poul his apostle in his writing to tymothe shulde not ceesse for oure taking of offeringis &amp; dymes bi &thorn;e olde lawe. Seynt poul biddi&thorn; to tymothe &amp; rikene&thorn; hym silf as o man to whiche &thorn;at he speki&thorn; to, &amp; &yogh;yue&thorn; hem &thorn;is reule of god: "whanne we han fode &amp; hiling, be we payed of<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Tim. vi. [8.]</NOTE> &thorn;es &thorn;ingis." lord, si&thorn; &thorn;is is a skileful reule &thorn;at goddis lawe &yogh;yue&thorn; to prestis &amp; clerkis, why shulden &thorn;ey leeue &thorn;is for a willeful chesing &thorn;at &thorn;ey taken of &thorn;e olde lawe? specialy si&thorn; &thorn;es two lawis acorden bo&thorn;e in wordis &amp; resoun &thorn;at prestis shulden lyue on dymes &amp; be payed of fode &amp; hiling. certis &yogh;if god wolde &thorn;at &thorn;e toon ceesside, we shulden not take &thorn;es two to-gidere; but god were in &thorn;is to blame &thorn;at he telde not which he wolde were kept. si&thorn;en we taken dymes of &thorn;e olde lawe bi oure oune autorite, leeue we not &thorn;is bileue &thorn;at god &yogh;yue&thorn; vs bi poule apostle; algatis si&thorn; &thorn;is is skileful &amp; ynow to a trewe prest. &amp; of &thorn;is may men se ouer &thorn;at prestis shulden not gedere to hem dymes &amp; offerringis of many chirchis, &thorn;at weren ouer &thorn;er fode &amp; hilinge, for &thorn;us it were not leeueful to a prest for to do in &thorn;e olde lawe; myche more we shulden not do &thorn;us, si&thorn; crist kepte so streyt pouert. &YOGH;if a prest my&yogh;te be two men &amp; do fully &thorn;e trauel &thorn;at fellide to hem, &thorn;anne it were to hym a coulur to take ful hire of two men; for men ben nou more insufficient &thorn;an &thorn;ei weren in cristis tyme. but &yogh;it it semy&thorn; excusable to haue to-gidere many benefisis, so &thorn;at &thorn;ey come not alle to-gidere but to a skileful sustenaunse of man. but be &thorn;ou war heere wi&thorn; 
<PB REF="00000499.tif" N="433"> ydilnesse &amp; wi&thorn; exceesse of dispensis, &amp; algatis putte &thorn;y bisynesse to serue god &amp; helpe his chirche, &amp; loue more &thorn;es two &thorn;ingis &thorn;an worldly worchip or worldly <MILESTONE N="11b" UNIT="page">richees. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;er ben many mennus lawis of departing of persouns godis, hou &thorn;ey shulen be delid on foure partis. hou &thorn;ey &amp; herne shulen first take mesurably of &thorn;es godis; &thorn;e secound part shulde be &yogh;ouyn to pore &amp; nedy folc wi&thorn;-outeward; &thorn;e &thorn;ridde part shulde be &yogh;ouun to making of &thorn;e chirche &amp; ournementis of it; &amp; &thorn;e four&thorn;e part shulde be dispendid to kepe &thorn;e housis of &thorn;e personage. &amp; &thorn;is parting were ofte vnskileful, &amp; &thorn;us siche general lawe were nou&yogh;t. &amp; &thorn;er ben o&thorn;ere difficultees heere, what &thorn;ing men shulden ti&thorn;e, as wode or erbis or o&thorn;er fruyt; wher laboreris shulden ti&thorn;e &thorn;er hire; &amp; hooris or vsureris ti&thorn;e &thorn;er wynnyng; wi&thorn; many siche doutis in lawe; &thorn;e whiche dyuynes shulden leeue vntretid, &amp; lyue in pouert &amp; serue &thorn;e chirche. for cristis prestis shulden haue no custom to ocupie hem wi&thorn; siche stryues, but gedere al &thorn;er bisynesse to serue god &amp; his chirche.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="18" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 18<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>it were to telle ouer &thorn;is hou &thorn;es herdis shulden kepe &thorn;er sheep in hoolynesse of &thorn;er oune lif &amp; in preching of goddis word. &amp; &thorn;anne &thorn;ey ledden hem bi grene lesewis &amp; water of heuene &thorn;at ben hoolsum, &amp; &thorn;is is &thorn;e firste offyss of &thorn;re &thorn;at falli&thorn; to a goostly shepparde. first shulde &thorn;e persoun fle in hym silf lustly fode &amp; proud aray, &amp; &thorn;enke on &thorn;is, &thorn;at his godis whanne &thorn;ei ben gederid, be &thorn;ey neuere so many, ben gederid of his pore pari&yogh;schens, as ben wedewis &amp; nedy men; so &thorn;at o peny gederid &thorn;us wolde saue &thorn;e lif of his sheep &thorn;at steruy&thorn;. &amp; &thorn;us it is a fendis boost to a curat to auaunte hym &thorn;at he may so myche dispende bi &yogh;eere, si&thorn; &thorn;ei ben cuylid pens of pore men; &amp; &thorn;is is noon auaunt to &thorn;e persoun, but resoun to rikene for al &thorn;is almes. &amp; &thorn;is is more &thorn;an worldly dette, si&thorn;en he is holdun to &yogh;elde betere; &amp; oure iuge 
<PB REF="00000500.tif" N="434"> may not be disseyued, si&thorn; he is crist wisdom of god. &thorn;es curatis &thorn;at lyuen to lustly shulden &thorn;enke hou godis &thorn;at &thorn;ey han ben gederid of pouert of symple men bi streit nede &amp; hard lif. but who wolde waste a precious water &thorn;at were distillid bi bisy trauel, &amp; caste &thorn;is water in a lake where it stood to no mannus profit? &amp; &thorn;es men &thorn;at lyuen &thorn;us lustly ben &thorn;e more vnhable to preche &amp; to preye; but no drede, si&thorn; oure <MILESTONE N="12" UNIT="page">god is resoun &amp; &thorn;e freest man &thorn;at may be, he wole &thorn;at curatis haue skileful fode; but &thorn;er lust may not be iuge heere, but resoun must nedis iuge, for it mut iuge at domes day. &amp; &thorn;e same skile is of o&thorn;er aparel, to bac, to chaumbre &amp; to halle, as many han to costly clo&thorn;is, furrours &amp; girdlis &amp; shap of hem; &amp; ende of &thorn;is is worldly glory &amp; no profit to &thorn;er soulis; &amp; &thorn;e same synne is in aparel of chaumbre, as in proud beddis testeris &amp; curteyns: bi &thorn;is may men se veyn dispensis &thorn;at &thorn;e fendis cautil ha&thorn; foundun. curiouste stondi&thorn; in hallis, bo&thorn;e in making of &thorn;e housis, in doseris, bancurs &amp; cu&yogh;shens, &amp; mo veyn &thorn;ingis &thorn;an we kunnen rikene, as ben di&yogh;schis &amp; coupis of siluer &amp; o&thorn;er vessel, &amp; costly naprye. in alle siche shulden persouns &thorn;enke of &thorn;is reule &thorn;at god ha&thorn; &yogh;ouyn of skileful<NOTE PLACE="foot">skilefuly MS.</NOTE> ende of alle siche &thorn;ingis; &amp; mesure &thorn;e menes bi &thorn;is ende, &amp; euere more drawe to pouert, &thorn;at it shyne in alle siche &thorn;ingis. but prestis wasting in o&thorn;ere &thorn;ingis, as ben horsis, haukis &amp; houndis, &amp; costly making of feestis, ben ful dampnable bifore god; for &thorn;ey shynen wi&thorn; worldly ioye, &amp; ben writun wi&thorn; vicis a&yogh;enus resoun. what skile is it at &thorn;e day of doom to answere to &thorn;e lord of &thorn;es godis &thorn;at pore men, &thorn;at shulden haue &thorn;es godis, peri&yogh;sche wi&thorn;-outen bi many defautis, &amp; her godis be wastid wi&thorn;-ynne wi&thorn; rot &amp; wormes &amp; o&thorn;er maner. &thorn;is is no skileful acounte to god to &yogh;yue hym rikenyng of his ty&thorn;is.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="19" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000501.tif" N="435">
<HEAD>Capitulum 19<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>of &thorn;is wasting of goddis godis springen synnes &thorn;at harmen &thorn;e chirche, for siche curatis &yogh;yuen not ensaumple hou men shulen fi&yogh;te a&yogh;enus &thorn;er fleys. but it may falle many tymes &thorn;at siche persouns bi lecchery waste &thorn;er pore pari&yogh;schens godis, &amp; &thorn;is is a greet synne. it is yuel to kepe a wast hors in stable to destrie pore mennus godis, but it is worse to have a womman wi&thorn;-ynne or wi&thorn;-oute at racke &amp; at manger, for &thorn;is holding is more costly &amp; more wast to body &amp; soule. &thorn;e lawe speki&thorn; of siche holours &thorn;at synnen &thorn;us out of matrimonye, hou &thorn;ey ben not weddid wi&thorn; &thorn;e chirche ne wi&thorn; god, &thorn;at is &thorn;e soulis spouse; &amp; hou men shulden not here &thorn;er massis, &amp; bi &thorn;e same sky<MILESTONE N="12b" UNIT="page">le take not of hem noon o&thorn;er spiritual seruyss. for al &thorn;er lif is wlappid wi&thorn; synne, &amp; &thorn;ey don harm what euere &thorn;ei don. &amp; &thorn;us men shulden not &yogh;yue hem offeringis ne o&thorn;ere ti&thorn;is, &thorn;e while &thorn;ey lyuen &thorn;us, for &thorn;at were consent to &thorn;er synne, &amp; to nurshe hem a&yogh;enus crist. but ech man of &thorn;is world, be he neuere so my&yogh;ti heere, &thorn;at maki&thorn; &thorn;us party a&yogh;enus crist, mut nedis falle &amp; destrie hym silf; for treu&thorn;e mut vencusche al o&thorn;er &thorn;ing. &amp; &thorn;is wi&thorn;drawing of temporal godis were betere bridil a&yogh;enus siche men &thorn;an to amersy hem bi officials, bi erchedekenes or bi bischops; for siche robbing is but nurshing of more synne. for siche a persoun wole robbe his pari&yogh;s whanne he may bie his synne &thorn;us li&yogh;tly; &amp; so &thorn;e pore men of his pari&yogh;s shulen bie his synne bi double weye, bo&thorn;e &thorn;ey shulen paye &thorn;erfore to &thorn;e bischop, and be puny&yogh;schid bi consent of soule. but what is &thorn;e pari&yogh;s holpun herby, but &yogh;if &thorn;e fend helpe a man? for bodily &amp; goostly &thorn;is curat doi&thorn; harm to his sheep more falsly &thorn;an koude &thorn;e fend, for he is more homely enemye. &amp; &thorn;is wi&thorn;-drawing of godis for &thorn;is synne semy&thorn; to strecche for o&thorn;ere synnes, for &yogh;if an herde be doump at home &amp; &yogh;yue hym to worldly ocupacioun, &amp; wi&thorn;-drawe his goostly help fro his sheep &thorn;at he shulde fede, 
<PB REF="00000502.tif" N="436"> or &yogh;if he stonde in lordis courtis or in offiss of &thorn;e king or of o&thorn;ere, and leeue &thorn;e seruyss &thorn;at god axi&thorn; to kepe his sheep in goddis lawe; &yogh;if &thorn;is synne passe lecchery, it shulde be more puny&yogh;shid bi skile. &amp; so men shulden wi&thorn;-drawe &thorn;er ti&thorn;is &amp; &yogh;yue hem to o&thorn;ere wisely. it were an almes &amp; greet wit to &yogh;yue ti&thorn;is of siche wolues to o&thorn;ere pari&yogh;schens &thorn;at ben trauelid bi lawis &thorn;at anticrist ha&thorn; brou&yogh;t yn; &amp; so ofte tyme &thorn;e remenaunt of ti&thorn;is were to litil for dispensis &thorn;at anticrist maki&thorn; to pursue siche men, &thorn;at stonden for resoun of goddis lawe. &amp; hou euere iuges speken heere, &thorn;is were not a&yogh;enus goddis lawe, for al siche almes of ti&thorn;is shulde be bo&thorn;e skileful &amp; willeful; but what skile is it to hire a wolf to do harm to a pari&yogh;s? &thorn;is were a mouyng of &thorn;e fend, &thorn;at stiri&thorn; euere a&yogh;enus skile. &amp; &thorn;e same skile is of curatis &thorn;at stonden in &thorn;e court of rome forto gete mo benefisis, or to serue &thorn;at wickid court; <MILESTONE N="13" UNIT="page">for &thorn;es ben smyttid wi&thorn; symonye &amp; don men harm ouer &thorn;e see, as a iust man of ynde profiti&thorn; to engli&yogh;sch men; for &thorn;e lord &thorn;at see&thorn; &thorn;is meede is euery where to dele it wel. for sum help axi&thorn; bodily residense, &amp; sum help axi&thorn; noon; as preyeris &amp; many o&thorn;ere gode dedis ben as wel don afer as neer; but &thorn;is is noon herdis offiss to be hirid for ti&thorn;is or offeringis.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="20" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 20<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>it were for to wite ouer hou prelatis shulden teche &thorn;er sugetis to vencu&yogh;sche &thorn;e world &amp; &thorn;e fend, for to &thorn;is lore ben &thorn;ei holdun. lore to vencu&yogh;she &thorn;e world stondi&thorn; specialy in charite, &amp; in fleyng of coueytise to godis of &thorn;er pari&yogh;s &amp; o&thorn;ere; &amp; so it semy&thorn; an yuel lore to &yogh;yue pari&yogh;schens ensaumple to plete &amp; to stryue wi&thorn; hem for litil, whanne &thorn;ey han ynow bi-syde. for siche ple is groundid in wronge don a&yogh;enus goddis lawe, for bi goddis lawe prestis shulden haue no more but fode &amp; hiling for &thorn;er offiss, &amp; al &thorn;e remenaunt of &thorn;er hire &thorn;ey shulden hope of god in blis. Also it falli&thorn; 
<PB REF="00000503.tif" N="437"> comynly &thorn;at a curat dispendi&thorn; as myche in plees mayntenyd for his ti&thorn;is as ben &thorn;e ti&thorn;is in hem silf; but where is &thorn;anne encrees of his wynnyng? it semy&thorn; &thorn;at wra&thorn;&thorn;e of his pari&yogh;schen &amp; harm of hym stonden for &thorn;e wynnyng; but hou stondi&thorn; &thorn;is wi&thorn; charite to &thorn;e man &thorn;at prestis shulden algatis loue? &amp; &thorn;us biddi&thorn; poul to cristenmen, but specialy<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Rom. xii. 19.]</NOTE> to curatis, &thorn;at &thorn;ey shulden be moost dere &amp; not defende &thorn;er oune persone; myche more &thorn;ey shulden not defende &thorn;e godis &thorn;at ben not sib to hem, but men shulden &yogh;yue stede to ire &amp; algatis prelatis, in suffering of wronge for siche ire, bayti&thorn; a pari&yogh;shen a&yogh;enus &thorn;e persoun longe tyme aftir. &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;e pope feyne heere &thorn;at he &yogh;yue&thorn; lawis &amp; weye to hem to defende a mannus wrongis in his court; &amp; &thorn;is is shewid for many wrongis ben ri&yogh;tid &thorn;ere. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ey clepen hym a champioun of ri&yogh;t of god, &thorn;at can wel plete &amp;, as &thorn;ey speken, wynne to hooly chirche godis &thorn;at shulden falle to it. preise &thorn;ey &thorn;is court &thorn;at han mater, but certis heere is no mater; for &thorn;is is a cautel of &thorn;e fend contrarie to goddis lawe. studie &thorn;ey cristis paciense &amp; make &thorn;ei &thorn;er chayer in cristis cros, &amp; loke &thorn;ey whe&thorn;er crist or his apostlis tau&yogh;ten &thorn;us to plete for worldly &thorn;ingis. &amp; certis &thorn;ey moten nedis sue crist &yogh;if &thorn;ey wolen holde &thorn;e weye to heuene. fro a litil errour out <MILESTONE N="13b" UNIT="page">of &thorn;is weye may a man come bi grace a&yogh;en, but myche errour wi&thorn; errour of wit maki&thorn; man to growe in more errour, &amp; no drede, proue who euere wole, a special medicyn a&yogh;enus &thorn;e world is to leeue stryues in worldly causis; for &thorn;us tau&yogh;te crist wi&thorn; his membris. &amp; &thorn;us who so wole ouercome &thorn;e fend, leeue he &thorn;e fendis lawe &amp; &thorn;e world, &amp; lede he his lif bi cristis lawe, &amp; &thorn;us he shal best vencu&yogh;she hym &amp; &yogh;yue ensaumple to o&thorn;ere men, bo&thorn;e to his pari&yogh;shens &amp; o&thorn;ere, hou &thorn;ey shulden vencu&yogh;she &thorn;e fend. for &thorn;es two lawis ben graues to &thorn;e fend to gnare men in his net. &yogh;if &thorn;ou fle pride &amp; his retenu, &thorn;anne &thorn;ou vencu&yogh;chist wel &thorn;e fend; &amp; teche &thorn;ou &thorn;is rewle to o&thorn;er men, &amp; &thorn;anne &thorn;ou doost a curatis office.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="21" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000504.tif" N="438">
<HEAD>Capitulum 21<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>&yogh;it it were to speke more of &thorn;is pastoure to &yogh;yue to &thorn;es sheep. for we shulen take as bileue &thorn;at goddis lawe passi&thorn; alle o&thorn;ere, bo&thorn;e in autorite &amp; in treu&thorn;e &amp; in wit. first in autorite; for as god passi&thorn; men, so goddis lawe mut passe in autorite mannus lawe, &amp; herfore god bad his apostlis not to preche mannus lawe but for to preche &thorn;e gospel to al maner of men. &amp; myche more ben &thorn;ey to blame &thorn;at prechen iapis &amp; gabbingis; for goddis word mut euere be trewe &yogh;if it be wel vndirstondun, &amp; &thorn;is word is more hoolsum to men si&thorn;en it is bileue &amp; it techi&thorn; to sue crist, &amp; &thorn;at mut ech man do &thorn;at shal be sauyd. &amp; &thorn;erfore &thorn;enke we heronne ny&yogh;t &amp; day, bo&thorn;e wakinge &amp; slepinge, for whanne o&thorn;ere lawis moten haue ende &thorn;anne it shal dwelle in blis; &amp; &thorn;e herte of &thorn;is lawe is &thorn;e gospel of iesu crist. preche prestis &thorn;is herte to men &amp; teche &thorn;ey hem to loue crist; for he is cursid &thorn;at loue&thorn; hym not &amp; sue&thorn; hym not, as poul sei&thorn;. &amp; certis &thorn;at prest is to blame &thorn;at shulde so frely haue &thorn;e gospel, &amp; leeue&thorn; &thorn;e preching &thorn;er-of &amp; turny&thorn; hym to mannus fablis. for &thorn;e lawe of god dampny&thorn; hym &thorn;at chesi&thorn; &thorn;e worse &amp; &thorn;e heuyere &amp; leeue&thorn; &thorn;e betere &amp; &thorn;e li&yogh;tere, bo&thorn;e to hym &amp; to &thorn;e puple. &amp; god axi&thorn; not dyuysiouns ne rymes of hym &thorn;at shulde preche, but to telle euene goddis gospel &amp; wordis to stire men &thorn;erby. &amp; &thorn;us curatis ben not excusid &thorn;at leeuen to preche to &thorn;er sheep, for a man shulde not be curat but &yogh;if he koude vn <MILESTONE N="14" UNIT="page">dirstonde &thorn;e gospel, &amp; he ha&thorn; to myche wanting of wit &thorn;at can-not teche hem herby. &amp; &yogh;if a curat falle a caas &thorn;at he be lettid of &thorn;is preching bi hap or defaute of kynde, whanne he prechide bifore wel, teche he his floc bi hooly lif &amp; god wole haue hym excusid. &thorn;e secounde offiss &thorn;at falli&thorn; to herdis is to kepe &thorn;er sheep fro woluys, as false freris, &thorn;at comen to men to robbe &thorn;er wolle &amp; do hem harm, ben clepid of crist woluys of raueyn. and of &thorn;is perel shulden persouns warne men. &amp; what o&thorn;ere false prechouris &thorn;at 
<PB REF="00000505.tif" N="439"> comen to men &amp; prechen herfore, &thorn;ei ben woluys or foxis or houndis, &amp; alle &thorn;es shulden be chased fro &thorn;e floc. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde offiss &thorn;at falli&thorn; to persouns is to greese &thorn;er scabbid sheep &amp; to telle hem medicyn of goddis lawe wherby &thorn;at &thorn;ey may be hool; &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;es herdis faylen in &thorn;es &thorn;re, &thorn;ey ben hirid hynes or woluys. &amp; heere shulden persouns take hede &thorn;at &thorn;ey spuylen not &thorn;er sheep for wrongis &thorn;at &thorn;er prelatis axen; for &thorn;ey shulden leeue &thorn;er cure bifore.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="22" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 22<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>it were forto wite ouer hou curatis wasten pore mennus godis in makinge &thorn;er kyn riche; bisyde &thorn;at &thorn;ey spenden in &thorn;er oune persone; &amp; &thorn;us ben many in englond maad riche fro ful symple staat. &amp; it semy&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;e kyng of pride ha&thorn; tau&yogh;t &thorn;is bi his firste synne, for many curatis han delit to haue riche men of &thorn;er kyn &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;er eldris weren noble men, as &yogh;if &thorn;er kynrede were noble; &amp; &thorn;us hem silf shulden seme noble, as &yogh;if &thorn;ey camen of greet blood. &amp; siche ben turnyd in-to woluys fro herdis staat, as ipocritis; for &thorn;ey semen to have an herdis staat, &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ey ben many tymes fendis. for we shulden wite &thorn;is at &thorn;e bigynnyng &thorn;at prestis ben maad prelatis of men, not to lyue worldlyly ne lustly ne proudely, but to lyue in bisy trauel to kepe &thorn;er sheep &amp; wynne hem heuene; &amp; so &thorn;ei moten lyue trewely, trauelously &amp; perelously, si&thorn;en &thorn;ei moten putte &thorn;er oune lif for &thorn;er sheep, as crist dide. to &thorn;is riching of &thorn;ersouns kyn moue&thorn; &thorn;e fend &thorn;es ipocritis bi feyned mersy &amp; bi kynde; &amp; bo&thorn;e he sei&thorn; comen of god. <MILESTONE N="14b" UNIT="page">What man shulde not haue mersy on his pore kyn to helpe hem, for heere is more cause of mersy &thorn;an to helpe o&thorn;ere straunge men; as a man loue&thorn; bi kynde more his lemes &thorn;an o&thorn;ere mennus, so bi kynde he shulde loue more his kyn &thorn;an o&thorn;ere strange men. &amp; by &thorn;is cause many prelatis coueyten to be riche &amp; auaunsen men of &thorn;er kyn, al &yogh;if &thorn;ey ben idiotis; but &thorn;e bileue of iesu 
<PB REF="00000506.tif" N="440"> crist shulde teche men to quenche &thorn;is pride. crist louyde ful wel his kyn, as his modir &amp; his cosyns, but he louyde hem not to be worldly riche but forto lyue a pore lif, bitwixe siche richees &amp; beggyng; for &thorn;us men shulden haue lyued in staat of innocense &amp; staat of blis, &amp; &thorn;is is best for &thorn;e soule &thorn;e which men shulden moost loue. &amp; &thorn;e loue of crist is loue so nedeful to cristenmen, &thorn;at &thorn;er loue is but hate but &yogh;if it be ensaumplid of cristis loue. &amp; &thorn;us clerkis haten &thorn;er kyn &thorn;at maken hem riche of pore mennus godis; for bi &thorn;is &thorn;ey harmen &thorn;er soule &amp; maken hem synne bi many weyes. &thorn;er body is &thorn;us more vnhable to serue &thorn;er soule in temperure, &amp; &thorn;ey ben felowis bi assent to robbe &thorn;es pore men of &thorn;er godis; &amp; no drede cause of &thorn;is pride is vnprofitable to hem, for nobley in vertues shulde be coueytid &amp; worldly nobley litil teld by, but in as myche as it helpide men to kepe nobley in vertues. &amp; in tokene of &thorn;is &thorn;ing crist cam bo&thorn;e of riche men &amp; pore, as of kyngis &amp; bonde men &thorn;e while &thorn;ey lyueden in egipt. &amp; bo&thorn;e &thorn;es condiciouns diden good whanne grace of crist mouyde men to vertues. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;es prelatis harmen &thorn;er kyn to make hem riche on &thorn;is maner. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;es curatis louynge &thorn;us &thorn;er kyn synnen many weyes in maner of loue, for &thorn;ey louen &thorn;er oune fleys more &thorn;an &thorn;ey louen &thorn;er bri&thorn;eren in god, &amp; crist sei&thorn; &thorn;ey ben not wor&thorn;y of crist to be clepid cristenmen; &amp; &yogh;it crist shulde be oure nexste fadir, &amp; his chirche oure nexste modir. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;es prelatis &thorn;at turnen &thorn;is loue synnen bo&thorn;e in god &amp; man, &amp; disusen kyndely wille as don synneris in leccherye; &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ey synnen in mersy &amp; loue &amp; in god &amp; &thorn;er pore parischens. &amp; herfore sei&thorn; poul &thorn;at persouns offiss shulde not be to parte &thorn;es godis, but to preche &amp; teche &thorn;e folc &amp; holde hem payed wi&thorn; fode &amp; hiling. but litil errour &amp; ydilnesse in &thorn;e bigynnyng of a staat bringi&thorn; in <MILESTONE N="15" UNIT="page">more aftir, as it falli&thorn; heere &amp; in o&thorn;ere statis.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="23" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000507.tif" N="441">
<HEAD>Capitulum 23<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>it were forto declare heere &thorn;at ri&yogh;t preching of goddis word is &thorn;e mooste wor&thorn;y dede &thorn;at prestis don heere among men. for crist, mesure of al good, vside moost &thorn;is werk heere &amp; tau&yogh;te whanne he wente to heuene his apostlis to do &thorn;is werk; &amp; &thorn;us, si&thorn;en crist is best maystir, it is shewid of bileue &thorn;at preching is &thorn;e beste werk &thorn;at a prest doi&thorn; in &thorn;is weye. Also goodnesse of werkis is mesurid bi fruyt &thorn;at come&thorn; of hem; but more fruyt come&thorn; of good preching &thorn;an of ony o&thorn;er werk, &amp; &thorn;erfore siche good preching is &thorn;e beste werk &thorn;at a prest doi&thorn;; for bi &thorn;is werk a prest geti&thorn; goddis children &amp; maki&thorn; hem to come to heuene. &amp; herfore sei&thorn; poul to his puple: "in crist iesu<NOTE PLACE="marg">[1 Cor. iv. 15.]</NOTE> y haue gendrid &yogh;ou;" &amp; herfore crist preisi&thorn; more preching of &thorn;e gospel &thorn;at gendri&thorn; &thorn;is chirche &thorn;an gendring of his oune body, al &yogh;if &thorn;ey bo&thorn;e ben gode werkis. &amp; &thorn;us seyn clerkis &thorn;at gendrure, si&thorn; it saue&thorn; comyn kynde, is betere &thorn;an is nurshing &thorn;at saue&thorn; o persone of &thorn;is kynde. &amp; &thorn;us sei&thorn; crist in lukis gospel to a womman &thorn;at blisside cristis modir &amp; sayde, "blissid be &thorn;e wombe &thorn;at bare &thorn;ee &amp; &thorn;e tetis<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Luke xi. 27.]</NOTE> &thorn;at &thorn;ou hast sokun," &amp; crist seyde: "&yogh;e but blissid ben &thorn;ey &thorn;at heren goddis word &amp; kepen it." &amp; bi &thorn;e same skile or myche more &thorn;ei ben blissid &thorn;at prechen goddis word. lord, hou wor&thorn;y werk it is to gendre god in mannus soule bi seed &thorn;at is goddis word; for &thorn;is mut haue greet meede in heuene, bo&thorn;e for &thorn;e werk in hym silf &amp; of &thorn;e children &thorn;at comen &thorn;er-of. &amp; herfore sei&thorn; ioon euangelist &thorn;at he ha&thorn; no more grace heere &thorn;an to here his children go in treu&thorn;e. &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ou seist &thorn;at a prest may not gete siche children in god; certis he may bi help off god, &amp; ellis no man may gete a child, for god &yogh;yue&thorn; bi hym silf &thorn;e soule, &amp; who gat a child but &yogh;if it were &yogh;ouyn? &amp; herfore &thorn;enki&thorn; seynt austyn wel &thorn;at crist dide more myracle bi his apostlis to turne so manye he&thorn;en men in so short while fro so wickid 
<PB REF="00000508.tif" N="442"> lif for to be &thorn;us cristis children, &thorn;an weren o&thorn;ere myraclis of crist; &amp; herfore &thorn;e apostlis chosen more to preche &thorn;an to do bodily almes. Also &thorn;e more &thorn;at crist helpi&thorn; to a werk &thorn;e more it is good; but crist helpi&thorn; more specialy to preching &thorn;an to o&thorn;er werk, &amp; &thorn;erfore it mut nedis be betere for crist endi&thorn; it &thorn;us graciously. &amp; herfore seyn wise doctours &thorn;at it is more to preche wel &thorn;an to do ony o&thorn;er craft, as phisik or alkemonye; &amp; herfore crist <MILESTONE N="15b" UNIT="page">bad his apostlis do many werkis but noon as &thorn;is. for in &thorn;is a prest clo&thorn;i&thorn; hym in cristis persone &amp; geti&thorn; cristis bro&thorn;er, his sister &amp; his modir. &amp; of &thorn;is may a man gedere &thorn;at it is more synne to fayle in &thorn;is &thorn;an to fayle in o&thorn;ere werkis &thorn;at ben not so gode as &thorn;is is. lord, si&thorn; &thorn;e synne of sodom cryede to god for greet veniaunse, hou shal &thorn;is synne &thorn;at letti&thorn; &thorn;is gendrure crye to god to be a-vengid.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="24" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 24<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>it were to wite ouer &thorn;is hou men fallen in &thorn;is synne, &amp; what medicyn were a&yogh;enus it, si&thorn; &thorn;is werk is so precious. &thorn;re maner of folc synnen heere; sumtyme &thorn;e prest &thorn;at shulde preche, &thorn;e puple &thorn;at shulde here &thorn;is preching, &amp; he &thorn;at letti&thorn; goddis word to renne. &thorn;is prechoure may synne on many maners bi &thorn;at &thorn;at he sowi&thorn; not good seed, but iapis &amp; gabbingis or o&thorn;ere tryuolis, &amp; leeue&thorn; to preche &thorn;e word of god. for luk sei&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;at is seed &thorn;at no defaute is foundun ynne, al &yogh;if &thorn;re defautes ben in &thorn;e lond vpon which &thorn;is seed is castun. on o&thorn;er maner &thorn;is prest &thorn;at sowi&thorn; may meddle venym wi&thorn; &thorn;is seed, as whanne he prechi&thorn; for veyn glory or for coueytise of worldly good. &amp; herfore sei&thorn; poul to his puple &thorn;at we ben not holours of goddis word, but of clennesse, as we speken of god, we speken bifore god in crist. &amp; wolde god &thorn;at prechours nou wolde lerne &thorn;is lessoun of poul; &thorn;anne &thorn;ey shulden speke of god &amp; not &thorn;us of rotun seed, &amp; as &thorn;ei weren bifore god, kepinge good maner in &thorn;is lordis presence. &amp; &thorn;ey shulden preche for cristis worchip 
<PB REF="00000509.tif" N="443"> on his maner not for muc. for among alle symonyes &thorn;at euere crist sufferide in &thorn;e chirche &thorn;is is &thorn;e fouleste of alle o&thorn;ere, vsid ofte of prechour beggeres, for &thorn;ey wolen gedere comynly godis aftir &thorn;at &thorn;ey han prechid; o&thorn;er money or corn or what o&thorn;ere godis &thorn;at &thorn;ey may gete. &amp; &thorn;e fonnydnesse of &thorn;e puple maki&thorn; hem parcneris of &thorn;e beggeris synne, for whanne &thorn;ey &yogh;yuen hem godis heere &thorn;ey assenten to &thorn;er symonye. &amp; &thorn;is is a foul errour &thorn;at many seyn in &thorn;is mater &thorn;at &thorn;ey &yogh;yuen for goddis loue &amp; &thorn;at is ynow for hem, for certis &thorn;is wiss lord axi&thorn; bo&thorn;e his godis &amp; good maner. &amp; for &thorn;is good maner man ha&thorn; meede, &amp; &yogh;if he fayli&thorn; hym wanti&thorn; meede; &amp; to destrie &thorn;is errour sei&thorn; crist in &thorn;e gospel of seynt matheu &thorn;at summe dampnyd men shulen seye to crist: "sire,<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Matt. vii. 22.]</NOTE> kestiden we not out fendis <MILESTONE N="16" UNIT="page">in &thorn;y name &amp; diden vertues in &thorn;y name?" but crist shal seye to &thorn;ese men: "so&thorn;ely, y seye to &yogh;ou y knowe &yogh;ou not as children of blis, for &yogh;ee failiden of good maner." lord, si&thorn; &thorn;es men shulen be dampnyd &thorn;at prechen goddis word in cristis name &amp; casten out fendis &amp; don vertues, what meede shulen &thorn;es beggeris haue, &thorn;at faylen in &thorn;is &amp; ly&yogh;en on crist &amp; seyn &thorn;at crist beggide &thorn;us to holde vp &thorn;er newe ordris. crist wiste ful wel &thorn;at &thorn;es shulden come whanne he bad hem not go fro hous to hous,<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Mark vi. 8-10.]</NOTE> but dwelle in oon &amp; wende not &thorn;ennus, &amp; bere not vpon &thorn;er backis baggis ne sachels to begge &thorn;us.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="25" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 25<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>as anentis two o&thorn;ere defautis &thorn;at letten goddis word to growe, crist telli&thorn; &thorn;re defautis in &thorn;e er&thorn;e &thorn;at shulde take &thorn;is word. summen ben bi-syde &thorn;e weye, &amp; so bisied wi&thorn; &thorn;e world &thorn;at goddis word taki&thorn; not wi&thorn; hem, but &thorn;e fendis letten it. o&thorn;ere men ben drye as stoons &amp; han no delit in wordis but &yogh;if &thorn;ey sounen to worldly wynnyng, &amp; &thorn;ese wanten bo&thorn;e grace &amp; wisdom. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde maner of men &thorn;at heren goddis word ben so prickid wi&thorn; worldly richees &thorn;at &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000510.tif" N="444"> &thorn;enking on &thorn;es godis letti&thorn; &thorn;e word of god to growe; &amp; to &thorn;es &thorn;re may be reducid al &thorn;e synne in &thorn;e hereris. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde men synnen more, as ben emperour prelatis &thorn;at wolen not suffere a man to preche whanne he telli&thorn; &thorn;er defautis but whanne he preisi&thorn; hem &amp; herne, &amp; &thorn;is nurschi&thorn; myche synne. for siche prelatis &thorn;at kunnen not preche or wolen not for bisynesse, &amp; letten o&thorn;ere trewe prestis to preche bi &thorn;er lordly cautels, passen &thorn;e fend in &thorn;is synne bi menes &thorn;at he ha&thorn; ordeyned to hem. for &thorn;e fend ha&thorn; no iurisdiccioun ne feyned power as &thorn;ey han, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;at he may not do hym-silf he doi&thorn; bi siche seruauntis to hym. &amp; no drede &thorn;is is &thorn;e fendis dede to lette men to sowe goddis word, for &thorn;erby &thorn;er soulis shulden be fed &amp; goddis worchip be don of men, but &thorn;ey maken a goostly hungir &amp; stoppen &thorn;e worchip of god. but where is a worse condicioun folowinge prelatis of anticrist? it were yuel to lette gendrure maad in laweful matrymonye, &thorn;at pharao dide not in egipt but dreynte &thorn;e children whanne &thorn;ey weren borun, but &thorn;is is worse wi&thorn;-outen mesure to lette &thorn;us crist to be gendrid in men. siche a prelat semy&thorn; a wickid hayward to lette trewe men forto trauele &amp; go euene bi goddis weye, in which crist ha&thorn; &yogh;ouyn hem leeue to go. for god &thorn;at &yogh;yue&thorn; siche wit &amp; wille shapi&thorn; &thorn;e puple to take &thorn;is seed. <MILESTONE N="16b" UNIT="page">&amp; it is al oon to seye &thorn;at y shul lette &thorn;ee bi iurisdiccioun, &amp; to seye &thorn;is is a place &thorn;at &thorn;e fend is lord of &amp; not crist; &amp; as &thorn;es wordis ben nedis false, so is &thorn;is iurisdiccioun; for he ha&thorn; no ri&yogh;t to seye &thorn;es wordis, but &thorn;ei ben falsly feyned of &thorn;e fend. &amp; freris procuren comynly bo&thorn;e lordis &amp; bischops to lette &thorn;is preching, so &thorn;at &thorn;er fals preching be sprad &amp; &thorn;er wynnyng a&yogh;enus crist, &amp; &thorn;us is &thorn;e puple robbid of goostly help &amp; bodily. We graunten &thorn;at iurisdiccioun shulde lette false prechours to preche; but nou ha&thorn; &thorn;e fend turnyd cristis chirche bi his prelatis, &thorn;at he &thorn;at wolde treuly preche &thorn;e word of &thorn;e gospel wi&thorn;-outen hire, he shal be put a-bac, &amp; contrarie prechour shal be takun, &amp; &thorn;us wickid hay|wardis of &thorn;e fend letten &thorn;is seed &thorn;at crist shulde sowe.</P>


</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="26" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000511.tif" N="445">
<HEAD>Capitulum 26<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>ant &thorn;us &thorn;er ben many causis &thorn;at letten goddis word to renne, &amp; &thorn;e fend ha&thorn; trauelid aboute &thorn;es causis many &yogh;eer ful bisily; for trewe preching of goddis word displesi&thorn; myche to &thorn;e fend. o cause is dowing of &thorn;e chirche &amp; riching &thorn;er-of ouer cristis wille, for bi &thorn;is prelatis slepen in synne &amp; ben to fatte to preche &thorn;e puple, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;er bisynesse is stoppid to gete hem more of worldly muc. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei fallen in an-o&thorn;er cause &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben not payed of poulis reule to haue ynow of fode &amp; hiling. &amp; heere breken out &thorn;es freris ordris, for al &yogh;if &thorn;ei han no worldly lordchip as han prestis &thorn;at ben dowid, &yogh;it &thorn;ei spuylen men of moeblis &amp; wasten hem in noumbre &amp; housis, &amp; &thorn;is excees is more synne &thorn;an synne of &thorn;e fend in o persone. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ey turnen &thorn;e ende of &thorn;er preching for-to gete hem siche godis. &amp; &thorn;is entent mut nedis make falsed in maner of &thorn;er preching, for &thorn;ei shapen &thorn;er sermouns more to gete hem good &thorn;an to profite to &thorn;e chirche; &amp; as &thorn;e firste wile of &thorn;e fend bigan soone in siluestris tyme, so &thorn;is secound wile bigan in grounding of &thorn;es newe ordris. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde cause &thorn;at letti&thorn; trewe preching is appropring of chirches. for whanne chirches ben approprid, &thorn;es curatis tellen not bi &thorn;is preching, as munkis or chanouns or o&thorn;ere collegies, but bi gedering of godis; &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ey ben maad slowe to preche &amp; stronge to gedere dymes to hem. &amp; &thorn;is cautel cam latere yn &amp; is alarged by &thorn;e pope. &thorn;e four&thorn;e cause is bringing in of false freris bi many cuntreys; for, as it is seid bifore, &thorn;ei letten trewe preching to renne &amp; maken curatis bi many weyes to leeue &thorn;is moost wor&thorn;y offiss. First &thorn;ey robben hem many weyes &amp; maken hem bisy for to lyue, for &thorn;ey deprauen hem to &thorn;er parischens bi flori&yogh;shid wordis &thorn;at &thorn;ey bringen yn; &amp; no drede &thorn;ey shapen &thorn;er sermouns bi dyuy <MILESTONE N="17" UNIT="page">siouns &amp; o&thorn;ere iapis &thorn;at &thorn;ey maken moost plese &thorn;e puple. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ey erren in bileue &amp; maken &thorn;e puple to trowe to hem &thorn;at sermouns ben nou&yogh;t but in &thorn;er 
<PB REF="00000512.tif" N="446"> foorme &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei stoppen symple curatis &thorn;at &thorn;ei doren not preche to &thorn;e puple, &amp; &thorn;is defaute of preching of crist is more &thorn;an defaute in hereris. &amp; so as crist sei&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel, bo&thorn;e sodom &amp; gomor shulen be lesse punyshid at domes day &thorn;an &thorn;es newe sectis brou&yogh;t yn; for &thorn;ey synneden in mannus seed, but &thorn;es synnen in seed of god, &thorn;at is goddis word, &thorn;at prestis shulden preche to turne &thorn;e lewid puple to god. &amp; as it is seyd bifore, &thorn;e puple is smyttid bi &thorn;is synne, for &thorn;e puple assenti&thorn; to hem bi iapis &amp; wilis &thorn;at &thorn;ey tellen hem. &thorn;e puple shulde not trowe to &thorn;e prechour what euere he seye in &thorn;is staat, but &yogh;if his word be groundid in god as goddis lawe or suynge &thorn;er-of. for &thorn;is staat is not couenable to telle iapis ne bourdis to men, but &thorn;at &thorn;at wole trewely fede &thorn;er soule, as is &thorn;e gospel &amp; o&thorn;er goddis lawe. &amp; &thorn;is bourding or o&thorn;ere iapis shulde make &thorn;es freris suspect heere &amp; make hem wante worldly wynnyng, for &thorn;ey ben wor&thorn;y myche more peyne; but lewidnesse of &thorn;e puple maki&thorn; hem nurshe &thorn;er mooste enemyes. &amp; god make &thorn;is enemyte knowun. for &thorn;is is &thorn;e laste &amp; &thorn;e mooste fendis cautel; but good wille &amp; trewe speche of goddis lawe shulde make hem knowun. for failing of goddis word &amp; coueytise of mennus good shewen opinly to men whoos children &thorn;at &thorn;ey ben. lord, si&thorn;en pari&yogh;shens shulden take &thorn;e preching of &thorn;er oune curat &amp; &thorn;e mynistring &thorn;at he shulde do, for &thorn;at shulde suffise to &thorn;at puple, Why shulden not men fle fro &thorn;es false prophetis, as crist biddi&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel? but bullis of &thorn;e court of rome blynden many men heere, for it seme&thorn; &thorn;e hed of errour &amp; propre nest of anticrist.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="27" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 2[7<SUP>m.</SUP>]</HEAD>
<P>of &thorn;is may wise men see &thorn;at &thorn;es foure sectis newe brou&yogh;t in, as emperour clerkis, munkis &amp; chanouns &amp; &thorn;es foure ordris of freris, disturblen moost &thorn;is fi&yogh;tinge chirche &amp; putten it fro &thorn;e cours of crist, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;es men &thorn;at nurshen hem, as worldly lordis &amp; fonnyd comyns &amp; lewid 
<PB REF="00000513.tif" N="447"> prestis, &thorn;at kunnen not speke or doren not speke in goddis cause, nurshen anticrist &amp; hise traytourly a&yogh;enus crist. &thorn;at ordre &thorn;at crist ha&thorn; ordeyned in his chirche shulden we holde, &amp; mende errours in &thorn;is ordre; &amp; not bringe in newe charg to &thorn;e chirche. for <MILESTONE N="17b" UNIT="page">as wanting of gode partis is defaute in oure modir body, so superfluyte is defaute in &thorn;e same body; For &thorn;is bringi&thorn; in ydilnesse &amp; charging of hooly chirche. &amp; bileue techi&thorn; men &thorn;at &thorn;er is as myche wit in &thorn;e ordenaunse of crist as in &thorn;e wordis of his gospel; and bileue techi&thorn; ouer &thorn;at crist faylide not to his chirche to &yogh;yue his ordenaunse to it in &thorn;e making of hir partis. for men putten as myche wit or more to good ordenaunse of man as to worching of man aftir &thorn;is ordenaunse bifore. for wisere men moten ordeyne first, &amp; lesse wiss moten worche &thorn;er-aftir. &amp; &thorn;is moue&thorn; many men to speke a&yogh;enus &thorn;es foure sectis, for no man kan grounde hem in &thorn;e ordenaunse of cristis lawe, &amp; no man sei&thorn; &thorn;at crist for&yogh;at hem &yogh;if crist wolde &thorn;at &thorn;ey weren of his chirche; &amp; &thorn;us men putten vpon crist o&thorn;er foly or necgligense. but who shulde here &thorn;is blasfemye but &yogh;if he spake sharply a&yogh;enus it? cristis ordenaunse is put bi-hynde &amp; his lore, &amp; o&thorn;er brou&yogh;t in, &amp; &thorn;is turne&thorn; &thorn;e chirche vpsedoun, &amp; letti&thorn; men to serue crist. and lewid foolis, &thorn;at arguen heere &thorn;at crist ordeyned not &thorn;is prest, shulden lerne &thorn;e lawe of porfirie, hou god ordeynede in a comyn &thorn;ing alle &thorn;e synguleris &thorn;er-of. &amp; &thorn;us dwelle &thorn;ou in &thorn;e iust boundis &thorn;at god ha&thorn; ordeyned for his prest, &amp; &thorn;anne god ha&thorn; ordeyned &thorn;ee in &thorn;e comyn kynde of prestis. but anticrist can-not grounde &thorn;at god ordeynede &thorn;e kynde of popis, ne of o&thorn;ere emperour clerkis, ne of munkis, ne of chanouns, ne of foure ordris of freris, al &yogh;if he ordeynede good to come of hem; as god ordeynede no man to synne al &yogh;if he ordeynede good to come of synne. &amp; &thorn;es foure ordris smacchen synne, si&thorn;en &thorn;ei tellen not first cristis ordenaunse, but bringing yn of &thorn;e fend to reuerse &thorn;e ordenaunse of crist. &amp; &thorn;us lordis of &thorn;is world &thorn;at mayntenen lumpis of &thorn;es ordris &amp; &thorn;er housis &amp; possessiouns, wi&thorn; o&thorn;ere &thorn;ingis &thorn;at &thorn;ey han foundun, moten 
<PB REF="00000514.tif" N="448"> nedis synne, in as myche as &thorn;ei reuersen cristis ordenaunse, &amp; in &thorn;at &thorn;at &thorn;ey letten pore prestis to preche &thorn;e gospel to &thorn;e puple, al &yogh;if &thorn;ey ben not of &thorn;es newe ordris &thorn;at ben closid in cayms castels. y rede not of cristis apostlis &thorn;at &thorn;ey kepten &thorn;is maner of preching, whanne &thorn;e hooly goost hadde tau&yogh;t hem to gete to crist al &thorn;is world. &amp; &thorn;at prest &thorn;at sue&thorn; &thorn;is goost is in &thorn;at ordre &thorn;at crist ha&thorn; ordeyned. wedding wi&thorn; &thorn;es newe bilawis, passinge &thorn;e wedding wi&thorn; goddis lawe, maki&thorn; &thorn;es newe rotun sectis &amp; putti&thorn; bi-hynde &thorn;e sect of crist. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;es ordris newe brou&yogh;t in bringen wi&thorn; hem a newe bileue, &thorn;at noon of cristis sect wi&thorn;-outen hem lyue&thorn; so hoolyly as &thorn;ey, &thorn;at lordis han a passinge merit to grounde &thorn;es ordris &amp; &yogh;yue hem godis, but &thorn;ey <MILESTONE N="18" UNIT="page">wolen not do &thorn;is charite, be &thorn;ey neuere woxun so ryche, but &thorn;ey wolden ra&thorn;ere destrie o&thorn;ere newe ordris &thorn;at ben brou&yogh;t in; &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;e laste ordre of freris sei&thorn; a&yogh;enus goddis lawe &thorn;at willeful begging is more meedeful &thorn;an ony lif of &thorn;es o&thorn;ere ordris.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="28" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 28<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>men may se bi lif of ordris hou cristis ordenaunse is lettid. crist ordeynede, as hym &thorn;ou&yogh;te best, &thorn;at his disciplis aftir his steying to heuene shulden be departid oon fro an o&thorn;er. &amp; ech of hem shulde haue his folc, &amp; shulden not be weddid wi&thorn; mannus lawe, ne wi&thorn; folc, ne wi&thorn; housis, but holde hem payed of goddis lawe, &amp; chaunge folc as god mouyde hem, &amp; haue no propre dwelling of &thorn;er oune, as crist &thorn;er maystir tau&yogh;te bifore. Al &thorn;is is reuersid nou bi help &amp; assent of men; for herto helpen &thorn;e pope &amp; prelatis, worldly lordis &amp; ordris hem silf, &amp; pore men ben nedid to helpe as beestis led to be killid. costly chirchis of &thorn;es ordris &amp; o&thorn;ere housis &thorn;at &thorn;ey han destrien olde pari&yogh;s chirchis &thorn;at weren ordeyned bi cristis apostlis. &amp; si&thorn; crist is lord of alle &amp; not contrarie to hym silf, no drede men han not his godis &thorn;us to reuerse his ordenaunse; &amp; &thorn;us ben manye 
<PB REF="00000515.tif" N="449"> cayms castels maad &amp; maytened to &thorn;es ordris a&yogh;enus leeue of &thorn;e cheef lord. but who dredi&thorn; &thorn;at ne he is wro&thorn; her-wi&thorn;? &amp; &thorn;is seme&thorn; &thorn;e cause of werris &amp; wrongis &thorn;at ben nou growun in &thorn;e chirche. lordis &amp; men &thorn;at mi&yogh;ten helpe heere shulden make men turne to cristis ordre. &amp; &yogh;if persouns hadden no glebe &amp; no propre hous as eritage, &thorn;ey sueden more crist &amp; his apostlis; &amp; wolde god &thorn;ey wolden do &thorn;us. For it is takun of bileue &thorn;at &thorn;e ordenaunse of crist bi-syde siche housis &amp; cloystris spedi&thorn; more to do his seruyss &thorn;an siche contrarie ordenaunsis; &amp; her-fore &thorn;es newe ordris moten nedis lyue contrarie to crist. for si&thorn;en ordenaunsis &amp; lyues gon to-gidere of men heere, as cristis ordenaunse is chaungid, so lyues of &thorn;es lumpis ben chaungid, &amp; no drede to &thorn;e worse, as mannus ordenaunse is worse &thorn;an cristis. &amp; &yogh;it lordis of &thorn;is world to whom crist was so kynde ben not payed of &thorn;is reuersinge, but ben brou&yogh;t in bi &thorn;e fend to haue dwellinge in &thorn;er housis bo&thorn;e curatis &amp; &thorn;es newe ordris, as &thorn;ou mayst se in lordis housis persouns or munkis or chanouns &amp; algatis freris to lede &thorn;er meyne. but god mut algatis punyshe &thorn;is, for &thorn;es persouns shulden kepe &thorn;er sheep aftir &thorn;e lawe &thorn;at god ha&thorn; &yogh;ouyn hem. but who may reuerse goddis ordenaunse <MILESTONE N="18b" UNIT="page">heere but &yogh;if he renne in his offense, &amp; &thorn;us lordis synnen heere bo&thorn;e a&yogh;enus god &amp; man &amp; letten goddis pees to be tau&yogh;t, &amp; &thorn;us londis moten nedis be dis|turblid. &amp; as anentis &thorn;es newe ordris &thorn;at ben scaterid in lordis housis, it is a more vnkyndly wondir, &amp; helpi&thorn; &thorn;e fend to marre &thorn;er housis. for as &thorn;ey seyn &thorn;at groundiden &thorn;es cloystris, &thorn;es men my&yogh;ten no more dwelle out &thorn;er-of &thorn;an fi&yogh;s my&yogh;te dwelle out of water, for vertu &thorn;at &thorn;ey han &thorn;er|ynne. for ellis &thorn;es cloystris weren not nedeful ne &thorn;er oo&thorn; to kepe &thorn;er reule. &amp; siche wondris newe brou&yogh;t in moten nedis marre men of &thorn;e world, for daliaunse wi&thorn; newe deuels bringi&thorn; in newe giles to lette cristenmen. but sum men grucchen more heere &thorn;at persouns ben holden &thorn;us traytourly a&yogh;enus &thorn;e seruyss &thorn;at crist ha&thorn; lymytid to kepe &thorn;e soulis of his sheep, &amp; no drede crist preisi&thorn; moost &thorn;is offiss among 
<PB REF="00000516.tif" N="450"> alle o&thorn;ere, &amp; &yogh;it consenten &thorn;es worldly lordis in cowardise a&yogh;enus crist, for &thorn;ey destrien not siche traytours of god, but &thorn;at shulde be &thorn;er hye offiss.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="29" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 29<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>men my&yogh;ten heere touche ouer &thorn;is what maner man is able bi god to be chosun to curatis offiss, &amp; who shulde chese hym, &amp; on what maner. &amp; no drede siche a prest &thorn;at ha&thorn; bo&thorn;e wit &amp; wille to do &thorn;e &thorn;re offisis of an herde, &thorn;at ben teld bifore tyme, shulde be takun to &thorn;is offis aftir &thorn;e lawe &amp; wille of god. but who shulde chese hym &thorn;erto is myche strif by mannus lawe; as &thorn;e pope sei&thorn; &thorn;at he shulde lymyte alle curatis to siche offisis. bischops seyn &thorn;at &thorn;ei shulden &yogh;yue siche offiss who euere presenti&thorn;, &amp; lewyd patrouns seyn &thorn;at &thorn;ey shulden presente to siche offiss bi &thorn;er lordchip, but goddis lawe telli&thorn; litil or nou&yogh;t of siche chesing of curatis. &amp; no drede &thorn;at ne coueytise &amp; pride reyngnen in alle &thorn;es &thorn;re cheseris, for &thorn;e pope ha&thorn; &thorn;e firste fruytis &amp; many &yogh;iftis gon bi symonye, &amp; two o&thorn;ere axen seruyss of hym &thorn;at &thorn;ey maken curat. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;enken summen &thorn;at bi goddis lawe &amp; resoun curatis shulden wel do &thorn;er offiss &amp; haue no more but fode &amp; hiling, &amp; o&thorn;er &thorn;e puple &thorn;at shulde be tau&yogh;t or prestis bi &thorn;er oune wille shulden chese &thorn;is seruyss of prestis; &amp; &thorn;anne it were more meedeful, and no strif shulde &thorn;anne falle aboute &thorn;e godis of &thorn;is curat, for he shulde haue no wast godis but &thorn;at &thorn;at were nedeful to his offiss. &amp; instuyng wi&thorn; inducting &amp; many o&thorn;ere mannus lawis weren not to charge, but ri&yogh;t offiss &thorn;at &thorn;is curat shulde do. &amp; it semy&thorn; a greet &thorn;raldom brou&yogh;t in bi anticrist &thorn;at a puple &thorn;at &thorn;e pope knowi&thorn; not, as he knowi&thorn; not &thorn;is able prest, shulde be nedid bi &thorn;e pope to take &thorn;is prest, &amp; &yogh;yue hym godis more &thorn;an goddis <MILESTONE N="19" UNIT="page">lawe lymyti&thorn; hou euere &thorn;at he mynistre; for bo&thorn;e &thorn;is almes shulde be meedeful &amp; frely don bi goddis lawe, &amp; it were to greet seruage to nede men 
<PB REF="00000517.tif" N="451"> to &yogh;yue &thorn;er godis to a prest &thorn;at dide hem harm, &yogh;e &yogh;if he were cause of &thorn;er dampnyng. but &thorn;e fendis part is so strong, &amp; streng&thorn;id bi ipocrisie &thorn;at mannus lawe is so hooly &amp; biddi&thorn; men to obesche &thorn;erto vp payne of &thorn;er dampnacioun, &thorn;at goddis lawe is put bihynde. men shulden bi goddis lawe &yogh;yue &thorn;is almes frely &amp; wisely to &thorn;at prelat &thorn;at seruede hem trewely in &thorn;is offiss, and so &thorn;ey moten kunne goddis lawe &amp; holde hem payed of &thorn;is &yogh;ifte, for &thorn;us diden poul &amp; o&thorn;ere apostlis. what lawe shulde reuerse &thorn;is resoun? &amp; it semy&thorn; not a popis offiss to make &thorn;us prelatis in vnknowun cuntreys; for it is ne&thorn;er groundid in goddis lawe &thorn;at &thorn;er shulde be siche a pope ne &thorn;at he shulde &thorn;us reule &thorn;e puple bi &thorn;e lordchip of his lawe. &amp; no drede &yogh;if &thorn;es two shulden be, crist wolde haue ensaumplid hem; for crist failide not in siche hye poyntis &thorn;at weren so nedeful to his chirche. &amp; &thorn;us crist in leeuyng of &thorn;is techi&thorn; &thorn;at it shulde not be, for ellis crist were defauty in ordeynyng for his chirche.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="30" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 30<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>&yogh;it trewe men han delit to reherse &thorn;is bileue, for it is more precious &thorn;an ony gold or precious stoon, &amp; triacle to lordis &amp; many o&thorn;ere to a&yogh;enstonde &thorn;e fend &amp; hise. &amp; &thorn;is bileue stondi&thorn; in &thorn;is, &thorn;at no man shulde sue o&thorn;er pope ne bishop ne ony aungel but in as myche as he sue&thorn; crist, for crist is bo&thorn;e god &amp; man. &amp; &thorn;is bileue wolde teche lordis to purge &thorn;er reumes of anticrist; &amp; si&thorn;en &thorn;ei han many skiles &thorn;at prestis shulden not be &thorn;us dowid, bo&thorn;e bi &thorn;e olde lawe &amp; &thorn;e newe, &amp; bi &thorn;e lif &thorn;at crist ledde, &thorn;ey shulden be heere hardy in bileue &amp; lette &thorn;is dowing of anticrist, &amp; ne&thorn;er obesche to pope ne bischop but &yogh;if &thorn;ey tau&yogh;ten &thorn;at &thorn;ey sueden crist in &thorn;is. &amp; seyntis &thorn;at &thorn;ey kunnen alegge shulden ne&thorn;er be heere suyd ne trowid, but &yogh;if it be tau&yogh;t &thorn;at &thorn;ei sueden crist in &thorn;at &thorn;at &thorn;ey helden wi&thorn; &thorn;is dowing. &amp; si&thorn;en lordis han conscience her-of &amp; it is synne to do a&yogh;enus conscience, &thorn;ey 
<PB REF="00000518.tif" N="452"> shulden axe of popis &amp; prelatis hou &thorn;ey grounden &thorn;is in crist. &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ey wolen not or kunnen not, in &thorn;at &thorn;ey shewen &thorn;at &thorn;ey ben foolis to holde &thorn;is &amp; lyue &thorn;er-aftir, si&thorn; it is not groundid vpon crist. &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ey seyn &thorn;at crist groundi&thorn; it to be don of his vikeris, shewe &thorn;ey where &amp; in what maner, &amp; &thorn;anne &thorn;er conscience is clerid. &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ey <MILESTONE N="19b" UNIT="page">gabben or feynen heere men shulden not trowe hem in &thorn;is, but haue hem suspect of errour, si&thorn; &thorn;ey suen not crist in &thorn;is. for crist was neuere axid questioun &thorn;at ne he suyde his godhed &amp; made asee&thorn; vpon resoun to hem &thorn;at axiden &thorn;is questioun of hym. &amp; &thorn;us shul|den kyngis axe &thorn;e pope hou he groundi&thorn; &thorn;is dowing on crist, &amp; to robbe &thorn;us reumes, &amp; to make hym prelatis at his wille, si&thorn; crist tau&yogh;te his apostlis to chese mathy bi lot. &amp; &thorn;is principle of bileue shulden prestis holde &amp; lerne goddis lawe, &amp; not obesche to pope or bishop but in &thorn;at &thorn;at crist groundi&thorn; it; &amp; in &thorn;is cause &thorn;ey may chalenge help of &thorn;er er&thorn;ely lord, &amp;, &yogh;if hem faylide help heere, be redy to suffere martirdom. &amp; ciprian made &thorn;is lawe, &amp; it is in &thorn;e popis bokis, &thorn;at crist onely shulde be herd in &thorn;at &thorn;at he speki&thorn; moost principaly. &amp; &thorn;us si&thorn; ne&thorn;er popis ne bischopis kunnen grounde bi crist &thorn;is curatis offiss, ne &thorn;at &thorn;ey shulden &thorn;us make persouns, &thorn;e chirche shulde a&yogh;enstonde hem &amp; turne a&yogh;en to goddis lawe in &thorn;e lyuyng of curatis. &amp; it falli&thorn; to kyngis heere to ordeyne &thorn;es prelatis bi goddis lawe, for &thorn;ey shulden quykene &thorn;e kyngis puple &amp; helpe &thorn;at &thorn;e kynge ledde not deuels. &amp; si&thorn; &thorn;is is &thorn;e fouleste offiss &thorn;at men han heere in er&thorn;e, kyngis shulden helpe &amp; mayntene &thorn;er curatis a&yogh;enus anticrist &amp; hise; &amp; &thorn;us &yogh;if &thorn;is bileue of poul were wisely suyd of clerkis &amp; defendid of worldly lordis, as &thorn;ey ben holdun to defende it, errours of reumes shulden be destried &thorn;at ben brou&yogh;t in bi anti|crist. for wise curatis shulden a&yogh;enstonde it &amp; seculer lordis shulden mayntene hem, &amp; &thorn;us noon errour in goddis lawe reyngny&thorn; but for foly of clerkis, &amp; for slou&thorn;e of worldly lordis &thorn;at helpen not heere a&yogh;enus &thorn;e fend. &amp; &thorn;us of alle worldly godis &thorn;at clerkis han in &thorn;er hond, bo&thorn;e clerkis &amp; pore men shulden be lordis of &thorn;es godis, for &thorn;ey shulden 
<PB REF="00000519.tif" N="453"> lyue in grace &amp; haue of hem &thorn;at hem nedi&thorn;; &amp; no drede &thorn;es two shulden be goostly lordis &amp; not worldly. &amp; many men may be to-gedere &thorn;us goostly lordis of o &thorn;yng, &amp; haue vss &thorn;at acordi&thorn; to hem of &thorn;e same &thorn;ing wi&thorn;-outen chiding, as seyntes &thorn;at ben in heuene han vss of alle &thorn;es worldly godis, but &thorn;ey wasten not &thorn;es godis but han ioye &thorn;at goddis wille is don of hem; &amp; &thorn;is is &thorn;e freest vss &thorn;at men han off worldly godis. &amp; &thorn;us &yogh;if &thorn;is principle of bileue were wel practisid of &thorn;e chirche, goddis lawe shulde turne a&yogh;en &amp; mannus lawe shulde be dispisid, for no dedis shulden be acceptid but &yogh;if &thorn;ey ben groundid in cristis lawe, &amp; so alle maner of men <MILESTONE N="20" UNIT="page">shulden stonde in ground of crist &amp; his lawe.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="31" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 31<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>it were for to wite ouer &thorn;is hou cristis chirche is disseyued bi suppliyng of vikeris, &amp; &thorn;es persouns ben absent &thorn;e while. for &thorn;es persouns moten nedis serue crist or in doynge wel or in sufferinge, &amp; herfore &thorn;ey han of cristis chirche &thorn;er large hire of goddis godis. ech siche persoun mut nedis answere bi resoun to god for alle his sheep, but mannus lawe bigili&thorn; not god to answere &thorn;us for herdis offiss, &amp; &thorn;erfore it mut be groundid in goddis lawe to holde &thorn;us residense bi vikere. but it semy&thorn; certeyn of goddis lawe &thorn;at noon may teche &thorn;is bi resoun to be &thorn;us herde of &thorn;es sheep, &amp; to be &thorn;us absent fro hem; &amp; herfore it semy&thorn; not but to be a feynyng of &thorn;e fend. &amp; &thorn;erfore &thorn;is herdis floc may resonably wi&thorn;-drawe his hire for he traueli&thorn; not on hem bi &thorn;at lawe &thorn;at he axi&thorn; his hire. &amp; cursing is a fendis fynding to curse men &thorn;us for worldly godis; for &thorn;anne hauyng of &thorn;es godis is more desirid &thorn;an blessing of &thorn;er sheep; but who may holde charite &amp; &thorn;us chese &thorn;is worldly hauyng? for a man shulde loue more his sheep &thorn;an alle his godis or his body, si&thorn; he shulde putte his lif for his sheep, as crist dide. &amp; &thorn;is moue&thorn; many men to sette litil bi siche cursing; for whanne man curse&thorn; vn|skilefuly, 
<PB REF="00000520.tif" N="454"> he cursi&thorn; hym silf &amp; not his sheep. also &thorn;re offisis of goostly herde moten haue his presence wi&thorn; his sheep; for who can preche to his sheep, or defende hem fro wolues, or heele hem as curatis shulden, but &yogh;if he be present wi&thorn; his sheep? &amp; &thorn;us siche residense bi viker maki&thorn; hym to leese herdis offiss &amp; &thorn;is excusi&thorn; hym not to god, ne his seruyss in &thorn;e mene tyme maki&thorn; hym herde of &thorn;es sheep, ne wor&thorn;y to take &thorn;is hire of god. &yogh;if he waste tyme in &thorn;is absence &amp; profite not to hooly chirche, &thorn;ys los of tyme accusi&thorn; hym bifore crist, &thorn;e firste herde. &yogh;if he do good to &thorn;e chirche in preiyng or in studiynge, leue, what is &thorn;is to herdis offis, al &yogh;if it dispose men &thorn;erto. men may wel &yogh;yue to siche &thorn;er almes, but not as to herdis of hem. &amp; si&thorn; god hati&thorn; falsed of men, &thorn;is shulde not be don bifore god. &amp; si&thorn; a man in no staat shulde do ou&yogh;t &thorn;at he shamede to do bifore god, it semy&thorn; &thorn;at no man shulde holde &thorn;is offiss &amp; be absent in his body. &amp; &thorn;us men ben not contynuel herdis for &thorn;e tyme &thorn;at &thorn;ey ben absent &amp; kepen not &thorn;er sheep bi &thorn;er presence, al &yogh;if &thorn;ey profiten to &thorn;es men. for <MILESTONE N="20b" UNIT="page">ech man &thorn;at is in grace profiti&thorn; to ech able man goostly, &amp; &thorn;us ech siche were herde of ech, but &thorn;is abusioun were to straunge. &yogh;if a man be presently ny&yogh; his sheep, &amp; fayle not to fede hem &amp; to defende hem &amp; to greesse hem in tyme, his bodily presense is skileful to hym to dwelle vpon &thorn;es sheep. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;e persoun &thorn;at al &thorn;e wouke disposi&thorn; hym to preche to his sheep or to defende hem &amp; greesse hem, so &thorn;at his absense be resonable, dwelli&thorn; a shepparde al &thorn;is tyme; &amp; his presence doi&thorn; his cure &amp; counforti&thorn; his sheep &amp; febli&thorn; &thorn;er enemyes. &amp; as glotouns arguen &thorn;at bi &thorn;e same skile &thorn;ey may ete more til &thorn;at &thorn;ey han etun to myche, so hirid hynes arguen heere &thorn;at, bi &thorn;e same skile &thorn;at &thorn;ey may be absent fro &thorn;es sheep foure dayes or<NOTE PLACE="foot">of MS</NOTE> fyue, &thorn;ey may be absent for a mone&thorn;e or an half &yogh;eer or more tyme: &amp; &thorn;is resoun ha&thorn; more colour of herdis &thorn;at studien in scole. &amp; y can-not answere heere &yogh;if men studien goddis lawe, &amp; in &thorn;e mene tyme failen 
<PB REF="00000521.tif" N="455"> not to &thorn;er sheep in &thorn;ingis &thorn;at perteynen to &thorn;er offiss. but for bodily residense of an able herde vpon his sheep is more sikir &thorn;an siche absence, it is good to chese &thorn;e sikere. also as poul sei&thorn;, ech man shal bere his oune charge, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;e viker of &thorn;is herde is chargid for his oune persone as myche as he may bere, hou beri&thorn; he &thorn;e persouns charge? For in tyme of apostlis &thorn;at iurisdiccioun was not brou&yogh;t in, but oon shulde preche in o tyme &amp; an-o&thorn;er in an-o&thorn;er; alle &thorn;es weren persouns of &thorn;es sheep &amp; he &thorn;at more tau&yogh;te was betere curat. &amp; &thorn;us it semy&thorn; &thorn;at it shulde be of many persones of o pari&yogh;s, &amp; &thorn;at persoun &thorn;at profiti&thorn; more is betere herde to &thorn;is pari&yogh;s. for ellis men my&yogh;ten feyne falsly as many herdis as &thorn;ey wolden, &amp; echoon to pile &thorn;e puple where oon sufficide for hem alle. as prest &amp; viker &amp; persoun, official, erchedekene &amp; bischop, wi&thorn; many men bitwixe hem, ben ful chargious to &thorn;e pari&yogh;s, &amp; &thorn;ei alle don not &thorn;e offiss &thorn;at a good herde shulde do; but siche charging of &thorn;e chirche shulde be fled as greet synne. for it is nou&yogh;t to bigile god &amp; make an vnhable man persoun &thorn;at can-not on herdis cure but his sheep kunnen gouerne hym, al &yogh;if he gedere bi a proctour &thorn;e fruytis, as offeringis &amp; dymes. for ellis a child or a greke or what offis &thorn;at he bare my&yogh;te be persoun heere in englond &yogh;if &thorn;e pope hadde &yogh;ouyn hym leeue, but siche &thorn;at is not goddis orde|naunse excusi&thorn; not at domes day.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="32" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 32<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>by &thorn;is sentence may men se hou &thorn;is prelacye is perelous for it is not fully groundid in crist <MILESTONE N="21" UNIT="page">ne in o&thorn;er of his lawis. for &thorn;e fend ha&thorn; mouyd men bi pride &amp; bi coueytise forto bihete &thorn;at &thorn;ey wolen do more &thorn;an &thorn;ey han power or wit to do; for take &thorn;ou hede to oure popis, to bischops &amp; to oure persouns, and &thorn;ey recken litil of &thorn;er charge hou myche it be &amp; hou large, so &thorn;at hem come wynnyng &amp; worldly worchip bi &thorn;er staat. &amp; so si&thorn; &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000522.tif" N="456"> staat of prelacye taki&thorn; sumwhat of goddis lawe &amp; sumwhat of mannus lawe contrarie to goddis lawe, trewe men shulden purge &thorn;is staat &amp; lyue clene bi goddis lawe. for saracenes wi&thorn; o&thorn;ere sectis holden myche of cristis lawe, but o&thorn;ere lawis &thorn;at &thorn;ey meddlen maken &thorn;is sect displese to god; &amp; god woot wher straunge lawis ben meddlid more vndir oure pope wi&thorn; cristis lawe &thorn;an &thorn;ey ben meddlid in o&thorn;ere sectis. it semy&thorn; &thorn;at prestis &thorn;at kepen pari&yogh;schis shulden teche hem &thorn;e gospel of crist bo&thorn;e bi lif &amp; bi word, &amp; moue hem to holde charite, &amp; bisie hem not in o&thorn;ere &thorn;ingis ne&thorn;er of &thorn;e world ne mannus lawe, &amp; make obediense to &thorn;er prelatis as myche as goddis lawe techi&thorn;. fode &amp; hiling moten &thorn;ey haue; &amp; it is skileful &thorn;at &thorn;er pari&yogh;s fynde hem &thorn;ese bi title of almes, &amp; take &thorn;ey no more hede to dymes. but &thorn;is lif mut nedis be brou&yogh;t in bi litil &amp; litil for anticrist. &amp; &thorn;is lore were good to persouns, to &yogh;yue no tribut to &thorn;er prelatis &amp; make no straunge dispensis but &yogh;if goddis lawe mouyde &thorn;er-to. for alle &thorn;es dispensis at &thorn;e laste moten be gederid of pore men; &amp; certis &thorn;is is a foul offiss of a prest to robbe his puple to &yogh;yue to bischop or erchedekene godis &thorn;at god biddi&thorn; not. as senage &amp; procurasies, &amp; o&thorn;ere tributis &thorn;at ben feyned, ben not groundid in goddis lawe &amp; &thorn;erfore men shulden dispise hem. &yogh;yuyng of taliage to &thorn;e kyng is licly groundid in goddis lawe, for crist &yogh;af mekely to &thorn;e emperour tribut, as &thorn;e gospel sei&thorn;, but he &yogh;af not to &thorn;e hye bischops ne pharisees ne saducees. but siche curatis moten arme hem wi&thorn; help of god &amp; of trewe men, for cursingis &amp; suspendingis wolen renne a&yogh;enus siche curatis. si&thorn; bischops of ierusalem maden crist be cursid &amp; suspendid for &thorn;ey seiden he was not on goddis half but wi&thorn; belsebub a prince of deuels, &amp; &thorn;ey puttiden men out of synagoge &thorn;at confessiden crist apertly, &amp; aftir &thorn;ei suspendiden hym in &thorn;e cros ful felly. &thorn;is hangyng vp vsid nou is not so fel but fals ynow; for &thorn;ey wolen hange vp treu&thorn;e &amp; mayntenyng of goddis lawe; &amp; &thorn;ei ponderen wi&thorn; &thorn;is suspending &thorn;at &thorn;ei don it for ri&yogh;twisenesse to teche curatis obedience &amp; meke|nesse 
<PB REF="00000523.tif" N="457"> bi goddis lawe, &amp; al &thorn;is is falsly feyned bi anticristis <MILESTONE N="21b" UNIT="page">ipocrisie. but trewe prestis shulden trowe heere &thorn;at ne&thorn;er &thorn;e word of &thorn;er prelat ne &thorn;e word of &thorn;er somenour han so myche maliss wi&thorn; hem &thorn;at ne &thorn;ey may preche &amp; serue god aftir &thorn;is suspending. &amp; &thorn;e moost harm &thorn;at &thorn;ei don is priuyng or sleyng; &amp; &thorn;is shulden curatis mekely suffere, for &thorn;is wolde turne hem to myche good. &amp; summen tellen wi&thorn; myche declaring &thorn;at ground of &thorn;is he&thorn;en custom springi&thorn; in &thorn;e chirche of &thorn;e pope &amp; of &thorn;e floc groundid on hym. &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;is man bi ipocrisie sei&thorn; &thorn;at he sue&thorn; nexst crist of alle &thorn;e men heere in er&thorn;e, &amp; ha&thorn; moost power of crist &amp; of feynyng of &thorn;is power; hou he presenti&thorn; cristis persone &amp; passi&thorn; alle cristis apostlis in graunting of priuylegies &amp; pardoun, it passi&thorn; many mennus wit for greetnesse of &thorn;is power. &amp; summen seyn &thorn;at &thorn;is speche falli&thorn; not fro fendis gabbing but &yogh;if &thorn;e pope speke bi &thorn;e contrarie, as a mount ha&thorn; his name of mouyng, for among alle men in er&thorn;e &thorn;is ipocrite lyue&thorn; ferrest fro crist. crist hadde not propre good wher-ynne he shulde reste his hed; men seyn &thorn;is pope ha&thorn; more &thorn;an half of &thorn;e empire wi&thorn;-outen his spuyling. crist was moost meke &amp; moost seruysable &amp; girte hym wi&thorn; a clo&thorn; &amp; wayschide his disciplis feet, as &thorn;e gospel of ioon telli&thorn;; &thorn;e pope sitti&thorn; in his troone &amp; maki&thorn; lordis to kisse his feet. crist wente mekely fro plase to place &amp; prechide &thorn;e gospel &amp; tau&yogh;te pouert; &thorn;e pope dwelli&thorn; in auynoun &amp; doi&thorn; not &thorn;is but &thorn;e contrarie. &amp; so si&thorn; &thorn;at anticrist is he &thorn;at is a&yogh;enus crist, it semy&thorn; bi his feyned lif &thorn;at he is opyn anticrist. &amp; &yogh;if he shulde be clepid an hil for stablenesse in &thorn;is lif, &thorn;is hye hil eclipsi&thorn; &thorn;is sunne &amp; maki&thorn; wyndis &amp; yuele wederis; for goddis lawe is lettid to shyne bi lawis &thorn;at &thorn;is hil vsi&thorn;, &amp; coolding fro charite maki&thorn; stormes bi &thorn;is hil; but grace of god ha&thorn; helpid men to cleue &thorn;is hil &amp; make it knowun, &amp; god contynue his help heere &amp; make his lawe to shyne frely. Amen.</P>
