<DIV2 N="1" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD><MILESTONE N="25" UNIT="page">Capitulum primum.</HEAD>
<P>god sei&thorn; bi ieremye &thorn;at he wakide eerly to his puple<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Jer. xxv. 4.]</NOTE> &amp; criede his lawe bi his prophetis, &thorn;at weren martrid in goddis cause &amp; for profit of his chirche, bo&thorn;e for clerkis, lordis &amp; comyns. but god sei&thorn; by salomon &thorn;at his wisdom<NOTE PLACE="marg">Prov. i. [20-28.]</NOTE> crye&thorn; in stretis but men dispisen his counsel &amp; wolen not lyue bi his lore, &amp; &thorn;erfore god shal ley&yogh;e in &thorn;e tyme &thorn;at &thorn;ey shulen perische; &thorn;anne &thorn;ei shulen crie to hym &amp; he shal not here &amp; spede hem. &thorn;us god moue&thorn; many men in tyme of grace to telle his lawe; &amp; &yogh;it anticrist dispisi&thorn; it &amp; lordis ben necgligent in &thorn;er help. &amp; for prestis faylen heere on &thorn;er syde, as o&thorn;ere men don, summe prestis &thorn;enken &thorn;at &thorn;ey shulden crye &amp; telle goddis lawe to &thorn;e puple; for it may falle &thorn;at &thorn;ey bo&thorn;e shulen perische for &thorn;er necgligense. ground of cristenmennus bileue sei&thorn; &thorn;at crist is god &amp; man, &amp; was porerste man of lif &amp; mekerste &amp; moost vertuous. cristen|men taken ouer &thorn;at petre was cristis viker, &amp; suyde hym in maner of lif &amp; tau&yogh;te &thorn;e chirche bi his lore. &thorn;e fend hadde enuye to crist &amp; o&thorn;ere men &thorn;at suyden hym, &amp; temptide prestis to worldly lordchipis as he temptide crist in his persone &amp;, as he li&yogh;ede in &thorn;is tempting &amp; seyde &thorn;at he wolde &yogh;yue to crist alle &thorn;e reumes of &thorn;e world so &thorn;at he wolde loute hym, so bi craft of his lesingis he ha&thorn; getun lordchip to clerkis. so &thorn;at nou myche of &thorn;is world holdi&thorn; on anticristis syde; as many seyen &thorn;at &thorn;e pope shulde bi vertu of cristis lif be seculer lord of al &thorn;is world, &amp; bi his leeue kyngis ben lordis. &amp; &thorn;e fendis part is heere so strong &amp; colourid wi&thorn; so many cautels &thorn;at fewe men doren putte hem out to stonde &amp; speke for goddis cause. but &yogh;it men trowen, as &thorn;ei doren, &thorn;at crist chees to be pore to &yogh;yue ensaumple to his prestis &amp; o&thorn;ere men to triste in god, &amp; leeue to triste in 
<PB REF="00000527.tif" N="461"> &thorn;is world for &thorn;ey moten dye &amp; leeue it. &amp; petre was pore aftir crist, &amp; alle &thorn;e apostlis but scarioth, for he wolde be riche &amp; haue in propre, &amp; &thorn;is brou&yogh;t hym to double de&thorn;. but &thorn;e fend ha&thorn; blyndid men, bo&thorn;e clerkis &amp; lordis, in &thorn;e chirche &thorn;at &thorn;ey bileuen &thorn;e contrarye; &amp; &thorn;is defaute in bileue reuersi&thorn; cristenmennus lif, &amp; letti&thorn; hem to sue crist. for &thorn;e fend coueyti&thorn; myche to quenche bileue in &thorn;e chirche, for &thorn;is is &thorn;e firste vertu &amp; ground of cristis religioun. &amp; for &thorn;e pope is holdun moost &amp; nexst viker of iesu crist, &thorn;erfore &thorn;e fend in &thorn;e pope ha&thorn; gederid many worldly poyntis <MILESTONE N="25b" UNIT="page">bo&thorn;e of lordchip &amp; worldly lif, &amp; casti&thorn; to disseyue &thorn;e chirche by hym. For manye taken as bileue &thorn;at he may not do amys, but what &thorn;ing &thorn;at he graunti&thorn; or sei&thorn; crist mut conferme it; &amp; bi &thorn;is cautel of &thorn;e fend ben many men dampnyd to helle. &amp; ground of al &thorn;is disseyt is lesing contrarye to treu&thorn;e; for as &thorn;e fend disseyuede eue bi lesing &thorn;at she shulde not dye, whanne god hadde seyd &thorn;at she shulde dye what day &thorn;at she eet of &thorn;e appul, so &thorn;e fend disseyue&thorn; &thorn;e chirche bi oon as opyn lesing, &thorn;at crist was heere worldly lord moost hye of alle o&thorn;ere, &amp; so shulde his viker be &thorn;at is clepid &thorn;e pope of rome. but whanne crist was temptid heere he seyde: "go, satanas." to teche alle cristenmen hou &thorn;at crist wolde be pore; &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;er ben fewe men &thorn;at wolen defende &thorn;is bileue, for anticrist ha&thorn; many clerkis &thorn;at maken it derk bi many weyes.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 2<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>it were to wite ouer hou god shewi&thorn; loue to his chirche bi dyuysioun of &thorn;es popis &thorn;at is nou late fallun. oure bileue techi&thorn; bi poul &thorn;at alle &thorn;ingis fallen to good<NOTE PLACE="marg">Rom. viii. [28.]</NOTE> to goddis children &thorn;at dreden hym, &amp; &thorn;us shulden cris|tenmen take hem. &thorn;e firste bok of goddis lawe telli&thorn; hou god manaasside &thorn;e fend: "y shal putte enemyte," sei&thorn; god,<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Gen. iii. 15.]</NOTE> "bitwixe &thorn;ee &amp; womman, &amp; bitwixe &thorn;y seed &amp; heere seed, &amp; she shal al to-squatte &thorn;yn heed." &amp; so taken summen &thorn;at 
<PB REF="00000528.tif" N="462"> hooly preyer of &thorn;e chirche maad to crist &amp; his modir moue&thorn; hym to sende &thorn;is grace doun to departe &thorn;e heed of anticrist, so &thorn;at his falsed be more knowun. &amp; it seme&thorn; to hem &thorn;at &thorn;e pope is anticrist heere in er&thorn;e. for he is a&yogh;enus crist bo&thorn;e in lif &amp; in lore. crist was moost pore man fro his bir&thorn;e to his de&thorn;, &amp; lefte worldly richees &amp; beggyng, aftir &thorn;e staat of innocense; but anticrist a&yogh;enus &thorn;is, fro &thorn;e tyme &thorn;at he be maad pope til &thorn;e tyme &thorn;at he be deed heere, coueyti&thorn; to be worldly riche, &amp; casti&thorn; bi manye shrewid weyes hou &thorn;at he may &thorn;us be riche. crist was moost meke man &amp; bad lerne &thorn;is of hym; but men seyen &thorn;at &thorn;e pope is moost proud man of er&thorn;e, &amp; maki&thorn; lordis to kysse his feet where crist wayschide his postlis feet. Crist was moost homely man in lif, in dede &amp; in word; men seyen &thorn;at &thorn;is pope is not nexst crist in &thorn;is, for where crist wente on his feet bo&thorn;e to citees &amp; litil tounnes, &thorn;ey seyen &thorn;is pope wole be closid in a castel wi&thorn; greet aray. Where crist cam to ioon baptist to be baptisid of hym, &thorn;e pope sendi&thorn; <MILESTONE N="26" UNIT="page">aftir men to come to hym where euere he be; &yogh;e, &yogh;if crist haue sumnyd hem for to come not to hym. crist bicliptide &yogh;onge &amp; pore in tokene of his homelynesse; men seyen &thorn;at &thorn;e pope wole biclippe worldly worchip, &amp; not trewe men for goddis sake lest he vnworchipe hym silf. crist was bisy to preche &thorn;e gospel not for his worldly worchip ne wynnyng; men seyen &thorn;at &thorn;e pope leeue&thorn; &thorn;is, but he wole gladly make a lawe &amp; make &thorn;is lawe in more worchip &amp; more drede &thorn;an cristis lawe. crist louede so myche his floc &thorn;at he puttide his lif for hem, &amp; sufferide sharp peyne &amp; de&thorn; for to brynge hem to blis; men seyen &thorn;at &thorn;e pope loue&thorn; so myche worchip of &thorn;e world, &thorn;at he wole feyne asoyling to men to go strey&yogh;t to heuene, so &thorn;at &thorn;ey do a trauel &thorn;at sounne&thorn; to his worldly worchip. &amp; so his foly may be cause of de&thorn; of many &thorn;ousynd men bo&thorn;e in body &amp; in soule, but hou sue&thorn; he crist in &thorn;is? crist was so pacient &amp; so myche sufferide his oune wrong, &thorn;at he preyede for his enemyes &amp; tau&yogh;te his postlis to take no veniaunse; men seyen &thorn;at &thorn;e pope of rome wole be vengid on alle maners, bo&thorn;e bi 
<PB REF="00000529.tif" N="463"> sleyng &amp; bi cursing &amp; o&thorn;ere peynes &thorn;at he feyne&thorn;. crist tau&yogh;te men to lyue wel bi his oune lif &amp; his wordis, for what he tau&yogh;te he did in dede, &amp; bad men trowe to his werkis; men seyen &thorn;at &thorn;e pope goi&thorn; al bi contrarye weye to &thorn;is, for his lif is not ensaumple to o&thorn;ere men hou &thorn;ey shulden lyue, for no man shulde lyue lik to hym, as he feyne&thorn; bi his hye staat. crist in ech his dede &amp; his word sou&yogh;te &thorn;e glory of god, &amp; sufferide many reproues in his manheed for &thorn;is ende; men seyen &thorn;at &thorn;e pope a&yogh;enward seki&thorn; his oune glory on alle weyes, &yogh;e, &yogh;if goddis worchip be lost. &amp; &thorn;us he feyne&thorn; many vngroundid gabbingis. &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;is &thorn;ing &amp; many siche ben so&thorn;e of &thorn;e pope of rome, he is very anticrist &amp; not cristis viker heere.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="3" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 3<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>&thorn;is dyuysioun of &thorn;es popis may turne to good of many reumes, &thorn;at men trowe to no&thorn;er of hem but, for loue of iesu crist, in as myche as &thorn;ey suen crist in &thorn;er lif &amp; in &thorn;er lore. for &yogh;if &thorn;ei gabben of &thorn;er staat &amp; seyen &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben cristis vikeris, &amp; &thorn;ey ben contrarye to hym bo&thorn;e in lif &amp; in lore, <MILESTONE N="26b" UNIT="page">&thorn;o men &thorn;at ben led bi &thorn;es wolues moten go &thorn;e brode weye to helle; &amp; &thorn;is seme&thorn; &thorn;e perelous tyme &thorn;at poul ha&thorn; teld to &thorn;e chirche. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;is were a bileue &thorn;at ech man shulde grounde hym ynne, &thorn;at men shulden trowe to no pope but as he groundi&thorn; hym in crist; &amp; men shulden asaye &thorn;is ground, wher it be good wi&thorn;-oute disseyt. &amp; &thorn;us what &thorn;e pope bade do, but &yogh;if he tau&yogh;te &thorn;at crist bade it, men shulden not do &thorn;is aftir hym in &thorn;at &thorn;at he were cristis viker, for it may falle &thorn;at &thorn;e fend disseyue men bi anticrist, &amp; chalenge more &thorn;an crist dide &amp; &thorn;us bringe strif in cristendom. for &thorn;e fend may moue mennus hertis to loue so myche worldly godis &thorn;at &thorn;ey stryue &amp; fi&yogh;te to-gidere for departing of &thorn;es godis; &amp; &thorn;us may anticrist &amp; hise lette men to lyue in pees, lest &thorn;at &thorn;is lif in pees make men to knowe his giles. &amp; &thorn;us god ha&thorn; ordeyned medicyn to knowe falsed of anticrist, &thorn;at 
<PB REF="00000530.tif" N="464"> he hie&thorn; hym aboue crist, &amp; so ouer god, as poul sei&thorn;. profere reumes to &thorn;es popis &thorn;at &thorn;ey wolen obesche to hem in &thorn;e foorme of goddis lawe, but no more &thorn;an crist axide; &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ey ben not payed her-of, &thorn;ey shewen &thorn;at &thorn;ey ben anticrist, si&thorn; &thorn;e mooste pride of hym is &thorn;at he hie&thorn; hym aboue god. &amp; &yogh;if reumes holde &thorn;is reule, &thorn;anne &thorn;ey may be dischargid of blasfemyes of indulgensis, &amp; of o&thorn;ere false feynyngis; for it may falle &thorn;at &thorn;e pope graunte to riche worldly men &thorn;at &thorn;ey shulen go strei&yogh;t to heuene wi&thorn;-oute peyne of purgatorye, &amp; denye &thorn;is to pore men, kepe &thorn;ey neuere so goddis lawe. siche many giles of &thorn;e fend blynden men bi his viker, so &thorn;at treu&thorn;e of goddis lawe is turnyd in-to &thorn;is vikeris falseed. &amp; shortly for to seye, &yogh;if men stonden bi &thorn;is bileue, &thorn;e pope shal not take of reumes ne&thorn;er money ne worldly godis. &amp; herfore sei&thorn; poul, cristis vikere, &thorn;at he seki&thorn; &thorn;es grekis soulis &amp; he seki&thorn; not her godis, but weye to brynge hem to blis. &amp; no drede &thorn;us doi&thorn; crist to alle reumes &thorn;at ben his children, for he robbi&thorn; not his children, but &yogh;yue&thorn; hem alle maner godis, bo&thorn;e goostly godis &amp; worldly. &amp; &thorn;us dide crist heere in er&thorn;e, &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;e pope passe heere crist &amp; robbe his children as a wolf, no drede he is anticrist &amp; opynly &thorn;e fendis viker. &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ou seyst &thorn;e pope mut haue godis of reumes to saue his <MILESTONE N="27" UNIT="page">staat, he shulde be pore, as crist was, &amp; charge not men, as crist dide not. &thorn;is reule shulde teche men where a prelat were anticrist, &amp; hou &thorn;ey shulden obesche to hym, &amp; in what &thorn;ing leeue his lore.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="4" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 4<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>si&thorn;en ech seculer cristenman shulde willefuly chese his prelat, &amp; loue hym bi goddis lawe as men louyden in &thorn;e firste staat, &thorn;at was staat of innocense, as alle men shulden haue louyd &thorn;anne, &amp; men shulen loue in staat of blis, for &thorn;ere shal loue be at &thorn;e fulle; herfore shulden men seke weyes to loue &thorn;at man &thorn;at shulde be pope. &amp; among causis of loue &thorn;e mooste cause &thorn;at euere god ordeynede shulde be 
<PB REF="00000531.tif" N="465"> good doyng of men; for bi &thorn;is cause god maki&thorn; hym silf louyd, &amp; hem more louyd &thorn;at more don good. &thorn;e good &thorn;at &thorn;e pope shulde do shulde be lore to come to heuene, &amp; so &thorn;is pope mut kunne &thorn;is lore ouer o&thorn;ere &thorn;at ben his sheep; &amp; si&thorn; &thorn;is lore is fully tau&yogh;t in goddis lawe, as we bileuen, &thorn;is pope mut passingly kunne goddis lawe &amp; resoun &thorn;er-of. but nou in &thorn;e reume of englond stryuen manye of &thorn;e sacrid oost. summe seyen &thorn;at &thorn;is oost fro &thorn;e tyme &thorn;at it be sacrid is verily goddis body &amp; &thorn;er-wi&thorn; breed, whit &amp; round; &amp; in &thorn;is weye stonden lewid men bo&thorn;e more &amp; lesse, &amp; longe han don. o&thorn;ere seyen &thorn;at &thorn;is oost is nou&yogh;t or an accident, &thorn;e which &thorn;ey kunnen not nemyn to men, but it is not goddis body. &thorn;is questioun shulden reumes sende to &thorn;e pope, to knowe his wit, what we shulden trowe of &thorn;is oost fro &thorn;e tyme &thorn;at it be sacrid; &amp; here-ynne shulde he not feyne but teche bi &thorn;e gospel or bi resoun what men shulden bileue heere, or ellis he were no witty pope. &amp; &thorn;es reumes shulden take no man to &thorn;er pope bifore &thorn;at tyme &thorn;at he hadde tau&yogh;t hem wel heere by good ground of goddis lawe. For wel we witen &thorn;at he kan heere no skile but of cristis word; but crist, whanne he blesside &thorn;is breed, seyde &thorn;at "&thorn;is is my body"; &amp; we bileuen &thorn;at crist li&yogh;ide neuere, but seyde euere so&thorn; to greet witt. &amp; &yogh;if foure sectis in &thorn;is lond seyen heere so&thorn; of &thorn;e popis lawe, he ha&thorn; seyd many hundrid wynter &thorn;at &thorn;is oost is not goddis body, but accident wi&thorn;-oute suget. &amp; &yogh;if reumes leeuen &thorn;is lore &amp; taken hem anticrist to pope, he may make hem to bileue what euere he wole bi litil &amp; litil; for hooly chirche ha&thorn; bileuyd &thorn;is &thorn;ousinde <MILESTONE N="27b" UNIT="page">wynter &amp; more to, &thorn;at &thorn;is oost is goddis body in foorme of breed, &amp; wyn his blood. &amp; trewe men shulden knowe heere &thorn;at &thorn;is poynt is not so hye &thorn;at ne &thorn;ey may wite &thorn;e so&thorn;e, &amp; knowe it betere &thorn;an o&thorn;ere poyntis &thorn;at crist ha&thorn; tau&yogh;t in oure bileue. heere may cristenmen soone wite which clerk or lord loue&thorn; treu&thorn;e &amp; ha&thorn; wille to stonde &thorn;erfore &amp; suffere a magrey &yogh;if he shulde. &amp; certis &thorn;at pope &thorn;at fayli&thorn; heere o&thorn;er for kunnyng or for wille is vnhable to take to pope &amp; lede his floc bi goddis 
<PB REF="00000532.tif" N="466"> lawe. &amp; what sect grucchi&thorn; a&yogh;enus &thorn;is is suspect of heresye, for what shulde it harme ony man &thorn;at &thorn;is treu&thorn;e were wel discussid: but it were good to cristenmen to laste in &thorn;er olde bileue, &thorn;at &thorn;is breed is goddis body &amp; &thorn;is wyn is goddis blood, &amp; not an vnknowun &thorn;ing wi&thorn;-oute resoun or autorite; for men shulden holde &thorn;er olde bileue but &yogh;if &thorn;e contrarye were wel tau&yogh;te. &amp; &thorn;us it were a blessid dede &thorn;at lordis wolden not &yogh;yue &thorn;er almes ne&thorn;er to o prest ne o&thorn;er, bifore &thorn;ey tau&yogh;ten bi good witnesse what &thorn;ing were &thorn;is sacrid oost, bo&thorn;e in his kynde &amp; in figure, by maner &thorn;at &thorn;e gospel speki&thorn;. &amp; &thorn;us &yogh;if god wolde fouche-saf, hooly chirche shulde be purgid of heresyes in &thorn;is mater, aboute which &thorn;ey dispenden myche, as in prestis &thorn;at syngen masse; &amp; certis it were ydolatrye to loute &thorn;us an accident. &amp; no man durste seye til nou &thorn;at accident is goddis body, for &thorn;is newe word may haue no ground, &amp; was not knowun &thorn;at &thorn;ousinde &yogh;eer &thorn;at sathanas was boundun in helle, &amp; &yogh;it he shame&thorn; to seye &thorn;is gabbing.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="5" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 5<SUP>tum.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>but heere grucchi&thorn; anticrist &amp; dredi&thorn; &thorn;at manye of his clerkis shulen wante &thorn;er worldly worchip, &amp; &thorn;us his lordchip shal be lesse. for &yogh;if goddis lawe were kept clene wi&thorn;-oute &thorn;e fendis lawe, &amp; &thorn;e ordenaunse of crist were clene wi&thorn;-outen anticristis, where shulden &thorn;es foure sectis be lordis as &thorn;ey nou ben? &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;e chirche were destried &thorn;at ha&thorn; be so longe in growing. Heere han trewe men seyd ofte &thorn;at &thorn;is is a fendis resoun, as &yogh;if &thorn;e arguere wolde mene &thorn;at crist faylide in his lawe &amp; in his ordenaunse which he ordeynede in &thorn;e chirche, &amp; &thorn;us men menen alle in dede &thorn;at ben of &thorn;es foure sectis. but, lord, where is vnbileue in heretik but &yogh;if &thorn;is be oon? &amp; &thorn;us it seme&thorn; &thorn;at alle &thorn;es foure smacchen sum what of heresye, &amp; &thorn;ey louen not iesu crist, for &thorn;ey haten &thorn;us his lawe. but poul sei&thorn; a so&thorn; word &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. xvi. [22.]</NOTE><MILESTONE N="28" UNIT="page">"who euere loue&thorn; not iesu crist he is cursid of god, 
<PB REF="00000533.tif" N="467"> &amp; puttid fro hym as heretik." &amp; so &thorn;e mooste inconuenient &thorn;at anticrist kan bringe of &thorn;is is &thorn;at cristis lawe were holdun clene wi&thorn;-outen anticristis; but &thorn;is fruyt were blessid &amp; profitable to &thorn;e chirche. for &thorn;is kepte crist in his apostlis, &amp; &thorn;anne cam &thorn;e chirche to heuene &amp; growide in vertus heere in er&thorn;e; &amp; si&thorn;en ha&thorn; it sunkun doun. &thorn;anne shulden cristenmen knowe &thorn;e vertu of crist &amp; of his lawe; hou &thorn;at he is god almy&yogh;ty &amp; his lawe is fully ynow; &amp; &thorn;anne shulden men wite aftir hou o&thorn;ere lawes, &thorn;at men han foundun, harmen &thorn;e chirche many weyes, &amp; maken goddis lawe lesse louyd. For keping of &thorn;es newe lawis occupie&thorn; mennus witt &amp; wille, &amp; axi&thorn; of hem a bisy trauel, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ey letten goddis lawe. &amp; &thorn;us &yogh;if anticristis lawe were good, &yogh;it cristis lawe mut nedis be betere &amp; sufficient in hym silf; &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;e to&thorn;er is to myche &amp; doi&thorn; harm in cristis chirche, &amp; letti&thorn; cristis lawe to be suyd. &amp; &thorn;us bringing in of &thorn;es lawis, &thorn;at letti&thorn; &thorn;e vse of cristis lawe, is &thorn;e mooste priuey synne &thorn;at &thorn;e fend ha&thorn; foundun a&yogh;enus &thorn;e chirche. &amp; so &thorn;is blessid word wolde sue, &thorn;at foure sectis newe foundun shulden be voydid fro &thorn;e chirche, as &thorn;ey shulen not come to blis. for alle &thorn;es sectis han mannus signes, &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;es signes weren fully stryed, &thorn;es sectis weren &thorn;anne destried, as men seyen &thorn;at ben weddid wi&thorn; hem. but it is not so of cristis sect ne of prestis &thorn;at crist ordeynede. for ioon baptist was a prest, as alle men in heuene shulen be prestis. for crounne &amp; clo&thorn; maken no prest, ne &thorn;e emperours bischop wi&thorn; his wordis, but power &thorn;at crist &yogh;yue&thorn;; &amp; &thorn;us bi lif ben prestis knowun. &amp; &thorn;us cristen|men shulden not lette for &thorn;e drede of &thorn;e fend &amp; for power of his clerkis to sue &amp; holde cristis lawe. but wel y woot &thorn;at &thorn;is chirche ha&thorn; be many day in growing, &amp; summe clepen it not cristis chirche, but &thorn;e chirche of wickid spiritis. &amp; dauy&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Psalm xxvi. 5.]</NOTE> hatide &thorn;is chirche as ech cristenman shulde do. &amp; man may no betere knowe anticristis clerk &thorn;an bi &thorn;is, &thorn;at he loue&thorn; &thorn;is chirche &amp; hati&thorn; &thorn;e chirche of criste; &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;e pope be an heed to mayntene &thorn;is chirche a&yogh;enus crist, he is opyn anticrist &amp; no part of cristis chirche. &amp; &yogh;if <MILESTONE N="28b" UNIT="page">he &amp; his secte be voyde 
<PB REF="00000534.tif" N="468"> fro cristis lawe, &amp; clensid wi&thorn; besumms, &amp; maad fair wi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke xi. [25.]</NOTE> sensible signes, &thorn;anne &thorn;e fend ha&thorn; a tokene to dwelle homely wi&thorn; &thorn;es men; for &thorn;es ben wordis of crist, &thorn;e whiche moten nedis be trewe. &amp; &thorn;us shulde anticrist drede of &thorn;e word &thorn;at crist sei&thorn; aftir, &thorn;at &thorn;is kynrede of prestis is &thorn;e worste of alle o&thorn;ere. for many men trowen heere &thorn;at as prestis in &thorn;e olde lawe, fro &thorn;e time of machabees vnto &thorn;at &thorn;ei hadden slayn crist, weren &thorn;e worste kynrede &thorn;at god sufferide &thorn;anne to lyue; so aftir cristis steying, &yogh;if prestis leeuen cristis lawe &amp; bicomen reuleris of &thorn;is world by newe lawis &thorn;at &thorn;ey han shapun, &thorn;is is nou &thorn;e worste kynrede &thorn;at is on lyue heere in er&thorn;e.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="6" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 6<SUP>tum.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>&yogh;it anticrist argue&thorn; &thorn;at &yogh;if &thorn;is sentense wente for&thorn;, &thorn;e pope were as pore a man as ony bischop of englond; but &thorn;is were a&yogh;enus resoun, &thorn;at &thorn;e hiere man shulde be byne&thorn;e. Heere men seyen to anticrist &thorn;at he argue&thorn; a&yogh;enus crist, &amp; &thorn;erfore cristenmen moten nede answere sharply heere for crist; for &yogh;if &thorn;is foly wente for&thorn;, si&thorn; crist was moost pore man &amp; his apostlis pore aftir, &thorn;ey weren leest wor&thorn; in &thorn;is world. but what blasfeme durste seye &thorn;us, si&thorn; it is a&yogh;enus bileue. &amp; &thorn;us goddis lawe techi&thorn; &thorn;at willeful pouert of a prest, &yogh;if he haue mekenesse in his soule &amp; o&thorn;ere vertues more &thorn;an o&thorn;ere, he is herby more to god, &amp; &thorn;is hyenesse shulden prestis coueyte. &amp; &thorn;us alle prestis of englond shulden be pore men, as &thorn;e pope, for &thorn;ey moten forsake &thorn;er richees &yogh;if &thorn;ey wolen be cristis prestis. for bileue techi&thorn; wel &thorn;at crist bad his prestis be<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luke xiv. [33.]</NOTE> siche; &amp; we fynden neuere bi resoun &thorn;at crist chaungide euere his wille. &amp; si&thorn; crist is god in heuene, it is ful hard to reuerse his lawe, for no drede men moten rikene &thorn;erfore at &thorn;e day of dom. &amp; heere men sliden out of bileue, bo&thorn;e prestis &amp; seculeris, whanne &thorn;ey tellen more bi a cronycle of foly of an emperour &thorn;an &thorn;ey tellen bi cristis lawe, &thorn;at is emperour of heuene. &amp; &thorn;e fend conferme&thorn; his part, &amp; maki&thorn; 
<PB REF="00000535.tif" N="469"> seyntis be canonysed, &thorn;e whiche resseyueden siche dowyng, to proue &thorn;at &thorn;is was wel don. but heere men knowen &thorn;e fendis cautels, &amp; sliden not fro bileue for &thorn;is; for canonysing of &thorn;es seyntis is not bileue of cristenmen. &amp; &thorn;us &yogh;if &thorn;es ben seyntes in heuene, &thorn;is is bi vertu of crist &thorn;at &thorn;ey turnyden at &thorn;e laste to hym, &amp; hadden sorowe for &thorn;er synne. &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ou axe prof her-of, we seyen &thorn;at &yogh;if &thorn;ou proue &thorn;at &thorn;es be seyntis, it wole sue of oure bileue &thorn;at &thorn;es seyntis sorowiden &thorn;us, &yogh;if &thorn;ey weren worldly men &thorn;us, for ellis &thorn;ey my&yogh;ten not come to heuene. But myraclis maad of deed men ben &thorn;e fendis euydense; for god may suffre <MILESTONE N="29" UNIT="page">&thorn;e fend to do siche signes &amp; many mo. for ellis wolde not poul seye &thorn;at a man<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. xiii. [2.]</NOTE> my&yogh;te remoue hillis &amp; &yogh;it fayle of charite. but &yogh;if &thorn;es signes my&yogh;ten li&yogh;tly fayle, stonde we in bileue of crist, &amp; leeue we siche signes of &thorn;e fend. for bileue is insensible &amp; more trewe &thorn;an siche signes; as &thorn;is treu&thorn;e is insensible &thorn;at two &amp; &thorn;re maken fyue, &amp; &yogh;it it is more certeyn &thorn;an ony sensible &thorn;ing heere. &thorn;us bileue of hooly writ passi&thorn; alle &thorn;es clepid myraclis. &amp; &thorn;us wite wel lordis &amp; reumes &thorn;at &thorn;ey moten nedis answere to god hou &thorn;ey han holdun his lawe &amp; stondun sad in his bileue. no drede bo&thorn;e lordis &amp; reumes my&yogh;ten wel constreyne prestis to holde &thorn;e pouert &thorn;at crist ordeynede, for honeste of his prestis &amp; profit of lordis &amp; comyns. &amp; whanne lordis leeuen &thorn;is power, &thorn;ey assenten to &thorn;e fend; &amp; &thorn;ey moten nedis be dampnyd for &thorn;is assent but &yogh;if &thorn;ey amenden it, &amp; &thorn;is is blynding of &thorn;e fend &thorn;at &thorn;ey han grauntid &thorn;is almes. &amp; so &thorn;ey moten be trewe men &amp; algatis mayntene it for&thorn;, for &yogh;if men loken hou it cam in, it cam not in bi very almes, but bi blyndnesse of &thorn;e world &amp; ipocrisie &thorn;at &thorn;e fend tau&yogh;te. &amp; euere &thorn;e lengere &thorn;at it lasti&thorn;, &thorn;e more peyne han deed mennus soulis. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;e fend stiri&thorn; men to laste in synne a&yogh;enus god; but wite &thorn;ey wel wi&thorn; &thorn;e fend &thorn;at god mut nedis be &thorn;er lord. &thorn;us &yogh;if lordis han first be foolis, o&thorn;er in dowyng or leeuynge to helpe, &thorn;ey shulden haue sorowe of &thorn;is synne &amp; haaste hem to make asee&thorn;. &amp; wite &thorn;ey wel &thorn;at god mut nedis be cheef lord of alle creaturis, 
<PB REF="00000536.tif" N="470"> &amp; but &yogh;if god graunte hem leeue to &yogh;yue &thorn;us prestis &thorn;es worldly godis, &thorn;e &yogh;ifte &thorn;at &thorn;ey &yogh;auen is nou&yogh;t bi vertu of &thorn;e cheef lord. &amp; &thorn;us anticrist &amp; al his help can ne&thorn;er argue heere ne answere; &amp; y am certeyn on domes-day no man may answere wel heere. &thorn;erfore mende hem lordis &amp; reumes, &amp; serue &thorn;ei crist for &thorn;er goode, for litil seruyss for &thorn;is tyme disserue&thorn; myche meede in heuene. lord, si&thorn; lordis &amp; reumes bo&thorn;e chesen a pope at &thorn;er oune wille, what sholde moue hem to chese &thorn;is pope more hye &thorn;an crist wolde chalenge of men? crist axide noon er&thorn;ly lordchip ne er&thorn;ly godis, but &yogh;af heuenely, &amp; whanne he tok his oune godis he tok hem for help of his tenauntis, &amp; algatis in siche a mesure &thorn;at he was not charious to hem. &amp; &thorn;is lore han freris for&yogh;eten &amp; alle &thorn;es o&thorn;ere newe sectis. &thorn;us &thorn;e grace <MILESTONE N="29b" UNIT="page">of god ha&thorn; mouyd to trete &thorn;is mater among cristenmen, to loke wher &thorn;ey wolen helpe hem silf whanne god ha&thorn; so graciously bigunnyn.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="7" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 7<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>&thorn;er ben groundis &thorn;e whiche crist kepte contrarie to keping of prelatis nou. for crist tau&yogh;te &thorn;at hoolynesse shulde be hid in mennus hertis &amp; not shewid to &thorn;e puple in sensible signes wi&thorn;-oute fruyt; for &thorn;anne men hopiden reward of god &amp; axiden not glory of &thorn;is world. but nou it is turnyd vpsedoun fro religioun &thorn;at crist ordeynede, for nou he is ne&thorn;er pope ne prelat, but &yogh;if he haue a worldly meyne &thorn;at shewe his hyenesse to &thorn;e world, as he were a seculer lord, &amp; bi &thorn;is gile ha&thorn; &thorn;e fend brou&yogh;t in &thorn;at more prestis shulden haue worldly glorye. &amp; &thorn;is maki&thorn; &thorn;e pope &amp; bischops to axe richessis to &thorn;er staat; for, as &thorn;ei seyen, &thorn;er staat wolde perische but &yogh;if siche richesse shewide it out. first &thorn;es prelatis blasfemen in crist &amp; in his hooly apostlis. for bileue techi&thorn; vs &thorn;at crist was bischop of mennus soulis, betere bi a &thorn;ousynd part &thorn;an any si&thorn; &thorn;e chirche was dowyd, &amp; so weren cristis apostlis betere &thorn;an ony pope of rome. 
<PB REF="00000537.tif" N="471"> For &thorn;is name is newe foundun, &amp; it bitokeni&thorn; wundirful; for summe &thorn;enken it greet wundir &thorn;at worldly glory &amp; hoolynesse shulden be knyttid in o persone; si&thorn; crist forsok it in word &amp; dede, &amp; bi his lore his apostlis, lord, why shulden not prelatis do nou so? &amp; by &thorn;is cause ha&thorn; &thorn;e fend brou&yogh;t yn &thorn;at religioun of &thorn;es newe ordris shal be shewid in sensible signes, as habitis, &amp; bikenes, &amp; hye housis, &amp; herfore ha&thorn; &thorn;e fend brou&yogh;t in &thorn;at cumpany of many lumpis shal be ioyned to o persone for worldly worchip of &thorn;er staat. &thorn;us &thorn;er ben many cardenals &amp; many men knyttid to hem; myche meyne to a bischop, &amp; manye persones in an ordre, &amp; al is charge to comyn men, &amp; streng&thorn;e to &thorn;e fendis part. crist ordeynede &thorn;at his apostlis fro tyme &thorn;at he steyede to heuene shulden be scaterid in many cuntreys &amp; conquere wickid men to crist. wel y rede &thorn;at seynt petre dwelte in a corieris hous, but<NOTE PLACE="marg">Acts x. [6.]</NOTE> y rede not of cardenal ne page &thorn;at he hadde wi&thorn; hym; &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;is apostle cam to cornely &amp; conuertide hym wi&thorn; o&thorn;ere. &amp; &thorn;us may cristenmen lerne bo&thorn;e of crist &amp; his apostlis &thorn;at religioun of crist is not in siche worldly signes. &amp; so men moten o&thorn;er denye bileue, or seye &thorn;at cristis religioun stondi&thorn; not in siche signes as nou &thorn;e chirche is chargid wi&thorn;. so&thorn; it is <MILESTONE N="30" UNIT="page">&thorn;at seculer prinsis &amp; worldly lordis moten haue siche worldly signes, for &thorn;ey shulden teche to drede god by austernete &amp; worldly drede. but it is a&yogh;enus cristis wille &thorn;at prestis meddle &thorn;es two to-gidere, for &thorn;ey shulden teche bi mekenesse &amp; paciense, as crist dide. &amp; herfore biddi&thorn; god in his lawe &thorn;at his men shulden not be clo&thorn;id in wollun<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Deut. xxii. 11.]</NOTE> &amp; lynnun partid to-gidere, to teche &thorn;is dyuersite in figure. crist was bo&thorn;e kyng &amp; prest, as he is bo&thorn;e god &amp; man, &amp; &thorn;us sum &thorn;ing falli&thorn; to hym &thorn;at no cristenman may come to; but in siche poyntis shulden men lerne to sue bi vertues crist afer, &amp; go not bifore crist, as dide presumpcion of petre; &amp; &thorn;erfore crist clepide hym sathanas &amp; bad petre go aftir hym. crist as a goode maystir hadde twelue apostlis to teche hem; anticrist ordeyne&thorn; many twelue to lyue worldly &amp; charge &thorn;e chirche. crist koude ensaumple kynghod &amp; 
<PB REF="00000538.tif" N="472"> presthod in her groundis, but prestis &thorn;at comen aftir crist ben not able to do so; &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ey passen &thorn;er maystir crist, bo&thorn;e in presthod &amp; in kny&yogh;thod. &amp; &thorn;us &yogh;if popis wolden haue cardenals, &thorn;ey shulden chese gode men &amp; pore, &amp; loke &thorn;at &thorn;ey chargide not &thorn;e chirche bi costly aray &amp; idilnesse; but nou men seyen &thorn;at cardenals ben brou&yogh;t yn bi anticrist to bargeyne by symonye, &amp; by o&thorn;ere disseytis bigile men, &amp; &thorn;us as &thorn;e pope is wundirful, so cardenals ben an herre to &thorn;e fendis hous. &amp; o&thorn;ere ground han &thorn;ey noon, but for anticrist wole &thorn;us.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="8" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 8<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>&yogh;it it were to reherse &thorn;e euydensis &thorn;at anticrist maki&thorn; to proue &thorn;at it were betere clerkis to be riche &thorn;an pore as crist; for bi &thorn;is richees &thorn;ei don sum good, &amp; bi so myche &thorn;ey ben &thorn;e betere. for &thorn;ey ben of mannus kynde, as ben lordis &thorn;at han siche godis, &amp; &thorn;ey han wit to spende &thorn;es godis as han o&thorn;ere, or ellis more. Why shulden not &thorn;ey be betere bi &thorn;es richessis as o&thorn;ere ben? Heere men seyen to anticrist &thorn;at wolde affeerme crist a fool, as &thorn;e fend helde crist a fool for he wolde not take of hym alle &thorn;e reumes of &thorn;e world for a litil seruyss to hym, &thorn;at crist as a good god wolde &thorn;at his prestis weren in worchip &amp; fer fro perels of &thorn;e fend, &amp; &thorn;us he forbad to his prestis to haue to myche of er&thorn;ly godis &amp; to myche bisynesse aboute hem; but crist &yogh;af hem goostly godis &amp; ocupiyng bi charite. &amp; &yogh;if we marken staat of innocense &amp; staat &thorn;at aungels han in heuene, &thorn;ey shulden not be &thorn;us <MILESTONE N="30b" UNIT="page">oppressid wi&thorn; er&thorn;ely drit as riche men ben, but &thorn;ey han more clene lif &amp; more likinge to mannus soule. &amp; for &thorn;is cause ordeynede crist &thorn;at his prestis shulden wante &thorn;es richessis, &amp; ensaumplide in hym silf &amp; his apostlis hou &thorn;ey shulden lyue. crist wolde wel &thorn;at his prestis hadden &thorn;e vse of worldly godis as myche as wolde do hem good, but not to myche to lette &thorn;er soule, as men shulden bifore synne &amp; 
<PB REF="00000539.tif" N="473"> aungels han in &thorn;er lif. &amp; bi &thorn;is vse men shulden haue goostly lordchip of alle &thorn;es godis, &amp; bi &thorn;e fruyt of vertues haue delit in her god. &amp; &thorn;us crist ordeynede to prestis moost hye staat &amp; moost parfit of alle &thorn;re partis of &thorn;e chirche, &yogh;if &thorn;at prestis wolden lyue &thorn;er-aftir; as crist &yogh;af to laboreris worldly godis &amp; trauel also, &amp; crist grauntide to his apostlis to trauele aboute er&thorn;ly godis, but he forfendide hem to prynte &thorn;er soulis to myche wi&thorn; er&thorn;ly godis. crist grauntide to worldly lordis to haue gouernayle of siche godis, but he grauntide to his prestis to gouerne soulis bi weye of vertues; &amp; &thorn;is shulden &thorn;ey do bi meke wille, &amp; leeue lordchip &amp; austernete. &amp; &thorn;is he tau&yogh;te in dede &amp; word for loue &thorn;at he hadde to his prestis. se we nou &thorn;e fendis foly, what he mene&thorn; whanne he argue&thorn;. he wolde mene &thorn;at crist was a fool &amp; to scars in leste godis. austyn sei&thorn; ofte-tyme &thorn;at &thorn;er ben &thorn;re godis of man; godis of vertues, &amp; godis of kynde, &amp; godis of fortune, &thorn;at ben &thorn;e leste. crist ordeynede men to be riche in godis of vertu, for &thorn;ey ben best; &amp; crist ordeynede godis of kynde as myche as &thorn;ey shulden serue to &thorn;e soule. he ordeynede not so greet a body ne so strong to a man as ha&thorn; an hors or o&thorn;er beeste, for it wolde do harm to &thorn;e soule. crist ordeynede godis of fortune &thorn;at wolden suffise to mannus body; &amp; &thorn;us he ordeynede godis of vertu wyngis to men to fle to heuene; ant anticrist wolde faste to men godis of fortune bi coueytise, &thorn;at shulden drenge a man to helle, &amp; for &thorn;is ende he shapi&thorn; &thorn;is. wel y graunte &thorn;at er&thorn;ly godis &amp; worldly lordchipis ben gode, for &thorn;ei ben goddis creaturis &amp; shapun of god for good ende. but godis of vertu ben &thorn;e betere &thorn;at prestis shulden haue passingly, &amp; more perel is in &thorn;e firste godis, &amp; &thorn;erfore crist wolde not &thorn;at his prestis hadden but litil of &thorn;es godis, for perels &amp; letting of betere godis. &amp; heere shulden worldly men take hede, bo&thorn;e &thorn;e lordis <MILESTONE N="31" UNIT="page">&amp; &thorn;e comyns, &thorn;at &thorn;ey dissusen not worldly godis, but take hem in mesure to &thorn;at ende &thorn;at crist ha&thorn; ordeyned hem to be vsid, &amp; not a&yogh;enus his ordenaunse. crist &yogh;af hem not worldly godis to charge his prestis wi&thorn; &thorn;is lordchip, ne to 
<PB REF="00000540.tif" N="474"> stire hem to fleysly synnes, as ben gloterye &amp; lecherye; &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;es two partis of &thorn;e chirche foulen &thorn;us prestis wi&thorn; &thorn;es godis, wite &thorn;ey wel &thorn;at god wole punysche bo&thorn;e &thorn;es partis &amp; his prestis. &amp; &thorn;us we graunten &thorn;at riche prestis don sum good wi&thorn; &thorn;is richees, for so don &thorn;e fendis in helle wi&thorn; godis &thorn;at crist ha&thorn; &yogh;ouyn to hem, but ne&thorn;eles &thorn;ey don amys; for &thorn;ey shulden sette al &thorn;er bisynesse &thorn;at &thorn;ey han nou in worldly godis to serue crist bi godis of grace, &amp; &thorn;is is a greet defaute. We graunten &thorn;at prestis ben of mannus kynde, as ben lordis &amp; weddid men, but &yogh;it &thorn;ey shulden not haue &thorn;is lordchip ne kyndely gendrure of children, but &yogh;if &thorn;ey wolden leeue &thorn;is staat &amp; bicome weddid men, for we bileuen &thorn;at maydynhot &amp; goostly gendrure is betere &thorn;an &thorn;is. &amp; so supposen we &thorn;at &thorn;es prestis han betere wit &thorn;an seculer lordis, applye &thorn;ey &thorn;is betere wit in betere vse to serue god; as beestis han wit to ete &amp; drynke, but prestis wit shulde not stonde in &thorn;is, but hou &thorn;ey my&yogh;ten teche men to lyue in vertues bi goddis lawe. but &thorn;is may not prestis do bi robbing of lordis &amp; of comyns of &thorn;er lordchip &amp; er&thorn;ely godis; for &thorn;is is a&yogh;enus god &amp; man.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="9" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 9<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>by &thorn;is sentense &thorn;at heere is seyd shulden anticrist &amp; hise haue shame to defoule cristis prestis a&yogh;enus &thorn;e ordenaunse &thorn;at crist made. &amp; worldly lordis &amp; o&thorn;ere foolis &thorn;at helpen anticrist heere shulden haue shame of &thorn;is help, as &thorn;ey shulen shame at domes day; &amp; &thorn;is shame shal be more bi colour of ipocrisye, for &thorn;ey seyen in &thorn;es dedis &thorn;at &thorn;ey don &thorn;us for cristis worchip. for crist ordeynede amys, but worldly lordis amendiden hym, as &thorn;e emperour of rome whanne he made his prestis lordis he amendide &thorn;e apostlis staat ouer &thorn;e ordenaunse of crist. but al &thorn;is smacchi&thorn; blasfemye &amp; wole bringe &thorn;es lordis doun, as &thorn;e emperours staat is lesse for &thorn;is dede a&yogh;enus crist. For no man may do a&yogh;enus crist but &yogh;if he 
<PB REF="00000541.tif" N="475"> be punysshid for &thorn;is dede, but punysshing of mannus soule is more to drede &thorn;an worldly harm. &amp; &thorn;us anticrist <MILESTONE N="31b" UNIT="page">my&yogh;te not for shame canonyse &thorn;is emperour; for it is knowun &thorn;ing to men &thorn;at &thorn;is emperour reuerside crist. &amp; it seme&thorn; to many men &thorn;at o cause why he dide &thorn;us was to hye his oune prestis, wi&thorn; o&thorn;er blynd deuocioun; so &thorn;at as &thorn;e emperour passide o&thorn;ere worldly lordis, so shulde his prest of rome &amp; hise passe o&thorn;ere lordis prestis. &amp; to &thorn;is wit he made hym lord of rome &amp; myche of his empire, &amp; made hym &amp; his cardenals ride in reed on hye ors; for hym &thorn;ou&yogh;te shame &thorn;at his clerkis shulden not passe clerkis of o&thorn;ere lordis, but as he passide hem bi his empire, so his prest shulde passe o&thorn;ere. &amp; certis &thorn;is were an yuel ground to canonyse &thorn;is man in heuene; as it were no good cause to charge &thorn;e chirche to halewe hym, al &yogh;if he seyde &thorn;at &yogh;if he sawe a prest lie bi a womman he wolde hile hem wi&thorn; his mentile, &amp; not sclaundre hem of &thorn;is synne. &yogh;if &thorn;is emperour be in blis, certis &thorn;at is not for &thorn;is dede; for fynees was a iust prest, for he stikide &thorn;e man &amp; &thorn;e womman for &thorn;er synne a&yogh;enus god, &amp; &thorn;us he vengide goddis wrong. &thorn;is emperour dide many godis, but &yogh;it men dursten neuere hidir-to charge &thorn;e chirche to holde his day, &amp; trowe &thorn;at he were seynt in heuene. &amp; so men seyen of seynt siluester, &thorn;at &yogh;if god wole he is blissid, but &thorn;anne he hadde myche sorowe aftir for &thorn;is lordchip &thorn;at he toke, as seynt petre synnede ofte &amp; bi oure fei&thorn; he is nou seynt, but we han no siche fei&thorn; &thorn;at siluestre is &thorn;us in blis. for it is nede to cristenmen to wite what &thorn;ing is bileue, &amp; to wite what is byne&thorn;e bileue, &amp; putte not oure trou&thorn;e in siche &thorn;ing. but it is licly to many men &thorn;at siluestre synnede in his hiyng, &amp; petre ne poule ne o&thorn;ere apostle wolde neuere haue takun &thorn;is staat; but &thorn;e fruyt of his sorowe &amp; o&thorn;ere gode dedis &thorn;at he dide, wi&thorn; &thorn;e grace of goddis wille, my&yogh;ten haue maad hym seynt aftir. &amp; &thorn;us men shewen bi opyn skyle defaute of anticristis resoun. many &thorn;ingis ben gode &amp; holsum echone in his kynde, &amp; &thorn;e mynging of &thorn;es &thorn;ingis is vnholsum to man to take; so presthod &amp; worldly lordchip ben bo&thorn;e gode in &thorn;er 
<PB REF="00000542.tif" N="476"> kynde, &amp; &thorn;e mynging of &thorn;es two were venemous, &yogh;e in &thorn;e pope. for &thorn;is lordchip <MILESTONE N="32" UNIT="page">wolde quenche &thorn;e pouert &thorn;at crist ha&thorn; bedun. &amp; a coorde is a good &thorn;ing, &amp; faste knytting &thorn;er-wi&thorn; is good bo&thorn;e to man &amp; to beeste in plasis where it wolde do good; but knytte &thorn;is coorde to mannus &thorn;rote &amp; it my&yogh;te soone strangle &thorn;is man. so bynde &thorn;ou lordchip of &thorn;is world to seculer men &thorn;at han wit &amp; vertu to worche aftir &thorn;is lordchip, aftir &thorn;e lawe &thorn;at crist ha&thorn; &yogh;ouyn, &amp; it may do myche good, goddis worchip &amp; his chirchis profit; but knytte &thorn;is lordchip to cristis prest &amp; it wole lette hym to speke &thorn;e lawe of god &amp; soulis heel&thorn;e, &amp; strangle hym &amp; many o&thorn;ere. &thorn;us alle &thorn;e resouns &thorn;at &thorn;e fend can make a&yogh;enus crist &amp; cristis prestis may be auoydid bi oure fei&thorn;, &amp; make heretikis to shame of hem.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="10" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 10<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>&yogh;it argue&thorn; anticrist &thorn;at bi &thorn;is fel foly perpetual almes in abbeys &amp; in collegies shulde be destried: but where were more synne? &amp; si&thorn; it is greet meede to do almes for a tyme, it were myche more meede to contynue perpetual almes; &amp; &thorn;us charteres of lordis &amp; kyngis of &thorn;er perpetual almes shulden be destried, &amp; goostly help &thorn;at sue&thorn; &thorn;er-of, &amp; no drede &thorn;e pope is ground of alle siche perpetual almes. Heere han trewe men ofte seyd &thorn;at it were myche betere &thorn;at men lyueden opyn lif &thorn;an in siche nestis of &thorn;e fend; for siche abbeys &amp; collegies ben hordis of synne to herbore hym. &amp; herfore sei&thorn; crist in &thorn;e gospel &thorn;at men shulden not be<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. vi. [25.]</NOTE> bisi to &thorn;e morowe; but anticrist ha&thorn; hardy maner to holde his castel for many &yogh;eere. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;at crist durste not do, ne his apostlis aftir hym, anticrist dare blyndly do in holding of siche castels, &amp; &thorn;is is a fendis cautel &thorn;at he ha&thorn; brou&yogh;t yn of newe. heritage of er&thorn;ly lordis goi&thorn; ofte tyme amys whanne tirauntis &amp; goddis traytours comen eyris aftir gode men; but &yogh;it god ordeyne&thorn; grace heere, &amp; ordeyne&thorn; summe to wante eyris, &amp; bi many priuey weyes he taki&thorn; yuel fro gode men 
<PB REF="00000543.tif" N="477"> but whanne siche hord of &thorn;e fend is perpetuald in o heed, be it good be it yuel, it lasti&thorn; many mennus lyues, &amp; it is comynly yuel. for crist hadde but twelue apostlis &amp; ledde hem in trauel &amp; pouert &amp; hooly preching of his word, &amp; &yogh;it scarioth was a shrewe for al &thorn;e vertu &thorn;at crist shewide. lord, wher popis &amp; er&thorn;ly lordis han more vertu &thorn;an crist hadde heere? &amp; &thorn;us siche nestis <MILESTONE N="32b" UNIT="page">shulden not be callid perpetuel almes of worldly lordis, but dennes of &thorn;eues, &amp; nestis of serpentis, &amp; homely housis of quye deuels. &amp; &thorn;ey don harm to cristis chirge bi perpetualte in &thorn;er synne; &amp; o&thorn;er ground han no men forto founde siche dennes, but &thorn;at crist forfendide hem &amp; shewide &thorn;er perel in scarioth. &amp; se &thorn;e cautel of &thorn;e fend, hou quentely he ha&thorn; brou&yogh;t &thorn;is yn. he moue&thorn; &thorn;es founderis to pride, &amp; sei&thorn; &thorn;ey ben comun of grete men, &thorn;at han foundid perpetuel abbeys in so myche multitude. where is more satanas pride a&yogh;enus mekenesse of iesu crist? for oure bileue techi&thorn; vs &thorn;at a man doi&thorn; no lengere merit &thorn;an &thorn;e while he lyue&thorn; heere in er&thorn;e; hou shulde &thorn;is meede euere laste? &thorn;es founderis sufficiden not to founde &thorn;er oune soule in vertues; hou shulden &thorn;ei &thorn;anne suffise to make so longe vertuous men? &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;er come good of &thorn;is ground, pore deed men &thorn;at god loue&thorn; betere han more meede of &thorn;is good &thorn;an han &thorn;es proude founderis. &amp; se hou anticrist &amp; &thorn;es lordis stryuen as fendis in &thorn;is poynt. anti|crist sei&thorn; &thorn;at al &thorn;is lordchip felde to hym bi title of crist, &amp; so &thorn;es lordis &yogh;auen a&yogh;en godis &thorn;at &thorn;ey hadden vniustly holdun, &amp; so &thorn;ei han no more meede but maken asee&thorn; for formere synne; &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ey dwellen ay in synne &thorn;e while &thorn;ei holden ony lordchip fro &thorn;e chirche. &amp; &thorn;us it is not perpetual almes, but perpetual part of makinge asee&thorn;. &amp; certis summe wordis &thorn;at heere ben seyd ben so&thorn;e, &amp; summe opyn blasfemye, si&thorn;en crist, &thorn;at is lord of alle, forfendide siche nestis in &thorn;e gospel, &amp; ordeynede to his moost dere children &thorn;at &thorn;ey shulden not haue siche dwellinge place. &amp; &thorn;is he ordeynede for &thorn;is ende, &thorn;at men shulden coueyte &thorn;e place of heuene. &amp; to &thorn;e foorme of anticristis skile: he &amp; alle hise kunnen not grounde &thorn;at 
<PB REF="00000544.tif" N="478"> &thorn;is was euere ony almes to make &thorn;us siche cayms castels. so&thorn;ely in &thorn;e olde lawe was salomons temple a figure of &thorn;e chirche in &thorn;e newe lawe, but not &thorn;at &thorn;e chirche shulde be siche, but fre &amp; large vndir &thorn;e cope of heuene, &amp; stonde in vertues of mannus soule; but anticrist wole close it nou in coolde stones &thorn;at moten perisshe. &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;is founding vn|groundid was noon almes at &thorn;e bigynnyng, &amp; it is not aftir quykenyd to be almes wi&thorn;-oute skile; but almes were to sue crist &amp; ordeyne mennus lif aftir his lawe. crist is god &thorn;at chalengi&thorn; propre to ordeyne siche <MILESTONE N="33" UNIT="page">perpetuytes, for he is lord wi&thorn;-outen ende; who dare take fro hym &thorn;is lordchip? do men good for &thorn;er lif, &amp; &yogh;yue &thorn;ei to crist perpetuyte, for he can &amp; may do &thorn;is as hym liki&thorn; in his chirche. &amp; &thorn;us errour in siche synnes ha&thorn; destried many kynredis &amp; punysshid many soulis in helle, who so wyste &thorn;e so&thorn;e bi crist. &amp; &thorn;us siche charteres of seculer lordis &amp; of popis ben ofte witnessis of &thorn;e errours of &thorn;er eldris &thorn;at weren grounderis of &thorn;es synnes.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="11" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 11<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>but &yogh;it anticrist grucchi&thorn; &amp; sei&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;is is heresye, for it techi&thorn; a weye bi which hooly chirche shulde be destried. for &yogh;if &thorn;er were no pope in er&thorn;e ne no cardenals his felowis, &thorn;er were no patriarkis, ne archibischops, ne bischops, ne erchedekenes, ne officials, ne persouns, ne prestis. &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;es ordris perisshiden &thorn;us, er&thorn;ely lordis shulden sunnere perische, &amp; so &thorn;e chirche shulde dwelle wi&thorn;-outen ordre, as fendis wanten ordre in helle &amp; ben in horrour wi&thorn;-outen ende. Heere it ha&thorn; be seyd ofte bi witnesse of trewe men &thorn;at &thorn;er mut nedis be an ordre of &thorn;re partis of &thorn;e chirche, &thorn;at ben clerkis, lordis &amp; comyns, &amp; in ech of hem is ordre. for crist, &thorn;at is bo&thorn;e god &amp; man &amp; heed &amp; ground of hooly chirche, puttide &thorn;is ordre pleynly &amp; &yogh;af lawis to contynue it, &amp; a man may no more shewe &thorn;at he is anticrist hym silf &thorn;an to reuerse 
<PB REF="00000545.tif" N="479"> &thorn;is ordre, &amp; feyne a newe wi&thorn;-oute ground. &amp; si&thorn; we taken of goddis lawe &thorn;at crist dwelli&thorn; wi&thorn;-outen ende, he were a fool out of bileue &thorn;at diffiede heere of cristis help. crist wole ordeyne to his chirche prestis &amp; ordre &thorn;at is nedeful, al &yogh;if &thorn;es foure sectis weren sunkun doun to &thorn;er fadir. leue whanne &thorn;e pope was deed &amp; cardenals weren not &yogh;it sprongun, in whois hond was &thorn;e chirche &thorn;at wandri&thorn; heere vpon er&thorn;e? certis in cristis hond, &thorn;at dwelli&thorn; euere heed of hooly chirche; &amp; he mut nedis ordeyne prestis, summe hyere &amp; summe lowere, aftir &thorn;at he &yogh;yue&thorn; hem grace to profite more aftir his lawe. &amp; &thorn;us &yogh;if &thorn;er weren no popis, ne cardenals, ne emperours prelatis, hooly chirche shulde stonde wel bi &thorn;e ordre &thorn;at crist puttide. &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ou axe who shulde make &thorn;es prestis, &amp; bi what wordis &amp; whois autorite, certis bileue nedi&thorn; vs to seye &thorn;at crist mut make &thorn;es prestis, o&thorn;er bi wordis hid to vs or bi grace wi&thorn;-oute wordis, as crist not wi&thorn;-outen cause made apostlis &amp; telde vs not bi what wor<MILESTONE N="33b" UNIT="page">dis he made hem; why shulde not crist do &yogh;it so? trowe we &thorn;at crist sitting in heuene is lettid to strecche his grace so fer? si&thorn; he is bo&thorn;e god &amp; man, &amp; gouerny&thorn; vs in o&thorn;ere &thorn;ingis. &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ou seye &thorn;at on &thorn;is maner my&yogh;te ech man feyne hym silf a staat, &amp; seye &thorn;at he is hierste man &thorn;at dwelli&thorn; in er&thorn;e vndir crist; so&thorn; it is &thorn;at many pseudois may speke myche wi&thorn;-oute ground, &amp; &thorn;erfore crist ha&thorn; &yogh;ouyn a lawe to trowe hem not but &yogh;if &thorn;ey grounden hem. &amp; si&thorn; crist bad trowe to his werkis &amp; &yogh;af ne&thorn;er bullis ne lettris selid, men shulden more trowe hooly werkis &thorn;an popis bullis or bischops lettris. for alle &thorn;ese ben not gospel, but &thorn;e fende may regne vndir &thorn;es writtis; for bo&thorn;e popis, bischopis &amp; prestis may be wi&thorn; &thorn;es &thorn;e fendis children, &amp; no partis of hooly chirche but fendis ordeyned to be dampnyd. trowe &thorn;ou to vertuous dedis of prestis, &amp; algatis to &thorn;er mekenesse, &thorn;at &thorn;ey coueyten noon hye staat &thorn;at is not groundid in goddis lawe. &amp; so proude prestis &amp; coueytous ben suspect of prestis staat. but &thorn;is suspicioun is not bileue ne hope &thorn;at man shulde haue. but ne&thorn;eles ech man heere shulde lyue in hope &thorn;at bi his lif 
<PB REF="00000546.tif" N="480"> he shulde come to heuene, for mekenesse &amp; o&thorn;ere vertues &thorn;at he ha&thorn;. &amp; &thorn;us we shulden lyue in bileue in hope &amp; in charite, &amp; who so wanti&thorn; hope heere he is an opyn anticrist. &thorn;us we hopen to be sauyd, al &yogh;if &thorn;es prelatis ben opyn fendis, &amp; oure bileue &amp; hope is picchid in &thorn;e grace of iesu crist, &amp; oure gode werkis may we knowe wi&thorn; entent in oure soule. many men trowen more to gode werkis &thorn;an to staat of pope or bischop, &amp; so alle &thorn;es pontificals ben byne&thorn;e hooly writ, so &thorn;at &yogh;if &thorn;ey alle weren brent cristendom shulde stonde wel. for ellis &yogh;if freris founden wordis to sacre &thorn;e armes of a prest, &amp; &thorn;e pope &yogh;aue hym meede to fi&yogh;te wi&thorn; o&thorn;ere cristenmen, he were out of bileue &thorn;at trowede not to al &thorn;is. but fer be it fro cristenmen to trowe siche cautels of &thorn;e fend; &amp; bi &thorn;is may men se answere to &thorn;e foorme of anticristis resoun. &thorn;es wordis of &thorn;e emperours prelatis &thorn;at ben not groundid in goddis lawe destrien not hooly chirche, ne &thorn;e ordre &thorn;at crist ha&thorn; sett; but founding of &thorn;es newe ordris distemperi&thorn; &thorn;e ordris of crist, &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;e fend steli&thorn; in mo men to his stede. &thorn;e ordre of kyngis &amp; dukis &amp; kny&yogh;tis &amp; of seruauntis to hem ben groundid <MILESTONE N="34" UNIT="page">in goddis lawe, but not of popis &amp; cardenals. crist ordeynede bi his ordre &thorn;at his apostlis &amp; his prestis shulden be felowis &amp; meke men &amp; telle not hye bi hem silf, &amp; so crist maki&thorn; distinccioun bi-twixe ordre of er&thorn;ly lordis &amp; ordre of his prestis. for &thorn;at ordre is hid to god &amp; stondi&thorn; in mekenesse &amp; o&thorn;ere dedis of charite; &amp; so blyndenesse of anticrist shulde not disproue &thorn;es worldly lordis, ne proue &thorn;at bi &thorn;e same skyle mut be &thorn;is ordre of emperours prelatis.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="12" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>Capitulum 12<SUP>m.</SUP></HEAD>
<P>&yogh;it anticrist argue&thorn; &thorn;at it is nedeful to &thorn;e chirche &thorn;at &thorn;e pope &amp; his cardenals &amp; o&thorn;ere prelatis reule it. for who shulde ellis assoyle men &amp; graunte hem so large in|dulgensis bo&thorn;e of peyne &amp; of synne, haue &thorn;ei neuere so longe synned. &amp; o&thorn;ere priuylegies of &thorn;e pope may not be teld of 
<PB REF="00000547.tif" N="481"> er&thorn;ly men. in &thorn;is mater han cristenmen seyd priuely as &thorn;ey dursten, &thorn;at it were good men to be war lest anticrist disseyue hem. &amp; god wite it, men wolden wi&thorn; wille seye treu&thorn;e for worchip of crist &amp; for profit of his chirche &amp; hope to gete blis in heuene. bo&thorn;e cristenmen &amp; anticrist grounden hem on iesu crist, but &thorn;ey fallen in-to dyuerse weyes bi &thorn;e tempting of &thorn;e fend. anticrist leeue&thorn; mekenesse &amp; paciense wi&thorn; o&thorn;ere vertues, but cristenmen holden &thorn;es vertues, summe more &amp; summe lesse. &amp; holde we &thorn;us cristis lawe wi&thorn;-outen nouelries of anticrist, &amp; seye we hou cristenmen shulden do in &thorn;ys fendis blast. &amp; &thorn;us men seyen bi cristis lore &thorn;at anticrist faili&thorn; first whanne he sei&thorn; &thorn;at it is nedeful &thorn;at &thorn;e pope &amp; cardenals reule cristis chirche. for whanne cristis chirche &thorn;rof, weren no siche pope &amp; cardenals; &amp; si&thorn;en &thorn;es prelatis weren comun yn regnede anticrist wi&thorn; synne. &amp; anentis asoyling, bileue techi&thorn; cristenmen &thorn;at iesu crist mut nedis asoyle &yogh;if ony man shule be assoylid, &amp; anticrist may not for shame denye opynly &thorn;is bileue; but he sei&thorn; &thorn;at crist mut nedis assente wi&thorn; hym in asoyling, &amp; he groundi&thorn; &thorn;is bi &thorn;e gospel, but it is shame to reherse it. so&thorn; it is crist grauntide to petre &thorn;at what &thorn;ing he asoylide on er&thorn;e shulde be asoylid in heuene, &amp; so it is of bynding; but &thorn;is was lymytid to petre &amp; hise &thorn;at suyden &thorn;e <MILESTONE N="34b" UNIT="page">steppis &thorn;at petre wente, &amp; whanne &thorn;er soyling &amp; &thorn;er bynding acordide wi&thorn; god in heuene. but nou it is no bileue &thorn;at &thorn;es gon petris steppis, &amp; suen crist &thorn;e strei&yogh;t weye &thorn;at shulde lede herdis to heuene. &amp; also it is no bileue &thorn;at what tyme &thorn;at &thorn;es prelatis feynen hem to asoyle, &thorn;ey acorden wi&thorn; crist aboue; &amp; so it is no bileue &thorn;at &thorn;ei acorden euere wi&thorn; crist. For as &thorn;ey synnen in o&thorn;er &thorn;ing, so &thorn;ey synnen in &thorn;is poynt; for he &thorn;at discordi&thorn; fro goddis wille in his lif &amp; in his dede may li&yogh;tly discorde fro god in profecye of siche asoyling. men preyen gode cristen|men bi &thorn;e vertu of iesu crist &thorn;at &thorn;ey dampne not &thorn;es wordis to li&yogh;tly wi&thorn;-outen skyle, but reste in resoun &amp; goddis lawe &amp; holde al &thorn;at &thorn;ese techen. for &thorn;is shulden alle cristenmen do &amp; passe not &thorn;e boundis of &thorn;is; &amp; &thorn;is shulden men telle opynly 
<PB REF="00000548.tif" N="482"> to suffere de&thorn; for loue of treu&thorn;e. &amp; bi &thorn;is may men se what &thorn;ei shulen trowe of indulgensis. it is no poynt of bileue &thorn;at &thorn;e pope euere more in graunting of &thorn;es indulgensis acordi&thorn; wi&thorn; goddis wille; as it is no bileue &thorn;at so longe shal &thorn;is world stonde, as &thorn;e pope graunti&thorn; indulgensis. but bileue techi&thorn; cristenmen &thorn;at indulgensis shulen no lengere laste; &amp; &thorn;us it is no bileue &yogh;if &thorn;e pope, for bidding of a kyng, graunti&thorn; so large indulgensis &thorn;at a man may in a masse tyme where euere he heri&thorn; &thorn;is masse gete twenti &thorn;ousynd &yogh;eer of pardoun, &amp; &thorn;at wole passe alle &thorn;e tyme &thorn;at soulis shulen dwelle in purgatorye; &amp; &thorn;us he shal not dwelle in peyne bi &thorn;e graunt of &thorn;is pope. manye siche &thorn;ingis ben writun &thorn;at ben nou&yogh;t of bileue, &amp; &thorn;erfore it is perelous to trowe hem as bileue. We bileuen on cristis lawe &thorn;at &yogh;if man synnede neuere so longe, &amp; were neuere asoylid of pope ne of his prest vndir hym, &yogh;if he wolde forsake his synne &amp; be contrit for formere synne &amp; ende &thorn;is lif on &thorn;is maner, god wolde for&yogh;yue hym his synne. We kunnen not telle hou longe &thorn;at god wolde punysshe hym in purgatorye, &amp; &thorn;is is more grace of god &thorn;an &thorn;e pope telli&thorn; in his lawe, for he wole nedis constreyne men to be asoylid of hym or hise, but &thorn;is durste noon apostle do. &amp; &thorn;us it is no bileue, as it is no bileue &thorn;at &thorn;is or &thorn;is is very pope. for mannus choys maki&thorn; no prest, hou euere &thorn;is lawe be hyed. for enleuene apostlis to-gidere dursten not chese mathy apostle, &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;e hooly goost was wi&thorn; hem &amp; coueytise was awey. &amp; &thorn;us seyen summe trewe men &thorn;at siche grauntis of &thorn;e pope &thorn;at ben not groundid in goddis lawe ben prauylegies, &amp; litil wor&thorn;, &amp; si&thorn; &thorn;ey ben not bileue, axe ground of hem bifore &thorn;ou bie hem.</P>
<TRAILER>Explicit tractatus de papa.</TRAILER>
</DIV2>
